1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),1,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 1:1-2,1,1,1,N,1,1,"That man hath perfect blessedness,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),1,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 1:1-2,1,1,1,Y,2,1,who walketh not astray
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),1,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 1:1-2,1,1,1,N,3,1,"In counsel of ungodly men,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),1,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 1:1-2,1,1,1,Y,4,1,"nor stands in sinners' way,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),1,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 1:1-2,1,1,2,N,5,1,Nor sitteth in the scorner's chair:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),1,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 1:1-2,1,1,2,Y,6,2,But placeth his delight
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),1,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 1:1-2,1,1,2,N,7,2,"Upon God's law, and meditates"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),1,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 1:1-2,1,1,2,Y,8,2,on his law day and night.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),1,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 1:3-6,2,2,3,N,9,3,He shall be like a tree that grows
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),1,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 1:3-6,2,2,3,Y,10,3,"near planted by a river,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),1,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 1:3-6,2,2,3,N,11,3,"Which in his season yields his fruit,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),1,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 1:3-6,2,2,3,Y,12,3,and his leaf fadeth never:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),1,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 1:3-6,2,2,4,N,13,3,And all he doth shall prosper well.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),1,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 1:3-6,2,2,4,Y,14,4,The wicked are not so;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),1,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 1:3-6,2,2,4,N,15,4,"But like they are unto the chaff,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),1,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 1:3-6,2,2,4,Y,16,4,which wind drives to and fro.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),1,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 1:3-6,2,3,5,N,17,5,In judgment therefore shall not stand
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),1,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 1:3-6,2,3,5,Y,18,5,such as ungodly are;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),1,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 1:3-6,2,3,5,N,19,5,Nor in th' assembly of the just
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),1,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 1:3-6,2,3,5,Y,20,5,shall wicked men appear.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),1,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 1:3-6,2,3,6,N,21,6,For why? the way of godly men
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),1,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 1:3-6,2,3,6,Y,22,6,unto the Lord is known:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),1,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 1:3-6,2,3,6,N,23,6,Whereas the way of wicked men
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),1,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 1:3-6,2,3,6,Y,24,6,shall quite be overthrown.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),2,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 2:1-6,1,1,1,N,1,1,Why rage the heathen? and vain things
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),2,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 2:1-6,1,1,1,Y,2,1,why do the people mind?
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),2,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 2:1-6,1,1,1,N,3,2,"Kings of the earth do set themselves,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),2,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 2:1-6,1,1,1,Y,4,2,"and princes are combin'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),2,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 2:1-6,1,1,2,N,5,2,"To plot against the Lord, and his"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),2,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 2:1-6,1,1,2,Y,6,2,"Anointed, saying thus,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),2,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 2:1-6,1,1,2,N,7,3,"Let us asunder break their bands,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),2,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 2:1-6,1,1,2,Y,8,3,and cast their cords from us.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),2,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 2:1-6,1,2,3,N,9,4,He that in heaven sits shall laugh;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),2,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 2:1-6,1,2,3,Y,10,4,the Lord shall scorn them all.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),2,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 2:1-6,1,2,3,N,11,5,"Then shall he speak to them in wrath,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),2,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 2:1-6,1,2,3,Y,12,5,in rage he vex them shall.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),2,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 2:1-6,1,2,4,N,13,6,"Yet, notwithstanding, I have him"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),2,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 2:1-6,1,2,4,Y,14,6,to be my King appointed;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),2,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 2:1-6,1,2,4,N,15,6,"And over Sion, my holy hill,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),2,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 2:1-6,1,2,4,Y,16,6,I have him King anointed.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),2,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 2:7-12,2,3,5,N,17,7,The sure decree I will declare:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),2,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 2:7-12,2,3,5,Y,18,7,"The Lord hath said to me,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),2,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 2:7-12,2,3,5,N,19,7,Thou art mine only Son; this day
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),2,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 2:7-12,2,3,5,Y,20,7,I have begotten thee.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),2,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 2:7-12,2,3,6,N,21,8,"Ask of me, and for heritage"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),2,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 2:7-12,2,3,6,Y,22,8,the heathen I'll make thine;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),2,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 2:7-12,2,3,6,N,23,8,"And, for possession, I to thee"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),2,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 2:7-12,2,3,6,Y,24,8,will give earth's utmost line.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),2,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 2:7-12,2,4,7,N,25,9,"Thou shalt, as with a weighty rod"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),2,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 2:7-12,2,4,7,Y,26,9,"of iron, break them all;"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),2,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 2:7-12,2,4,7,N,27,9,"And, as a potter's sherd, thou shalt"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),2,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 2:7-12,2,4,7,Y,28,9,them dash in pieces small.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),2,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 2:7-12,2,4,8,N,29,10,"Now therefore, kings, be wise; be taught,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),2,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 2:7-12,2,4,8,Y,30,10,ye judges of the earth:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),2,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 2:7-12,2,4,8,N,31,11,"Serve God in fear, and see that ye"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),2,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 2:7-12,2,4,8,Y,32,11,join trembling with your mirth.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),2,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 2:7-12,2,5,9,N,33,12,"Kiss ye the Son, lest in his ire"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),2,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 2:7-12,2,5,9,Y,34,12,"ye perish from the way,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),2,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 2:7-12,2,5,9,N,35,12,If once his wrath begin to burn:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),2,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 2:7-12,2,5,9,Y,36,12,bless'd all that on him stay.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),3,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 3:1-8,1,1,1,N,1,1,"O Lord, how are my foes increas'd?"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),3,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 3:1-8,1,1,1,Y,2,1,against me many rise.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),3,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 3:1-8,1,1,1,N,3,2,"Many say of my soul, For him"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),3,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 3:1-8,1,1,1,Y,4,2,in God no succour lies.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),3,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 3:1-8,1,1,2,N,5,3,"Yet thou my shield and glory art,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),3,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 3:1-8,1,1,2,Y,6,3,th' uplifter of mine head.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),3,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 3:1-8,1,1,2,N,7,4,"I cry'd, and, from his holy hill,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),3,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 3:1-8,1,1,2,Y,8,4,the Lord me answer made.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),3,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 3:1-8,1,2,3,N,9,5,I laid me down and slept; I wak'd;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),3,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 3:1-8,1,2,3,Y,10,5,for God sustained me.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),3,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 3:1-8,1,2,3,N,11,6,I will not fear though thousands ten
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),3,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 3:1-8,1,2,3,Y,12,6,set round against me be.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),3,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 3:1-8,1,2,4,N,13,7,"Arise, O Lord; save me, my God;"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),3,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 3:1-8,1,2,4,Y,14,7,for thou my foes hast stroke
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),3,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 3:1-8,1,2,4,N,15,7,"All on the cheek-bone, and the teeth"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),3,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 3:1-8,1,2,4,Y,16,7,of wicked men hast broke.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),3,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 3:1-8,1,3,5,N,17,8,Salvation doth appertain
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),3,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 3:1-8,1,3,5,Y,18,8,unto the Lord alone:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),3,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 3:1-8,1,3,5,N,19,8,"Thy blessing, Lord, for evermore"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),3,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 3:1-8,1,3,5,Y,20,8,thy people is upon.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),4,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 4:1-3,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Give ear unto me when I call,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),4,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 4:1-3,1,1,1,Y,2,1,God of my righteousness:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),4,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 4:1-3,1,1,1,N,3,1,"Have mercy, hear my pray'r; thou hast"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),4,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 4:1-3,1,1,1,Y,4,1,enlarg'd me in distress.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),4,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 4:1-3,1,1,2,N,5,2,O ye the sons of men! how long
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),4,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 4:1-3,1,1,2,Y,6,2,will ye love vanities?
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),4,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 4:1-3,1,1,2,N,7,2,"How long my glory turn to shame,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),4,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 4:1-3,1,1,2,Y,8,2,and will ye follow lies?
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),4,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 4:1-3,1,2,3,N,9,3,"But know, that for himself the Lord"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),4,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 4:1-3,1,2,3,Y,10,3,the godly man doth chuse:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),4,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 4:1-3,1,2,3,N,11,3,"The Lord, when I on him do call,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),4,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 4:1-3,1,2,3,Y,12,3,to hear will not refuse.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),4,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 4:4-8,2,2,4,N,13,4,"Fear, and sin not; talk with your heart"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),4,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 4:4-8,2,2,4,Y,14,4,"on bed, and silent be."
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),4,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 4:4-8,2,2,4,N,15,5,"Off 'rings present of righteousness,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),4,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 4:4-8,2,2,4,Y,16,5,and in the Lord trust ye.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),4,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 4:4-8,2,3,5,N,17,6,O who will shew us any good?
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),4,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 4:4-8,2,3,5,Y,18,6,is that which many say:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),4,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 4:4-8,2,3,5,N,19,6,"But of thy countenance the light,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),4,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 4:4-8,2,3,5,Y,20,6,"Lord, lift on us alway."
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),4,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 4:4-8,2,3,6,N,21,7,"Upon my heart, bestow'd by thee,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),4,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 4:4-8,2,3,6,Y,22,7,more gladness I have found
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),4,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 4:4-8,2,3,6,N,23,7,"Than they, ev'n then, when corn and wine"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),4,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 4:4-8,2,3,6,Y,24,7,did most with them abound.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),4,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 4:4-8,2,4,7,N,25,8,"I will both lay me down in peace,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),4,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 4:4-8,2,4,7,Y,26,8,and quiet sleep will take;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),4,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 4:4-8,2,4,7,N,27,8,Because thou only me to dwell
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),4,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 4:4-8,2,4,7,Y,28,8,"in safety, Lord, dost make."
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),5,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 5:1-7,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Give ear unto my words, O Lord"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),5,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 5:1-7,1,1,1,Y,2,1,my meditation weigh.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),5,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 5:1-7,1,1,1,N,3,2,"Hear my loud cry, my King, my God;"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),5,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 5:1-7,1,1,1,Y,4,2,for I to thee will pray.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),5,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 5:1-7,1,1,2,N,5,3,"Lord, thou shalt early hear my voice:"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),5,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 5:1-7,1,1,2,Y,6,3,I early will direct
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),5,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 5:1-7,1,1,2,N,7,3,"My pray'r to thee; and, looking up,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),5,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 5:1-7,1,1,2,Y,8,3,an answer will expect.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),5,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 5:1-7,1,2,3,N,9,4,For thou art not a God that doth
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),5,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 5:1-7,1,2,3,Y,10,4,in wickedness delight;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),5,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 5:1-7,1,2,3,N,11,4,"Neither shall evil dwell with thee,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),5,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 5:1-7,1,2,3,Y,12,5,Nor fools stand in thy sight.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),5,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 5:1-7,1,2,4,N,13,5,All that ill-doers are thou hat'st;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),5,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 5:1-7,1,2,4,Y,14,6,Cutt'st off that liars be:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),5,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 5:1-7,1,2,4,N,15,6,The bloody and deceitful man
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),5,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 5:1-7,1,2,4,Y,16,6,abhorred is by thee.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),5,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 5:1-7,1,3,5,N,17,7,But I into thy house will come
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),5,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 5:1-7,1,3,5,Y,18,7,in thine abundant grace;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),5,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 5:1-7,1,3,5,N,19,7,And I will worship in thy fear
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),5,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 5:1-7,1,3,5,Y,20,7,toward thy holy place.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),5,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 5:8-12,2,3,6,N,21,8,"Because of those mine enemies,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),5,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 5:8-12,2,3,6,Y,22,8,"Lord, in thy righteousness"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),5,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 5:8-12,2,3,6,N,23,8,Do thou me lead; do thou thy way
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),5,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 5:8-12,2,3,6,Y,24,8,make straight before my face.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),5,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 5:8-12,2,4,7,N,25,9,"For in their mouth there is no truth,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),5,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 5:8-12,2,4,7,Y,26,9,their inward part is ill;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),5,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 5:8-12,2,4,7,N,27,9,"Their throat's an open sepulchre,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),5,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 5:8-12,2,4,7,Y,28,9,their tongue doth flatter still.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),5,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 5:8-12,2,4,8,N,29,10,"O God, destroy them; let them be"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),5,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 5:8-12,2,4,8,Y,30,10,by their own counsel quell'd:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),5,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 5:8-12,2,4,8,N,31,10,"Them for their many sins cast out,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),5,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 5:8-12,2,4,8,Y,32,10,for they 'gainst thee rebell'd.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),5,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 5:8-12,2,5,9,N,33,11,"But let all joy that trust in thee,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),5,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 5:8-12,2,5,9,Y,34,11,and still make shouting noise;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),5,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 5:8-12,2,5,9,N,35,11,For them thou sav'st: let all that love
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),5,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 5:8-12,2,5,9,Y,36,11,thy name in thee rejoice.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),5,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 5:8-12,2,5,10,N,37,12,"For, Lord, unto the righteous man"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),5,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 5:8-12,2,5,10,Y,38,12,thou wilt thy blessing yield:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),5,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 5:8-12,2,5,10,N,39,12,With favour thou wilt compass him
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),5,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 5:8-12,2,5,10,Y,40,12,"about, as with a shield."
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 6:1-5 I,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Lord, in thy wrath rebuke me not;"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 6:1-5 I,1,1,1,N,2,1,Nor in thy hot rage chasten me.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 6:1-5 I,1,1,1,N,3,2,"Lord, pity me, for I am weak:"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 6:1-5 I,1,1,1,N,4,2,"Heal me, for my bones vexed be."
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 6:1-5 I,1,1,2,N,5,3,My soul is also vexed sore;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 6:1-5 I,1,1,2,N,6,3,"But, Lord, how long stay wilt thou make?"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 6:1-5 I,1,1,2,N,7,4,"Return, O Lord, my soul set free;"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 6:1-5 I,1,1,2,N,8,4,"O save me, for thy mercies' sake."
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 6:1-5 I,1,2,3,N,9,5,Because those that deceased are
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 6:1-5 I,1,2,3,N,10,5,Of thee shall no remembrance have;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 6:1-5 I,1,2,3,N,11,5,And who is he that will to thee
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 6:1-5 I,1,2,3,N,12,5,Give praises lying in the grave?
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 6:6-10 I,2,2,4,N,13,6,"I with my groaning weary am,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 6:6-10 I,2,2,4,N,14,6,I also all the night my bed
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 6:6-10 I,2,2,4,N,15,6,Have caused for to swim; and I
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 6:6-10 I,2,2,4,N,16,6,With tears my couch have watered.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 6:6-10 I,2,3,5,N,17,7,"Mine eye, consum'd with grief, grows old,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 6:6-10 I,2,3,5,N,18,7,Because of all mine enemies.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 6:6-10 I,2,3,5,N,19,8,"Hence from me, wicked workers all;"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 6:6-10 I,2,3,5,N,20,8,For God hath heard my weeping cries.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 6:6-10 I,2,3,6,N,21,9,"God hath my supplication heard,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 6:6-10 I,2,3,6,N,22,9,My pray'r received graciously
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 6:6-10 I,2,3,6,N,23,10,"Sham'd and sore vex'd be all my foes,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 6:6-10 I,2,3,6,N,24,10,Sham'd and back turned suddenly.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 6:1-5 II,1,3,1,N,1,1,"In thy great indignation,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 6:1-5 II,1,3,1,Y,2,1,"O Lord, rebuke me not;"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 6:1-5 II,1,3,1,N,3,1,"Nor on me lay thy chast 'ning hand,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 6:1-5 II,1,3,1,Y,4,1,in thy displeasure hot.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 6:1-5 II,1,3,2,N,5,2,"Lord, I am weak, therefore on me"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 6:1-5 II,1,3,2,Y,6,2,"have mercy, and me spare:"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 6:1-5 II,1,3,2,N,7,2,"Heal me, O Lord, because thou know'st"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 6:1-5 II,1,3,2,Y,8,2,my bones much vexed are.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 6:1-5 II,1,4,3,N,9,3,"My soul is vexed sore: but, Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 6:1-5 II,1,4,3,Y,10,3,how long stay wilt thou make?
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 6:1-5 II,1,4,3,N,11,4,"Return, Lord, free my soul; and save"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 6:1-5 II,1,4,3,Y,12,4,"me, for thy mercies' sake."
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 6:1-5 II,1,4,4,N,13,5,Because of thee in death there shall
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 6:1-5 II,1,4,4,Y,14,5,no more remembrance be:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 6:1-5 II,1,4,4,N,15,5,"Of those that in the grave do lie,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 6:1-5 II,1,4,4,Y,16,5,who shall give thanks to thee?
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 6:6-10 II,2,5,5,N,17,6,"I with my groaning weary am,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 6:6-10 II,2,5,5,Y,18,6,and all the night my bed
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 6:6-10 II,2,5,5,N,19,6,I caused for to swim; with tears
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 6:6-10 II,2,5,5,Y,20,6,my couch I watered.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 6:6-10 II,2,5,6,N,21,7,"By reason of my vexing grief,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 6:6-10 II,2,5,6,Y,22,7,mine eye consumed is;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 6:6-10 II,2,5,6,N,23,7,"It waxeth old, because of all"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 6:6-10 II,2,5,6,Y,24,7,that be mine enemies.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 6:6-10 II,2,6,7,N,25,8,"But now, depart from me all ye"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 6:6-10 II,2,6,7,Y,26,8,that work iniquity:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 6:6-10 II,2,6,7,N,27,8,"For why? the Lord hath heard my voice,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 6:6-10 II,2,6,7,Y,28,8,when I did mourn and cry.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 6:6-10 II,2,6,8,N,29,9,Unto my supplication
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 6:6-10 II,2,6,8,Y,30,9,the Lord did hearing give:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 6:6-10 II,2,6,8,N,31,9,"When I to him my prayer make,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 6:6-10 II,2,6,8,Y,32,9,the Lord will it receive.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 6:6-10 II,2,7,9,N,33,10,"Let all be sham'd and troubled sore,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 6:6-10 II,2,7,9,Y,34,10,That en'mies are to me;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 6:6-10 II,2,7,9,N,35,10,"Let them turn back, and suddenly"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),6,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 6:6-10 II,2,7,9,Y,36,10,ashamed let them be.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:1-5,1,1,1,N,1,1,"O Lord my God, in thee do I"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:1-5,1,1,1,Y,2,1,my confidence repose:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:1-5,1,1,1,N,3,1,Save and deliver me from all
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:1-5,1,1,1,Y,4,1,my persecuting foes;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:1-5,1,1,2,N,5,2,Lest that the enemy my soul
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:1-5,1,1,2,Y,6,2,"should, like a lion, tear,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:1-5,1,1,2,N,7,2,"In pieces rending it, while there"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:1-5,1,1,2,Y,8,2,is no deliverer.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:1-5,1,2,3,N,9,3,"O Lord my God, if it be so"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:1-5,1,2,3,Y,10,3,that I committed this;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:1-5,1,2,3,N,11,3,If it be so that in my hands
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:1-5,1,2,3,Y,12,3,iniquity there is:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:1-5,1,2,4,N,13,4,If I rewarded ill to him
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:1-5,1,2,4,Y,14,4,that was at peace with me;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:1-5,1,2,4,N,15,4,"(Yea, ev'n the man that without cause"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:1-5,1,2,4,Y,16,4,my foe was I did free;)
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:1-5,1,3,5,N,17,5,Then let the foe pursue and take
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:1-5,1,3,5,Y,18,5,"my soul, and my life thrust"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:1-5,1,3,5,N,19,5,"Down to the earth, and let him lay"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:1-5,1,3,5,Y,20,5,mine honour in the dust.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:6-8,2,3,6,N,21,6,"Rise in thy wrath, Lord, raise thyself,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:6-8,2,3,6,Y,22,6,for my foes raging be;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:6-8,2,3,6,N,23,6,"And, to the judgment which thou hast"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:6-8,2,3,6,Y,24,6,"commanded, wake for me."
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:6-8,2,4,7,N,25,7,So shall th' assembly of thy folk
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:6-8,2,4,7,Y,26,7,about encompass thee:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:6-8,2,4,7,N,27,7,"Thou, therefore, for their sakes, return"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:6-8,2,4,7,Y,28,7,unto thy place on high.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:6-8,2,4,8,N,29,8,The Lord he shall the people judge:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:6-8,2,4,8,Y,30,8,"my judge, Jehovah, be,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:6-8,2,4,8,N,31,8,"After my righteousness, and mine"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:6-8,2,4,8,Y,32,8,integrity in me.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:9-13,3,5,9,N,33,9,O let the wicked's malice end;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:9-13,3,5,9,Y,34,9,but stablish stedfastly
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:9-13,3,5,9,N,35,9,The righteous: for the righteous God
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:9-13,3,5,9,Y,36,9,the hearts and reins doth try.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:9-13,3,5,10,N,37,10,"In God, who saves th' upright in heart,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:9-13,3,5,10,Y,38,10,is my defence and stay.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:9-13,3,5,10,N,39,11,"God just men judgeth, God is wroth"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:9-13,3,5,10,Y,40,11,with ill men ev'ry day.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:9-13,3,6,11,N,41,12,"If he do not return again,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:9-13,3,6,11,Y,42,12,then he his sword will whet;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:9-13,3,6,11,N,43,12,"His bow he hath already bent,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:9-13,3,6,11,Y,44,12,and hath it ready set:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:9-13,3,6,12,N,45,13,He also hath for him prepar'd
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:9-13,3,6,12,Y,46,13,the instruments of death;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:9-13,3,6,12,N,47,13,Against the persecutors he
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:9-13,3,6,12,Y,48,13,his shafts ordained hath.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:14-17,4,7,13,N,49,14,"Behold, he with iniquity"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:14-17,4,7,13,Y,50,14,"doth travail, as in birth;"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:14-17,4,7,13,N,51,14,"A mischief he conceived hath,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:14-17,4,7,13,Y,52,14,and falsehood shall bring forth.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:14-17,4,7,14,N,53,15,"He made a pit and digg'd it deep,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:14-17,4,7,14,Y,54,15,another there to take;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:14-17,4,7,14,N,55,15,But he is fall'n into the ditch
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:14-17,4,7,14,Y,56,15,which he himself did make.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:14-17,4,8,15,N,57,16,Upon his own head his mischief
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:14-17,4,8,15,Y,58,16,shall be returned home;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:14-17,4,8,15,N,59,16,His vi'lent dealing also down
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:14-17,4,8,15,Y,60,16,on his own pate shall come.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:14-17,4,8,16,N,61,17,According to his righteousness
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:14-17,4,8,16,Y,62,17,the Lord I'll magnify;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:14-17,4,8,16,N,63,17,And will sing praise unto the name
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),7,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 7:14-17,4,8,16,Y,64,17,of God that is most high.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),8,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 8:1-2,1,1,1,N,1,1,"How excellent in all the earth,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),8,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 8:1-2,1,1,1,Y,2,1,"Lord, our Lord, is thy name!"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),8,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 8:1-2,1,1,1,N,3,1,Who hast thy glory far advanc'd
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),8,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 8:1-2,1,1,1,Y,4,1,above the starry frame.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),8,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 8:1-2,1,1,2,N,5,2,From infants' and from sucklings' mouth
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),8,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 8:1-2,1,1,2,Y,6,2,"thou didest strength ordain,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),8,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 8:1-2,1,1,2,N,7,2,"For thy foes' cause, that so thou might'st"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),8,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 8:1-2,1,1,2,Y,8,2,th' avenging foe restrain.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),8,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 8:3-9,2,2,3,N,9,3,"When I look up unto the heav'ns,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),8,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 8:3-9,2,2,3,Y,10,3,"which thine own fingers fram'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),8,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 8:3-9,2,2,3,N,11,3,"Unto the moon, and to the stars,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),8,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 8:3-9,2,2,3,Y,12,3,which were by thee ordain'd;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),8,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 8:3-9,2,2,4,N,13,4,"Then say I, What is man, that he"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),8,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 8:3-9,2,2,4,Y,14,4,remember'd is by thee?
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),8,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 8:3-9,2,2,4,N,15,4,"Or what the son of man, that thou"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),8,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 8:3-9,2,2,4,Y,16,4,so kind to him should'st be?
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),8,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 8:3-9,2,3,5,N,17,5,For thou a little lower hast
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),8,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 8:3-9,2,3,5,Y,18,5,him than the angels made;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),8,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 8:3-9,2,3,5,N,19,5,With glory and with dignity
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),8,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 8:3-9,2,3,5,Y,20,5,thou crowned hast his head.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),8,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 8:3-9,2,3,6,N,21,6,"Of thy hands' works thou mad'st him lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),8,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 8:3-9,2,3,6,Y,22,6,all under's feet didst lay;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),8,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 8:3-9,2,3,6,N,23,7,"All sheep and oxen, yea, and beasts"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),8,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 8:3-9,2,3,6,Y,24,7,that in the field do stray;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),8,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 8:3-9,2,4,7,N,25,8,"Fowls of the air, fish of the sea,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),8,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 8:3-9,2,4,7,Y,26,8,all that pass through the same.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),8,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 8:3-9,2,4,7,N,27,9,"How excellent in all the earth,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),8,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 8:3-9,2,4,7,Y,28,9,"Lord, our Lord, is thy name!"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:1-6,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Lord, thee I'll praise with all my heart,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:1-6,1,1,1,Y,2,1,thy wonders all proclaim.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:1-6,1,1,1,N,3,2,"In thee, most High, I'll greatly joy,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:1-6,1,1,1,Y,4,2,and sing unto thy name.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:1-6,1,1,2,N,5,3,"When back my foes were turn'd, they fell,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:1-6,1,1,2,Y,6,3,and perish'd at thy sight:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:1-6,1,1,2,N,7,4,For thou maintain'dst my right and cause;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:1-6,1,1,2,Y,8,4,on throne sat'st judging right.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:1-6,1,2,3,N,9,5,"The heathen thou rebuked hast,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:1-6,1,2,3,Y,10,5,the wicked overthrown;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:1-6,1,2,3,N,11,5,"Thou hast put out their names, that they"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:1-6,1,2,3,Y,12,5,may never more be known.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:1-6,1,2,4,N,13,6,O en'my! now destructions have
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:1-6,1,2,4,Y,14,6,an end perpetual:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:1-6,1,2,4,N,15,6,Thou cities raz'd; perish'd with them
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:1-6,1,2,4,Y,16,6,is their memorial.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:7-10,2,3,5,N,17,7,God shall endure for aye; he doth
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:7-10,2,3,5,Y,18,7,for judgment set his throne;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:7-10,2,3,5,N,19,8,"In righteousness to judge the world,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:7-10,2,3,5,Y,20,8,justice to give each one.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:7-10,2,3,6,N,21,9,God also will a refuge be
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:7-10,2,3,6,Y,22,9,for those that are oppress'd;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:7-10,2,3,6,N,23,9,A refuge will he be in times
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:7-10,2,3,6,Y,24,9,of trouble to distress'd.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:7-10,2,4,7,N,25,10,"And they that know thy name, in thee"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:7-10,2,4,7,Y,26,10,their confidence will place:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:7-10,2,4,7,N,27,10,For thou hast not forsaken them
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:7-10,2,4,7,Y,28,10,that truly seek thy face.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:11-14,3,4,8,N,29,11,"O sing ye praises to the Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:11-14,3,4,8,Y,30,11,that dwells in Sion hill;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:11-14,3,4,8,N,31,11,And all the nations among
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:11-14,3,4,8,Y,32,11,his deeds record ye still.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:11-14,3,5,9,N,33,12,"When he enquireth after blood,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:11-14,3,5,9,Y,34,12,he then rememb'reth them:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:11-14,3,5,9,N,35,12,The humble folk he not forgets
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:11-14,3,5,9,Y,36,12,that call upon his name.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:11-14,3,5,10,N,37,13,"Lord, pity me; behold the grief"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:11-14,3,5,10,Y,38,13,which I from foes sustain;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:11-14,3,5,10,N,39,13,"Ev'n thou, who from the gates of death"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:11-14,3,5,10,Y,40,13,dost raise me up again;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:11-14,3,6,11,N,41,14,"That I, in Sion's daughters' gates,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:11-14,3,6,11,Y,42,14,may all thy praise advance;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:11-14,3,6,11,N,43,14,And that I may rejoice always
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:11-14,3,6,11,Y,44,14,in thy deliverance.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:15-20,4,6,12,N,45,15,The heathen are sunk in the pit
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:15-20,4,6,12,Y,46,15,which they themselves prepar'd;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:15-20,4,6,12,N,47,15,And in the net which they have hid
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:15-20,4,6,12,Y,48,15,their own feet fast are snar'd.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:15-20,4,7,13,N,49,16,The Lord is by the judgment known
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:15-20,4,7,13,Y,50,16,which he himself hath wrought:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:15-20,4,7,13,N,51,16,The sinners' hands do make the snares
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:15-20,4,7,13,Y,52,16,wherewith themselves are caught.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:15-20,4,7,14,N,53,17,They who are wicked into hell
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:15-20,4,7,14,Y,54,17,each one shall turned be;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:15-20,4,7,14,N,55,17,And all the nations that forget
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:15-20,4,7,14,Y,56,17,to seek the Lord most high.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:15-20,4,8,15,N,57,18,For they that needy are shall not
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:15-20,4,8,15,Y,58,18,forgotten be alway;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:15-20,4,8,15,N,59,18,The expectation of the poor
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:15-20,4,8,15,Y,60,18,shall not be lost for aye.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:15-20,4,8,16,N,61,19,"Arise, Lord, let not man prevail;"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:15-20,4,8,16,Y,62,19,judge heathen in thy sight:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:15-20,4,8,16,N,63,20,"That they may know themselves but men,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),9,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 9:15-20,4,8,16,Y,64,20,"the nations, Lord, affright."
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:1-5,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Wherefore is it that thou, O Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:1-5,1,1,1,Y,2,1,dost stand from us afar?
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:1-5,1,1,1,N,3,1,"And wherefore hidest thou thyself,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:1-5,1,1,1,Y,4,1,when times so troublous are?
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:1-5,1,1,2,N,5,2,The wicked in his loftiness
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:1-5,1,1,2,Y,6,2,doth persecute the poor:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:1-5,1,1,2,N,7,2,In these devices they have fram'd
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:1-5,1,1,2,Y,8,2,let them be taken sure.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:1-5,1,2,3,N,9,3,The wicked of his heart's desire
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:1-5,1,2,3,Y,10,3,doth talk with boasting great;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:1-5,1,2,3,N,11,3,"He blesseth him that's covetous,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:1-5,1,2,3,Y,12,3,whom yet the Lord doth hate.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:1-5,1,2,4,N,13,4,"The wicked, through his pride of face,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:1-5,1,2,4,Y,14,4,on God he doth not call;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:1-5,1,2,4,N,15,4,And in the counsels of his heart
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:1-5,1,2,4,Y,16,4,the Lord is not at all.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:1-5,1,3,5,N,17,5,His ways they always grievous are;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:1-5,1,3,5,Y,18,5,thy judgments from his sight
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:1-5,1,3,5,N,19,5,Removed are: at all his foes
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:1-5,1,3,5,Y,20,5,he puffeth with despight.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:6-10,2,3,6,N,21,6,"Within his heart he thus hath said,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:6-10,2,3,6,Y,22,6,I shall not moved be;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:6-10,2,3,6,N,23,6,And no adversity at all
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:6-10,2,3,6,Y,24,6,shall ever come to me.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:6-10,2,4,7,N,25,7,"His mouth with cursing, fraud, deceit,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:6-10,2,4,7,Y,26,7,is fill'd abundantly;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:6-10,2,4,7,N,27,7,And underneath his tongue there is
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:6-10,2,4,7,Y,28,7,mischief and vanity.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:6-10,2,4,8,N,29,8,He closely sits in villages;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:6-10,2,4,8,Y,30,8,he slays the innocent:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:6-10,2,4,8,N,31,8,Against the poor that pass him by
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:6-10,2,4,8,Y,32,8,his cruel eyes are bent.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:6-10,2,5,9,N,33,9,"He, lion-like, lurks in his den;"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:6-10,2,5,9,Y,34,9,he waits the poor to take;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:6-10,2,5,9,N,35,9,"And when he draws him in his net,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:6-10,2,5,9,Y,36,9,his prey he doth him make.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:6-10,2,5,10,N,37,10,"Himself he humbleth very low,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:6-10,2,5,10,Y,38,10,"he croucheth down withal,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:6-10,2,5,10,N,39,10,That so a multitude of poor
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:6-10,2,5,10,Y,40,10,may by his strong ones fall.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:11-15,3,6,11,N,41,11,"He thus hath said within his heart,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:11-15,3,6,11,Y,42,11,The Lord hath quite forgot;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:11-15,3,6,11,N,43,11,"He hides his countenance, and he"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:11-15,3,6,11,Y,44,11,for ever sees it not.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:11-15,3,6,12,N,45,12,"O Lord, do thou arise; O God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:11-15,3,6,12,Y,46,12,lift up thine hand on high:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:11-15,3,6,12,N,47,12,Put not the meek afflicted ones
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:11-15,3,6,12,Y,48,12,out of thy memory.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:11-15,3,7,13,N,49,13,Why is it that the wicked man
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:11-15,3,7,13,Y,50,13,thus doth the Lord despise?
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:11-15,3,7,13,N,51,13,Because that God will it require
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:11-15,3,7,13,Y,52,13,he in his heart denies.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:11-15,3,7,14,N,53,14,Thou hast it seen; for their mischief
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:11-15,3,7,14,Y,54,14,and spite thou wilt repay:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:11-15,3,7,14,N,55,14,The poor commits himself to thee;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:11-15,3,7,14,Y,56,14,thou art the orphan's stay.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:11-15,3,8,15,N,57,15,"The arm break of the wicked man,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:11-15,3,8,15,Y,58,15,and of the evil one;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:11-15,3,8,15,N,59,15,"Do thou seek out his wickedness,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:11-15,3,8,15,Y,60,15,until thou findest none.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:16-18,4,8,16,N,61,16,"The Lord is King through ages all,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:16-18,4,8,16,Y,62,16,ev'n to eternity;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:16-18,4,8,16,N,63,16,The heathen people from his land
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:16-18,4,8,16,Y,64,16,are perish'd utterly.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:16-18,4,9,17,N,65,17,"O Lord, of those that humble are"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:16-18,4,9,17,Y,66,17,thou the desire didst hear;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:16-18,4,9,17,N,67,17,"Thou wilt prepare their heart, and thou"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:16-18,4,9,17,Y,68,17,to hear wilt bend thine ear;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:16-18,4,9,18,N,69,18,"To judge the fatherless, and those"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:16-18,4,9,18,Y,70,18,that are oppressed sore;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:16-18,4,9,18,N,71,18,"That man, that is but sprung of earth,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),10,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 10:16-18,4,9,18,Y,72,18,may them oppress no more.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),11,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 11:1-2,1,1,1,N,1,1,I in the Lord do put my trust:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),11,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 11:1-2,1,1,1,Y,2,1,how is it then that ye
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),11,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 11:1-2,1,1,1,N,3,1,"Say to my soul, Flee, as a bird,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),11,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 11:1-2,1,1,1,Y,4,1,unto your mountain high?
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),11,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 11:1-2,1,1,2,N,5,2,"For, lo, the wicked bend their bow,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),11,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 11:1-2,1,1,2,Y,6,2,"their shafts on string they fit,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),11,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 11:1-2,1,1,2,N,7,2,That those who upright are in heart
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),11,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 11:1-2,1,1,2,Y,8,2,they privily may hit.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),11,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 11:3-7,2,2,3,N,9,3,"If the foundations be destroy'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),11,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 11:3-7,2,2,3,Y,10,3,what hath the righteous done?
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),11,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 11:3-7,2,2,3,N,11,4,"God in his holy temple is,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),11,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 11:3-7,2,2,3,Y,12,4,in heaven is his throne:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),11,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 11:3-7,2,2,4,N,13,4,"His eyes do see, his eye-lids try"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),11,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 11:3-7,2,2,4,Y,14,5,men's sons. The just he proves:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),11,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 11:3-7,2,2,4,N,15,5,"But his soul hates the wicked man,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),11,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 11:3-7,2,2,4,Y,16,5,and him that vi'lence loves.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),11,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 11:3-7,2,3,5,N,17,6,"Snares, fire and brimstone, furious storms,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),11,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 11:3-7,2,3,5,Y,18,6,on sinners he shall rain:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),11,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 11:3-7,2,3,5,N,19,6,"This, as the portion of their cup,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),11,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 11:3-7,2,3,5,Y,20,6,doth unto them pertain.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),11,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 11:3-7,2,3,6,N,21,7,Because the Lord most righteous doth
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),11,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 11:3-7,2,3,6,Y,22,7,in righteousness delight;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),11,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 11:3-7,2,3,6,N,23,7,And with a pleasant countenance
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),11,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 11:3-7,2,3,6,Y,24,7,beholdeth the upright.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),12,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 12:1-4,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Help, Lord, because the godly man"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),12,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 12:1-4,1,1,1,Y,2,1,doth daily fade away;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),12,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 12:1-4,1,1,1,N,3,1,And from among the sons of men
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),12,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 12:1-4,1,1,1,Y,4,1,the faithful do decay.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),12,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 12:1-4,1,1,2,N,5,2,Unto his neighbour ev'ry one
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),12,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 12:1-4,1,1,2,Y,6,2,doth utter vanity:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),12,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 12:1-4,1,1,2,N,7,2,"They with a double heart do speak,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),12,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 12:1-4,1,1,2,Y,8,2,and lips of flattery.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),12,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 12:1-4,1,2,3,N,9,3,"God shall cut off all flatt'ring lips,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),12,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 12:1-4,1,2,3,Y,10,3,"tongues that speak proudly thus,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),12,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 12:1-4,1,2,3,N,11,4,"We'll with our tongue prevail, our lips"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),12,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 12:1-4,1,2,3,Y,12,4,are ours: who's lord o'er us?
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),12,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 12:5-8,2,2,4,N,13,5,"For poor oppress'd, and for the sighs"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),12,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 12:5-8,2,2,4,Y,14,5,"of needy, rise will I,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),12,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 12:5-8,2,2,4,N,15,5,"Saith God, and him in safety set"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),12,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 12:5-8,2,2,4,Y,16,5,from such as him defy.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),12,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 12:5-8,2,3,5,N,17,6,The words of God are words most pure;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),12,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 12:5-8,2,3,5,Y,18,6,they be like silver try'd
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),12,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 12:5-8,2,3,5,N,19,6,"In earthen furnace, seven times"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),12,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 12:5-8,2,3,5,Y,20,6,that hath been purify'd.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),12,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 12:5-8,2,3,6,N,21,7,"Lord, thou shalt them preserve and keep"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),12,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 12:5-8,2,3,6,Y,22,7,for ever from this race.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),12,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 12:5-8,2,3,6,N,23,8,"On each side walk the wicked, when"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),12,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 12:5-8,2,3,6,Y,24,8,vile men are high in place.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),13,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 13:1-4,1,1,1,N,1,1,"How long wilt thou forget me, Lord?"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),13,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 13:1-4,1,1,1,Y,2,1,shall it for ever be?
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),13,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 13:1-4,1,1,1,N,3,1,O how long shall it be that thou
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),13,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 13:1-4,1,1,1,Y,4,1,wilt hide thy face from me?
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),13,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 13:1-4,1,1,2,N,5,2,"How long take counsel in my soul,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),13,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 13:1-4,1,1,2,Y,6,2,"still sad in heart, shall I?"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),13,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 13:1-4,1,1,2,N,7,2,How long exalted over me
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),13,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 13:1-4,1,1,2,Y,8,2,shall be mine enemy?
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),13,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 13:1-4,1,2,3,N,9,3,"O Lord my God, consider well,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),13,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 13:1-4,1,2,3,Y,10,3,and answer to me make:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),13,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 13:1-4,1,2,3,N,11,3,"Mine eyes enlighten, lest the sleep"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),13,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 13:1-4,1,2,3,Y,12,3,of death me overtake:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),13,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 13:1-4,1,2,4,N,13,4,"Lest that mine enemy should say,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),13,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 13:1-4,1,2,4,Y,14,4,Against him I prevail'd;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),13,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 13:1-4,1,2,4,N,15,4,"And those that trouble me rejoice,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),13,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 13:1-4,1,2,4,Y,16,4,when I am mov'd and fail'd.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),13,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 13:5-6,2,3,5,N,17,5,But I have all my confidence
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),13,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 13:5-6,2,3,5,Y,18,5,thy mercy set upon;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),13,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 13:5-6,2,3,5,N,19,5,My heart within me shall rejoice
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),13,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 13:5-6,2,3,5,Y,20,5,in thy salvation.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),13,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 13:5-6,2,3,6,N,21,6,I will unto the Lord my God
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),13,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 13:5-6,2,3,6,Y,22,6,"sing praises cheerfully,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),13,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 13:5-6,2,3,6,N,23,6,Because he hath his bounty shown
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),13,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 13:5-6,2,3,6,Y,24,6,to me abundantly.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),14,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 14:1-3,1,1,1,N,1,1,"That there is not a God, the fool"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),14,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 14:1-3,1,1,1,Y,2,1,doth in his heart conclude:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),14,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 14:1-3,1,1,1,N,3,1,"They are corrupt, their works are vile;"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),14,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 14:1-3,1,1,1,Y,4,1,not one of them doth good.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),14,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 14:1-3,1,1,2,N,5,2,Upon men's sons the Lord from heav'n
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),14,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 14:1-3,1,1,2,Y,6,2,"did cast his eyes abroad,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),14,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 14:1-3,1,1,2,N,7,2,"To see if any understood,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),14,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 14:1-3,1,1,2,Y,8,2,and did seek after God.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),14,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 14:1-3,1,2,3,N,9,3,"They altogether filthy are,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),14,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 14:1-3,1,2,3,Y,10,3,they all aside are gone;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),14,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 14:1-3,1,2,3,N,11,3,"And there is none that doeth good,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),14,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 14:1-3,1,2,3,Y,12,3,"yea, sure there is not one."
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),14,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 14:4-7,2,2,4,N,13,4,These workers of iniquity
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),14,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 14:4-7,2,2,4,Y,14,4,"do they not know at all,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),14,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 14:4-7,2,2,4,N,15,4,"That they my people eat as bread,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),14,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 14:4-7,2,2,4,Y,16,4,and on God do not call?
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),14,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 14:4-7,2,3,5,N,17,5,There fear'd they much; for God is with
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),14,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 14:4-7,2,3,5,Y,18,5,the whole race of the just.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),14,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 14:4-7,2,3,5,N,19,6,"You shame the counsel of the poor,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),14,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 14:4-7,2,3,5,Y,20,6,because God is his trust.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),14,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 14:4-7,2,3,6,N,21,7,Let Isr'el's help from Sion come:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),14,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 14:4-7,2,3,6,Y,22,7,when back the Lord shall bring
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),14,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 14:4-7,2,3,6,N,23,7,"His captives, Jacob shall rejoice,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),14,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 14:4-7,2,3,6,Y,24,7,and Israel shall sing.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),15,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 15:1-5,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Within thy tabernacle, Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),15,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 15:1-5,1,1,1,Y,2,1,who shall abide with thee?
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),15,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 15:1-5,1,1,1,N,3,1,And in thy high and holy hill
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),15,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 15:1-5,1,1,1,Y,4,1,who shall a dweller be?
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),15,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 15:1-5,1,1,2,N,5,2,"The man that walketh uprightly,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),15,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 15:1-5,1,1,2,Y,6,2,"and worketh righteousness,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),15,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 15:1-5,1,1,2,N,7,2,"And as he thinketh in his heart,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),15,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 15:1-5,1,1,2,Y,8,2,so doth he truth express.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),15,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 15:1-5,1,2,3,N,9,3,"Who doth not slander with his tongue,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),15,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 15:1-5,1,2,3,Y,10,3,nor to his friend doth hurt;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),15,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 15:1-5,1,2,3,N,11,3,Nor yet against his neighbour doth
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),15,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 15:1-5,1,2,3,Y,12,3,take up an ill report.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),15,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 15:1-5,1,2,4,N,13,4,In whose eyes vile men are despis'd;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),15,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 15:1-5,1,2,4,Y,14,4,but those that God do fear
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),15,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 15:1-5,1,2,4,N,15,4,"He honoureth; and changeth not,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),15,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 15:1-5,1,2,4,Y,16,4,though to his hurt he swear.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),15,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 15:1-5,1,3,5,N,17,5,"His coin puts not to usury,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),15,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 15:1-5,1,3,5,Y,18,5,nor take reward will he
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),15,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 15:1-5,1,3,5,N,19,5,Against the guiltless. Who doth thus
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),15,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 15:1-5,1,3,5,Y,20,5,shall never moved be.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),16,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 16:1-6,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Lord, keep me; for I trust in thee."
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),16,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 16:1-6,1,1,1,Y,2,2,"To God thus was my speech,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),16,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 16:1-6,1,1,1,N,3,2,Thou art my Lord; and unto thee
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),16,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 16:1-6,1,1,1,Y,4,2,my goodness doth not reach:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),16,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 16:1-6,1,1,2,N,5,3,"To saints on earth, to th' excellent,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),16,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 16:1-6,1,1,2,Y,6,3,where my delight's all plac'd.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),16,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 16:1-6,1,1,2,N,7,4,Their sorrows shall be multiply'd
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),16,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 16:1-6,1,1,2,Y,8,4,to other gods that haste:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),16,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 16:1-6,1,2,3,N,9,4,Of their drink-offerings of blood
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),16,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 16:1-6,1,2,3,Y,10,4,I will no off 'ring make;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),16,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 16:1-6,1,2,3,N,11,4,"Yea, neither I their very names"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),16,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 16:1-6,1,2,3,Y,12,4,up in my lips will take.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),16,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 16:1-6,1,2,4,N,13,5,God is of mine inheritance
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),16,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 16:1-6,1,2,4,Y,14,5,and cup the portion;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),16,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 16:1-6,1,2,4,N,15,5,The lot that fallen is to me
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),16,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 16:1-6,1,2,4,Y,16,5,thou dost maintain alone.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),16,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 16:1-6,1,3,5,N,17,6,Unto me happily the lines
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),16,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 16:1-6,1,3,5,Y,18,6,in pleasant places fell;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),16,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 16:1-6,1,3,5,N,19,6,"Yea, the inheritance I got"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),16,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 16:1-6,1,3,5,Y,20,6,in beauty doth excel.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),16,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 16:7-11,2,3,6,N,21,7,"I bless the Lord, because he doth"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),16,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 16:7-11,2,3,6,Y,22,7,by counsel me conduct;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),16,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 16:7-11,2,3,6,N,23,7,And in the seasons of the night
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),16,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 16:7-11,2,3,6,Y,24,7,my reins do me instruct.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),16,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 16:7-11,2,4,7,N,25,8,Before me still the Lord I set:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),16,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 16:7-11,2,4,7,Y,26,8,sith it is so that he
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),16,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 16:7-11,2,4,7,N,27,8,"Doth ever stand at my right hand,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),16,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 16:7-11,2,4,7,Y,28,8,I shall not moved be.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),16,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 16:7-11,2,4,8,N,29,9,"Because of this my heart is glad,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),16,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 16:7-11,2,4,8,Y,30,9,and joy shall be exprest
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),16,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 16:7-11,2,4,8,N,31,9,Ev'n by my glory; and my flesh
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),16,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 16:7-11,2,4,8,Y,32,9,in confidence shall rest.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),16,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 16:7-11,2,5,9,N,33,10,Because my soul in grave to dwell
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),16,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 16:7-11,2,5,9,Y,34,10,shall not be left by thee;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),16,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 16:7-11,2,5,9,N,35,10,Nor wilt thou give thine Holy One
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),16,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 16:7-11,2,5,9,Y,36,10,corruption to see.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),16,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 16:7-11,2,5,10,N,37,11,Thou wilt me shew the path of life:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),16,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 16:7-11,2,5,10,Y,38,11,of joys there is full store
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),16,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 16:7-11,2,5,10,N,39,11,Before thy face; at thy right hand
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),16,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 16:7-11,2,5,10,Y,40,11,are pleasures evermore.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:1-4,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Lord, hear the right, attend my cry,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:1-4,1,1,1,Y,2,1,"unto my pray'r give heed,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:1-4,1,1,1,N,3,1,That doth not in hypocrisy
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:1-4,1,1,1,Y,4,1,from feigned lips proceed.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:1-4,1,1,2,N,5,2,And from before thy presence forth
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:1-4,1,1,2,Y,6,2,my sentence do thou send:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:1-4,1,1,2,N,7,2,Toward these things that equal are
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:1-4,1,1,2,Y,8,2,do thou thine eyes intend.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:1-4,1,2,3,N,9,3,"Thou prov'dst mine heart, thou visit'dst me"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:1-4,1,2,3,Y,10,3,"by night, thou didst me try,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:1-4,1,2,3,N,11,3,Yet nothing found'st; for that my mouth
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:1-4,1,2,3,Y,12,3,"shall not sin, purpos'd I."
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:1-4,1,2,4,N,13,4,"As for men's works, I, by the word"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:1-4,1,2,4,Y,14,4,"that from thy lips doth flow,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:1-4,1,2,4,N,15,4,Did me preserve out of the paths
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:1-4,1,2,4,Y,16,4,wherein destroyers go.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:5-7,2,3,5,N,17,5,"Hold up my goings, Lord, me guide"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:5-7,2,3,5,Y,18,5,"in those thy paths divine,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:5-7,2,3,5,N,19,5,So that my footsteps may not slide
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:5-7,2,3,5,Y,20,5,out of those ways of thine.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:5-7,2,3,6,N,21,6,"I called have on thee, O God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:5-7,2,3,6,Y,22,6,because thou wilt me hear:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:5-7,2,3,6,N,23,6,"That thou may'st hearken to my speech,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:5-7,2,3,6,Y,24,6,to me incline thine ear.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:5-7,2,4,7,N,25,7,"Thy wondrous loving-kindness show,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:5-7,2,4,7,Y,26,7,"thou that, by thy right hand,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:5-7,2,4,7,N,27,7,Sav'st them that trust in thee from those
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:5-7,2,4,7,Y,28,7,that up against them stand.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:8-12,3,4,8,N,29,8,As th' apple of the eye me keep;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:8-12,3,4,8,Y,30,8,in thy wings shade me close
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:8-12,3,4,8,N,31,9,"From lewd oppressors, compassing"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:8-12,3,4,8,Y,32,9,"me round, as deadly foes."
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:8-12,3,5,9,N,33,10,In their own fat they are inclos'd;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:8-12,3,5,9,Y,34,10,their mouth speaks loftily.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:8-12,3,5,9,N,35,11,Our steps they compass'd; and to ground
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:8-12,3,5,9,Y,36,11,down bowing set their eye.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:8-12,3,5,10,N,37,12,He like unto a lion is
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:8-12,3,5,10,Y,38,12,"that's greedy of his prey,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:8-12,3,5,10,N,39,12,"Or lion young, which lurking doth"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:8-12,3,5,10,Y,40,12,in secret places stay.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:13-15,4,6,11,N,41,13,"Arise, and disappoint my foe,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:13-15,4,6,11,Y,42,13,"and cast him down, O Lord:"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:13-15,4,6,11,N,43,13,"My soul save from the wicked man,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:13-15,4,6,11,Y,44,13,the man which is thy sword.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:13-15,4,6,12,N,45,14,"From men, which are thy hand, O Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:13-15,4,6,12,Y,46,14,"from worldly men me save,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:13-15,4,6,12,N,47,14,Which only in this present life
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:13-15,4,6,12,Y,48,14,their part and portion have.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:13-15,4,7,13,N,49,14,Whose belly with thy treasure hid
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:13-15,4,7,13,Y,50,14,thou fill'st: they children have
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:13-15,4,7,13,N,51,14,In plenty; of their goods the rest
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:13-15,4,7,13,Y,52,14,they to their children leave.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:13-15,4,7,14,N,53,15,"But as for me, I thine own face"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:13-15,4,7,14,Y,54,15,in righteousness will see;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:13-15,4,7,14,N,55,15,"And with thy likeness, when I wake,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),17,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 17:13-15,4,7,14,Y,56,15,I satisfy'd shall be.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:1-6,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Thee will I love, O Lord, my strength."
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:1-6,1,1,1,Y,2,2,"My fortress is the Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:1-6,1,1,1,N,3,2,"My rock, and he that doth to me"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:1-6,1,1,1,Y,4,2,deliverance afford:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:1-6,1,1,2,N,5,2,"My God, my strength, whom I will trust,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:1-6,1,1,2,Y,6,2,"a buckler unto me,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:1-6,1,1,2,N,7,2,"The horn of my salvation,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:1-6,1,1,2,Y,8,2,"and my high tow'r, is he."
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:1-6,1,2,3,N,9,3,"Upon the Lord, who worthy is"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:1-6,1,2,3,Y,10,3,"of praises, will I cry;"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:1-6,1,2,3,N,11,3,And then shall I preserved be
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:1-6,1,2,3,Y,12,3,safe from mine enemy.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:1-6,1,2,4,N,13,4,"Floods of ill men affrighted me,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:1-6,1,2,4,Y,14,4,death's pangs about me went;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:1-6,1,2,4,N,15,5,Hell's sorrows me environed;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:1-6,1,2,4,Y,16,5,death's snares did me prevent.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:1-6,1,3,5,N,17,6,"In my distress I call'd on God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:1-6,1,3,5,Y,18,6,cry to my God did I;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:1-6,1,3,5,N,19,6,"He from his temple heard my voice,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:1-6,1,3,5,Y,20,6,to his ears came my cry.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:7-10,2,3,6,N,21,7,"Th' earth, as affrighted, then did shake,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:7-10,2,3,6,Y,22,7,trembling upon it seiz'd:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:7-10,2,3,6,N,23,7,"The hills' foundations moved were,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:7-10,2,3,6,Y,24,7,because he was displeas'd.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:7-10,2,4,7,N,25,8,"Up from his nostrils came a smoke,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:7-10,2,4,7,Y,26,8,and from his mouth there came
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:7-10,2,4,7,N,27,8,"Devouring fire, and coals by it"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:7-10,2,4,7,Y,28,8,were turned into flame.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:7-10,2,4,8,N,29,9,"He also bowed down the heav'ns,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:7-10,2,4,8,Y,30,9,and thence he did descend;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:7-10,2,4,8,N,31,9,And thickest clouds of darkness did
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:7-10,2,4,8,Y,32,9,under his feet attend.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:7-10,2,5,9,N,33,10,"And he upon a cherub rode,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:7-10,2,5,9,Y,34,10,and thereon he did fly;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:7-10,2,5,9,N,35,10,"Yea, on the swift wings of the wind"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:7-10,2,5,9,Y,36,10,his flight was from on high.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:11-15,3,5,10,N,37,11,He darkness made his secret place:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:11-15,3,5,10,Y,38,11,"about him, for his tent,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:11-15,3,5,10,N,39,11,"Dark waters were, and thickest clouds"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:11-15,3,5,10,Y,40,11,of th' airy firmament.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:11-15,3,6,11,N,41,12,"And at the brightness of that light,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:11-15,3,6,11,Y,42,12,"which was before his eye,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:11-15,3,6,11,N,43,12,"His thick clouds pass'd away, hailstones"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:11-15,3,6,11,Y,44,12,and coals of fire did fly.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:11-15,3,6,12,N,45,13,The Lord God also in the heav'ns
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:11-15,3,6,12,Y,46,13,did thunder in his ire;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:11-15,3,6,12,N,47,13,"And there the Highest gave his voice,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:11-15,3,6,12,Y,48,13,hailstones and coals of fire.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:11-15,3,7,13,N,49,14,"Yea, he his arrows sent abroad,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:11-15,3,7,13,Y,50,14,and them he scattered;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:11-15,3,7,13,N,51,14,"His lightnings also he shot out,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:11-15,3,7,13,Y,52,14,and them discomfited.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:11-15,3,7,14,N,53,15,"The waters' channels then were seen,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:11-15,3,7,14,Y,54,15,the world's foundations vast
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:11-15,3,7,14,N,55,15,"At thy rebuke discover'd were,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:11-15,3,7,14,Y,56,15,and at thy nostrils' blast.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:16-19,4,8,15,N,57,16,"And from above the Lord sent down,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:16-19,4,8,15,Y,58,16,and took me from below;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:16-19,4,8,15,N,59,16,"From many waters he me drew,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:16-19,4,8,15,Y,60,16,which would me overflow.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:16-19,4,8,16,N,61,17,"He me reliev'd from my strong foes,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:16-19,4,8,16,Y,62,17,and such as did me hate;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:16-19,4,8,16,N,63,17,Because he saw that they for me
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:16-19,4,8,16,Y,64,17,"too strong were, and too great."
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:16-19,4,9,17,N,65,18,They me prevented in the day
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:16-19,4,9,17,Y,66,18,of my calamity;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:16-19,4,9,17,N,67,18,But even then the Lord himself
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:16-19,4,9,17,Y,68,18,a stay was unto me.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:16-19,4,9,18,N,69,19,He to a place where liberty
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:16-19,4,9,18,Y,70,19,and room was hath me brought;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:16-19,4,9,18,N,71,19,"Because he took delight in me,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:16-19,4,9,18,Y,72,19,he my deliv'rance wrought.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:20-24,5,10,19,N,73,20,According to my righteousness
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:20-24,5,10,19,Y,74,20,"he did me recompense,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:20-24,5,10,19,N,75,20,He me repaid according to
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:20-24,5,10,19,Y,76,20,my hands' pure innocence.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:20-24,5,10,20,N,77,21,"For I God's ways kept, from my God"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:20-24,5,10,20,Y,78,21,did not turn wickedly.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:20-24,5,10,20,N,79,22,"His judgments were before me, I"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:20-24,5,10,20,Y,80,22,his laws put not from me.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:20-24,5,11,21,N,81,23,Sincere before him was my heart;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:20-24,5,11,21,Y,82,23,with him upright was I;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:20-24,5,11,21,N,83,23,And watchfully I kept myself
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:20-24,5,11,21,Y,84,23,from mine iniquity.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:20-24,5,11,22,N,85,24,After my righteousness the Lord
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:20-24,5,11,22,Y,86,24,"hath recompensed me,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:20-24,5,11,22,N,87,24,After the cleanness of my hands
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:20-24,5,11,22,Y,88,24,appearing in his eye.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:25-30,6,12,23,N,89,25,"Thou gracious to the gracious art,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:25-30,6,12,23,Y,90,25,to upright men upright:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:25-30,6,12,23,N,91,26,"Pure to the pure, froward thou kyth'st"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:25-30,6,12,23,Y,92,26,unto the froward wight.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:25-30,6,12,24,N,93,27,For thou wilt the afflicted save
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:25-30,6,12,24,Y,94,27,in grief that low do lie:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:25-30,6,12,24,N,95,27,But wilt bring down the countenance
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:25-30,6,12,24,Y,96,27,of them whose looks are high.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:25-30,6,13,25,N,97,28,"The Lord will light my candle so,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:25-30,6,13,25,Y,98,28,that it shall shine full bright:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:25-30,6,13,25,N,99,28,The Lord my God will also make
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:25-30,6,13,25,Y,100,28,my darkness to be light.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:25-30,6,13,26,N,101,29,"By thee through troops of men I break,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:25-30,6,13,26,Y,102,29,and them discomfit all;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:25-30,6,13,26,N,103,29,"And, by my God assisting me,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:25-30,6,13,26,Y,104,29,I overleap a wall.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:25-30,6,14,27,N,105,30,"As for God, perfect is his way:"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:25-30,6,14,27,Y,106,30,the Lord his word is try'd;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:25-30,6,14,27,N,107,30,He is a buckler to all those
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:25-30,6,14,27,Y,108,30,who do in him confide.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:31-36,7,14,28,N,109,31,Who but the Lord is God? but he
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:31-36,7,14,28,Y,110,31,who is a rock and stay?
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:31-36,7,14,28,N,111,32,"'Tis God that girdeth me with strength,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:31-36,7,14,28,Y,112,32,and perfect makes my way.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:31-36,7,15,29,N,113,33,"He made my feet swift as the hinds,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:31-36,7,15,29,Y,114,33,set me on my high places.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:31-36,7,15,29,N,115,34,"Mine hands to war he taught, mine arms"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:31-36,7,15,29,Y,116,34,brake bows of steel in pieces.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:31-36,7,15,30,N,117,35,The shield of thy salvation
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:31-36,7,15,30,Y,118,35,thou didst on me bestow:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:31-36,7,15,30,N,119,35,"Thy right hand held me up, and great"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:31-36,7,15,30,Y,120,35,thy kindness made me grow.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:31-36,7,16,31,N,121,36,And in my way my steps thou hast
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:31-36,7,16,31,Y,122,36,"enlarged under me,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:31-36,7,16,31,N,123,36,"That I go safely, and my feet"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:31-36,7,16,31,Y,124,36,are kept from sliding free.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:37-42,8,16,32,N,125,37,"Mine en'mies I pursued have,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:37-42,8,16,32,Y,126,37,and did them overtake;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:37-42,8,16,32,N,127,37,Nor did I turn again till I
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:37-42,8,16,32,Y,128,37,an end of them did make.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:37-42,8,17,33,N,129,38,"I wounded them, they could not rise;"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:37-42,8,17,33,Y,130,38,they at my feet did fall.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:37-42,8,17,33,N,131,39,Thou girdedst me with strength for war;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:37-42,8,17,33,Y,132,39,my foes thou brought'st down all:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:37-42,8,17,34,N,133,40,And thou hast giv'n to me the necks
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:37-42,8,17,34,Y,134,40,of all mine enemies;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:37-42,8,17,34,N,135,40,"That I might them destroy and slay,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:37-42,8,17,34,Y,136,40,who did against me rise.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:37-42,8,18,35,N,137,41,"They cried out, but there was none"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:37-42,8,18,35,Y,138,41,that would or could them save;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:37-42,8,18,35,N,139,41,"Yea, they did cry unto the Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:37-42,8,18,35,Y,140,41,but he no answer gave.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:37-42,8,18,36,N,141,42,Then did I beat them small as dust
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:37-42,8,18,36,Y,142,42,before the wind that flies;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:37-42,8,18,36,N,143,42,And I did cast them out like dirt
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:37-42,8,18,36,Y,144,42,upon the street that lies.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:43-45,9,19,37,N,145,43,"Thou mad'st me free from people's strife,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:43-45,9,19,37,Y,146,43,and heathen's head to be:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:43-45,9,19,37,N,147,43,A people whom I have not known
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:43-45,9,19,37,Y,148,43,shall service do to me.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:43-45,9,19,38,N,149,44,"At hearing they shall me obey,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:43-45,9,19,38,Y,150,44,to me they shall submit.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:43-45,9,19,38,N,151,45,"Strangers for fear shall fade away,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:43-45,9,19,38,Y,152,45,who in close places sit.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:46-50,10,20,39,N,153,46,"God lives, bless'd be my Rock; the God"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:46-50,10,20,39,Y,154,46,of my health praised be.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:46-50,10,20,39,N,155,47,"God doth avenge me, and subdues"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:46-50,10,20,39,Y,156,47,the people under me.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:46-50,10,20,40,N,157,48,He saves me from mine enemies;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:46-50,10,20,40,Y,158,48,"yea, thou hast lifted me"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:46-50,10,20,40,N,159,48,Above my foes; and from the man
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:46-50,10,20,40,Y,160,48,of vi'lence set me free.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:46-50,10,21,41,N,161,49,Therefore to thee will I give thanks
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:46-50,10,21,41,Y,162,49,the heathen folk among;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:46-50,10,21,41,N,163,49,"And to thy name, O Lord, I will"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:46-50,10,21,41,Y,164,49,sing praises in a song.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:46-50,10,21,42,N,165,50,He great deliv'rance gives his king:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:46-50,10,21,42,Y,166,50,he mercy doth extend
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:46-50,10,21,42,N,167,50,"To David, his anointed one,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),18,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 18:46-50,10,21,42,Y,168,50,and his seed without end.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),19,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 19:1-6,1,1,1,N,1,1,"The heav'ns God's glory do declare,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),19,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 19:1-6,1,1,1,Y,2,1,the skies his hand-works preach:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),19,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 19:1-6,1,1,1,N,3,2,"Day utters speech to day, and night"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),19,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 19:1-6,1,1,1,Y,4,2,to night doth knowledge teach.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),19,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 19:1-6,1,1,2,N,5,3,There is no speech nor tongue to which
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),19,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 19:1-6,1,1,2,Y,6,3,their voice doth not extend:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),19,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 19:1-6,1,1,2,N,7,4,"Their line is gone through all the earth,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),19,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 19:1-6,1,1,2,Y,8,4,their words to the world's end.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),19,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 19:1-6,1,2,3,N,9,4,In them he set the sun a tent;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),19,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 19:1-6,1,2,3,Y,10,5,"Who, bridegroom-like, forth goes"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),19,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 19:1-6,1,2,3,N,11,5,"From's chamber, as a strong man doth"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),19,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 19:1-6,1,2,3,Y,12,5,to run his race rejoice.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),19,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 19:1-6,1,2,4,N,13,6,"From heav'n's end is his going forth,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),19,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 19:1-6,1,2,4,Y,14,6,circling to th' end again;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),19,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 19:1-6,1,2,4,N,15,6,And there is nothing from his heat
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),19,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 19:1-6,1,2,4,Y,16,6,that hidden doth remain.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),19,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 19:7-11,2,3,5,N,17,7,"God's law is perfect, and converts"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),19,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 19:7-11,2,3,5,Y,18,7,the soul in sin that lies:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),19,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 19:7-11,2,3,5,N,19,7,"God's testimony is most sure,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),19,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 19:7-11,2,3,5,Y,20,7,and makes the simple wise.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),19,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 19:7-11,2,3,6,N,21,8,"The statutes of the Lord are right,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),19,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 19:7-11,2,3,6,Y,22,8,and do rejoice the heart:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),19,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 19:7-11,2,3,6,N,23,8,"The Lord's command is pure, and doth"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),19,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 19:7-11,2,3,6,Y,24,8,light to the eyes impart.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),19,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 19:7-11,2,4,7,N,25,9,"Unspotted is the fear of God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),19,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 19:7-11,2,4,7,Y,26,9,and doth endure for ever:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),19,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 19:7-11,2,4,7,N,27,9,The judgments of the Lord are true
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),19,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 19:7-11,2,4,7,Y,28,9,and righteous altogether.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),19,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 19:7-11,2,4,8,N,29,10,"They more than gold, yea, much fine gold,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),19,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 19:7-11,2,4,8,Y,30,10,to be desired are:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),19,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 19:7-11,2,4,8,N,31,10,"Than honey, honey from the comb"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),19,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 19:7-11,2,4,8,Y,32,10,"that droppeth, sweeter far."
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),19,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 19:7-11,2,5,9,N,33,11,"Moreover, they thy servant warn"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),19,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 19:7-11,2,5,9,Y,34,11,how he his life should frame:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),19,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 19:7-11,2,5,9,N,35,11,A great reward provided is
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),19,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 19:7-11,2,5,9,Y,36,11,for them that keep the same.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),19,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 19:12-14,3,5,10,N,37,12,Who can his errors understand?
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),19,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 19:12-14,3,5,10,Y,38,12,O cleanse thou me within
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),19,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 19:12-14,3,5,10,N,39,13,From secret faults. Thy servant keep
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),19,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 19:12-14,3,5,10,Y,40,13,from all presumptuous sin:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),19,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 19:12-14,3,6,11,N,41,13,And do not suffer them to have
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),19,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 19:12-14,3,6,11,Y,42,13,dominion over me:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),19,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 19:12-14,3,6,11,N,43,13,"Then, righteous and innocent,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),19,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 19:12-14,3,6,11,Y,44,13,I from much sin shall be.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),19,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 19:12-14,3,6,12,N,45,14,"The words which from my mouth proceed,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),19,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 19:12-14,3,6,12,Y,46,14,"the thoughts sent from my heart,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),19,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 19:12-14,3,6,12,N,47,14,"Accept, O Lord, for thou my strength"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),19,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 19:12-14,3,6,12,Y,48,14,and my Redeemer art.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),20,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 20:1-5,1,1,1,N,1,1,Jehovah hear thee in the day
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),20,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 20:1-5,1,1,1,Y,2,1,when trouble he doth send:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),20,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 20:1-5,1,1,1,N,3,1,And let the name of Jacob's God
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),20,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 20:1-5,1,1,1,Y,4,1,thee from all ill defend.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),20,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 20:1-5,1,1,2,N,5,2,"O let him help send from above,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),20,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 20:1-5,1,1,2,Y,6,2,out of his sanctuary:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),20,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 20:1-5,1,1,2,N,7,2,"From Sion, his own holy hill,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),20,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 20:1-5,1,1,2,Y,8,2,let him give strength to thee.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),20,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 20:1-5,1,2,3,N,9,3,"Let him remember all thy gifts,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),20,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 20:1-5,1,2,3,Y,10,3,accept thy sacrifice:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),20,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 20:1-5,1,2,3,N,11,4,"Grant thee thine heart's wish, and fulfil"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),20,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 20:1-5,1,2,3,Y,12,4,thy thoughts and counsel wise.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),20,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 20:1-5,1,2,4,N,13,5,In thy salvation we will joy;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),20,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 20:1-5,1,2,4,Y,14,5,in our God's name we will
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),20,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 20:1-5,1,2,4,N,15,5,Display our banners: and the Lord
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),20,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 20:1-5,1,2,4,Y,16,5,thy prayers all fulfil.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),20,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 20:6-9,2,3,5,N,17,6,Now know I God his king doth save:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),20,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 20:6-9,2,3,5,Y,18,6,he from his holy heav'n
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),20,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 20:6-9,2,3,5,N,19,6,"Will hear him, with the saving strength"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),20,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 20:6-9,2,3,5,Y,20,6,by his own right hand giv'n.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),20,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 20:6-9,2,3,6,N,21,7,"In chariots some put confidence,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),20,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 20:6-9,2,3,6,Y,22,7,some horses trust upon:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),20,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 20:6-9,2,3,6,N,23,7,But we remember will the name
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),20,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 20:6-9,2,3,6,Y,24,7,of our Lord God alone.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),20,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 20:6-9,2,4,7,N,25,8,"We rise, and upright stand, when they"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),20,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 20:6-9,2,4,7,Y,26,8,"are bowed down, and fall."
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),20,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 20:6-9,2,4,7,N,27,9,"Deliver, Lord; and let the King"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),20,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 20:6-9,2,4,7,Y,28,9,"us hear, when we do call."
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),21,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 21:1-4,1,1,1,N,1,1,"The king in thy great strength, O Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),21,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 21:1-4,1,1,1,Y,2,1,shall very joyful be:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),21,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 21:1-4,1,1,1,N,3,1,In thy salvation rejoice
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),21,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 21:1-4,1,1,1,Y,4,1,how veh'mently shall he!
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),21,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 21:1-4,1,1,2,N,5,2,Thou hast bestowed upon him
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),21,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 21:1-4,1,1,2,Y,6,2,all that his heart would have;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),21,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 21:1-4,1,1,2,N,7,2,And thou from him didst not withhold
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),21,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 21:1-4,1,1,2,Y,8,2,whate'er his lips did crave.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),21,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 21:1-4,1,2,3,N,9,3,For thou with blessings him prevent'st
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),21,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 21:1-4,1,2,3,Y,10,3,of goodness manifold;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),21,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 21:1-4,1,2,3,N,11,3,And thou hast set upon his head
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),21,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 21:1-4,1,2,3,Y,12,3,a crown of purest gold.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),21,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 21:1-4,1,2,4,N,13,4,"When he desired life of thee,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),21,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 21:1-4,1,2,4,Y,14,4,thou life to him didst give;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),21,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 21:1-4,1,2,4,N,15,4,"Ev'n such a length of days, that he"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),21,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 21:1-4,1,2,4,Y,16,4,for evermore should live.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),21,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 21:5-7,2,3,5,N,17,5,In that salvation wrought by thee
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),21,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 21:5-7,2,3,5,Y,18,5,his glory is made great;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),21,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 21:5-7,2,3,5,N,19,5,Honour and comely majesty
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),21,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 21:5-7,2,3,5,Y,20,5,thou hast upon him set.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),21,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 21:5-7,2,3,6,N,21,6,Because that thou for evermore
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),21,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 21:5-7,2,3,6,Y,22,6,most blessed hast him made;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),21,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 21:5-7,2,3,6,N,23,6,And thou hast with thy countenance
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),21,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 21:5-7,2,3,6,Y,24,6,made him exceeding glad.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),21,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 21:5-7,2,4,7,N,25,7,Because the king upon the Lord
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),21,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 21:5-7,2,4,7,Y,26,7,his confidence doth lay;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),21,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 21:5-7,2,4,7,N,27,7,And through the grace of the most High
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),21,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 21:5-7,2,4,7,Y,28,7,shall not be mov'd away.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),21,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 21:8-13,3,4,8,N,29,8,Thine hand shall all those men find out
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),21,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 21:8-13,3,4,8,Y,30,8,that en'mies are to thee;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),21,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 21:8-13,3,4,8,N,31,8,Ev'n thy right hand shall find out those
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),21,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 21:8-13,3,4,8,Y,32,8,of thee that haters be.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),21,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 21:8-13,3,5,9,N,33,9,"Like fiery ov'n thou shalt them make,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),21,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 21:8-13,3,5,9,Y,34,9,when kindled is thine ire;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),21,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 21:8-13,3,5,9,N,35,9,"God shall them swallow in his wrath,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),21,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 21:8-13,3,5,9,Y,36,9,devour them shall the fire.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),21,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 21:8-13,3,5,10,N,37,10,"Their fruit from earth thou shalt destroy,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),21,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 21:8-13,3,5,10,Y,38,10,their seed men from among:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),21,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 21:8-13,3,5,10,N,39,11,For they beyond their might 'gainst thee
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),21,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 21:8-13,3,5,10,Y,40,11,did plot mischief and wrong.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),21,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 21:8-13,3,6,11,N,41,12,"Thou therefore shalt make them turn back,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),21,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 21:8-13,3,6,11,Y,42,12,when thou thy shafts shalt place
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),21,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 21:8-13,3,6,11,N,43,12,"Upon thy strings, made ready all"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),21,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 21:8-13,3,6,11,Y,44,12,to fly against their face.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),21,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 21:8-13,3,6,12,N,45,13,"In thy great pow'r and strength, O Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),21,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 21:8-13,3,6,12,Y,46,13,be thou exalted high;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),21,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 21:8-13,3,6,12,N,47,13,"So shall we sing with joyful hearts,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),21,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 21:8-13,3,6,12,Y,48,13,thy power praise shall we.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:1-5,1,1,1,N,1,1,"My God, my God, why hast thou me"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:1-5,1,1,1,Y,2,1,forsaken? why so far
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:1-5,1,1,1,N,3,1,"Art thou from helping me, and from"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:1-5,1,1,1,Y,4,1,my words that roaring are?
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:1-5,1,1,2,N,5,2,"All day, my God, to thee I cry,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:1-5,1,1,2,Y,6,2,yet am not heard by thee;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:1-5,1,1,2,N,7,2,And in the season of the night
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:1-5,1,1,2,Y,8,2,I cannot silent be.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:1-5,1,2,3,N,9,3,"But thou art holy, thou that dost"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:1-5,1,2,3,Y,10,3,inhabit Isr'el's praise.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:1-5,1,2,3,N,11,4,"Our fathers hop'd in thee, they hop'd"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:1-5,1,2,3,Y,12,4,and thou didst them release.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:1-5,1,2,4,N,13,5,"When unto thee they sent their cry,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:1-5,1,2,4,Y,14,5,to them deliv'rance came:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:1-5,1,2,4,N,15,5,"Because they put their trust in thee,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:1-5,1,2,4,Y,16,5,they were not put to shame.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:6-10,2,3,5,N,17,6,"But as for me, a worm I am,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:6-10,2,3,5,Y,18,6,and as no man am priz'd:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:6-10,2,3,5,N,19,6,"Reproach of men I am, and by"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:6-10,2,3,5,Y,20,6,the people am despis'd.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:6-10,2,3,6,N,21,7,All that me see laugh me to scorn;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:6-10,2,3,6,Y,22,7,shoot out the lip do they;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:6-10,2,3,6,N,23,7,"They nod and shake their heads at me,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:6-10,2,3,6,Y,24,7,"and, mocking, thus do say,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:6-10,2,4,7,N,25,8,"This man did trust in God, that he"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:6-10,2,4,7,Y,26,8,would free him by his might:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:6-10,2,4,7,N,27,8,"Let him deliver him, sith he"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:6-10,2,4,7,Y,28,8,had in him such delight.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:6-10,2,4,8,N,29,9,But thou art he out of the womb
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:6-10,2,4,8,Y,30,9,that didst me safely take;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:6-10,2,4,8,N,31,9,When I was on my mother's breasts
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:6-10,2,4,8,Y,32,9,thou me to hope didst make.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:6-10,2,5,9,N,33,10,"And I was cast upon thy care,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:6-10,2,5,9,Y,34,10,ev'n from the womb till now;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:6-10,2,5,9,N,35,10,"And from my mother's belly, Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:6-10,2,5,9,Y,36,10,my God and guide art thou.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:11-15,3,5,10,N,37,11,"Be not far off, for grief is near,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:11-15,3,5,10,Y,38,11,and none to help is found.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:11-15,3,5,10,N,39,12,"Bulls many compass me, strong bulls"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:11-15,3,5,10,Y,40,12,of Bashan me surround.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:11-15,3,6,11,N,41,13,"Their mouths they open'd wide on me,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:11-15,3,6,11,Y,42,13,"upon me gape did they,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:11-15,3,6,11,N,43,13,Like to a lion ravening
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:11-15,3,6,11,Y,44,13,and roaring for his prey.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:11-15,3,6,12,N,45,14,"Like water I'm pour'd out, my bones"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:11-15,3,6,12,Y,46,14,all out of joint do part:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:11-15,3,6,12,N,47,14,"Amidst my bowels, as the wax,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:11-15,3,6,12,Y,48,14,so melted is my heart.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:11-15,3,7,13,N,49,15,My strength is like a potsherd dry'd;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:11-15,3,7,13,Y,50,15,my tongue it cleaveth fast
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:11-15,3,7,13,N,51,15,Unto my jaws; and to the dust
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:11-15,3,7,13,Y,52,15,of death thou brought me hast.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:16-21,4,7,14,N,53,16,For dogs have compass'd me about:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:16-21,4,7,14,Y,54,16,"the wicked, that did meet"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:16-21,4,7,14,N,55,16,"In their assembly, me inclos'd;"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:16-21,4,7,14,Y,56,16,they pierc'd my hands and feet.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:16-21,4,8,15,N,57,17,I all my bones may tell; they do
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:16-21,4,8,15,Y,58,17,upon me look and stare.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:16-21,4,8,15,N,59,18,"Upon my vesture lots they cast,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:16-21,4,8,15,Y,60,18,and clothes among them share.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:16-21,4,8,16,N,61,19,"But be not far, O Lord, my strength;"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:16-21,4,8,16,Y,62,19,haste to give help to me.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:16-21,4,8,16,N,63,20,"From sword my soul, from pow'r of dogs"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:16-21,4,8,16,Y,64,20,my darling set thou free.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:16-21,4,9,17,N,65,21,Out of the roaring lion's mouth
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:16-21,4,9,17,Y,66,21,do thou me shield and save:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:16-21,4,9,17,N,67,21,For from the horns of unicorns
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:16-21,4,9,17,Y,68,21,an ear to me thou gave.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:22-26,5,9,18,N,69,22,I will shew forth thy name unto
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:22-26,5,9,18,Y,70,22,those that my brethren are;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:22-26,5,9,18,N,71,22,Amidst the congregation
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:22-26,5,9,18,Y,72,22,thy praise I will declare.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:22-26,5,10,19,N,73,23,"Praise ye the Lord, who do him fear;"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:22-26,5,10,19,Y,74,23,him glorify all ye
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:22-26,5,10,19,N,75,23,The seed of Jacob: fear him all
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:22-26,5,10,19,Y,76,23,that Isr'el's children be.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:22-26,5,10,20,N,77,24,For he despis'd not nor abhorr'd
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:22-26,5,10,20,Y,78,24,th' afflicted's misery;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:22-26,5,10,20,N,79,24,"Nor from him hid his face, but heard"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:22-26,5,10,20,Y,80,24,when he to him did cry.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:22-26,5,11,21,N,81,25,Within the congregation great
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:22-26,5,11,21,Y,82,25,my praise shall be of thee;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:22-26,5,11,21,N,83,25,My vows before them that him fear
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:22-26,5,11,21,Y,84,25,shall be perform'd by me.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:22-26,5,11,22,N,85,26,"The meek shall eat, and shall be fill'd;"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:22-26,5,11,22,Y,86,26,they also praise shall give
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:22-26,5,11,22,N,87,26,Unto the Lord that do him seek:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:22-26,5,11,22,Y,88,26,your heart shall ever live.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:27-31,6,12,23,N,89,27,"All ends of th' earth remember shall,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:27-31,6,12,23,Y,90,27,and turn the Lord unto;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:27-31,6,12,23,N,91,27,All kindreds of the nations
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:27-31,6,12,23,Y,92,27,to him shall homage do:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:27-31,6,12,24,N,93,28,Because the kingdom to the Lord
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:27-31,6,12,24,Y,94,28,doth appertain as his;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:27-31,6,12,24,N,95,28,Likewise among the nations
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:27-31,6,12,24,Y,96,28,the Governor he is.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:27-31,6,13,25,N,97,29,"Earth's fat ones eat, and worship shall:"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:27-31,6,13,25,Y,98,29,all who to dust descend
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:27-31,6,13,25,N,99,29,Shall bow to him; none of them can
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:27-31,6,13,25,Y,100,29,his soul from death defend.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:27-31,6,13,26,N,101,30,A seed shall service do to him;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:27-31,6,13,26,Y,102,30,unto the Lord it shall
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:27-31,6,13,26,N,103,30,Be for a generation
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:27-31,6,13,26,Y,104,30,reckon'd in ages all.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:27-31,6,14,27,N,105,31,"They shall come, and they shall declare"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:27-31,6,14,27,Y,106,31,his truth and righteousness
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:27-31,6,14,27,N,107,31,"Unto a people yet unborn,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),22,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 22:27-31,6,14,27,Y,108,31,and that he hath done this.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),23,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 23:1-6,1,1,1,N,1,1,"The Lord's my shepherd, I'll not want."
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),23,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 23:1-6,1,1,1,Y,2,2,He makes me down to lie
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),23,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 23:1-6,1,1,1,N,3,2,In pastures green: he leadeth me
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),23,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 23:1-6,1,1,1,Y,4,2,the quiet waters by.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),23,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 23:1-6,1,1,2,N,5,3,My soul he doth restore again;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),23,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 23:1-6,1,1,2,Y,6,3,and me to walk doth make
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),23,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 23:1-6,1,1,2,N,7,3,"Within the paths of righteousness,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),23,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 23:1-6,1,1,2,Y,8,3,ev'n for his own name's sake.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),23,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 23:1-6,1,2,3,N,9,4,"Yea, though I walk in death's dark vale,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),23,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 23:1-6,1,2,3,Y,10,4,yet will I fear none ill:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),23,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 23:1-6,1,2,3,N,11,4,For thou art with me; and thy rod
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),23,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 23:1-6,1,2,3,Y,12,4,and staff me comfort still.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),23,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 23:1-6,1,2,4,N,13,5,My table thou hast furnished
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),23,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 23:1-6,1,2,4,Y,14,5,in presence of my foes;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),23,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 23:1-6,1,2,4,N,15,5,"My head thou dost with oil anoint,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),23,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 23:1-6,1,2,4,Y,16,5,and my cup overflows.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),23,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 23:1-6,1,3,5,N,17,6,Goodness and mercy all my life
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),23,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 23:1-6,1,3,5,Y,18,6,shall surely follow me:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),23,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 23:1-6,1,3,5,N,19,6,And in God's house for evermore
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),23,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 23:1-6,1,3,5,Y,20,6,my dwelling-place shall be.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),24,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 24:1-2,1,1,1,N,1,1,"The earth belongs unto the Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),24,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 24:1-2,1,1,1,Y,2,1,and all that it contains;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),24,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 24:1-2,1,1,1,N,3,1,"The world that is inhabited,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),24,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 24:1-2,1,1,1,Y,4,1,and all that there remains.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),24,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 24:1-2,1,1,2,N,5,2,For the foundations thereof
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),24,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 24:1-2,1,1,2,Y,6,2,"he on the seas did lay,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),24,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 24:1-2,1,1,2,N,7,2,And he hath it established
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),24,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 24:1-2,1,1,2,Y,8,2,upon the floods to stay.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),24,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 24:3-6,2,2,3,N,9,3,Who is the man that shall ascend
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),24,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 24:3-6,2,2,3,Y,10,3,into the hill of God?
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),24,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 24:3-6,2,2,3,N,11,3,Or who within his holy place
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),24,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 24:3-6,2,2,3,Y,12,3,shall have a firm abode?
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),24,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 24:3-6,2,2,4,N,13,4,"Whose hands are clean, whose heart is pure,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),24,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 24:3-6,2,2,4,Y,14,4,and unto vanity
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),24,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 24:3-6,2,2,4,N,15,4,"Who hath not lifted up his soul,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),24,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 24:3-6,2,2,4,Y,16,4,nor sworn deceitfully.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),24,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 24:3-6,2,3,5,N,17,5,He from th' Eternal shall receive
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),24,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 24:3-6,2,3,5,Y,18,5,"the blessing him upon,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),24,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 24:3-6,2,3,5,N,19,5,"And righteousness, ev'n from the God"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),24,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 24:3-6,2,3,5,Y,20,5,of his salvation.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),24,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 24:3-6,2,3,6,N,21,6,This is the generation
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),24,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 24:3-6,2,3,6,Y,22,6,"that after him enquire,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),24,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 24:3-6,2,3,6,N,23,6,"O Jacob, who do seek thy face"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),24,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 24:3-6,2,3,6,Y,24,6,with their whole heart's desire.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),24,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 24:7-10,3,4,7,N,25,7,"Ye gates, lift up your heads on high;"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),24,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 24:7-10,3,4,7,Y,26,7,"ye doors that last for aye,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),24,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 24:7-10,3,4,7,N,27,7,"Be lifted up, that so the King"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),24,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 24:7-10,3,4,7,Y,28,7,of glory enter may.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),24,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 24:7-10,3,4,8,N,29,8,But who of glory is the King?
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),24,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 24:7-10,3,4,8,Y,30,8,The mighty Lord is this;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),24,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 24:7-10,3,4,8,N,31,8,"Ev'n that same Lord, that great in might"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),24,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 24:7-10,3,4,8,Y,32,8,and strong in battle is.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),24,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 24:7-10,3,5,9,N,33,9,"Ye gates, lift up your heads; ye doors,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),24,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 24:7-10,3,5,9,Y,34,9,"doors that do last for aye,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),24,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 24:7-10,3,5,9,N,35,9,"Be lifted up, that so the King"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),24,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 24:7-10,3,5,9,Y,36,9,of glory enter may.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),24,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 24:7-10,3,5,10,N,37,10,But who is he that is the King
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),24,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 24:7-10,3,5,10,Y,38,10,of glory? who is this?
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),24,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 24:7-10,3,5,10,N,39,10,"The Lord of hosts, and none but he,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),24,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 24:7-10,3,5,10,Y,40,10,the King of glory is.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:1-6 I,1,1,1,N,1,1,To thee I lift my soul:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:1-6 I,1,1,1,Y,2,2,"O Lord, I trust in thee:"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:1-6 I,1,1,1,N,3,2,"My God, let me not be asham'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:1-6 I,1,1,1,Y,4,2,nor foes triumph o'er me.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:1-6 I,1,1,2,N,5,3,Let none that wait on thee
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:1-6 I,1,1,2,Y,6,3,be put to shame at all;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:1-6 I,1,1,2,N,7,3,"But those that without cause transgress,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:1-6 I,1,1,2,Y,8,3,let shame upon them fall.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:1-6 I,1,2,3,N,9,4,"Shew me thy ways, O Lord;"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:1-6 I,1,2,3,Y,10,4,"thy paths, O teach thou me:"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:1-6 I,1,2,3,N,11,5,"And do thou lead me in thy truth,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:1-6 I,1,2,3,Y,12,5,therein my teacher be:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:1-6 I,1,2,4,N,13,5,For thou art God that dost
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:1-6 I,1,2,4,Y,14,5,"to me salvation send,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:1-6 I,1,2,4,N,15,5,And I upon thee all the day
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:1-6 I,1,2,4,Y,16,5,expecting do attend.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:1-6 I,1,3,5,N,17,6,"Thy tender mercies, Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:1-6 I,1,3,5,Y,18,6,"I pray thee to remember,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:1-6 I,1,3,5,N,19,6,And loving-kindnesses; for they
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:1-6 I,1,3,5,Y,20,6,have been of old for ever.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:7-11 I,2,3,6,N,21,7,My sins and faults of youth
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:7-11 I,2,3,6,Y,22,7,"do thou, O Lord, forget:"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:7-11 I,2,3,6,N,23,7,"After thy mercy think on me,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:7-11 I,2,3,6,Y,24,7,and for thy goodness great.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:7-11 I,2,4,7,N,25,8,God good and upright is:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:7-11 I,2,4,7,Y,26,8,the way he'll sinners show.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:7-11 I,2,4,7,N,27,9,"The meek in judgment he will guide,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:7-11 I,2,4,7,Y,28,9,and make his path to know.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:7-11 I,2,4,8,N,29,10,The whole paths of the Lord
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:7-11 I,2,4,8,Y,30,10,"are truth and mercy sure,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:7-11 I,2,4,8,N,31,10,"To those that do his cov'nant keep,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:7-11 I,2,4,8,Y,32,10,and testimonies pure.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:7-11 I,2,5,9,N,33,11,"Now, for thine own name's sake,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:7-11 I,2,5,9,Y,34,11,"O Lord, I thee entreat"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:7-11 I,2,5,9,N,35,11,To pardon mine iniquity;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:7-11 I,2,5,9,Y,36,11,for it is very great.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:12-15 I,3,5,10,N,37,12,What man is he that fears
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:12-15 I,3,5,10,Y,38,12,"the Lord, and doth him serve?"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:12-15 I,3,5,10,N,39,12,Him shall he teach the way that he
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:12-15 I,3,5,10,Y,40,12,"shall choose, and still observe."
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:12-15 I,3,6,11,N,41,13,His soul shall dwell at ease;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:12-15 I,3,6,11,Y,42,13,and his posterity
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:12-15 I,3,6,11,N,43,13,"Shall flourish still, and of the earth"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:12-15 I,3,6,11,Y,44,13,inheritors shall be.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:12-15 I,3,6,12,N,45,14,With those that fear him is
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:12-15 I,3,6,12,Y,46,14,the secret of the Lord;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:12-15 I,3,6,12,N,47,14,The knowledge of his covenant
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:12-15 I,3,6,12,Y,48,14,he will to them afford.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:12-15 I,3,7,13,N,49,15,Mine eyes upon the Lord
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:12-15 I,3,7,13,Y,50,15,continually are set:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:12-15 I,3,7,13,N,51,15,For he it is that shall bring forth
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:12-15 I,3,7,13,Y,52,15,my feet out of the net.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:16-22 I,4,7,14,N,53,16,"Turn unto me thy face,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:16-22 I,4,7,14,Y,54,16,and to me mercy show;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:16-22 I,4,7,14,N,55,16,"Because that I am desolate,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:16-22 I,4,7,14,Y,56,16,and am brought very low.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:16-22 I,4,8,15,N,57,17,My heart's griefs are increas'd:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:16-22 I,4,8,15,Y,58,17,me from distress relieve.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:16-22 I,4,8,15,N,59,18,"See mine affliction and my pain,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:16-22 I,4,8,15,Y,60,18,and all my sins forgive.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:16-22 I,4,8,16,N,61,19,"Consider thou my foes,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:16-22 I,4,8,16,Y,62,19,because they many are;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:16-22 I,4,8,16,N,63,19,And it a cruel hatred is
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:16-22 I,4,8,16,Y,64,19,which they against me bear.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:16-22 I,4,9,17,N,65,20,"O do thou keep my soul,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:16-22 I,4,9,17,Y,66,20,do thou deliver me:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:16-22 I,4,9,17,N,67,20,"And let me never be asham'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:16-22 I,4,9,17,Y,68,20,because I trust in thee.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:16-22 I,4,9,18,N,69,21,Let uprightness and truth
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:16-22 I,4,9,18,Y,70,21,"keep me, who thee attend."
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:16-22 I,4,9,18,N,71,22,"Redemption, Lord, to Israel"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 25:16-22 I,4,9,18,Y,72,22,from all his troubles send.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:1-6 II,1,9,1,N,1,1,"To thee I lift my soul, O Lord:"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:1-6 II,1,9,1,Y,2,2,"My God, I trust in thee:"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:1-6 II,1,9,1,N,3,2,Let me not be asham'd; let not
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:1-6 II,1,9,1,Y,4,2,my foes triumph o'er me.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:1-6 II,1,9,2,N,5,3,"Yea, let thou none ashamed be"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:1-6 II,1,9,2,Y,6,3,that do on thee attend:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:1-6 II,1,9,2,N,7,3,"Ashamed let them be, O Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:1-6 II,1,9,2,Y,8,3,who without cause offend.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:1-6 II,1,10,3,N,9,4,"Thy ways, Lord, shew; teach me thy paths:"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:1-6 II,1,10,3,Y,10,5,"Lead me in truth, teach me:"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:1-6 II,1,10,3,N,11,5,For of my safety thou art God;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:1-6 II,1,10,3,Y,12,5,all day I wait on thee.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:1-6 II,1,10,4,N,13,6,"Thy mercies, that most tender are,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:1-6 II,1,10,4,Y,14,6,"do thou, O Lord, remember,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:1-6 II,1,10,4,N,15,6,And loving-kindnesses; for they
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:1-6 II,1,10,4,Y,16,6,have been of old for ever.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:7-11 II,2,11,5,N,17,7,"Let not the errors of my youth,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:7-11 II,2,11,5,Y,18,7,"nor sins, remember'd be:"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:7-11 II,2,11,5,N,19,7,"In mercy, for thy goodness' sake,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:7-11 II,2,11,5,Y,20,7,"O Lord, remember me."
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:7-11 II,2,11,6,N,21,8,"The Lord is good and gracious,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:7-11 II,2,11,6,Y,22,8,he upright is also:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:7-11 II,2,11,6,N,23,8,He therefore sinners will instruct
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:7-11 II,2,11,6,Y,24,8,in ways that they should go.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:7-11 II,2,12,7,N,25,9,The meek and lowly he will guide
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:7-11 II,2,12,7,Y,26,9,in judgment just alway:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:7-11 II,2,12,7,N,27,9,To meek and poor afflicted ones
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:7-11 II,2,12,7,Y,28,9,he'll clearly teach his way.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:7-11 II,2,12,8,N,29,10,The whole paths of the Lord our God
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:7-11 II,2,12,8,Y,30,10,"are truth and mercy sure,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:7-11 II,2,12,8,N,31,10,"To such as keep his covenant,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:7-11 II,2,12,8,Y,32,10,and testimonies pure.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:7-11 II,2,13,9,N,33,11,"Now, for thine own name's sake, O Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:7-11 II,2,13,9,Y,34,11,I humbly thee entreat
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:7-11 II,2,13,9,N,35,11,To pardon mine iniquity;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:7-11 II,2,13,9,Y,36,11,for it is very great.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:12-15 II,3,13,10,N,37,12,What man fears God? him shall he teach
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:12-15 II,3,13,10,Y,38,12,the way that he shall chuse.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:12-15 II,3,13,10,N,39,13,His soul shall dwell at ease; his seed
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:12-15 II,3,13,10,Y,40,13,"the earth, as heirs, shall use."
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:12-15 II,3,14,11,N,41,14,The secret of the Lord is with
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:12-15 II,3,14,11,Y,42,14,such as do fear his name;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:12-15 II,3,14,11,N,43,14,And he his holy covenant
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:12-15 II,3,14,11,Y,44,14,will manifest to them.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:12-15 II,3,14,12,N,45,15,Towards the Lord my waiting eyes
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:12-15 II,3,14,12,Y,46,15,continually are set;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:12-15 II,3,14,12,N,47,15,For he it is that shall bring forth
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:12-15 II,3,14,12,Y,48,15,my feet out of the net.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:16-22 II,4,15,13,N,49,16,"O turn thee unto me, O God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:16-22 II,4,15,13,Y,50,16,have mercy me upon;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:16-22 II,4,15,13,N,51,16,"Because I solitary am,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:16-22 II,4,15,13,Y,52,16,and in affliction.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:16-22 II,4,15,14,N,53,17,Enlarg'd the griefs are of mine heart;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:16-22 II,4,15,14,Y,54,17,me from distress relieve.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:16-22 II,4,15,14,N,55,18,"See mine affliction and my pain,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:16-22 II,4,15,14,Y,56,18,and all my sins forgive.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:16-22 II,4,16,15,N,57,19,"Consider thou mine enemies,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:16-22 II,4,16,15,Y,58,19,because they many are;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:16-22 II,4,16,15,N,59,19,And it a cruel hatred is
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:16-22 II,4,16,15,Y,60,19,which they against me bear.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:16-22 II,4,16,16,N,61,20,"O do thou keep my soul; O God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:16-22 II,4,16,16,Y,62,20,do thou deliver me:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:16-22 II,4,16,16,N,63,20,Let me not be asham'd; for I
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:16-22 II,4,16,16,Y,64,20,do put my trust in thee.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:16-22 II,4,17,17,N,65,21,O let integrity and truth
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:16-22 II,4,17,17,Y,66,21,"keep me, who thee attend."
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:16-22 II,4,17,17,N,67,22,"Redemption, Lord, to Israel"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),25,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 25:16-22 II,4,17,17,Y,68,22,from all his troubles send.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),26,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 26:1-7,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Judge me, O Lord, for I have walk'd"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),26,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 26:1-7,1,1,1,Y,2,1,in mine integrity:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),26,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 26:1-7,1,1,1,N,3,1,I trusted also in the Lord;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),26,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 26:1-7,1,1,1,Y,4,1,slide therefore shall not I.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),26,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 26:1-7,1,1,2,N,5,2,"Examine me, and do me prove;"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),26,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 26:1-7,1,1,2,Y,6,2,"try heart and reins, O God:"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),26,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 26:1-7,1,1,2,N,7,3,"For thy love is before mine eyes,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),26,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 26:1-7,1,1,2,Y,8,3,thy truth's paths I have trode.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),26,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 26:1-7,1,2,3,N,9,4,"With persons vain I have not sat,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),26,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 26:1-7,1,2,3,Y,10,4,nor with dissemblers gone:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),26,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 26:1-7,1,2,3,N,11,5,Th' assembly of ill men I hate;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),26,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 26:1-7,1,2,3,Y,12,5,to sit with such I shun.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),26,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 26:1-7,1,2,4,N,13,6,"Mine hands in innocence, O Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),26,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 26:1-7,1,2,4,Y,14,6,I'll wash and purify;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),26,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 26:1-7,1,2,4,N,15,6,"So to thine holy altar go,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),26,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 26:1-7,1,2,4,Y,16,6,and compass it will I:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),26,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 26:1-7,1,3,5,N,17,7,"That I, with voice of thanksgiving,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),26,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 26:1-7,1,3,5,Y,18,7,"may publish and declare,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),26,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 26:1-7,1,3,5,N,19,7,"And tell of all thy mighty works,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),26,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 26:1-7,1,3,5,Y,20,7,that great and wondrous are.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),26,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 26:8-12,2,3,6,N,21,8,"The habitation of thy house,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),26,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 26:8-12,2,3,6,Y,22,8,"Lord, I have loved well;"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),26,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 26:8-12,2,3,6,N,23,8,"Yea, in that place I do delight"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),26,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 26:8-12,2,3,6,Y,24,8,where doth thine honour dwell.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),26,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 26:8-12,2,4,7,N,25,9,"With sinners gather not my soul,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),26,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 26:8-12,2,4,7,Y,26,9,and such as blood would spill:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),26,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 26:8-12,2,4,7,N,27,10,"Whose hands mischievous plots, right hand"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),26,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 26:8-12,2,4,7,Y,28,10,corrupting bribes do fill.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),26,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 26:8-12,2,4,8,N,29,11,"But as for me, I will walk on"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),26,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 26:8-12,2,4,8,Y,30,11,in mine integrity:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),26,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 26:8-12,2,4,8,N,31,11,"Do thou redeem me, and, O Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),26,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 26:8-12,2,4,8,Y,32,11,be merciful to me.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),26,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 26:8-12,2,5,9,N,33,12,My foot upon an even place
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),26,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 26:8-12,2,5,9,Y,34,12,doth stand with stedfastness:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),26,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 26:8-12,2,5,9,N,35,12,Within the congregations
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),26,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 26:8-12,2,5,9,Y,36,12,th' Eternal I will bless.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:1-3,1,1,1,N,1,1,"The Lord's my light and saving health,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:1-3,1,1,1,Y,2,1,who shall make me dismay'd?
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:1-3,1,1,1,N,3,1,"My life's strength is the Lord, of whom"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:1-3,1,1,1,Y,4,1,then shall I be afraid?
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:1-3,1,1,2,N,5,2,"When as mine enemies and foes,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:1-3,1,1,2,Y,6,2,"most wicked persons all,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:1-3,1,1,2,N,7,2,"To eat my flesh against me rose,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:1-3,1,1,2,Y,8,2,they stumbled and did fall.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:1-3,1,2,3,N,9,3,"Against me though an host encamp,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:1-3,1,2,3,Y,10,3,my heart yet fearless is:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:1-3,1,2,3,N,11,3,"Though war against me rise, I will"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:1-3,1,2,3,Y,12,3,be confident in this.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:4-6,2,2,4,N,13,4,"One thing I of the Lord desir'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:4-6,2,2,4,Y,14,4,"and will seek to obtain,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:4-6,2,2,4,N,15,4,That all days of my life I may
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:4-6,2,2,4,Y,16,4,within God's house remain;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:4-6,2,3,5,N,17,4,That I the beauty of the Lord
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:4-6,2,3,5,Y,18,4,"behold may and admire,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:4-6,2,3,5,N,19,4,And that I in his holy place
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:4-6,2,3,5,Y,20,4,may rev'rently enquire.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:4-6,2,3,6,N,21,5,For he in his pavilion shall
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:4-6,2,3,6,Y,22,5,me hide in evil days;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:4-6,2,3,6,N,23,5,"In secret of his tent me hide,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:4-6,2,3,6,Y,24,5,and on a rock me raise.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:4-6,2,4,7,N,25,6,"And now, ev'n at this present time,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:4-6,2,4,7,Y,26,6,mine head shall lifted be
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:4-6,2,4,7,N,27,6,"Above all those that are my foes,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:4-6,2,4,7,Y,28,6,and round encompass me:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:4-6,2,4,8,N,29,6,Therefore unto his tabernacle
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:4-6,2,4,8,Y,30,6,I'll sacrifices bring
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:4-6,2,4,8,N,31,6,"Of joyfulness; I'll sing, yea, I"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:4-6,2,4,8,Y,32,6,to God will praises sing.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:7-10,3,5,9,N,33,7,"O Lord, give ear unto my voice,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:7-10,3,5,9,Y,34,7,when I do cry to thee;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:7-10,3,5,9,N,35,7,"Upon me also mercy have,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:7-10,3,5,9,Y,36,7,and do thou answer me.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:7-10,3,5,10,N,37,8,"When thou didst say, Seek ye my face,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:7-10,3,5,10,Y,38,8,then unto thee reply
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:7-10,3,5,10,N,39,8,"Thus did my heart, Above all things"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:7-10,3,5,10,Y,40,8,"thy face, Lord, seek will I."
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:7-10,3,6,11,N,41,9,Far from me hide not thou thy face;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:7-10,3,6,11,Y,42,9,put not away from thee
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:7-10,3,6,11,N,43,9,Thy servant in thy wrath: thou hast
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:7-10,3,6,11,Y,44,9,an helper been to me.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:7-10,3,6,12,N,45,9,"O God of my salvation,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:7-10,3,6,12,Y,46,9,"leave me not, nor forsake:"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:7-10,3,6,12,N,47,10,"Though me my parents both should leave,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:7-10,3,6,12,Y,48,10,the Lord will me up take.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:11-14,4,7,13,N,49,11,"O Lord, instruct me in thy way,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:11-14,4,7,13,Y,50,11,to me a leader be
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:11-14,4,7,13,N,51,11,"In a plain path, because of those"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:11-14,4,7,13,Y,52,11,that hatred bear to me.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:11-14,4,7,14,N,53,12,Give me not to mine en'mies' will;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:11-14,4,7,14,Y,54,12,for witnesses that lie
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:11-14,4,7,14,N,55,12,"Against me risen are, and such"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:11-14,4,7,14,Y,56,12,as breathe out cruelty.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:11-14,4,8,15,N,57,13,"I fainted had, unless that I"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:11-14,4,8,15,Y,58,13,believed had to see
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:11-14,4,8,15,N,59,13,The Lord's own goodness in the land
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:11-14,4,8,15,Y,60,13,of them that living be.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:11-14,4,8,16,N,61,14,"Wait on the Lord, and be thou strong,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:11-14,4,8,16,Y,62,14,and he shall strength afford
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:11-14,4,8,16,N,63,14,"Unto thine heart; yea, do thou wait,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),27,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 27:11-14,4,8,16,Y,64,14,"I say, upon the Lord."
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),28,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 28:1-5,1,1,1,N,1,1,"To thee I'll cry, O Lord, my rock;"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),28,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 28:1-5,1,1,1,Y,2,1,hold not thy peace to me;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),28,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 28:1-5,1,1,1,N,3,1,Lest like those that to pit descend
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),28,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 28:1-5,1,1,1,Y,4,1,I by thy silence be.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),28,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 28:1-5,1,1,2,N,5,2,"The voice hear of my humble pray'rs,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),28,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 28:1-5,1,1,2,Y,6,2,when unto thee I cry;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),28,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 28:1-5,1,1,2,N,7,2,When to thine holy oracle
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),28,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 28:1-5,1,1,2,Y,8,2,I lift mine hands on high.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),28,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 28:1-5,1,2,3,N,9,3,With ill men draw me not away
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),28,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 28:1-5,1,2,3,Y,10,3,that work iniquity;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),28,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 28:1-5,1,2,3,N,11,3,"That speak peace to their friends, while in"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),28,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 28:1-5,1,2,3,Y,12,3,their hearts doth mischief lie.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),28,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 28:1-5,1,2,4,N,13,4,Give them according to their deeds
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),28,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 28:1-5,1,2,4,Y,14,4,and ills endeavoured:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),28,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 28:1-5,1,2,4,N,15,4,"And as their handy-works deserve,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),28,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 28:1-5,1,2,4,Y,16,4,to them be rendered.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),28,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 28:1-5,1,3,5,N,17,5,"God shall not build, but them destroy,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),28,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 28:1-5,1,3,5,Y,18,5,who would not understand
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),28,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 28:1-5,1,3,5,N,19,5,"The Lord's own works, nor did regard"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),28,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 28:1-5,1,3,5,Y,20,5,the doing of his hand.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),28,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 28:6-9,2,3,6,N,21,6,"For ever blessed be the Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),28,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 28:6-9,2,3,6,Y,22,6,for graciously he heard
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),28,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 28:6-9,2,3,6,N,23,6,"The voice of my petitions,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),28,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 28:6-9,2,3,6,Y,24,6,and prayers did regard.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),28,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 28:6-9,2,4,7,N,25,7,The Lord's my strength and shield; my heart
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),28,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 28:6-9,2,4,7,Y,26,7,upon him did rely;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),28,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 28:6-9,2,4,7,N,27,7,And I am helped: hence my heart
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),28,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 28:6-9,2,4,7,Y,28,7,"doth joy exceedingly,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),28,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 28:6-9,2,4,8,N,29,7,And with my song I will him praise.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),28,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 28:6-9,2,4,8,Y,30,8,Their strength is God alone:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),28,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 28:6-9,2,4,8,N,31,8,He also is the saving strength
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),28,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 28:6-9,2,4,8,Y,32,8,of his anointed one.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),28,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 28:6-9,2,5,9,N,33,9,"O thine own people do thou save,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),28,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 28:6-9,2,5,9,Y,34,9,bless thine inheritance;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),28,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 28:6-9,2,5,9,N,35,9,"Them also do thou feed, and them"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),28,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 28:6-9,2,5,9,Y,36,9,for evermore advance.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),29,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 29:1-4,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Give ye unto the Lord, ye sons"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),29,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 29:1-4,1,1,1,Y,2,1,"that of the mighty be,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),29,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 29:1-4,1,1,1,N,3,1,All strength and glory to the Lord
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),29,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 29:1-4,1,1,1,Y,4,1,with cheerfulness give ye.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),29,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 29:1-4,1,1,2,N,5,2,Unto the Lord the glory give
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),29,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 29:1-4,1,1,2,Y,6,2,that to his name is due;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),29,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 29:1-4,1,1,2,N,7,2,And in the beauty of holiness
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),29,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 29:1-4,1,1,2,Y,8,2,unto Jehovah bow.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),29,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 29:1-4,1,2,3,N,9,3,The Lord's voice on the waters is;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),29,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 29:1-4,1,2,3,Y,10,3,the God of majesty
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),29,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 29:1-4,1,2,3,N,11,3,"Doth thunder, and on multitudes"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),29,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 29:1-4,1,2,3,Y,12,3,of waters sitteth he.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),29,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 29:1-4,1,2,4,N,13,4,A pow'rful voice it is that comes
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),29,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 29:1-4,1,2,4,Y,14,4,out from the Lord most high;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),29,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 29:1-4,1,2,4,N,15,4,The voice of that great Lord is full
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),29,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 29:1-4,1,2,4,Y,16,4,of glorious majesty.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),29,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 29:5-11,2,3,5,N,17,5,The voice of the Eternal doth
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),29,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 29:5-11,2,3,5,Y,18,5,asunder cedars tear;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),29,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 29:5-11,2,3,5,N,19,5,"Yea, God the Lord doth cedars break"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),29,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 29:5-11,2,3,5,Y,20,5,that Lebanon doth bear.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),29,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 29:5-11,2,3,6,N,21,6,"He makes them like a calf to skip,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),29,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 29:5-11,2,3,6,Y,22,6,"ev'n that great Lebanon,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),29,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 29:5-11,2,3,6,N,23,6,"And, like to a young unicorn,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),29,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 29:5-11,2,3,6,Y,24,6,the mountain Sirion.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),29,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 29:5-11,2,4,7,N,25,7,God's voice divides the flames of fire;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),29,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 29:5-11,2,4,7,Y,26,8,The desert it doth shake:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),29,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 29:5-11,2,4,7,N,27,8,The Lord doth make the wilderness
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),29,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 29:5-11,2,4,7,Y,28,8,of Kadesh all to quake.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),29,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 29:5-11,2,4,8,N,29,9,"God's voice doth make the hinds to calve,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),29,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 29:5-11,2,4,8,Y,30,9,it makes the forest bare:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),29,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 29:5-11,2,4,8,N,31,9,And in his temple ev'ry one
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),29,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 29:5-11,2,4,8,Y,32,9,his glory doth declare.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),29,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 29:5-11,2,5,9,N,33,10,The Lord sits on the floods; the Lord
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),29,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 29:5-11,2,5,9,Y,34,10,"sits King, and ever shall."
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),29,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 29:5-11,2,5,9,N,35,11,"The Lord will give his people strength,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),29,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 29:5-11,2,5,9,Y,36,11,and with peace bless them all.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),30,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 30:1-4,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Lord, I will thee extol, for thou"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),30,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 30:1-4,1,1,1,Y,2,1,"hast lifted me on high,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),30,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 30:1-4,1,1,1,N,3,1,And over me thou to rejoice
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),30,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 30:1-4,1,1,1,Y,4,1,mad'st not mine enemy.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),30,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 30:1-4,1,1,2,N,5,2,"O thou who art the Lord my God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),30,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 30:1-4,1,1,2,Y,6,2,"I in distress to thee,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),30,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 30:1-4,1,1,2,N,7,2,"With loud cries lifted up my voice,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),30,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 30:1-4,1,1,2,Y,8,2,and thou hast healed me.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),30,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 30:1-4,1,2,3,N,9,3,"O Lord, my soul thou hast brought up,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),30,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 30:1-4,1,2,3,Y,10,3,and rescu'd from the grave;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),30,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 30:1-4,1,2,3,N,11,3,"That I to pit should not go down,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),30,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 30:1-4,1,2,3,Y,12,3,alive thou didst me save.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),30,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 30:1-4,1,2,4,N,13,4,"O ye that are his holy ones,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),30,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 30:1-4,1,2,4,Y,14,4,sing praise unto the Lord;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),30,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 30:1-4,1,2,4,N,15,4,"And give unto him thanks, when ye"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),30,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 30:1-4,1,2,4,Y,16,4,his holiness record.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),30,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 30:5-8,2,3,5,N,17,5,For but a moment lasts his wrath;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),30,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 30:5-8,2,3,5,Y,18,5,life in his favour lies:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),30,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 30:5-8,2,3,5,N,19,5,"Weeping may for a night endure,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),30,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 30:5-8,2,3,5,Y,20,5,at morn doth joy arise.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),30,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 30:5-8,2,3,6,N,21,6,"In my prosperity I said,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),30,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 30:5-8,2,3,6,Y,22,6,that nothing shall me move.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),30,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 30:5-8,2,3,6,N,23,7,"O Lord, thou hast my mountain made"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),30,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 30:5-8,2,3,6,Y,24,7,to stand strong by thy love:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),30,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 30:5-8,2,4,7,N,25,7,"But when that thou, O gracious God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),30,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 30:5-8,2,4,7,Y,26,7,"didst hide thy face from me,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),30,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 30:5-8,2,4,7,N,27,7,Then quickly was my prosp'rous state
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),30,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 30:5-8,2,4,7,Y,28,7,turn'd into misery.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),30,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 30:5-8,2,4,8,N,29,8,Wherefore unto the Lord my cry
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),30,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 30:5-8,2,4,8,Y,30,8,I caused to ascend:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),30,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 30:5-8,2,4,8,N,31,8,My humble supplication
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),30,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 30:5-8,2,4,8,Y,32,8,I to the Lord did send.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),30,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 30:9-12,3,5,9,N,33,9,"What profit is there in my blood,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),30,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 30:9-12,3,5,9,Y,34,9,when I go down to pit?
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),30,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 30:9-12,3,5,9,N,35,9,Shall unto thee the dust give praise?
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),30,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 30:9-12,3,5,9,Y,36,9,thy truth declare shall it?
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),30,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 30:9-12,3,5,10,N,37,10,"Hear, Lord, have mercy; help me, Lord:"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),30,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 30:9-12,3,5,10,Y,38,11,Thou turned hast my sadness
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),30,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 30:9-12,3,5,10,N,39,11,"To dancing; yea, my sackcloth loos'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),30,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 30:9-12,3,5,10,Y,40,11,and girded me with gladness;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),30,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 30:9-12,3,6,11,N,41,12,"That sing thy praise my glory may,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),30,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 30:9-12,3,6,11,Y,42,12,and never silent be.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),30,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 30:9-12,3,6,11,N,43,12,"O Lord my God, for evermore"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),30,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 30:9-12,3,6,11,Y,44,12,I will give thanks to thee.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:1-5,1,1,1,N,1,1,"In thee, O Lord, I put my trust,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:1-5,1,1,1,Y,2,1,sham'd let me never be;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:1-5,1,1,1,N,3,1,According to thy righteousness
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:1-5,1,1,1,Y,4,1,do thou deliver me.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:1-5,1,1,2,N,5,2,"Bow down thine ear to me, with speed"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:1-5,1,1,2,Y,6,2,send me deliverance:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:1-5,1,1,2,N,7,2,"To save me, my strong rock be thou,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:1-5,1,1,2,Y,8,2,and my house of defence.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:1-5,1,2,3,N,9,3,"Because thou art my rock, and thee"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:1-5,1,2,3,Y,10,3,I for my fortress take;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:1-5,1,2,3,N,11,3,"Therefore do thou me lead and guide,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:1-5,1,2,3,Y,12,3,ev'n for thine own name's sake.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:1-5,1,2,4,N,13,4,"And sith thou art my strength, therefore"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:1-5,1,2,4,Y,14,4,"pull me out of the net,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:1-5,1,2,4,N,15,4,Which they in subtilty for me
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:1-5,1,2,4,Y,16,4,so privily have set.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:1-5,1,3,5,N,17,5,Into thine hands I do commit
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:1-5,1,3,5,Y,18,5,"my sp'rit: for thou art he,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:1-5,1,3,5,N,19,5,"O thou, Jehovah, God of truth,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:1-5,1,3,5,Y,20,5,that hast redeemed me.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:6-8,2,3,6,N,21,6,Those that do lying vanities
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:6-8,2,3,6,Y,22,6,"regard, I have abhorr'd:"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:6-8,2,3,6,N,23,6,"But as for me, my confidence"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:6-8,2,3,6,Y,24,6,is fixed on the Lord.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:6-8,2,4,7,N,25,7,I'll in thy mercy gladly joy:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:6-8,2,4,7,Y,26,7,for thou my miseries
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:6-8,2,4,7,N,27,7,Consider'd hast; thou hast my soul
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:6-8,2,4,7,Y,28,7,known in adversities:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:6-8,2,4,8,N,29,8,And thou hast not inclosed me
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:6-8,2,4,8,Y,30,8,within the en'my's hand;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:6-8,2,4,8,N,31,8,And by thee have my feet been made
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:6-8,2,4,8,Y,32,8,in a large room to stand.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:9-13,3,5,9,N,33,9,"O Lord, upon me mercy have,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:9-13,3,5,9,Y,34,9,for trouble is on me:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:9-13,3,5,9,N,35,9,"Mine eye, my belly, and my soul,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:9-13,3,5,9,Y,36,9,with grief consumed be.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:9-13,3,5,10,N,37,10,"Because my life with grief is spent,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:9-13,3,5,10,Y,38,10,my years with sighs and groans:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:9-13,3,5,10,N,39,10,My strength doth fail; and for my sin
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:9-13,3,5,10,Y,40,10,consumed are my bones.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:9-13,3,6,11,N,41,11,"I was a scorn to all my foes,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:9-13,3,6,11,Y,42,11,and to my friends a fear;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:9-13,3,6,11,N,43,11,And specially reproach'd of those
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:9-13,3,6,11,Y,44,11,that were my neighbours near:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:9-13,3,6,12,N,45,11,When they me saw they from me fled.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:9-13,3,6,12,Y,46,12,"Ev'n so I am forgot,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:9-13,3,6,12,N,47,12,As men are out of mind when dead:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:9-13,3,6,12,Y,48,12,I'm like a broken pot.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:9-13,3,7,13,N,49,13,For slanders I of many heard;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:9-13,3,7,13,Y,50,13,"fear compass'd me, while they"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:9-13,3,7,13,N,51,13,"Against me did consult, and plot"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:9-13,3,7,13,Y,52,13,to take my life away.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:14-18,4,7,14,N,53,14,"But as for me, O Lord, my trust"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:14-18,4,7,14,Y,54,14,upon thee I did lay;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:14-18,4,7,14,N,55,14,"And I to thee, Thou art my God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:14-18,4,7,14,Y,56,14,did confidently say.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:14-18,4,8,15,N,57,15,My times are wholly in thine hand:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:14-18,4,8,15,Y,58,15,do thou deliver me
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:14-18,4,8,15,N,59,15,From their hands that mine enemies
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:14-18,4,8,15,Y,60,15,and persecutors be.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:14-18,4,8,16,N,61,16,Thy countenance to shine do thou
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:14-18,4,8,16,Y,62,16,upon thy servant make:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:14-18,4,8,16,N,63,16,"Unto me give salvation,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:14-18,4,8,16,Y,64,16,for thy great mercies' sake.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:14-18,4,9,17,N,65,17,"Let me not be asham'd, O Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:14-18,4,9,17,Y,66,17,for on thee call'd I have:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:14-18,4,9,17,N,67,17,"Let wicked men be sham'd, let them"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:14-18,4,9,17,Y,68,17,be silent in the grave.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:14-18,4,9,18,N,69,18,"To silence put the lying lips,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:14-18,4,9,18,Y,70,18,"that grievous things do say,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:14-18,4,9,18,N,71,18,"And hard reports, in pride and scorn,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:14-18,4,9,18,Y,72,18,on righteous men do lay.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:19-22,5,10,19,N,73,19,How great's the goodness thou for them
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:19-22,5,10,19,Y,74,19,"that fear thee keep'st in store,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:19-22,5,10,19,N,75,19,And wrought'st for them that trust in thee
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:19-22,5,10,19,Y,76,19,the sons of men before!
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:19-22,5,10,20,N,77,20,In secret of thy presence thou
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:19-22,5,10,20,Y,78,20,shalt hide them from man's pride:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:19-22,5,10,20,N,79,20,"From strife of tongues thou closely shalt,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:19-22,5,10,20,Y,80,20,"as in a tent, them hide."
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:19-22,5,11,21,N,81,21,All praise and thanks be to the Lord;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:19-22,5,11,21,Y,82,21,for he hath magnify'd
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:19-22,5,11,21,N,83,21,His wondrous love to me within
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:19-22,5,11,21,Y,84,21,a city fortify'd.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:19-22,5,11,22,N,85,22,"For from thine eyes cut off I am,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:19-22,5,11,22,Y,86,22,I in my haste had said;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:19-22,5,11,22,N,87,22,"My voice yet heard'st thou, when to thee"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:19-22,5,11,22,Y,88,22,with cries my moan I made.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:23-24,6,12,23,N,89,23,"O love the Lord, all ye his saints;"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:23-24,6,12,23,Y,90,23,because the Lord doth guard
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:23-24,6,12,23,N,91,23,"The faithful, and he plenteously"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:23-24,6,12,23,Y,92,23,proud doers doth reward.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:23-24,6,12,24,N,93,24,"Be of good courage, and he strength"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:23-24,6,12,24,Y,94,24,"unto your heart shall send,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:23-24,6,12,24,N,95,24,All ye whose hope and confidence
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),31,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 31:23-24,6,12,24,Y,96,24,doth on the Lord depend.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:1-2,1,1,1,N,1,1,O blessed is the man to whom
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:1-2,1,1,1,Y,2,1,is freely pardoned
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:1-2,1,1,1,N,3,1,"All the transgression he hath done,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:1-2,1,1,1,Y,4,1,whose sin is covered.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:1-2,1,1,2,N,5,2,Bless'd is the man to whom the Lord
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:1-2,1,1,2,Y,6,2,"imputeth not his sin,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:1-2,1,1,2,N,7,2,"And in whose sp'rit there is no guile,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:1-2,1,1,2,Y,8,2,nor fraud is found therein.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:3-5,2,2,3,N,9,3,"When as I did refrain my speech,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:3-5,2,2,3,Y,10,3,"and silent was my tongue,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:3-5,2,2,3,N,11,3,"My bones then waxed old, because"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:3-5,2,2,3,Y,12,3,I roared all day long.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:3-5,2,2,4,N,13,4,For upon me both day and night
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:3-5,2,2,4,Y,14,4,"thine hand did heavy lie,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:3-5,2,2,4,N,15,4,So that my moisture turned is
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:3-5,2,2,4,Y,16,4,in summer's drought thereby.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:3-5,2,3,5,N,17,5,I thereupon have unto thee
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:3-5,2,3,5,Y,18,5,"my sin acknowledged,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:3-5,2,3,5,N,19,5,And likewise mine iniquity
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:3-5,2,3,5,Y,20,5,I have not covered:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:3-5,2,3,6,N,21,5,I will confess unto the Lord
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:3-5,2,3,6,Y,22,5,"my trespasses, said I;"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:3-5,2,3,6,N,23,5,And of my sin thou freely didst
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:3-5,2,3,6,Y,24,5,forgive th' iniquity.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:6-7,3,4,7,N,25,6,For this shall ev'ry godly one
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:6-7,3,4,7,Y,26,6,his prayer make to thee;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:6-7,3,4,7,N,27,6,"In such a time he shall thee seek,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:6-7,3,4,7,Y,28,6,as found thou mayest be.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:6-7,3,4,8,N,29,6,"Surely, when floods of waters great"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:6-7,3,4,8,Y,30,6,"do swell up to the brim,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:6-7,3,4,8,N,31,6,"They shall not overwhelm his soul,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:6-7,3,4,8,Y,32,6,nor once come near to him.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:6-7,3,5,9,N,33,7,"Thou art my hiding-place, thou shalt"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:6-7,3,5,9,Y,34,7,from trouble keep me free:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:6-7,3,5,9,N,35,7,Thou with songs of deliverance
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:6-7,3,5,9,Y,36,7,about shalt compass me.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:8-11,4,5,10,N,37,8,"I will instruct thee, and thee teach"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:8-11,4,5,10,Y,38,8,the way that thou shalt go;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:8-11,4,5,10,N,39,8,"And, with mine eye upon thee set,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:8-11,4,5,10,Y,40,8,I will direction show.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:8-11,4,6,11,N,41,9,"Then be not like the horse or mule,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:8-11,4,6,11,Y,42,9,which do not understand;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:8-11,4,6,11,N,43,9,"Whose mouth, lest they come near to thee,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:8-11,4,6,11,Y,44,9,a bridle must command.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:8-11,4,6,12,N,45,10,Unto the man that wicked is
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:8-11,4,6,12,Y,46,10,his sorrows shall abound;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:8-11,4,6,12,N,47,10,But him that trusteth in the Lord
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:8-11,4,6,12,Y,48,10,mercy shall compass round.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:8-11,4,7,13,N,49,11,"Ye righteous, in the Lord be glad,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:8-11,4,7,13,Y,50,11,in him do ye rejoice:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:8-11,4,7,13,N,51,11,"All ye that upright are in heart,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),32,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 32:8-11,4,7,13,Y,52,11,for joy lift up your voice.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:1-5,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Ye righteous, in the Lord rejoice;"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:1-5,1,1,1,Y,2,1,"it comely is and right,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:1-5,1,1,1,N,3,1,"That upright men, with thankful voice,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:1-5,1,1,1,Y,4,1,should praise the Lord of might.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:1-5,1,1,2,N,5,2,"Praise God with harp, and unto him"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:1-5,1,1,2,Y,6,2,sing with the psaltery;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:1-5,1,1,2,N,7,2,Upon a ten-string'd instrument
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:1-5,1,1,2,Y,8,2,make ye sweet melody.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:1-5,1,2,3,N,9,3,"A new song to him sing, and play"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:1-5,1,2,3,Y,10,3,with loud noise skilfully;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:1-5,1,2,3,N,11,4,"For right is God's word, all his works"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:1-5,1,2,3,Y,12,4,are done in verity.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:1-5,1,2,4,N,13,5,To judgment and to righteousness
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:1-5,1,2,4,Y,14,5,a love he beareth still;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:1-5,1,2,4,N,15,5,The loving-kindness of the Lord
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:1-5,1,2,4,Y,16,5,the earth throughout doth fill.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:6-9,2,3,5,N,17,6,The heavens by the word of God
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:6-9,2,3,5,Y,18,6,did their beginning take;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:6-9,2,3,5,N,19,6,And by the breathing of his mouth
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:6-9,2,3,5,Y,20,6,he all their hosts did make.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:6-9,2,3,6,N,21,7,The waters of the seas he brings
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:6-9,2,3,6,Y,22,7,together as an heap;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:6-9,2,3,6,N,23,7,"And in storehouses, as it were,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:6-9,2,3,6,Y,24,7,he layeth up the deep.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:6-9,2,4,7,N,25,8,"Let earth, and all that live therein,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:6-9,2,4,7,Y,26,8,with rev'rence fear the Lord;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:6-9,2,4,7,N,27,8,Let all the world's inhabitants
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:6-9,2,4,7,Y,28,8,dread him with one accord.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:6-9,2,4,8,N,29,9,"For he did speak the word, and done"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:6-9,2,4,8,Y,30,9,it was without delay;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:6-9,2,4,8,N,31,9,"Established it firmly stood,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:6-9,2,4,8,Y,32,9,whatever he did say.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:10-12,3,5,9,N,33,10,God doth the counsel bring to nought
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:10-12,3,5,9,Y,34,10,which heathen folk do take;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:10-12,3,5,9,N,35,10,And what the people do devise
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:10-12,3,5,9,Y,36,10,of none effect doth make.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:10-12,3,5,10,N,37,11,O but the counsel of the Lord
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:10-12,3,5,10,Y,38,11,doth stand for ever sure;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:10-12,3,5,10,N,39,11,And of his heart the purposes
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:10-12,3,5,10,Y,40,11,from age to age endure.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:10-12,3,6,11,N,41,12,"That nation blessed is, whose God"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:10-12,3,6,11,Y,42,12,"Jehovah is, and those"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:10-12,3,6,11,N,43,12,"A blessed people are, whom for"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:10-12,3,6,11,Y,44,12,his heritage he chose.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:13-17,4,6,12,N,45,13,The Lord from heav'n sees and beholds
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:13-17,4,6,12,Y,46,13,all sons of men full well:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:13-17,4,6,12,N,47,14,He views all from his dwelling-place
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:13-17,4,6,12,Y,48,14,that in the earth do dwell.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:13-17,4,7,13,N,49,15,"He forms their hearts alike, and all"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:13-17,4,7,13,Y,50,15,their doings he observes.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:13-17,4,7,13,N,51,16,"Great hosts save not a king, much strength"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:13-17,4,7,13,Y,52,16,no mighty man preserves.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:13-17,4,7,14,N,53,17,An horse for preservation
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:13-17,4,7,14,Y,54,17,is a deceitful thing;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:13-17,4,7,14,N,55,17,And by the greatness of his strength
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:13-17,4,7,14,Y,56,17,can no deliv'rance bring.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:18-22,5,8,15,N,57,18,Behold on those that do him fear
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:18-22,5,8,15,Y,58,18,the Lord doth set his eye;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:18-22,5,8,15,N,59,18,Ev'n those who on his mercy do
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:18-22,5,8,15,Y,60,18,with confidence rely.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:18-22,5,8,16,N,61,19,"From death to free their soul, in dearth"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:18-22,5,8,16,Y,62,19,life unto them to yield.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:18-22,5,8,16,N,63,20,Our soul doth wait upon the Lord;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:18-22,5,8,16,Y,64,20,he is our help and shield.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:18-22,5,9,17,N,65,21,"Sith in his holy name we trust,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:18-22,5,9,17,Y,66,21,our heart shall joyful be.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:18-22,5,9,17,N,67,22,"Lord, let thy mercy be on us,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),33,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 33:18-22,5,9,17,Y,68,22,as we do hope in thee.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:1-7,1,1,1,N,1,1,God will I bless all times; his praise
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:1-7,1,1,1,Y,2,1,my mouth shall still express.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:1-7,1,1,1,N,3,2,My soul shall boast in God: the meek
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:1-7,1,1,1,Y,4,2,shall hear with joyfulness.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:1-7,1,1,2,N,5,3,"Extol the Lord with me, let us"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:1-7,1,1,2,Y,6,3,exalt his name together.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:1-7,1,1,2,N,7,4,"I sought the Lord, he heard, and did"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:1-7,1,1,2,Y,8,4,me from all fears deliver.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:1-7,1,2,3,N,9,5,"They look'd to him, and lighten'd were:"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:1-7,1,2,3,Y,10,5,not shamed were their faces.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:1-7,1,2,3,N,11,6,"This poor man cry'd, God heard, and sav'd"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:1-7,1,2,3,Y,12,6,him from all his distresses.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:1-7,1,2,4,N,13,7,"The angel of the Lord encamps,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:1-7,1,2,4,Y,14,7,and round encompasseth
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:1-7,1,2,4,N,15,7,"All those about that do him fear,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:1-7,1,2,4,Y,16,7,and them delivereth.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:8-10,2,3,5,N,17,8,O taste and see that God is good:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:8-10,2,3,5,Y,18,8,who trusts in him is bless'd.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:8-10,2,3,5,N,19,9,Fear God his saints: none that him fear
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:8-10,2,3,5,Y,20,9,shall be with want oppress'd.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:8-10,2,3,6,N,21,10,"The lions young may hungry be,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:8-10,2,3,6,Y,22,10,and they may lack their food:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:8-10,2,3,6,N,23,10,But they that truly seek the Lord
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:8-10,2,3,6,Y,24,10,shall not lack any good.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:11-15,3,4,7,N,25,11,"O children, hither do ye come,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:11-15,3,4,7,Y,26,11,and unto me give ear;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:11-15,3,4,7,N,27,11,I shall you teach to understand
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:11-15,3,4,7,Y,28,11,how ye the Lord should fear.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:11-15,3,4,8,N,29,12,"What man is he that life desires,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:11-15,3,4,8,Y,30,12,to see good would live long?
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:11-15,3,4,8,N,31,13,"Thy lips refrain from speaking guile,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:11-15,3,4,8,Y,32,13,and from ill words thy tongue.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:11-15,3,5,9,N,33,14,"Depart from ill, do good, seek peace,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:11-15,3,5,9,Y,34,14,pursue it earnestly.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:11-15,3,5,9,N,35,15,God's eyes are on the just; his ears
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:11-15,3,5,9,Y,36,15,are open to their cry.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:16-18,4,5,10,N,37,16,The face of God is set against
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:16-18,4,5,10,Y,38,16,"those that do wickedly,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:16-18,4,5,10,N,39,16,That he may quite out from the earth
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:16-18,4,5,10,Y,40,16,cut off their memory.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:16-18,4,6,11,N,41,17,"The righteous cry unto the Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:16-18,4,6,11,Y,42,17,he unto them gives ear;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:16-18,4,6,11,N,43,17,And they out of their troubles all
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:16-18,4,6,11,Y,44,17,by him deliver'd are.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:16-18,4,6,12,N,45,18,The Lord is ever nigh to them
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:16-18,4,6,12,Y,46,18,that be of broken sp'rit;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:16-18,4,6,12,N,47,18,To them he safety doth afford
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:16-18,4,6,12,Y,48,18,that are in heart contrite.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:19-22,5,7,13,N,49,19,The troubles that afflict the just
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:19-22,5,7,13,Y,50,19,in number many be;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:19-22,5,7,13,N,51,19,But yet at length out of them all
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:19-22,5,7,13,Y,52,19,the Lord doth set him free.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:19-22,5,7,14,N,53,20,"He carefully his bones doth keep,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:19-22,5,7,14,Y,54,20,whatever can befall;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:19-22,5,7,14,N,55,20,That not so much as one of them
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:19-22,5,7,14,Y,56,20,can broken be at all.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:19-22,5,8,15,N,57,21,Ill shall the wicked slay; laid waste
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:19-22,5,8,15,Y,58,21,shall be who hate the just.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:19-22,5,8,15,N,59,22,The Lord redeems his servants' souls;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),34,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 34:19-22,5,8,15,Y,60,22,none perish that him trust.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:1-6,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Plead, Lord, with those that plead; and fight"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:1-6,1,1,1,Y,2,1,with those that fight with me.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:1-6,1,1,1,N,3,2,"Of shield and buckler take thou hold,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:1-6,1,1,1,Y,4,2,stand up mine help to be.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:1-6,1,1,2,N,5,3,"Draw also out the spear, and do"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:1-6,1,1,2,Y,6,3,against them stop the way
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:1-6,1,1,2,N,7,3,"That me pursue: unto my soul,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:1-6,1,1,2,Y,8,3,"I'm thy salvation, say."
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:1-6,1,2,3,N,9,4,Let them confounded be and sham'd
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:1-6,1,2,3,Y,10,4,that for my soul have sought:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:1-6,1,2,3,N,11,4,"Who plot my hurt turn'd back be they,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:1-6,1,2,3,Y,12,4,and to confusion brought.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:1-6,1,2,4,N,13,5,Let them be like unto the chaff
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:1-6,1,2,4,Y,14,5,that flies before the wind;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:1-6,1,2,4,N,15,5,And let the angel of the Lord
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:1-6,1,2,4,Y,16,5,pursue them hard behind.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:1-6,1,3,5,N,17,6,"With darkness cover thou their way,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:1-6,1,3,5,Y,18,6,and let it slipp'ry prove;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:1-6,1,3,5,N,19,6,And let the angel of the Lord
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:1-6,1,3,5,Y,20,6,pursue them from above.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:7-12,2,3,6,N,21,7,For without cause have they for me
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:7-12,2,3,6,Y,22,7,"their net hid in a pit,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:7-12,2,3,6,N,23,7,They also have without a cause
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:7-12,2,3,6,Y,24,7,for my soul digged it.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:7-12,2,4,7,N,25,8,Let ruin seize him unawares;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:7-12,2,4,7,Y,26,8,his net he hid withal
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:7-12,2,4,7,N,27,8,Himself let catch; and in the same
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:7-12,2,4,7,Y,28,8,destruction let him fall.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:7-12,2,4,8,N,29,9,My soul in God shall joy; and glad
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:7-12,2,4,8,Y,30,9,in his salvation be:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:7-12,2,4,8,N,31,10,"And all my bones shall say, O Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:7-12,2,4,8,Y,32,10,"who is like unto thee,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:7-12,2,5,9,N,33,10,Which dost the poor set free from him
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:7-12,2,5,9,Y,34,10,that is for him too strong;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:7-12,2,5,9,N,35,10,The poor and needy from the man
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:7-12,2,5,9,Y,36,10,that spoils and does him wrong?
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:7-12,2,5,10,N,37,11,False witnesses rose; to my charge
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:7-12,2,5,10,Y,38,11,things I not knew they laid.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:7-12,2,5,10,N,39,12,"They, to the spoiling of my soul,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:7-12,2,5,10,Y,40,12,me ill for good repaid.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:13-17,3,6,11,N,41,13,"But as for me, when they were sick,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:13-17,3,6,11,Y,42,13,in sackcloth sad I mourn'd:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:13-17,3,6,11,N,43,13,"My humbled soul did fast, my pray'r"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:13-17,3,6,11,Y,44,13,into my bosom turn'd.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:13-17,3,6,12,N,45,14,Myself I did behave as he
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:13-17,3,6,12,Y,46,14,had been my friend or brother;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:13-17,3,6,12,N,47,14,"I heavily bow'd down, as one"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:13-17,3,6,12,Y,48,14,that mourneth for his mother.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:13-17,3,7,13,N,49,15,"But in my trouble they rejoic'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:13-17,3,7,13,Y,50,15,gath'ring themselves together;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:13-17,3,7,13,N,51,15,"Yea, abjects vile together did"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:13-17,3,7,13,Y,52,15,themselves against me gather:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:13-17,3,7,14,N,53,15,"I knew it not; they did me tear,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:13-17,3,7,14,Y,54,15,and quiet would not be.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:13-17,3,7,14,N,55,16,"With mocking hypocrites, at feasts"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:13-17,3,7,14,Y,56,16,they gnash'd their teeth at me.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:13-17,3,8,15,N,57,17,"How long, Lord, look'st thou on? from those"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:13-17,3,8,15,Y,58,17,destructions they intend
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:13-17,3,8,15,N,59,17,"Rescue my soul, from lions young"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:13-17,3,8,15,Y,60,17,my darling do defend.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:18-23,4,8,16,N,61,18,"I will give thanks to thee, O Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:18-23,4,8,16,Y,62,18,within th' assembly great;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:18-23,4,8,16,N,63,18,And where much people gather'd are
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:18-23,4,8,16,Y,64,18,thy praises forth will set.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:18-23,4,9,17,N,65,19,Let not my wrongful enemies
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:18-23,4,9,17,Y,66,19,proudly rejoice o'er me;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:18-23,4,9,17,N,67,19,"Nor who me hate without a cause,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:18-23,4,9,17,Y,68,19,let them wink with the eye.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:18-23,4,9,18,N,69,20,For peace they do not speak at all;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:18-23,4,9,18,Y,70,20,but crafty plots prepare
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:18-23,4,9,18,N,71,20,Against all those within the land
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:18-23,4,9,18,Y,72,20,that meek and quiet are.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:18-23,4,10,19,N,73,21,"With mouths set wide, they 'gainst me said,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:18-23,4,10,19,Y,74,21,"Ha, ha! our eye doth see."
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:18-23,4,10,19,N,75,22,"Lord, thou hast seen, hold not thy peace;"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:18-23,4,10,19,Y,76,22,"Lord, be not far from me."
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:18-23,4,10,20,N,77,23,"Stir up thyself; wake, that thou may'st"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:18-23,4,10,20,Y,78,23,"judgment to me afford,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:18-23,4,10,20,N,79,23,"Ev'n to my cause, O thou that art"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:18-23,4,10,20,Y,80,23,my only God and Lord.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:24-28,5,11,21,N,81,24,"O Lord my God, do thou me judge"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:24-28,5,11,21,Y,82,24,after thy righteousness;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:24-28,5,11,21,N,83,24,And let them not their joy 'gainst me
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:24-28,5,11,21,Y,84,24,triumphantly express:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:24-28,5,11,22,N,85,25,"Nor let them say within their hearts,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:24-28,5,11,22,Y,86,25,"Ah, we would have it thus;"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:24-28,5,11,22,N,87,25,"Nor suffer them to say, that he"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:24-28,5,11,22,Y,88,25,is swallow'd up by us.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:24-28,5,12,23,N,89,26,Sham'd and confounded be they all
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:24-28,5,12,23,Y,90,26,that at my hurt are glad;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:24-28,5,12,23,N,91,26,Let those against me that do boast
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:24-28,5,12,23,Y,92,26,with shame and scorn be clad.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:24-28,5,12,24,N,93,27,Let them that love my righteous cause
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:24-28,5,12,24,Y,94,27,"be glad, shout, and not cease"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:24-28,5,12,24,N,95,27,"To say, The Lord be magnify'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:24-28,5,12,24,Y,96,27,who loves his servant's peace.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:24-28,5,13,25,N,97,28,Thy righteousness shall also be
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:24-28,5,13,25,Y,98,28,declared by my tongue;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:24-28,5,13,25,N,99,28,The praises that belong to thee
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),35,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 35:24-28,5,13,25,Y,100,28,speak shall it all day long.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),36,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 36:1-4,1,1,1,N,1,1,The wicked man's transgression
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),36,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 36:1-4,1,1,1,Y,2,1,"within my heart thus says,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),36,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 36:1-4,1,1,1,N,3,1,Undoubtedly the fear of God
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),36,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 36:1-4,1,1,1,Y,4,1,is not before his eyes.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),36,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 36:1-4,1,1,2,N,5,2,Because himself he flattereth
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),36,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 36:1-4,1,1,2,Y,6,2,"in his own blinded eye,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),36,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 36:1-4,1,1,2,N,7,2,Until the hatefulness be found
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),36,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 36:1-4,1,1,2,Y,8,2,of his iniquity.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),36,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 36:1-4,1,2,3,N,9,3,"Words from his mouth proceeding are,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),36,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 36:1-4,1,2,3,Y,10,3,fraud and iniquity:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),36,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 36:1-4,1,2,3,N,11,3,"He to be wise, and to do good,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),36,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 36:1-4,1,2,3,Y,12,3,hath left off utterly.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),36,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 36:1-4,1,2,4,N,13,4,"He mischief, lying on his bed,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),36,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 36:1-4,1,2,4,Y,14,4,most cunningly doth plot:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),36,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 36:1-4,1,2,4,N,15,4,"He sets himself in ways not good,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),36,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 36:1-4,1,2,4,Y,16,4,ill he abhorreth not.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),36,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 36:5-9,2,3,5,N,17,5,"Thy mercy, Lord, is in the heav'ns;"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),36,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 36:5-9,2,3,5,Y,18,5,thy truth doth reach the clouds:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),36,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 36:5-9,2,3,5,N,19,6,Thy justice is like mountains great;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),36,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 36:5-9,2,3,5,Y,20,6,thy judgments deep as floods:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),36,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 36:5-9,2,3,6,N,21,6,"Lord, thou preservest man and beast."
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),36,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 36:5-9,2,3,6,Y,22,7,How precious is thy grace!
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),36,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 36:5-9,2,3,6,N,23,7,Therefore in shadow of thy wings
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),36,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 36:5-9,2,3,6,Y,24,7,men's sons their trust shall place.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),36,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 36:5-9,2,4,7,N,25,8,They with the fatness of thy house
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),36,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 36:5-9,2,4,7,Y,26,8,shall be well satisfy'd;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),36,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 36:5-9,2,4,7,N,27,8,From rivers of thy pleasures thou
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),36,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 36:5-9,2,4,7,Y,28,8,wilt drink to them provide.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),36,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 36:5-9,2,4,8,N,29,9,Because of life the fountain pure
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),36,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 36:5-9,2,4,8,Y,30,9,remains alone with thee;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),36,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 36:5-9,2,4,8,N,31,9,And in that purest light of thine
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),36,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 36:5-9,2,4,8,Y,32,9,we clearly light shall see.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),36,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 36:10-12,3,5,9,N,33,10,Thy loving-kindness unto them
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),36,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 36:10-12,3,5,9,Y,34,10,continue that thee know;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),36,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 36:10-12,3,5,9,N,35,10,And still on men upright in heart
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),36,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 36:10-12,3,5,9,Y,36,10,thy righteousness bestow.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),36,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 36:10-12,3,5,10,N,37,11,Let not the foot of cruel pride
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),36,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 36:10-12,3,5,10,Y,38,11,"come, and against me stand;"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),36,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 36:10-12,3,5,10,N,39,11,"And let me not removed be,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),36,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 36:10-12,3,5,10,Y,40,11,"Lord, by the wicked's hand."
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),36,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 36:10-12,3,6,11,N,41,12,"There fallen are they, and ruined,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),36,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 36:10-12,3,6,11,Y,42,12,that work iniquities:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),36,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 36:10-12,3,6,11,N,43,12,"Cast down they are, and never shall"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),36,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 36:10-12,3,6,11,Y,44,12,be able to arise.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:1-6,1,1,1,N,1,1,For evil-doers fret thou not
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:1-6,1,1,1,Y,2,1,thyself unquietly;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:1-6,1,1,1,N,3,1,Nor do thou envy bear to those
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:1-6,1,1,1,Y,4,1,that work iniquity.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:1-6,1,1,2,N,5,2,"For, even like unto the grass,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:1-6,1,1,2,Y,6,2,soon be cut down shall they;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:1-6,1,1,2,N,7,2,"And, like the green and tender herb,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:1-6,1,1,2,Y,8,2,they wither shall away.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:1-6,1,2,3,N,9,3,"Set thou thy trust upon the Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:1-6,1,2,3,Y,10,3,and be thou doing good;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:1-6,1,2,3,N,11,3,"And so thou in the land shalt dwell,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:1-6,1,2,3,Y,12,3,and verily have food.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:1-6,1,2,4,N,13,4,Delight thyself in God; he'll give
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:1-6,1,2,4,Y,14,4,thine heart's desire to thee.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:1-6,1,2,4,N,15,5,"Thy way to God commit, him trust,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:1-6,1,2,4,Y,16,5,it bring to pass shall he.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:1-6,1,3,5,N,17,6,"And, like unto the light, he shall"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:1-6,1,3,5,Y,18,6,thy righteousness display;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:1-6,1,3,5,N,19,6,And he thy judgment shall bring forth
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:1-6,1,3,5,Y,20,6,like noon-tide of the day.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:7-11,2,3,6,N,21,7,"Rest in the Lord, and patiently"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:7-11,2,3,6,Y,22,7,wait for him: do not fret
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:7-11,2,3,6,N,23,7,"For him who, prosp'ring in his way,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:7-11,2,3,6,Y,24,7,success in sin doth get.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:7-11,2,4,7,N,25,8,"Do thou from anger cease, and wrath"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:7-11,2,4,7,Y,26,8,see thou forsake also:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:7-11,2,4,7,N,27,8,"Fret not thyself in any wise,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:7-11,2,4,7,Y,28,8,that evil thou should'st do.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:7-11,2,4,8,N,29,9,For those that evil doers are
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:7-11,2,4,8,Y,30,9,shall be cut off and fall:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:7-11,2,4,8,N,31,9,But those that wait upon the Lord
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:7-11,2,4,8,Y,32,9,the earth inherit shall.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:7-11,2,5,9,N,33,10,"For yet a little while, and then"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:7-11,2,5,9,Y,34,10,the wicked shall not be;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:7-11,2,5,9,N,35,10,"His place thou shalt consider well,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:7-11,2,5,9,Y,36,10,but it thou shalt not see.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:7-11,2,5,10,N,37,11,But by inheritance the earth
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:7-11,2,5,10,Y,38,11,the meek ones shall possess:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:7-11,2,5,10,N,39,11,They also shall delight themselves
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:7-11,2,5,10,Y,40,11,in an abundant peace.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:12-15,3,6,11,N,41,12,"The wicked plots against the just,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:12-15,3,6,11,Y,42,12,and at him whets his teeth:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:12-15,3,6,11,N,43,13,"The Lord shall laugh at him, because"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:12-15,3,6,11,Y,44,13,his day he coming seeth.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:12-15,3,6,12,N,45,14,"The wicked have drawn out the sword,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:12-15,3,6,12,Y,46,14,"and bent their bow, to slay"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:12-15,3,6,12,N,47,14,"The poor and needy, and to kill"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:12-15,3,6,12,Y,48,14,men of an upright way.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:12-15,3,7,13,N,49,15,"But their own sword, which they have drawn,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:12-15,3,7,13,Y,50,15,shall enter their own heart:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:12-15,3,7,13,N,51,15,"Their bows which they have bent shall break,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:12-15,3,7,13,Y,52,15,and into pieces part.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:16-20,4,7,14,N,53,16,A little that a just man hath
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:16-20,4,7,14,Y,54,16,is more and better far
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:16-20,4,7,14,N,55,16,Than is the wealth of many such
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:16-20,4,7,14,Y,56,16,as lewd and wicked are.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:16-20,4,8,15,N,57,17,For sinners' arms shall broken be;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:16-20,4,8,15,Y,58,17,but God the just sustains.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:16-20,4,8,15,N,59,18,"God knows the just man's days, and still"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:16-20,4,8,15,Y,60,18,their heritage remains.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:16-20,4,8,16,N,61,19,They shall not be asham'd when they
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:16-20,4,8,16,Y,62,19,the evil time do see;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:16-20,4,8,16,N,63,19,"And when the days of famine are,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:16-20,4,8,16,Y,64,19,they satisfy'd shall be.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:16-20,4,9,17,N,65,20,"But wicked men, and foes of God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:16-20,4,9,17,Y,66,20,"as fat of lambs, decay;"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:16-20,4,9,17,N,67,20,"They shall consume, yea, into smoke"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:16-20,4,9,17,Y,68,20,they shall consume away.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:21-22,5,9,18,N,69,21,"The wicked borrows, but the same"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:21-22,5,9,18,Y,70,21,again he doth not pay;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:21-22,5,9,18,N,71,21,"Whereas the righteous mercy shews,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:21-22,5,9,18,Y,72,21,and gives his own away.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:21-22,5,10,19,N,73,22,For such as blessed be of him
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:21-22,5,10,19,Y,74,22,the earth inherit shall;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:21-22,5,10,19,N,75,22,And they that cursed are of him
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:21-22,5,10,19,Y,76,22,shall be destroyed all.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:23-28,6,10,20,N,77,23,A good man's footsteps by the Lord
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:23-28,6,10,20,Y,78,23,are ordered aright;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:23-28,6,10,20,N,79,23,And in the way wherein he walks
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:23-28,6,10,20,Y,80,23,he greatly doth delight.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:23-28,6,11,21,N,81,24,"Although he fall, yet shall he not"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:23-28,6,11,21,Y,82,24,be cast down utterly;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:23-28,6,11,21,N,83,24,Because the Lord with his own hand
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:23-28,6,11,21,Y,84,24,upholds him mightily.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:23-28,6,11,22,N,85,25,"I have been young, and now am old,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:23-28,6,11,22,Y,86,25,yet have I never seen
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:23-28,6,11,22,N,87,25,"The just man left, nor that his seed"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:23-28,6,11,22,Y,88,25,for bread have beggars been.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:23-28,6,12,23,N,89,26,"He's ever merciful, and lends:"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:23-28,6,12,23,Y,90,26,his seed is bless'd therefore.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:23-28,6,12,23,N,91,27,"Depart from evil, and do good,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:23-28,6,12,23,Y,92,27,and dwell for evermore.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:23-28,6,12,24,N,93,28,"For God loves judgment, and his saints"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:23-28,6,12,24,Y,94,28,leaves not in any case;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:23-28,6,12,24,N,95,28,They are kept ever: but cut off
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:23-28,6,12,24,Y,96,28,shall be the sinner's race.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:29-36,7,13,25,N,97,29,"The just inherit shall the land,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:29-36,7,13,25,Y,98,29,and ever in it dwell:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:29-36,7,13,25,N,99,30,The just man's mouth doth wisdom speak;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:29-36,7,13,25,Y,100,30,his tongue doth judgment tell.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:29-36,7,13,26,N,101,31,"In's heart the law is of his God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:29-36,7,13,26,Y,102,31,his steps slide not away.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:29-36,7,13,26,N,103,32,"The wicked man doth watch the just,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:29-36,7,13,26,Y,104,32,and seeketh him to slay.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:29-36,7,14,27,N,105,33,"Yet him the Lord will not forsake,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:29-36,7,14,27,Y,106,33,nor leave him in his hands:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:29-36,7,14,27,N,107,33,"The righteous will he not condemn,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:29-36,7,14,27,Y,108,33,when he in judgment stands.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:29-36,7,14,28,N,109,34,"Wait on the Lord, and keep his way,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:29-36,7,14,28,Y,110,34,and thee exalt shall he
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:29-36,7,14,28,N,111,34,Th' earth to inherit; when cut off
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:29-36,7,14,28,Y,112,34,the wicked thou shalt see.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:29-36,7,15,29,N,113,35,"I saw the wicked great in pow'r,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:29-36,7,15,29,Y,114,35,spread like a green bay-tree:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:29-36,7,15,29,N,115,36,"He pass'd, yea, was not; him I sought,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:29-36,7,15,29,Y,116,36,but found he could not be.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:37-40,8,15,30,N,117,37,"Mark thou the perfect, and behold"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:37-40,8,15,30,Y,118,37,the man of uprightness;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:37-40,8,15,30,N,119,37,Because that surely of this man
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:37-40,8,15,30,Y,120,37,the latter end is peace.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:37-40,8,16,31,N,121,38,But those men that transgressors are
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:37-40,8,16,31,Y,122,38,shall be destroy'd together;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:37-40,8,16,31,N,123,38,The latter end of wicked men
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:37-40,8,16,31,Y,124,38,shall be cut off for ever.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:37-40,8,16,32,N,125,39,But the salvation of the just
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:37-40,8,16,32,Y,126,39,is from the Lord above;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:37-40,8,16,32,N,127,39,He in the time of their distress
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:37-40,8,16,32,Y,128,39,their stay and strength doth prove.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:37-40,8,17,33,N,129,40,"The Lord shall help, and them deliver:"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:37-40,8,17,33,Y,130,40,he shall them free and save
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:37-40,8,17,33,N,131,40,From wicked men; because in him
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),37,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 37:37-40,8,17,33,Y,132,40,their confidence they have.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:1-4,1,1,1,N,1,1,"In thy great indignation,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:1-4,1,1,1,Y,2,1,"O Lord, rebuke me not;"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:1-4,1,1,1,N,3,1,"Nor on me lay thy chast'ning hand,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:1-4,1,1,1,Y,4,1,in thy displeasure hot.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:1-4,1,1,2,N,5,2,"For in me fast thine arrows stick,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:1-4,1,1,2,Y,6,2,thine hand doth press me sore:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:1-4,1,1,2,N,7,3,"And in my flesh there is no health,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:1-4,1,1,2,Y,8,3,nor soundness any more.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:1-4,1,2,3,N,9,3,"This grief I have, because thy wrath"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:1-4,1,2,3,Y,10,3,is forth against me gone;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:1-4,1,2,3,N,11,3,"And in my bones there is no rest,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:1-4,1,2,3,Y,12,3,for sin that I have done.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:1-4,1,2,4,N,13,4,Because gone up above mine head
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:1-4,1,2,4,Y,14,4,my great transgressions be;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:1-4,1,2,4,N,15,4,"And, as a weighty burden, they"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:1-4,1,2,4,Y,16,4,too heavy are for me.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:5-8,2,3,5,N,17,5,"My wounds do stink, and are corrupt;"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:5-8,2,3,5,Y,18,5,my folly makes it so.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:5-8,2,3,5,N,19,6,"I troubled am, and much bow'd down;"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:5-8,2,3,5,Y,20,6,all day I mourning go.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:5-8,2,3,6,N,21,7,For a disease that loathsome is
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:5-8,2,3,6,Y,22,7,"so fills my loins with pain,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:5-8,2,3,6,N,23,7,That in my weak and weary flesh
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:5-8,2,3,6,Y,24,7,no soundness doth remain.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:5-8,2,4,7,N,25,8,"So feeble and infirm am I,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:5-8,2,4,7,Y,26,8,"and broken am so sore,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:5-8,2,4,7,N,27,8,"That, through disquiet of my heart,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:5-8,2,4,7,Y,28,8,I have been made to roar.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:9-12,3,4,8,N,29,9,"O Lord, all that I do desire"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:9-12,3,4,8,Y,30,9,is still before thine eye;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:9-12,3,4,8,N,31,9,And of my heart the secret groans
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:9-12,3,4,8,Y,32,9,not hidden are from thee.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:9-12,3,5,9,N,33,10,"My heart doth pant incessantly,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:9-12,3,5,9,Y,34,10,my strength doth quite decay;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:9-12,3,5,9,N,35,10,"As for mine eyes, their wonted light"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:9-12,3,5,9,Y,36,10,is from me gone away.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:9-12,3,5,10,N,37,11,My lovers and my friends do stand
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:9-12,3,5,10,Y,38,11,at distance from my sore;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:9-12,3,5,10,N,39,11,And those do stand aloof that were
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:9-12,3,5,10,Y,40,11,kinsmen and kind before.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:9-12,3,6,11,N,41,12,"Yea, they that seek my life lay snares:"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:9-12,3,6,11,Y,42,12,who seek to do me wrong
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:9-12,3,6,11,N,43,12,"Speak things mischievous, and deceits"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:9-12,3,6,11,Y,44,12,imagine all day long.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:13-18,4,6,12,N,45,13,"But, as one deaf, that heareth not,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:13-18,4,6,12,Y,46,13,I suffer'd all to pass;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:13-18,4,6,12,N,47,13,"I as a dumb man did become,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:13-18,4,6,12,Y,48,13,whose mouth not open'd was:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:13-18,4,7,13,N,49,14,"As one that hears not, in whose mouth"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:13-18,4,7,13,Y,50,14,are no reproofs at all.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:13-18,4,7,13,N,51,15,"For, Lord, I hope in thee; my God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:13-18,4,7,13,Y,52,15,thou'lt hear me when I call.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:13-18,4,7,14,N,53,16,"For I said, Hear me, lest they should"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:13-18,4,7,14,Y,54,16,rejoice o'er me with pride;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:13-18,4,7,14,N,55,16,"And o'er me magnify themselves,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:13-18,4,7,14,Y,56,16,when as my foot doth slide.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:13-18,4,8,15,N,57,17,"For I am near to halt, my grief"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:13-18,4,8,15,Y,58,17,is still before mine eye:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:13-18,4,8,15,N,59,18,"For I'll declare my sin, and grieve"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:13-18,4,8,15,Y,60,18,for mine iniquity.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:19-22,5,8,16,N,61,19,"But yet mine en'mies lively are,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:19-22,5,8,16,Y,62,19,and strong are they beside;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:19-22,5,8,16,N,63,19,And they that hate me wrongfully
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:19-22,5,8,16,Y,64,19,are greatly multiply'd.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:19-22,5,9,17,N,65,20,"And they for good that render ill,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:19-22,5,9,17,Y,66,20,as en'mies me withstood;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:19-22,5,9,17,N,67,20,"Yea, ev'n for this, because that I"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:19-22,5,9,17,Y,68,20,do follow what is good.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:19-22,5,9,18,N,69,21,"Forsake me not, O Lord; my God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:19-22,5,9,18,Y,70,21,far from me never be.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:19-22,5,9,18,N,71,22,"O Lord, thou my salvation art,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),38,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 38:19-22,5,9,18,Y,72,22,haste to give help to me.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),39,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 39:1-4,1,1,1,N,1,1,"I said, I will look to my ways,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),39,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 39:1-4,1,1,1,Y,2,1,lest with my tongue I sin:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),39,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 39:1-4,1,1,1,N,3,1,In sight of wicked men my mouth
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),39,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 39:1-4,1,1,1,Y,4,1,with bridle I'll keep in.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),39,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 39:1-4,1,1,2,N,5,2,"With silence I as dumb became,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),39,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 39:1-4,1,1,2,Y,6,2,I did myself restrain
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),39,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 39:1-4,1,1,2,N,7,2,From speaking good; but then the more
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),39,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 39:1-4,1,1,2,Y,8,2,increased was my pain.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),39,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 39:1-4,1,2,3,N,9,3,My heart within me waxed hot;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),39,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 39:1-4,1,2,3,Y,10,3,"and, while I musing was,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),39,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 39:1-4,1,2,3,N,11,3,The fire did burn; and from my tongue
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),39,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 39:1-4,1,2,3,Y,12,3,these words I did let pass:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),39,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 39:1-4,1,2,4,N,13,4,"Mine end, and measure of my days,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),39,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 39:1-4,1,2,4,Y,14,4,"O Lord, unto me show"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),39,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 39:1-4,1,2,4,N,15,4,What is the same; that I thereby
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),39,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 39:1-4,1,2,4,Y,16,4,my frailty well may know.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),39,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 39:5-10,2,3,5,N,17,5,"Lo, thou my days an handbreadth mad'st;"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),39,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 39:5-10,2,3,5,Y,18,5,mine age is in thine eye
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),39,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 39:5-10,2,3,5,N,19,5,As nothing: sure each man at best
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),39,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 39:5-10,2,3,5,Y,20,5,is wholly vanity.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),39,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 39:5-10,2,3,6,N,21,6,Sure each man walks in a vain show;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),39,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 39:5-10,2,3,6,Y,22,6,they vex themselves in vain:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),39,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 39:5-10,2,3,6,N,23,6,"He heaps up wealth, and doth not know"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),39,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 39:5-10,2,3,6,Y,24,6,to whom it shall pertain.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),39,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 39:5-10,2,4,7,N,25,7,"And now, O Lord, what wait I for?"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),39,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 39:5-10,2,4,7,Y,26,7,my hope is fix'd on thee.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),39,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 39:5-10,2,4,7,N,27,8,"Free me from all my trespasses,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),39,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 39:5-10,2,4,7,Y,28,8,the fool's scorn make not me.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),39,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 39:5-10,2,4,8,N,29,9,"Dumb was I, op'ning not my mouth,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),39,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 39:5-10,2,4,8,Y,30,9,because this work was thine.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),39,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 39:5-10,2,4,8,N,31,10,Thy stroke take from me; by the blow
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),39,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 39:5-10,2,4,8,Y,32,10,of thine hand I do pine.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),39,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 39:11-13,3,5,9,N,33,11,When with rebukes thou dost correct
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),39,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 39:11-13,3,5,9,Y,34,11,"man for iniquity,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),39,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 39:11-13,3,5,9,N,35,11,Thou wastes his beauty like a moth:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),39,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 39:11-13,3,5,9,Y,36,11,sure each man's vanity.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),39,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 39:11-13,3,5,10,N,37,12,"Attend my cry, Lord, at my tears"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),39,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 39:11-13,3,5,10,Y,38,12,and pray'rs not silent be:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),39,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 39:11-13,3,5,10,N,39,12,"I sojourn as my fathers all,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),39,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 39:11-13,3,5,10,Y,40,12,and stranger am with thee.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),39,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 39:11-13,3,6,11,N,41,13,"O spare thou me, that I my strength"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),39,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 39:11-13,3,6,11,Y,42,13,"recover may again,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),39,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 39:11-13,3,6,11,N,43,13,"Before from hence I do depart,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),39,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 39:11-13,3,6,11,Y,44,13,and here no more remain.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:1-4,1,1,1,N,1,1,"I waited for the Lord my God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:1-4,1,1,1,Y,2,1,and patiently did bear;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:1-4,1,1,1,N,3,1,At length to me he did incline
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:1-4,1,1,1,Y,4,1,my voice and cry to hear.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:1-4,1,1,2,N,5,2,"He took me from a fearful pit,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:1-4,1,1,2,Y,6,2,"and from the miry clay,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:1-4,1,1,2,N,7,2,"And on a rock he set my feet,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:1-4,1,1,2,Y,8,2,establishing my way.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:1-4,1,2,3,N,9,3,"He put a new song in my mouth,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:1-4,1,2,3,Y,10,3,our God to magnify:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:1-4,1,2,3,N,11,3,"Many shall see it, and shall fear,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:1-4,1,2,3,Y,12,3,and on the Lord rely.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:1-4,1,2,4,N,13,4,O blessed is the man whose trust
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:1-4,1,2,4,Y,14,4,upon the Lord relies;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:1-4,1,2,4,N,15,4,"Respecting not the proud, nor such"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:1-4,1,2,4,Y,16,4,as turn aside to lies.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:5-8,2,3,5,N,17,5,"O Lord my God, full many are"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:5-8,2,3,5,Y,18,5,the wonders thou hast done;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:5-8,2,3,5,N,19,5,Thy gracious thoughts to us-ward far
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:5-8,2,3,5,Y,20,5,above all thoughts are gone:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:5-8,2,3,6,N,21,5,In order none can reckon them
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:5-8,2,3,6,Y,22,5,"to thee: if them declare,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:5-8,2,3,6,N,23,5,"And speak of them I would, they more"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:5-8,2,3,6,Y,24,5,than can be number'd are.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:5-8,2,4,7,N,25,6,No sacrifice nor offering
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:5-8,2,4,7,Y,26,6,didst thou at all desire;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:5-8,2,4,7,N,27,6,Mine ears thou bor'd: sin-off 'ring thou
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:5-8,2,4,7,Y,28,6,and burnt didst not require:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:5-8,2,4,8,N,29,7,"Then to the Lord these were my words,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:5-8,2,4,8,Y,30,7,"I come, behold and see;"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:5-8,2,4,8,N,31,7,Within the volume of the book
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:5-8,2,4,8,Y,32,7,it written is of me:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:5-8,2,5,9,N,33,8,"To do thy will I take delight,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:5-8,2,5,9,Y,34,8,O thou my God that art;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:5-8,2,5,9,N,35,8,"Yea, that most holy law of thine"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:5-8,2,5,9,Y,36,8,I have within my heart.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:9-10,3,5,10,N,37,9,Within the congregation great
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:9-10,3,5,10,Y,38,9,I righteousness did preach:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:9-10,3,5,10,N,39,9,"Lo, thou dost know, O Lord, that I"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:9-10,3,5,10,Y,40,9,refrained not my speech.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:9-10,3,6,11,N,41,10,I never did within my heart
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:9-10,3,6,11,Y,42,10,conceal thy righteousness;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:9-10,3,6,11,N,43,10,"I thy salvation have declar'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:9-10,3,6,11,Y,44,10,and shown thy faithfulness:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:9-10,3,6,12,N,45,10,"Thy kindness, which most loving is,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:9-10,3,6,12,Y,46,10,"concealed have not I,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:9-10,3,6,12,N,47,10,Nor from the congregation great
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:9-10,3,6,12,Y,48,10,have hid thy verity.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:11-14,4,7,13,N,49,11,"Thy tender mercies, Lord, from me"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:11-14,4,7,13,Y,50,11,O do thou not restrain;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:11-14,4,7,13,N,51,11,"Thy loving-kindness, and thy truth,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:11-14,4,7,13,Y,52,11,let them me still maintain.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:11-14,4,7,14,N,53,12,"For ills past reck'ning compass me,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:11-14,4,7,14,Y,54,12,and mine iniquities
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:11-14,4,7,14,N,55,12,"Such hold upon me taken have,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:11-14,4,7,14,Y,56,12,I cannot lift mine eyes:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:11-14,4,8,15,N,57,12,"They more than hairs are on mine head,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:11-14,4,8,15,Y,58,12,thence is my heart dismay'd.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:11-14,4,8,15,N,59,13,"Be pleased, Lord, to rescue me;"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:11-14,4,8,15,Y,60,13,"Lord, hasten to mine aid."
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:11-14,4,8,16,N,61,14,Sham'd and confounded be they all
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:11-14,4,8,16,Y,62,14,that seek my soul to kill;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:11-14,4,8,16,N,63,14,"Yea, let them backward driven be,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:11-14,4,8,16,Y,64,14,"and sham'd, that wish me ill."
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:15-17,5,9,17,N,65,15,For a reward of this their shame
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:15-17,5,9,17,Y,66,15,confounded let them be.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:15-17,5,9,17,N,67,15,"That in this manner scoffing say,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:15-17,5,9,17,Y,68,15,"Aha, aha! to me."
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:15-17,5,9,18,N,69,16,"In thee let all be glad, and joy,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:15-17,5,9,18,Y,70,16,who seeking thee abide;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:15-17,5,9,18,N,71,16,"Who thy salvation love, say still,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:15-17,5,9,18,Y,72,16,The Lord be magnify'd.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:15-17,5,10,19,N,73,17,"I'm poor and needy, yet the Lord"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:15-17,5,10,19,Y,74,17,of me a care doth take:
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:15-17,5,10,19,N,75,17,"Thou art my help and saviour,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),40,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 40:15-17,5,10,19,Y,76,17,"my God, no tarrying make."
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),41,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 41:1-4,1,1,1,N,1,1,Blessed is he that wisely doth
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),41,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 41:1-4,1,1,1,Y,2,1,the poor man's case consider;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),41,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 41:1-4,1,1,1,N,3,1,"For when the time of trouble is,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),41,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 41:1-4,1,1,1,Y,4,1,the Lord will him deliver.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),41,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 41:1-4,1,1,2,N,5,2,"God will him keep, yea, save alive;"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),41,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 41:1-4,1,1,2,Y,6,2,on earth he bless'd shall live;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),41,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 41:1-4,1,1,2,N,7,2,And to his enemies' desire
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),41,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 41:1-4,1,1,2,Y,8,2,thou wilt him not up give.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),41,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 41:1-4,1,2,3,N,9,3,God will give strength when he on bed
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),41,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 41:1-4,1,2,3,Y,10,3,of languishing doth mourn;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),41,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 41:1-4,1,2,3,N,11,3,"And in his sickness sore, O Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),41,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 41:1-4,1,2,3,Y,12,3,thou all his bed wilt turn.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),41,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 41:1-4,1,2,4,N,13,4,"I said, O Lord, do thou extend"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),41,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 41:1-4,1,2,4,Y,14,4,thy mercy unto me;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),41,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 41:1-4,1,2,4,N,15,4,O do thou heal my soul; for why?
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),41,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 41:1-4,1,2,4,Y,16,4,I have offended thee.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),41,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 41:5-9,2,3,5,N,17,5,"Those that to me are enemies,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),41,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 41:5-9,2,3,5,Y,18,5,"of me do evil say,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),41,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 41:5-9,2,3,5,N,19,5,"When shall he die, that so his name"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),41,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 41:5-9,2,3,5,Y,20,5,may perish quite away?
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),41,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 41:5-9,2,3,6,N,21,6,"To see me if he comes, he speaks"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),41,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 41:5-9,2,3,6,Y,22,6,vain words: but then his heart
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),41,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 41:5-9,2,3,6,N,23,6,"Heaps mischief to it, which he tells,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),41,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 41:5-9,2,3,6,Y,24,6,when forth he doth depart.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),41,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 41:5-9,2,4,7,N,25,7,"My haters jointly whispering,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),41,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 41:5-9,2,4,7,Y,26,7,'gainst me my hurt devise.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),41,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 41:5-9,2,4,7,N,27,8,"Mischief, say they, cleaves fast to him;"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),41,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 41:5-9,2,4,7,Y,28,8,"he li'th, and shall not rise."
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),41,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 41:5-9,2,4,8,N,29,9,"Yea, ev'n mine own familiar friend,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),41,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 41:5-9,2,4,8,Y,30,9,"on whom I did rely,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),41,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 41:5-9,2,4,8,N,31,9,"Who ate my bread, ev'n he his heel"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),41,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 41:5-9,2,4,8,Y,32,9,against me lifted high.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),41,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 41:10-13,3,5,9,N,33,10,"But, Lord, be merciful to me,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),41,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 41:10-13,3,5,9,Y,34,10,"and up again me raise,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),41,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 41:10-13,3,5,9,N,35,10,That I may justly them requite
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),41,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 41:10-13,3,5,9,Y,36,10,according to their ways.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),41,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 41:10-13,3,5,10,N,37,11,By this I know that certainly
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),41,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 41:10-13,3,5,10,Y,38,11,I favour'd am by thee;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),41,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 41:10-13,3,5,10,N,39,11,Because my hateful enemy
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),41,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 41:10-13,3,5,10,Y,40,11,triumphs not over me.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),41,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 41:10-13,3,6,11,N,41,12,"But as for me, thou me uphold'st"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),41,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 41:10-13,3,6,11,Y,42,12,in mine integrity;
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),41,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 41:10-13,3,6,11,N,43,12,And me before thy countenance
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),41,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 41:10-13,3,6,11,Y,44,12,thou sett'st continually.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),41,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 41:10-13,3,6,12,N,45,13,"The Lord, the God ofIsrael,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),41,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 41:10-13,3,6,12,Y,46,13,"be bless'd for ever then,"
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),41,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 41:10-13,3,6,12,N,47,13,From age to age eternally.
1650 Psalter,Book 1 (Psalm 1-41),41,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 41:10-13,3,6,12,Y,48,13,"Amen, yea, and amen."
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:1-2,1,1,1,N,1,1,Like as the hart for water-brooks
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:1-2,1,1,1,Y,2,1,in thirst doth pant and bray;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:1-2,1,1,1,N,3,1,"So pants my longing soul, O God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:1-2,1,1,1,Y,4,1,that come to thee I may.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:1-2,1,1,2,N,5,2,"My soul for God, the living God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:1-2,1,1,2,Y,6,2,doth thirst: when shall I near
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:1-2,1,1,2,N,7,2,"Unto thy countenance approach,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:1-2,1,1,2,Y,8,2,and in God's sight appear?
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:3-5,2,2,3,N,9,3,"My tears have unto me been meat,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:3-5,2,2,3,Y,10,3,"both in the night and day,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:3-5,2,2,3,N,11,3,"While unto me continually,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:3-5,2,2,3,Y,12,3,Where is thy God? they say.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:3-5,2,2,4,N,13,4,"My soul is poured out in me,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:3-5,2,2,4,Y,14,4,when this I think upon;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:3-5,2,2,4,N,15,4,Because that with the multitude
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:3-5,2,2,4,Y,16,4,I heretofore had gone:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:3-5,2,3,5,N,17,4,"With them into God's house I went,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:3-5,2,3,5,Y,18,4,with voice of joy and praise;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:3-5,2,3,5,N,19,4,"Yea, with the multitude that kept"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:3-5,2,3,5,Y,20,4,the solemn holy days.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:3-5,2,3,6,N,21,5,"O why art thou cast down, my soul?"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:3-5,2,3,6,Y,22,5,why in me so dismay'd?
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:3-5,2,3,6,N,23,5,"Trust God, for I shall praise him yet,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:3-5,2,3,6,Y,24,5,his count'nance is mine aid.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:6-7,3,4,7,N,25,6,"My God, my soul's cast down in me;"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:6-7,3,4,7,Y,26,6,thee therefore mind I will
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:6-7,3,4,7,N,27,6,"From Jordan's land, the Hermonites,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:6-7,3,4,7,Y,28,6,and ev'n from Mizar hill.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:6-7,3,4,8,N,29,7,At the noise of thy water-spouts
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:6-7,3,4,8,Y,30,7,deep unto deep doth call;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:6-7,3,4,8,N,31,7,"Thy breaking waves pass over me,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:6-7,3,4,8,Y,32,7,"yea, and thy billows all."
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:8-11,4,5,9,N,33,8,His loving-kindness yet the Lord
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:8-11,4,5,9,Y,34,8,"command will in the day,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:8-11,4,5,9,N,35,8,"His song's with me by night; to God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:8-11,4,5,9,Y,36,8,"by whom I live, I'll pray:"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:8-11,4,5,10,N,37,9,"And I will say to God my rock,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:8-11,4,5,10,Y,38,9,Why me forgett'st thou so?
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:8-11,4,5,10,N,39,9,"Why, for my foes' oppression,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:8-11,4,5,10,Y,40,9,thus mourning do I go?
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:8-11,4,6,11,N,41,10,"'Tis as a sword within my bones,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:8-11,4,6,11,Y,42,10,when my foes me upbraid;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:8-11,4,6,11,N,43,10,"Ev'n when by them, Where is thy God?"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:8-11,4,6,11,Y,44,10,'tis daily to me said.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:8-11,4,6,12,N,45,11,"O why art thou cast down, my soul?"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:8-11,4,6,12,Y,46,11,"why, thus with grief opprest,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:8-11,4,6,12,N,47,11,Art thou disquieted in me?
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:8-11,4,6,12,Y,48,11,in God still hope and rest:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:8-11,4,7,13,N,49,11,"For yet I know I shall him praise,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:8-11,4,7,13,Y,50,11,who graciously to me
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:8-11,4,7,13,N,51,11,"The health is of my countenance,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),42,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 42:8-11,4,7,13,Y,52,11,"yea, mine own God is he."
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),43,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 43:1-2,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Judge me, O God, and plead my cause"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),43,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 43:1-2,1,1,1,Y,2,1,against th' ungodly nation;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),43,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 43:1-2,1,1,1,N,3,1,"From the unjust and crafty man,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),43,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 43:1-2,1,1,1,Y,4,1,O be thou my salvation.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),43,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 43:1-2,1,1,2,N,5,2,For thou the God art of my strength;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),43,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 43:1-2,1,1,2,Y,6,2,why thrusts thou me thee fro'?
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),43,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 43:1-2,1,1,2,N,7,2,For th' enemy's oppression
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),43,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 43:1-2,1,1,2,Y,8,2,why do I mourning go?
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),43,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 43:3-5,2,2,3,N,9,3,O send thy light forth and thy truth;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),43,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 43:3-5,2,2,3,Y,10,3,"let them be guides to me,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),43,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 43:3-5,2,2,3,N,11,3,"And bring me to thine holy hill,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),43,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 43:3-5,2,2,3,Y,12,3,ev'n where thy dwellings be.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),43,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 43:3-5,2,2,4,N,13,4,"Then will I to God's altar go,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),43,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 43:3-5,2,2,4,Y,14,4,to God my chiefest joy:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),43,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 43:3-5,2,2,4,N,15,4,"Yea, God, my God, thy name to praise"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),43,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 43:3-5,2,2,4,Y,16,4,my harp I will employ.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),43,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 43:3-5,2,3,5,N,17,5,"Why art thou then cast down, my soul?"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),43,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 43:3-5,2,3,5,Y,18,5,what should discourage thee?
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),43,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 43:3-5,2,3,5,N,19,5,And why with vexing thoughts art thou
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),43,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 43:3-5,2,3,5,Y,20,5,disquieted in me?
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),43,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 43:3-5,2,3,6,N,21,5,Still trust in God; for him to praise
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),43,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 43:3-5,2,3,6,Y,22,5,good cause I yet shall have:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),43,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 43:3-5,2,3,6,N,23,5,"He of my count'nance is the health,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),43,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 43:3-5,2,3,6,Y,24,5,my God that doth me save.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:1-3,1,1,1,N,1,1,"O God, we with our ears have heard,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:1-3,1,1,1,Y,2,1,"our fathers have us told,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:1-3,1,1,1,N,3,1,"What works thou in their days hadst done,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:1-3,1,1,1,Y,4,1,ev'n in the days of old.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:1-3,1,1,2,N,5,2,"Thy hand did drive the heathen out,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:1-3,1,1,2,Y,6,2,and plant them in their place;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:1-3,1,1,2,N,7,2,"Thou didst afflict the nations,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:1-3,1,1,2,Y,8,2,but them thou didst increase.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:1-3,1,2,3,N,9,3,"For neither got their sword the land,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:1-3,1,2,3,Y,10,3,nor did their arm them save;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:1-3,1,2,3,N,11,3,"But thy right hand, arm, countenance;"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:1-3,1,2,3,Y,12,3,for thou them favour gave.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:4-8,2,2,4,N,13,4,"Thou art my King: for Jacob, Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:4-8,2,2,4,Y,14,4,deliv'rances command.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:4-8,2,2,4,N,15,5,"Through thee we shall push down our foes,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:4-8,2,2,4,Y,16,5,that do against us stand:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:4-8,2,3,5,N,17,5,"We, through thy name, shall tread down those"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:4-8,2,3,5,Y,18,5,that ris'n against us have.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:4-8,2,3,5,N,19,6,"For in my bow I shall not trust,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:4-8,2,3,5,Y,20,6,nor shall my sword me save.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:4-8,2,3,6,N,21,7,"But from our foes thou hast us sav'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:4-8,2,3,6,Y,22,7,our haters put to shame.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:4-8,2,3,6,N,23,8,"In God we all the day do boast,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:4-8,2,3,6,Y,24,8,and ever praise thy name.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:9-14,3,4,7,N,25,9,"But now we are cast off by thee,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:9-14,3,4,7,Y,26,9,and us thou putt'st to shame;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:9-14,3,4,7,N,27,9,"And when our armies do go forth,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:9-14,3,4,7,Y,28,9,thou go'st not with the same.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:9-14,3,4,8,N,29,10,"Thou mak'st us from the enemy,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:9-14,3,4,8,Y,30,10,"faint-hearted, to turn back;"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:9-14,3,4,8,N,31,10,And they who hate us for themselves
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:9-14,3,4,8,Y,32,10,our spoils away do take.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:9-14,3,5,9,N,33,11,Like sheep for meat thou gavest us;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:9-14,3,5,9,Y,34,11,'mong heathen cast we be.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:9-14,3,5,9,N,35,12,Thou didst for nought thy people sell;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:9-14,3,5,9,Y,36,12,their price enrich'd not thee.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:9-14,3,5,10,N,37,13,Thou mak'st us a reproach to be
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:9-14,3,5,10,Y,38,13,unto our neighbours near;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:9-14,3,5,10,N,39,13,Derision and a scorn to them
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:9-14,3,5,10,Y,40,13,that round about us are.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:9-14,3,6,11,N,41,14,A by-word also thou dost us
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:9-14,3,6,11,Y,42,14,among the heathen make;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:9-14,3,6,11,N,43,14,"The people, in contempt and spite,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:9-14,3,6,11,Y,44,14,at us their heads do shake.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:15-19,4,6,12,N,45,15,Before me my confusion
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:15-19,4,6,12,Y,46,15,continually abides;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:15-19,4,6,12,N,47,15,And of my bashful countenance
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:15-19,4,6,12,Y,48,15,the shame me ever hides:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:15-19,4,7,13,N,49,16,"For voice of him that doth reproach,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:15-19,4,7,13,Y,50,16,and speaketh blasphemy;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:15-19,4,7,13,N,51,16,"By reason of th' avenging foe,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:15-19,4,7,13,Y,52,16,and cruel enemy.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:15-19,4,7,14,N,53,17,"All this is come on us, yet we"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:15-19,4,7,14,Y,54,17,have not forgotten thee;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:15-19,4,7,14,N,55,17,Nor falsely in thy covenant
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:15-19,4,7,14,Y,56,17,behav'd ourselves have we.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:15-19,4,8,15,N,57,18,Back from thy way our heart not turn'd;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:15-19,4,8,15,Y,58,18,our steps no straying made;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:15-19,4,8,15,N,59,19,"Though us thou brak'st in dragons' place,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:15-19,4,8,15,Y,60,19,and cover'dst with death's shade.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:20-26,5,8,16,N,61,20,"If we God's name forgot, or stretch'd"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:20-26,5,8,16,Y,62,20,"to a strange god our hands,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:20-26,5,8,16,N,63,21,Shall not God search this out? for he
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:20-26,5,8,16,Y,64,21,heart's secrets understands.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:20-26,5,9,17,N,65,22,"Yea, for thy sake we're kill'd all day,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:20-26,5,9,17,Y,66,22,counted as slaughter-sheep.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:20-26,5,9,17,N,67,23,"Rise, Lord, cast us not ever off;"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:20-26,5,9,17,Y,68,23,"awake, why dost thou sleep?"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:20-26,5,9,18,N,69,24,O wherefore hidest thou thy face?
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:20-26,5,9,18,Y,70,24,"forgett'st our cause distress'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:20-26,5,9,18,N,71,25,And our oppression? For our soul
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:20-26,5,9,18,Y,72,25,is to the dust down press'd:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:20-26,5,10,19,N,73,25,Our belly also on the earth
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:20-26,5,10,19,Y,74,25,"fast cleaving, hold doth take."
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:20-26,5,10,19,N,75,26,"Rise for our help, and us redeem,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),44,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 44:20-26,5,10,19,Y,76,26,ev'n for thy mercies' sake.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:1-5 I,1,1,1,N,1,1,My heart brings forth a goodly thing;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:1-5 I,1,1,1,Y,2,1,my words that I indite
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:1-5 I,1,1,1,N,3,1,Concern the King: my tongue's a pen
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:1-5 I,1,1,1,Y,4,1,of one that swift doth write.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:1-5 I,1,1,2,N,5,2,Thou fairer art than sons of men:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:1-5 I,1,1,2,Y,6,2,into thy lips is store
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:1-5 I,1,1,2,N,7,2,Of grace infus'd; God therefore thee
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:1-5 I,1,1,2,Y,8,2,hath bless'd for evermore.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:1-5 I,1,2,3,N,9,3,"O thou that art the mighty One,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:1-5 I,1,2,3,Y,10,3,thy sword gird on thy thigh;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:1-5 I,1,2,3,N,11,3,"Ev'n with thy glory excellent,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:1-5 I,1,2,3,Y,12,3,and with thy majesty.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:1-5 I,1,2,4,N,13,4,"For meekness, truth, and righteousness,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:1-5 I,1,2,4,Y,14,4,in state ride prosp'rously;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:1-5 I,1,2,4,N,15,4,And thy right hand shall thee instruct
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:1-5 I,1,2,4,Y,16,4,in things that fearful be.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:1-5 I,1,3,5,N,17,5,Thine arrows sharply pierce the heart
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:1-5 I,1,3,5,Y,18,5,of th' en'mies of the King;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:1-5 I,1,3,5,N,19,5,And under thy subjection
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:1-5 I,1,3,5,Y,20,5,the people down do bring.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:6-9 I,2,3,6,N,21,6,"For ever and for ever is,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:6-9 I,2,3,6,Y,22,6,"O God, thy throne of might;"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:6-9 I,2,3,6,N,23,6,The sceptre of thy kingdom is
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:6-9 I,2,3,6,Y,24,6,a sceptre that is right.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:6-9 I,2,4,7,N,25,7,"Thou lovest right, and hatest ill;"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:6-9 I,2,4,7,Y,26,7,"for God, thy God, most high,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:6-9 I,2,4,7,N,27,7,Above thy fellows hath with th' oil
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:6-9 I,2,4,7,Y,28,7,of joy anointed thee.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:6-9 I,2,4,8,N,29,8,"Of aloes, myrrh, and cassia,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:6-9 I,2,4,8,Y,30,8,"a smell thy garments had,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:6-9 I,2,4,8,N,31,8,"Out of the iv'ry palaces,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:6-9 I,2,4,8,Y,32,8,whereby they made thee glad.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:6-9 I,2,5,9,N,33,9,Among thy women honourable
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:6-9 I,2,5,9,Y,34,9,kings' daughters were at hand:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:6-9 I,2,5,9,N,35,9,Upon thy right hand did the queen
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:6-9 I,2,5,9,Y,36,9,in gold of Ophir stand.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:10-12 I,3,5,10,N,37,10,"O daughter, hearken and regard,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:10-12 I,3,5,10,Y,38,10,and do thine ear incline;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:10-12 I,3,5,10,N,39,10,"Likewise forget thy father's house,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:10-12 I,3,5,10,Y,40,10,and people that are thine.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:10-12 I,3,6,11,N,41,11,Then of the King desir'd shall be
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:10-12 I,3,6,11,Y,42,11,thy beauty veh'mently:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:10-12 I,3,6,11,N,43,11,"Because he is thy Lord, do thou"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:10-12 I,3,6,11,Y,44,11,him worship rev'rently.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:10-12 I,3,6,12,N,45,12,The daughter there of Tyre shall be
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:10-12 I,3,6,12,Y,46,12,with gifts and off 'rings great:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:10-12 I,3,6,12,N,47,12,Those of the people that are rich
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:10-12 I,3,6,12,Y,48,12,thy favour shall entreat.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:13-17 I,4,7,13,N,49,13,"Behold, the daughter of the King"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:13-17 I,4,7,13,Y,50,13,all glorious is within;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:13-17 I,4,7,13,N,51,13,And with embroideries of gold
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:13-17 I,4,7,13,Y,52,13,her garments wrought have been.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:13-17 I,4,7,14,N,53,14,She shall be brought unto the King
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:13-17 I,4,7,14,Y,54,14,in robes with needle wrought;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:13-17 I,4,7,14,N,55,14,Her fellow-virgins following
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:13-17 I,4,7,14,Y,56,14,shall unto thee be brought.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:13-17 I,4,8,15,N,57,15,"They shall be brought with gladness great,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:13-17 I,4,8,15,Y,58,15,"and mirth on ev'ry side,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:13-17 I,4,8,15,N,59,15,"Into the palace of the King,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:13-17 I,4,8,15,Y,60,15,and there they shall abide.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:13-17 I,4,8,16,N,61,16,"Instead of those thy fathers dear,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:13-17 I,4,8,16,Y,62,16,"thy children thou may'st take,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:13-17 I,4,8,16,N,63,16,And in all places of the earth
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:13-17 I,4,8,16,Y,64,16,them noble princes make.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:13-17 I,4,9,17,N,65,17,Thy name remember'd I will make
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:13-17 I,4,9,17,Y,66,17,through ages all to be:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:13-17 I,4,9,17,N,67,17,The people therefore evermore
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 45:13-17 I,4,9,17,Y,68,17,shall praises give to thee.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:1-4 II,1,9,1,N,1,1,My heart inditing is
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:1-4 II,1,9,1,Y,2,1,good matter in a song:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:1-4 II,1,9,1,N,3,1,"I speak the things that I have made,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:1-4 II,1,9,1,Y,4,1,which to the King belong:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:1-4 II,1,9,2,N,5,1,"My tongue shall be as quick,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:1-4 II,1,9,2,Y,6,1,"his honour to indite,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:1-4 II,1,9,2,N,7,1,As is the pen of any scribe
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:1-4 II,1,9,2,Y,8,1,that useth fast to write.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:1-4 II,1,10,3,N,9,2,Thou'rt fairest of all men;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:1-4 II,1,10,3,Y,10,2,grace in thy lips doth flow:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:1-4 II,1,10,3,N,11,2,And therefore blessings evermore
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:1-4 II,1,10,3,Y,12,2,on thee doth God bestow.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:1-4 II,1,10,4,N,13,3,"Thy sword gird on thy thigh,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:1-4 II,1,10,4,Y,14,3,thou that art most of might:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:1-4 II,1,10,4,N,15,3,"Appear in dreadful majesty,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:1-4 II,1,10,4,Y,16,3,and in thy glory bright.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:1-4 II,1,11,5,N,17,4,"For meekness, truth, and right,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:1-4 II,1,11,5,Y,18,4,ride prosp'rously in state;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:1-4 II,1,11,5,N,19,4,And thy right hand shall teach to thee
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:1-4 II,1,11,5,Y,20,4,things terrible and great.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:5-9 II,2,11,6,N,21,5,Thy shafts shall pierce their hearts
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:5-9 II,2,11,6,Y,22,5,that foes are to the King;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:5-9 II,2,11,6,N,23,5,Whereby into subjection
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:5-9 II,2,11,6,Y,24,5,the people thou shalt bring.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:5-9 II,2,12,7,N,25,6,"Thy royal seat, O Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:5-9 II,2,12,7,Y,26,6,for ever shall remain:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:5-9 II,2,12,7,N,27,6,The sceptre of thy kingdom doth
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:5-9 II,2,12,7,Y,28,6,all righteousness maintain.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:5-9 II,2,12,8,N,29,7,"Thou lov'st right, and hat'st ill;"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:5-9 II,2,12,8,Y,30,7,"for God, thy God, most high,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:5-9 II,2,12,8,N,31,7,Above thy fellows hath with th' oil
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:5-9 II,2,12,8,Y,32,7,of joy anointed thee.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:5-9 II,2,13,9,N,33,8,Of myrrh and spices sweet
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:5-9 II,2,13,9,Y,34,8,"a smell thy garments had,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:5-9 II,2,13,9,N,35,8,"Out of the iv'ry palaces,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:5-9 II,2,13,9,Y,36,8,whereby they made thee glad.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:5-9 II,2,13,10,N,37,9,And in thy glorious train
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:5-9 II,2,13,10,Y,38,9,kings' daughters waiting stand;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:5-9 II,2,13,10,N,39,9,"And thy fair queen, in Ophir gold,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:5-9 II,2,13,10,Y,40,9,doth stand at thy right hand.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:10-12 II,3,14,11,N,41,10,"O daughter, take good heed,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:10-12 II,3,14,11,Y,42,10,"incline, and give good ear;"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:10-12 II,3,14,11,N,43,10,"Thou must forget thy kindred all,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:10-12 II,3,14,11,Y,44,10,and father's house most dear.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:10-12 II,3,14,12,N,45,11,Thy beauty to the King
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:10-12 II,3,14,12,Y,46,11,shall then delightful be:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:10-12 II,3,14,12,N,47,11,"And do thou humbly worship him,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:10-12 II,3,14,12,Y,48,11,because thy Lord is he.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:10-12 II,3,15,13,N,49,12,The daughter then of Tyre
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:10-12 II,3,15,13,Y,50,12,"there with a gift shall be,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:10-12 II,3,15,13,N,51,12,And all the wealthy of the land
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:10-12 II,3,15,13,Y,52,12,shall make their suit to thee.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:13-17 II,4,15,14,N,53,13,The daughter of the King
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:13-17 II,4,15,14,Y,54,13,all glorious is within;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:13-17 II,4,15,14,N,55,13,And with embroideries of gold
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:13-17 II,4,15,14,Y,56,13,her garments wrought have been.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:13-17 II,4,16,15,N,57,14,She cometh to the King
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:13-17 II,4,16,15,Y,58,14,in robes with needle wrought;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:13-17 II,4,16,15,N,59,14,The virgins that do follow her
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:13-17 II,4,16,15,Y,60,14,shall unto thee be brought.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:13-17 II,4,16,16,N,61,15,"They shall be brought with joy,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:13-17 II,4,16,16,Y,62,15,"and mirth on ev'ry side,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:13-17 II,4,16,16,N,63,15,"Into the palace of the King,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:13-17 II,4,16,16,Y,64,15,and there they shall abide.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:13-17 II,4,17,17,N,65,16,"And in thy fathers' stead,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:13-17 II,4,17,17,Y,66,16,"thy children thou may'st take,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:13-17 II,4,17,17,N,67,16,And in all places of the earth
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:13-17 II,4,17,17,Y,68,16,them noble princes make.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:13-17 II,4,17,18,N,69,17,I will shew forth thy name
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:13-17 II,4,17,18,Y,70,17,to generations all:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:13-17 II,4,17,18,N,71,17,Therefore the people evermore
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),45,Second,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 45:13-17 II,4,17,18,Y,72,17,to thee give praises shall.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),46,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 46:1-5,1,1,1,N,1,1,"God is our refuge and our strength,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),46,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 46:1-5,1,1,1,Y,2,1,in straits a present aid;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),46,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 46:1-5,1,1,1,N,3,2,"Therefore, although the earth remove,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),46,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 46:1-5,1,1,1,Y,4,2,we will not be afraid:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),46,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 46:1-5,1,1,2,N,5,2,Though hills amidst the seas be cast;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),46,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 46:1-5,1,1,2,Y,6,3,"Though waters roaring make,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),46,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 46:1-5,1,1,2,N,7,3,"And troubled be; yea, though the hills,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),46,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 46:1-5,1,1,2,Y,8,3,by swelling seas do shake.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),46,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 46:1-5,1,2,3,N,9,4,"A river is, whose streams do glad"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),46,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 46:1-5,1,2,3,Y,10,4,the city of our God;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),46,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 46:1-5,1,2,3,N,11,4,"The holy place, wherein the Lord"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),46,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 46:1-5,1,2,3,Y,12,4,most high hath his abode.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),46,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 46:1-5,1,2,4,N,13,5,God in the midst of her doth dwell;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),46,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 46:1-5,1,2,4,Y,14,5,nothing shall her remove:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),46,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 46:1-5,1,2,4,N,15,5,"The Lord to her an helper will,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),46,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 46:1-5,1,2,4,Y,16,5,"and that right early, prove."
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),46,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 46:6-7,2,3,5,N,17,6,"The heathen rag'd tumultuously,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),46,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 46:6-7,2,3,5,Y,18,6,the kingdoms moved were:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),46,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 46:6-7,2,3,5,N,19,6,"The Lord God uttered his voice,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),46,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 46:6-7,2,3,5,Y,20,6,the earth did melt for fear.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),46,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 46:6-7,2,3,6,N,21,7,The Lord of hosts upon our side
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),46,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 46:6-7,2,3,6,Y,22,7,doth constantly remain:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),46,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 46:6-7,2,3,6,N,23,7,"The God of Jacob's our refuge,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),46,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 46:6-7,2,3,6,Y,24,7,us safely to maintain.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),46,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 46:8-11,3,4,7,N,25,8,"Come, and behold what wondrous works"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),46,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 46:8-11,3,4,7,Y,26,8,have by the Lord been wrought;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),46,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 46:8-11,3,4,7,N,27,8,"Come, see what desolations"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),46,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 46:8-11,3,4,7,Y,28,8,he on the earth hath brought.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),46,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 46:8-11,3,4,8,N,29,9,Unto the ends of all the earth
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),46,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 46:8-11,3,4,8,Y,30,9,wars into peace he turns:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),46,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 46:8-11,3,4,8,N,31,9,"The bow he breaks, the spear he cuts,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),46,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 46:8-11,3,4,8,Y,32,9,in fire the chariot burns.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),46,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 46:8-11,3,5,9,N,33,10,"Be still, and know that I am God;"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),46,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 46:8-11,3,5,9,Y,34,10,among the heathen I
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),46,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 46:8-11,3,5,9,N,35,10,Will be exalted; I on earth
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),46,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 46:8-11,3,5,9,Y,36,10,will be exalted high.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),46,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 46:8-11,3,5,10,N,37,11,"Our God, who is the Lord of hosts,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),46,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 46:8-11,3,5,10,Y,38,11,is still upon our side;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),46,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 46:8-11,3,5,10,N,39,11,The God of Jacob our refuge
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),46,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 46:8-11,3,5,10,Y,40,11,for ever will abide.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),47,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 47:1-6,1,1,1,N,1,1,"All people, clap your hands; to God"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),47,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 47:1-6,1,1,1,Y,2,1,with voice of triumph shout:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),47,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 47:1-6,1,1,1,N,3,2,"For dreadful is the Lord most high,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),47,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 47:1-6,1,1,1,Y,4,2,great King the earth throughout.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),47,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 47:1-6,1,1,2,N,5,3,The heathen people under us
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),47,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 47:1-6,1,1,2,Y,6,3,he surely shall subdue;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),47,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 47:1-6,1,1,2,N,7,3,And he shall make the nations
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),47,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 47:1-6,1,1,2,Y,8,3,under our feet to bow.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),47,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 47:1-6,1,2,3,N,9,4,The lot of our inheritance
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),47,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 47:1-6,1,2,3,Y,10,4,"chuse out for us shall he,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),47,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 47:1-6,1,2,3,N,11,4,"Of Jacob, whom he loved well,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),47,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 47:1-6,1,2,3,Y,12,4,ev'n the excellency.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),47,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 47:1-6,1,2,4,N,13,5,"God is with shouts gone up, the Lord"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),47,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 47:1-6,1,2,4,Y,14,5,with trumpets sounding high.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),47,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 47:1-6,1,2,4,N,15,6,"Sing praise to God, sing praise, sing praise,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),47,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 47:1-6,1,2,4,Y,16,6,praise to our King sing ye.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),47,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 47:7-9,2,3,5,N,17,7,For God is King of all the earth;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),47,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 47:7-9,2,3,5,Y,18,7,with knowledge praise express.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),47,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 47:7-9,2,3,5,N,19,8,God rules the nations: God sits on
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),47,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 47:7-9,2,3,5,Y,20,8,his throne of holiness.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),47,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 47:7-9,2,3,6,N,21,9,The princes of the people are
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),47,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 47:7-9,2,3,6,Y,22,9,assembled willingly;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),47,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 47:7-9,2,3,6,N,23,9,Ev'n of the God of Abraham
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),47,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 47:7-9,2,3,6,Y,24,9,they who the people be.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),47,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 47:7-9,2,4,7,N,25,9,For why? the shields that do defend
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),47,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 47:7-9,2,4,7,Y,26,9,the earth are only his:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),47,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 47:7-9,2,4,7,N,27,9,"They to the Lord belong; yea, he"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),47,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 47:7-9,2,4,7,Y,28,9,exalted greatly is.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),48,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 48:1-6,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Great is the Lord, and greatly he"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),48,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 48:1-6,1,1,1,Y,2,1,"is to be praised still,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),48,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 48:1-6,1,1,1,N,3,1,"Within the city of our God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),48,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 48:1-6,1,1,1,Y,4,1,upon his holy hill.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),48,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 48:1-6,1,1,2,N,5,2,"Mount Sion stands most beautiful,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),48,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 48:1-6,1,1,2,Y,6,2,the joy of all the land;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),48,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 48:1-6,1,1,2,N,7,2,The city of the mighty King
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),48,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 48:1-6,1,1,2,Y,8,2,on her north side doth stand.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),48,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 48:1-6,1,2,3,N,9,3,The Lord within her palaces
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),48,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 48:1-6,1,2,3,Y,10,3,is for a refuge known.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),48,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 48:1-6,1,2,3,N,11,4,"For, lo, the kings that gather'd were"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),48,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 48:1-6,1,2,3,Y,12,4,"together, by have gone."
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),48,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 48:1-6,1,2,4,N,13,5,"But when they did behold the same,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),48,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 48:1-6,1,2,4,Y,14,5,"they, wond'ring, would not stay;"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),48,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 48:1-6,1,2,4,N,15,5,"But, being troubled at the sight,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),48,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 48:1-6,1,2,4,Y,16,5,they thence did haste away.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),48,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 48:1-6,1,3,5,N,17,6,Great terror there took hold on them;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),48,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 48:1-6,1,3,5,Y,18,6,they were possess'd with fear;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),48,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 48:1-6,1,3,5,N,19,6,"Their grief came like a woman's pain,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),48,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 48:1-6,1,3,5,Y,20,6,when she a child doth bear.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),48,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 48:7-10,2,3,6,N,21,7,Thou Tarshish ships with east wind break'st:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),48,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 48:7-10,2,3,6,Y,22,8,"As we have heard it told,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),48,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 48:7-10,2,3,6,N,23,8,"So, in the city of the Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),48,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 48:7-10,2,3,6,Y,24,8,our eyes did it behold;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),48,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 48:7-10,2,4,7,N,25,8,"In our God's city, which his hand"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),48,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 48:7-10,2,4,7,Y,26,8,for ever stablish will.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),48,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 48:7-10,2,4,7,N,27,9,"We of thy loving-kindness thought,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),48,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 48:7-10,2,4,7,Y,28,9,"Lord, in thy temple still."
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),48,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 48:7-10,2,4,8,N,29,10,"O Lord, according to thy name,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),48,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 48:7-10,2,4,8,Y,30,10,through all the earth's thy praise;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),48,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 48:7-10,2,4,8,N,31,10,"And thy right hand, O Lord, is full"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),48,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 48:7-10,2,4,8,Y,32,10,of righteousness always.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),48,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 48:11-14,3,5,9,N,33,11,"Because thy judgments are made known,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),48,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 48:11-14,3,5,9,Y,34,11,let Sion mount rejoice;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),48,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 48:11-14,3,5,9,N,35,11,Of Judah let the daughters all
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),48,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 48:11-14,3,5,9,Y,36,11,send forth a cheerful voice.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),48,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 48:11-14,3,5,10,N,37,12,"Walk about Sion, and go round;"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),48,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 48:11-14,3,5,10,Y,38,12,the high tow'rs thereof tell:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),48,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 48:11-14,3,5,10,N,39,13,"Consider ye her palaces,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),48,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 48:11-14,3,5,10,Y,40,13,and mark her bulwarks well;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),48,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 48:11-14,3,6,11,N,41,13,That ye may tell posterity.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),48,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 48:11-14,3,6,11,Y,42,14,For this God doth abide
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),48,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 48:11-14,3,6,11,N,43,14,Our God for evermore; he will
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),48,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 48:11-14,3,6,11,Y,44,14,ev'n unto death us guide.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:1-5,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Hear this, all people, and give ear,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:1-5,1,1,1,Y,2,1,all in the world that dwell;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:1-5,1,1,1,N,3,2,"Both low and high, both rich and poor."
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:1-5,1,1,1,Y,4,3,My mouth shall wisdom tell:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:1-5,1,1,2,N,5,3,My heart shall knowledge meditate.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:1-5,1,1,2,Y,6,4,I will incline mine ear
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:1-5,1,1,2,N,7,4,"To parables, and on the harp"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:1-5,1,1,2,Y,8,4,my sayings dark declare.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:1-5,1,2,3,N,9,5,"Amidst those days that evil be,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:1-5,1,2,3,Y,10,5,"why should I, fearing, doubt?"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:1-5,1,2,3,N,11,5,When of my heels th' iniquity
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:1-5,1,2,3,Y,12,5,shall compass me about.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:6-11,2,2,4,N,13,6,Whoe'er they be that in their wealth
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:6-11,2,2,4,Y,14,6,"their confidence do pitch,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:6-11,2,2,4,N,15,6,"And boast themselves, because they are"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:6-11,2,2,4,Y,16,6,become exceeding rich:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:6-11,2,3,5,N,17,7,Yet none of these his brother can
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:6-11,2,3,5,Y,18,7,redeem by any way;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:6-11,2,3,5,N,19,7,Nor can he unto God for him
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:6-11,2,3,5,Y,20,7,"sufficient ransom pay,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:6-11,2,3,6,N,21,8,"(Their soul's redemption precious is,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:6-11,2,3,6,Y,22,8,"and it can never be,)"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:6-11,2,3,6,N,23,9,"That still he should for ever live,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:6-11,2,3,6,Y,24,9,and not corruption see.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:6-11,2,4,7,N,25,10,"For why? he seeth that wise men die,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:6-11,2,4,7,Y,26,10,and brutish fools also
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:6-11,2,4,7,N,27,10,"Do perish; and their wealth, when dead,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:6-11,2,4,7,Y,28,10,to others they let go.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:6-11,2,4,8,N,29,11,"Their inward thought is, that their house"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:6-11,2,4,8,Y,30,11,and dwelling-places shall
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:6-11,2,4,8,N,31,11,Stand through all ages; they their lands
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:6-11,2,4,8,Y,32,11,by their own names do call.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:12-15,3,5,9,N,33,12,But yet in honour shall not man
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:12-15,3,5,9,Y,34,12,abide continually;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:12-15,3,5,9,N,35,12,"But passing hence, may be compar'd"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:12-15,3,5,9,Y,36,12,unto the beasts that die.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:12-15,3,5,10,N,37,13,Thus brutish folly plainly is
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:12-15,3,5,10,Y,38,13,their wisdom and their way;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:12-15,3,5,10,N,39,13,Yet their posterity approve
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:12-15,3,5,10,Y,40,13,what they do fondly say.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:12-15,3,6,11,N,41,14,"Like sheep they in the grave are laid,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:12-15,3,6,11,Y,42,14,and death shall them devour;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:12-15,3,6,11,N,43,14,And in the morning upright men
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:12-15,3,6,11,Y,44,14,shall over them have pow'r:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:12-15,3,6,12,N,45,14,Their beauty from their dwelling shall
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:12-15,3,6,12,Y,46,14,consume within the grave.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:12-15,3,6,12,N,47,15,"But from hell's hand God will me free,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:12-15,3,6,12,Y,48,15,for he shall me receive.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:16-20,4,7,13,N,49,16,Be thou not then afraid when one
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:16-20,4,7,13,Y,50,16,"enriched thou dost see,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:16-20,4,7,13,N,51,16,Nor when the glory of his house
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:16-20,4,7,13,Y,52,16,advanced is on high:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:16-20,4,7,14,N,53,17,For he shall carry nothing hence
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:16-20,4,7,14,Y,54,17,when death his days doth end;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:16-20,4,7,14,N,55,17,Nor shall his glory after him
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:16-20,4,7,14,Y,56,17,into the grave descend.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:16-20,4,8,15,N,57,18,Although he his own soul did bless
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:16-20,4,8,15,Y,58,18,whilst he on earth did live;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:16-20,4,8,15,N,59,18,"(And when thou to thyself dost well,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:16-20,4,8,15,Y,60,18,men will thee praises give;)
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:16-20,4,8,16,N,61,19,"He to his fathers' race shall go,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:16-20,4,8,16,Y,62,19,they never shall see light.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:16-20,4,8,16,N,63,20,Man honour'd wanting knowledge is
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),49,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 49:16-20,4,8,16,Y,64,20,like beasts that perish quite.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:1-2 I,1,1,1,N,1,1,"The mighty God, the Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:1-2 I,1,1,1,Y,2,1,"hath spoken, and did call"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:1-2 I,1,1,1,N,3,1,"The earth, from rising of the sun,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:1-2 I,1,1,1,Y,4,1,to where he hath his fall.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:1-2 I,1,1,2,N,5,2,"From out of Sion hill,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:1-2 I,1,1,2,Y,6,2,which of excellency
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:1-2 I,1,1,2,N,7,2,"And beauty the perfection is,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:1-2 I,1,1,2,Y,8,2,God shined gloriously.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:3-6 I,2,2,3,N,9,3,"Our God shall surely come,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:3-6 I,2,2,3,Y,10,3,keep silence shall not he:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:3-6 I,2,2,3,N,11,3,"Before him fire shall waste, great storms"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:3-6 I,2,2,3,Y,12,3,shall round about him be.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:3-6 I,2,2,4,N,13,4,Unto the heavens clear
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:3-6 I,2,2,4,Y,14,4,"he from above shall call,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:3-6 I,2,2,4,N,15,4,"And to the earth likewise, that he"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:3-6 I,2,2,4,Y,16,4,may judge his people all.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:3-6 I,2,3,5,N,17,5,Together let my saints
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:3-6 I,2,3,5,Y,18,5,"unto me gather'd be,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:3-6 I,2,3,5,N,19,5,Those that by sacrifice have made
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:3-6 I,2,3,5,Y,20,5,a covenant with me.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:3-6 I,2,3,6,N,21,6,And then the heavens shall
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:3-6 I,2,3,6,Y,22,6,his righteousness declare:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:3-6 I,2,3,6,N,23,6,Because the Lord himself is he
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:3-6 I,2,3,6,Y,24,6,by whom men judged are.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:7-11 I,3,4,7,N,25,7,"My people Isr'el hear,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:7-11 I,3,4,7,Y,26,7,"speak will I from on high,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:7-11 I,3,4,7,N,27,7,Against thee I will testify;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:7-11 I,3,4,7,Y,28,7,"God, ev'n thy God, am I."
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:7-11 I,3,4,8,N,29,8,I for thy sacrifice
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:7-11 I,3,4,8,Y,30,8,"no blame will on thee lay,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:7-11 I,3,4,8,N,31,8,"Nor for burnt-off 'rings, which to me"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:7-11 I,3,4,8,Y,32,8,thou offer'dst ev'ry day.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:7-11 I,3,5,9,N,33,9,I'll take no calf nor goats
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:7-11 I,3,5,9,Y,34,9,from house or fold of thine:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:7-11 I,3,5,9,N,35,10,"For beasts of forests, cattle all"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:7-11 I,3,5,9,Y,36,10,"on thousand hills, are mine."
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:7-11 I,3,5,10,N,37,11,The fowls on mountains high
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:7-11 I,3,5,10,Y,38,11,are all to me well known;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:7-11 I,3,5,10,N,39,11,"Wild beasts which in the fields do lie,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:7-11 I,3,5,10,Y,40,11,ev'n they are all mine own.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:12-15 I,4,6,11,N,41,12,"Then, if I hungry were,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:12-15 I,4,6,11,Y,42,12,I would not tell it thee;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:12-15 I,4,6,11,N,43,12,"Because the world, and fulness all"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:12-15 I,4,6,11,Y,44,12,"thereof, belongs to me."
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:12-15 I,4,6,12,N,45,13,Will I eat flesh of bulls?
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:12-15 I,4,6,12,Y,46,13,or goats' blood drink will I?
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:12-15 I,4,6,12,N,47,14,"Thanks offer thou to God, and pay"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:12-15 I,4,6,12,Y,48,14,thy vows to the most High.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:12-15 I,4,7,13,N,49,15,And call upon me when
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:12-15 I,4,7,13,Y,50,15,in trouble thou shalt be;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:12-15 I,4,7,13,N,51,15,"I will deliver thee, and thou"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:12-15 I,4,7,13,Y,52,15,my name shalt glorify.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:16-20 I,5,7,14,N,53,16,But to the wicked man
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:16-20 I,5,7,14,Y,54,16,"God saith, My laws and truth"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:16-20 I,5,7,14,N,55,16,Should'st thou declare? how dar'st thou take
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:16-20 I,5,7,14,Y,56,16,my cov'nant in thy mouth?
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:16-20 I,5,8,15,N,57,17,"Sith thou instruction hat'st,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:16-20 I,5,8,15,Y,58,17,which should thy ways direct;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:16-20 I,5,8,15,N,59,17,And sith my words behind thy back
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:16-20 I,5,8,15,Y,60,17,"thou cast'st, and dost reject."
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:16-20 I,5,8,16,N,61,18,"When thou a thief didst see,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:16-20 I,5,8,16,Y,62,18,with him thou didst consent;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:16-20 I,5,8,16,N,63,18,And with the vile adulterers
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:16-20 I,5,8,16,Y,64,18,partaker on thou went.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:16-20 I,5,9,17,N,65,19,"Thou giv'st thy mouth to ill,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:16-20 I,5,9,17,Y,66,19,thy tongue deceit doth frame;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:16-20 I,5,9,17,N,67,20,"Thou sitt'st, and 'gainst thy brother speak'st,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:16-20 I,5,9,17,Y,68,20,thy mother's son dost shame.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:21-23 I,6,9,18,N,69,21,"Because I silence kept,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:21-23 I,6,9,18,Y,70,21,while thou these things hast wrought;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:21-23 I,6,9,18,N,71,21,That I was altogether like
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:21-23 I,6,9,18,Y,72,21,"thyself, hath been thy thought;"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:21-23 I,6,10,19,N,73,21,"Yet I will thee reprove,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:21-23 I,6,10,19,Y,74,21,"and set before thine eyes,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:21-23 I,6,10,19,N,75,21,"In order ranked, thy misdeeds"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:21-23 I,6,10,19,Y,76,21,and thine iniquities.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:21-23 I,6,10,20,N,77,22,"Now, ye that God forget,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:21-23 I,6,10,20,Y,78,22,this carefully consider;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:21-23 I,6,10,20,N,79,22,"Lest I in pieces tear you all,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:21-23 I,6,10,20,Y,80,22,and none can you deliver.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:21-23 I,6,11,21,N,81,23,Whoso doth offer praise
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:21-23 I,6,11,21,Y,82,23,me glorifies; and I
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:21-23 I,6,11,21,N,83,23,"Will shew him God's salvation,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 50:21-23 I,6,11,21,Y,84,23,that orders right his way.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:1-2 II,1,11,1,N,1,1,"The mighty God, the Lord, hath spoke,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:1-2 II,1,11,1,Y,2,1,"and call'd the earth upon,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:1-2 II,1,11,1,N,3,1,Ev'n from the rising of the sun
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:1-2 II,1,11,1,Y,4,1,unto his going down.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:1-2 II,1,11,2,N,5,2,"From out of Sion, his own hill,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:1-2 II,1,11,2,Y,6,2,where the perfection high
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:1-2 II,1,11,2,N,7,2,"Of beauty is, from thence the Lord"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:1-2 II,1,11,2,Y,8,2,hath shined gloriously.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:3-6 II,2,12,3,N,9,3,"Our God shall come, and shall no more"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:3-6 II,2,12,3,Y,10,3,"be silent, but speak out:"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:3-6 II,2,12,3,N,11,3,"Before him fire shall waste, great storms"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:3-6 II,2,12,3,Y,12,3,shall compass him about.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:3-6 II,2,12,4,N,13,4,"He to the heavens from above,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:3-6 II,2,12,4,Y,14,4,"and to the earth below,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:3-6 II,2,12,4,N,15,4,"Shall call, that he his judgments may"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:3-6 II,2,12,4,Y,16,4,before his people show.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:3-6 II,2,13,5,N,17,5,Let all my saints together be
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:3-6 II,2,13,5,Y,18,5,unto me gathered;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:3-6 II,2,13,5,N,19,5,Those that by sacrifice with me
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:3-6 II,2,13,5,Y,20,5,a covenant have made.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:3-6 II,2,13,6,N,21,6,And then the heavens shall declare
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:3-6 II,2,13,6,Y,22,6,his righteousness abroad:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:3-6 II,2,13,6,N,23,6,Because the Lord himself doth come;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:3-6 II,2,13,6,Y,24,6,none else is judge but God.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:7-11 II,3,14,7,N,25,7,"Hear, O my people, and I'll speak;"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:7-11 II,3,14,7,Y,26,7,"O Israel by name,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:7-11 II,3,14,7,N,27,7,Against thee I will testify;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:7-11 II,3,14,7,Y,28,7,"God, ev'n thy God, I am."
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:7-11 II,3,14,8,N,29,8,I for thy sacrifices few
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:7-11 II,3,14,8,Y,30,8,"reprove thee never will,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:7-11 II,3,14,8,N,31,8,Nor for burnt-off 'rings to have been
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:7-11 II,3,14,8,Y,32,8,before me offer'd still.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:7-11 II,3,15,9,N,33,9,I'll take no bullock nor he-goats
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:7-11 II,3,15,9,Y,34,9,from house nor folds of thine:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:7-11 II,3,15,9,N,35,10,"For beasts of forests, cattle all"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:7-11 II,3,15,9,Y,36,10,"on thousand hills, are mine."
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:7-11 II,3,15,10,N,37,11,The fowls are all to me well known
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:7-11 II,3,15,10,Y,38,11,that mountains high do yield;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:7-11 II,3,15,10,N,39,11,And I do challenge as mine own
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:7-11 II,3,15,10,Y,40,11,the wild beasts of the field.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:12-15 II,4,16,11,N,41,12,"If I were hungry, I would not"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:12-15 II,4,16,11,Y,42,12,to thee for need complain;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:12-15 II,4,16,11,N,43,12,"For earth, and all its fulness, doth"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:12-15 II,4,16,11,Y,44,12,to me of right pertain.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:12-15 II,4,16,12,N,45,13,That I to eat the flesh of bulls
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:12-15 II,4,16,12,Y,46,13,take pleasure dost thou think?
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:12-15 II,4,16,12,N,47,13,"Or that I need, to quench my thirst,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:12-15 II,4,16,12,Y,48,13,the blood of goats to drink?
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:12-15 II,4,17,13,N,49,14,"Nay, rather unto me, thy God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:12-15 II,4,17,13,Y,50,14,thanksgiving offer thou:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:12-15 II,4,17,13,N,51,14,"To the most High perform thy word,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:12-15 II,4,17,13,Y,52,14,and fully pay thy vow:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:12-15 II,4,17,14,N,53,15,And in the day of trouble great
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:12-15 II,4,17,14,Y,54,15,see that thou call on me;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:12-15 II,4,17,14,N,55,15,"I will deliver thee, and thou"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:12-15 II,4,17,14,Y,56,15,my name shalt glorify.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:16-20 II,5,18,15,N,57,16,"But God unto the wicked saith,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:16-20 II,5,18,15,Y,58,16,Why should'st thou mention make
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:16-20 II,5,18,15,N,59,16,Of my commands? how dar'st thou in
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:16-20 II,5,18,15,Y,60,16,thy mouth my cov'nant take?
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:16-20 II,5,18,16,N,61,17,Sith it is so that thou dost hate
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:16-20 II,5,18,16,Y,62,17,all good instruction;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:16-20 II,5,18,16,N,63,17,"And sith thou cast'st behind thy back,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:16-20 II,5,18,16,Y,64,17,and slight'st my words each one.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:16-20 II,5,19,17,N,65,18,"When thou a thief didst see, then straight"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:16-20 II,5,19,17,Y,66,18,"thou join'dst with him in sin,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:16-20 II,5,19,17,N,67,18,And with the vile adulterers
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:16-20 II,5,19,17,Y,68,18,thou hast partaker been.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:16-20 II,5,19,18,N,69,19,"Thy mouth to evil thou dost give,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:16-20 II,5,19,18,Y,70,19,thy tongue deceit doth frame.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:16-20 II,5,19,18,N,71,20,"Thou sitt'st, and 'gainst thy brother speak'st,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:16-20 II,5,19,18,Y,72,20,thy mother's son to shame.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:21-23 II,6,20,19,N,73,21,"These things thou wickedly hast done,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:21-23 II,6,20,19,Y,74,21,and I have silent been:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:21-23 II,6,20,19,N,75,21,"Thou thought'st that I was like thyself,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:21-23 II,6,20,19,Y,76,21,and did approve thy sin:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:21-23 II,6,20,20,N,77,21,"But I will sharply thee reprove,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:21-23 II,6,20,20,Y,78,21,and I will order right
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:21-23 II,6,20,20,N,79,21,Thy sins and thy transgressions
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:21-23 II,6,20,20,Y,80,21,in presence of thy sight.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:21-23 II,6,21,21,N,81,22,"Consider this, and be afraid,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:21-23 II,6,21,21,Y,82,22,"ye that forget the Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:21-23 II,6,21,21,N,83,22,"Lest I in pieces tear you all,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:21-23 II,6,21,21,Y,84,22,when none can help afford.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:21-23 II,6,21,22,N,85,23,Who off'reth praise me glorifies:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:21-23 II,6,21,22,Y,86,23,I will shew God's salvation
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:21-23 II,6,21,22,N,87,23,To him that ordereth aright
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),50,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 50:21-23 II,6,21,22,Y,88,23,his life and conversation.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:1-4,1,1,1,N,1,1,"After thy loving-kindness, Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:1-4,1,1,1,Y,2,1,have mercy upon me:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:1-4,1,1,1,N,3,1,"For thy compassions great, blot out"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:1-4,1,1,1,Y,4,1,all mine iniquity.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:1-4,1,1,2,N,5,2,"Me cleanse from sin, and throughly wash"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:1-4,1,1,2,Y,6,2,from mine iniquity:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:1-4,1,1,2,N,7,3,For my transgressions I confess;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:1-4,1,1,2,Y,8,3,my sin I ever see.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:1-4,1,2,3,N,9,4,"'Gainst thee, thee only, have I sinn'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:1-4,1,2,3,Y,10,4,in thy sight done this ill;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:1-4,1,2,3,N,11,4,"That when thou speak'st thou may'st be just,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:1-4,1,2,3,Y,12,4,and clear in judging still.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:5-8,2,2,4,N,13,5,"Behold, I in iniquity"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:5-8,2,2,4,Y,14,5,was form'd the womb within;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:5-8,2,2,4,N,15,5,My mother also me conceiv'd
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:5-8,2,2,4,Y,16,5,in guiltiness and sin.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:5-8,2,3,5,N,17,6,"Behold, thou in the inward parts"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:5-8,2,3,5,Y,18,6,with truth delighted art;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:5-8,2,3,5,N,19,6,And wisdom thou shalt make me know
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:5-8,2,3,5,Y,20,6,within the hidden part.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:5-8,2,3,6,N,21,7,"Do thou with hyssop sprinkle me,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:5-8,2,3,6,Y,22,7,I shall be cleansed so;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:5-8,2,3,6,N,23,7,"Yea, wash thou me, and then I shall"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:5-8,2,3,6,Y,24,7,be whiter than the snow.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:5-8,2,4,7,N,25,8,Of gladness and of joyfulness
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:5-8,2,4,7,Y,26,8,make me to hear the voice;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:5-8,2,4,7,N,27,8,That so these very bones which thou
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:5-8,2,4,7,Y,28,8,hast broken may rejoice.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:9-15,3,4,8,N,29,9,"All mine iniquities blot out,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:9-15,3,4,8,Y,30,9,thy face hide from my sin.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:9-15,3,4,8,N,31,10,"Create a clean heart, Lord, renew"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:9-15,3,4,8,Y,32,10,a right sp'rit me within.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:9-15,3,5,9,N,33,11,"Cast me not from thy sight, nor take"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:9-15,3,5,9,Y,34,11,thy Holy Sp'rit away.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:9-15,3,5,9,N,35,12,Restore me thy salvation's joy;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:9-15,3,5,9,Y,36,12,with thy free Sp'rit me stay.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:9-15,3,5,10,N,37,13,Then will I teach thy ways unto
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:9-15,3,5,10,Y,38,13,those that transgressors be;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:9-15,3,5,10,N,39,13,And those that sinners are shall then
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:9-15,3,5,10,Y,40,13,be turned unto thee.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:9-15,3,6,11,N,41,14,"O God, of my salvation God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:9-15,3,6,11,Y,42,14,me from blood-guiltiness
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:9-15,3,6,11,N,43,14,Set free; then shall my tongue aloud
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:9-15,3,6,11,Y,44,14,sing of thy righteousness.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:9-15,3,6,12,N,45,15,"My closed lips, O Lord, by thee"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:9-15,3,6,12,Y,46,15,let them be opened;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:9-15,3,6,12,N,47,15,Then shall thy praises by my mouth
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:9-15,3,6,12,Y,48,15,abroad be published.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:16-19,4,7,13,N,49,16,"For thou desir'st not sacrifice,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:16-19,4,7,13,Y,50,16,else would I give it thee;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:16-19,4,7,13,N,51,16,Nor wilt thou with burnt-offering
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:16-19,4,7,13,Y,52,16,at all delighted be.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:16-19,4,7,14,N,53,17,A broken spirit is to God
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:16-19,4,7,14,Y,54,17,a pleasing sacrifice:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:16-19,4,7,14,N,55,17,"A broken and a contrite heart,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:16-19,4,7,14,Y,56,17,"Lord, thou wilt not despise."
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:16-19,4,8,15,N,57,18,"Shew kindness, and do good, O Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:16-19,4,8,15,Y,58,18,"to Sion, thine own hill:"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:16-19,4,8,15,N,59,18,The walls of thy Jerusalem
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:16-19,4,8,15,Y,60,18,build up of thy good will.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:16-19,4,8,16,N,61,19,"Then righteous off 'rings shall thee please,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:16-19,4,8,16,Y,62,19,"and off 'rings burnt, which they"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:16-19,4,8,16,N,63,19,"With whole burnt-off 'rings, and with calves,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),51,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 51:16-19,4,8,16,Y,64,19,shall on thine altar lay.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),52,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 52:1-5,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Why dost thou boast, O mighty man,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),52,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 52:1-5,1,1,1,Y,2,1,of mischief and of ill?
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),52,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 52:1-5,1,1,1,N,3,1,The goodness of Almighty God
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),52,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 52:1-5,1,1,1,Y,4,1,endureth ever still.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),52,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 52:1-5,1,1,2,N,5,2,Thy tongue mischievous calumnies
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),52,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 52:1-5,1,1,2,Y,6,2,"deviseth subtilely,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),52,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 52:1-5,1,1,2,N,7,2,"Like to a razor sharp to cut,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),52,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 52:1-5,1,1,2,Y,8,2,working deceitfully.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),52,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 52:1-5,1,2,3,N,9,3,"Ill more than good, and more than truth"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),52,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 52:1-5,1,2,3,Y,10,3,thou lovest to speak wrong:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),52,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 52:1-5,1,2,3,N,11,4,"Thou lovest all-devouring words,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),52,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 52:1-5,1,2,3,Y,12,4,O thou deceitful tongue.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),52,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 52:1-5,1,2,4,N,13,5,"So God shall thee destroy for aye,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),52,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 52:1-5,1,2,4,Y,14,5,"remove thee, pluck thee out"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),52,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 52:1-5,1,2,4,N,15,5,"Quite from thy house, out of the land"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),52,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 52:1-5,1,2,4,Y,16,5,of life he shall thee root.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),52,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 52:6-9,2,3,5,N,17,6,"The righteous shall it see, and fear,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),52,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 52:6-9,2,3,5,Y,18,6,and laugh at him they shall:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),52,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 52:6-9,2,3,5,N,19,7,"Lo, this the man is that did not"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),52,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 52:6-9,2,3,5,Y,20,7,make God his strength at all:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),52,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 52:6-9,2,3,6,N,21,7,But he in his abundant wealth
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),52,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 52:6-9,2,3,6,Y,22,7,his confidence did place;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),52,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 52:6-9,2,3,6,N,23,7,And he took strength unto himself
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),52,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 52:6-9,2,3,6,Y,24,7,from his own wickedness.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),52,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 52:6-9,2,4,7,N,25,8,But I am in the house of God
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),52,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 52:6-9,2,4,7,Y,26,8,like to an olive green:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),52,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 52:6-9,2,4,7,N,27,8,My confidence for ever hath
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),52,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 52:6-9,2,4,7,Y,28,8,upon God's mercy been.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),52,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 52:6-9,2,4,8,N,29,9,"And I for ever will thee praise,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),52,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 52:6-9,2,4,8,Y,30,9,because thou hast done this:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),52,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 52:6-9,2,4,8,N,31,9,I on thy name will wait; for good
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),52,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 52:6-9,2,4,8,Y,32,9,before thy saints it is.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),53,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 53:1-3,1,1,1,N,1,1,"That there is not a God, the fool"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),53,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 53:1-3,1,1,1,Y,2,1,doth in his heart conclude:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),53,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 53:1-3,1,1,1,N,3,1,"They are corrupt, their works are vile,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),53,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 53:1-3,1,1,1,Y,4,1,not one of them doth good.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),53,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 53:1-3,1,1,2,N,5,2,The Lord upon the sons of men
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),53,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 53:1-3,1,1,2,Y,6,2,"from heav'n did cast his eyes,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),53,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 53:1-3,1,1,2,N,7,2,To see if any one there was
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),53,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 53:1-3,1,1,2,Y,8,2,"that sought God, and was wise."
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),53,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 53:1-3,1,2,3,N,9,3,"They altogether filthy are,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),53,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 53:1-3,1,2,3,Y,10,3,they all are backward gone;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),53,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 53:1-3,1,2,3,N,11,3,"And there is none that doeth good,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),53,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 53:1-3,1,2,3,Y,12,3,"no, not so much as one."
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),53,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 53:4-6,2,2,4,N,13,4,"These workers of iniquity,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),53,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 53:4-6,2,2,4,Y,14,4,"do they not know at all,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),53,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 53:4-6,2,2,4,N,15,4,"That they my people eat as bread,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),53,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 53:4-6,2,2,4,Y,16,4,and on God do not call?
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),53,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 53:4-6,2,3,5,N,17,5,"Ev'n there they were afraid, and stood"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),53,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 53:4-6,2,3,5,Y,18,5,"with trembling, all dismay'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),53,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 53:4-6,2,3,5,N,19,5,Whereas there was no cause at all
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),53,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 53:4-6,2,3,5,Y,20,5,why they should be afraid:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),53,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 53:4-6,2,3,6,N,21,5,For God his bones that thee besieg'd
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),53,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 53:4-6,2,3,6,Y,22,5,hath scatter'd all abroad;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),53,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 53:4-6,2,3,6,N,23,5,"Thou hast confounded them, for they"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),53,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 53:4-6,2,3,6,Y,24,5,despised are of God.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),53,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 53:4-6,2,4,7,N,25,6,Let Isr'el's help from Sion come:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),53,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 53:4-6,2,4,7,Y,26,6,when back the Lord shall bring
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),53,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 53:4-6,2,4,7,N,27,6,"His captives, Jacob shall rejoice,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),53,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 53:4-6,2,4,7,Y,28,6,and Israel shall sing.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),54,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 54:1-3,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Save me, O God, by thy great name,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),54,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 54:1-3,1,1,1,Y,2,1,and judge me by thy strength:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),54,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 54:1-3,1,1,1,N,3,2,"My prayer hear, O God; give ear"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),54,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 54:1-3,1,1,1,Y,4,2,unto my words at length.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),54,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 54:1-3,1,1,2,N,5,3,For they that strangers are to me
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),54,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 54:1-3,1,1,2,Y,6,3,do up against me rise;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),54,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 54:1-3,1,1,2,N,7,3,"Oppressors seek my soul, and God"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),54,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 54:1-3,1,1,2,Y,8,3,set not before their eyes.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),54,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 54:4-7,2,2,3,N,9,4,"The Lord my God my helper is,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),54,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 54:4-7,2,2,3,Y,10,4,"lo, therefore I am bold:"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),54,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 54:4-7,2,2,3,N,11,4,He taketh part with ev'ry one
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),54,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 54:4-7,2,2,3,Y,12,4,that doth my soul uphold.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),54,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 54:4-7,2,2,4,N,13,5,Unto mine enemies he shall
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),54,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 54:4-7,2,2,4,Y,14,5,mischief and ill repay:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),54,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 54:4-7,2,2,4,N,15,5,"O for thy truth's sake cut them off,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),54,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 54:4-7,2,2,4,Y,16,5,and sweep them clean away.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),54,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 54:4-7,2,3,5,N,17,6,I will a sacrifice to thee
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),54,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 54:4-7,2,3,5,Y,18,6,give with free willingness;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),54,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 54:4-7,2,3,5,N,19,6,"Thy name, O Lord, because 'tis good,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),54,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 54:4-7,2,3,5,Y,20,6,with praise I will confess.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),54,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 54:4-7,2,3,6,N,21,7,For he hath me delivered
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),54,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 54:4-7,2,3,6,Y,22,7,from all adversities;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),54,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 54:4-7,2,3,6,N,23,7,And his desire mine eye hath seen
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),54,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 54:4-7,2,3,6,Y,24,7,upon mine enemies.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:1-8,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Lord, hear my pray'r, hide not thyself"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:1-8,1,1,1,Y,2,1,from my entreating voice:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:1-8,1,1,1,N,3,2,Attend and hear me; in my plaint
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:1-8,1,1,1,Y,4,2,I mourn and make a noise.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:1-8,1,1,2,N,5,3,"Because of th' en'my's voice, and for"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:1-8,1,1,2,Y,6,3,lewd men's oppression great:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:1-8,1,1,2,N,7,3,"On me they cast iniquity,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:1-8,1,1,2,Y,8,3,and they in wrath me hate.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:1-8,1,2,3,N,9,4,Sore pain'd within me is my heart:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:1-8,1,2,3,Y,10,4,death's terrors on me fall.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:1-8,1,2,3,N,11,5,"On me comes trembling, fear and dread"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:1-8,1,2,3,Y,12,5,o'erwhelmed me withal.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:1-8,1,2,4,N,13,6,"O that I, like a dove, had wings,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:1-8,1,2,4,Y,14,6,"said I, then would I flee"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:1-8,1,2,4,N,15,6,"Far hence, that I might find a place"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:1-8,1,2,4,Y,16,6,where I in rest might be.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:1-8,1,3,5,N,17,7,"Lo, then far off I wander would,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:1-8,1,3,5,Y,18,7,and in the desert stay;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:1-8,1,3,5,N,19,8,From windy storm and tempest I
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:1-8,1,3,5,Y,20,8,would haste to 'scape away.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:9-14,2,3,6,N,21,9,"O Lord, on them destruction bring,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:9-14,2,3,6,Y,22,9,and do their tongues divide;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:9-14,2,3,6,N,23,9,For in the city violence
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:9-14,2,3,6,Y,24,9,and strife I have espy'd.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:9-14,2,4,7,N,25,10,They day and night upon the walls
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:9-14,2,4,7,Y,26,10,do go about it round:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:9-14,2,4,7,N,27,10,"There mischief is, and sorrow there"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:9-14,2,4,7,Y,28,10,in midst of it is found.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:9-14,2,4,8,N,29,11,Abundant wickedness there is
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:9-14,2,4,8,Y,30,11,within her inward part;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:9-14,2,4,8,N,31,11,And from her streets deceitfulness
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:9-14,2,4,8,Y,32,11,and guile do not depart.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:9-14,2,5,9,N,33,12,"He was no foe that me reproach'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:9-14,2,5,9,Y,34,12,then that endure I could;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:9-14,2,5,9,N,35,12,"Nor hater that did 'gainst me boast,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:9-14,2,5,9,Y,36,12,from him me hide I would.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:9-14,2,5,10,N,37,13,"But thou, man, who mine equal, guide,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:9-14,2,5,10,Y,38,13,and mine acquaintance wast:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:9-14,2,5,10,N,39,14,"We join'd sweet counsels, to God's house"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:9-14,2,5,10,Y,40,14,in company we past.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:15-19,3,6,11,N,41,15,"Let death upon them seize, and down"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:15-19,3,6,11,Y,42,15,let them go quick to hell;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:15-19,3,6,11,N,43,15,For wickedness doth much abound
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:15-19,3,6,11,Y,44,15,among them where they dwell.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:15-19,3,6,12,N,45,16,I'll call on God: God will me save.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:15-19,3,6,12,Y,46,17,"I'll pray, and make a noise"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:15-19,3,6,12,N,47,17,"At ev'ning, morning, and at noon;"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:15-19,3,6,12,Y,48,17,and he shall hear my voice.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:15-19,3,7,13,N,49,18,"He hath my soul delivered,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:15-19,3,7,13,Y,50,18,that it in peace might be
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:15-19,3,7,13,N,51,18,From battle that against me was;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:15-19,3,7,13,Y,52,18,for many were with me.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:15-19,3,7,14,N,53,19,"The Lord shall hear, and them afflict,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:15-19,3,7,14,Y,54,19,of old who hath abode:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:15-19,3,7,14,N,55,19,"Because they never changes have,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:15-19,3,7,14,Y,56,19,therefore they fear not God.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:20-23,4,8,15,N,57,20,'Gainst those that were at peace with him
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:20-23,4,8,15,Y,58,20,he hath put forth his hand:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:20-23,4,8,15,N,59,20,"The covenant that he had made,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:20-23,4,8,15,Y,60,20,by breaking he profan'd.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:20-23,4,8,16,N,61,21,"More smooth than butter were his words,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:20-23,4,8,16,Y,62,21,while in his heart was war;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:20-23,4,8,16,N,63,21,"His speeches were more soft than oil,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:20-23,4,8,16,Y,64,21,and yet drawn swords they are.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:20-23,4,9,17,N,65,22,"Cast thou thy burden on the Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:20-23,4,9,17,Y,66,22,and he shall thee sustain;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:20-23,4,9,17,N,67,22,"Yea, he shall cause the righteous man"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:20-23,4,9,17,Y,68,22,unmoved to remain.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:20-23,4,9,18,N,69,23,"But thou, O Lord my God, those men"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:20-23,4,9,18,Y,70,23,"in justice shalt o'erthrow,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:20-23,4,9,18,N,71,23,And in destruction's dungeon dark
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:20-23,4,9,18,Y,72,23,at last shalt lay them low:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:20-23,4,10,19,N,73,23,The bloody and deceitful men
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:20-23,4,10,19,Y,74,23,shall not live half their days:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:20-23,4,10,19,N,75,23,But upon thee with confidence
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),55,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 55:20-23,4,10,19,Y,76,23,I will depend always.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),56,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 56:1-7,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Shew mercy, Lord, to me, for man"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),56,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 56:1-7,1,1,1,Y,2,1,would swallow me outright;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),56,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 56:1-7,1,1,1,N,3,1,"He me oppresseth, while he doth"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),56,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 56:1-7,1,1,1,Y,4,1,against me daily fight.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),56,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 56:1-7,1,1,2,N,5,2,They daily would me swallow up
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),56,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 56:1-7,1,1,2,Y,6,2,that hate me spitefully;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),56,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 56:1-7,1,1,2,N,7,2,For they be many that do fight
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),56,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 56:1-7,1,1,2,Y,8,2,"against me, O most High."
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),56,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 56:1-7,1,2,3,N,9,3,When I'm afraid I'll trust in thee:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),56,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 56:1-7,1,2,3,Y,10,4,In God I'll praise his word;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),56,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 56:1-7,1,2,3,N,11,4,"I will not fear what flesh can do,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),56,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 56:1-7,1,2,3,Y,12,4,my trust is in the Lord.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),56,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 56:1-7,1,2,4,N,13,5,Each day they wrest my words; their thoughts
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),56,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 56:1-7,1,2,4,Y,14,5,'gainst me are all for ill.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),56,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 56:1-7,1,2,4,N,15,6,"They meet, they lurk, they mark my steps,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),56,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 56:1-7,1,2,4,Y,16,6,waiting my soul to kill.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),56,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 56:1-7,1,3,5,N,17,7,But shall they by iniquity
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),56,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 56:1-7,1,3,5,Y,18,7,escape thy judgments so?
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),56,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 56:1-7,1,3,5,N,19,7,"O God, with indignation down"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),56,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 56:1-7,1,3,5,Y,20,7,do thou the people throw.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),56,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 56:8-13,2,3,6,N,21,8,My wand'rings all what they have been
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),56,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 56:8-13,2,3,6,Y,22,8,"thou know'st, their number took;"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),56,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 56:8-13,2,3,6,N,23,8,Into thy bottle put my tears:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),56,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 56:8-13,2,3,6,Y,24,8,are they not in thy book?
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),56,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 56:8-13,2,4,7,N,25,9,"My foes shall, when I cry, turn back;"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),56,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 56:8-13,2,4,7,Y,26,9,"I know't, God is for me."
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),56,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 56:8-13,2,4,7,N,27,10,In God his word I'll praise; his word
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),56,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 56:8-13,2,4,7,Y,28,10,in God shall praised be.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),56,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 56:8-13,2,4,8,N,29,11,In God I trust; I will not fear
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),56,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 56:8-13,2,4,8,Y,30,11,what man can do to me.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),56,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 56:8-13,2,4,8,N,31,12,"Thy vows upon me are, O God:"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),56,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 56:8-13,2,4,8,Y,32,12,I'll render praise to thee.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),56,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 56:8-13,2,5,9,N,33,13,"Wilt thou not, who from death me sav'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),56,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 56:8-13,2,5,9,Y,34,13,"my feet from falls keep free,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),56,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 56:8-13,2,5,9,N,35,13,To walk before God in the light
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),56,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 56:8-13,2,5,9,Y,36,13,of those that living be?
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),57,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 57:1-4,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Be merciful to me, O God;"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),57,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 57:1-4,1,1,1,Y,2,1,thy mercy unto me
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),57,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 57:1-4,1,1,1,N,3,1,Do thou extend; because my soul
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),57,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 57:1-4,1,1,1,Y,4,1,doth put her trust in thee:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),57,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 57:1-4,1,1,2,N,5,1,"Yea, in the shadow of thy wings"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),57,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 57:1-4,1,1,2,Y,6,1,"my refuge I will place,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),57,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 57:1-4,1,1,2,N,7,1,Until these sad calamities
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),57,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 57:1-4,1,1,2,Y,8,1,do wholly overpass.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),57,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 57:1-4,1,2,3,N,9,2,My cry I will cause to ascend
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),57,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 57:1-4,1,2,3,Y,10,2,unto the Lord most high;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),57,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 57:1-4,1,2,3,N,11,2,"To God, who doth all things for me"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),57,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 57:1-4,1,2,3,Y,12,2,perform most perfectly.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),57,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 57:1-4,1,2,4,N,13,3,"From heav'n he shall send down, and me"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),57,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 57:1-4,1,2,4,Y,14,3,from his reproach defend
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),57,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 57:1-4,1,2,4,N,15,3,That would devour me: God his truth
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),57,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 57:1-4,1,2,4,Y,16,3,and mercy forth shall send.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),57,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 57:1-4,1,3,5,N,17,4,"My soul among fierce lions is,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),57,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 57:1-4,1,3,5,Y,18,4,"I firebrands live among,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),57,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 57:1-4,1,3,5,N,19,4,"Men's sons, whose teeth are spears and darts,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),57,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 57:1-4,1,3,5,Y,20,4,a sharp sword is their tongue.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),57,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 57:5-11,2,3,6,N,21,5,Be thou exalted very high
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),57,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 57:5-11,2,3,6,Y,22,5,"above the heav'ns, O God;"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),57,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 57:5-11,2,3,6,N,23,5,Let thou thy glory be advanc'd
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),57,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 57:5-11,2,3,6,Y,24,5,o'er all the earth abroad.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),57,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 57:5-11,2,4,7,N,25,6,My soul's bow'd down; for they a net
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),57,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 57:5-11,2,4,7,Y,26,6,"have laid, my steps to snare:"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),57,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 57:5-11,2,4,7,N,27,6,Into the pit which they have digg'd
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),57,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 57:5-11,2,4,7,Y,28,6,"for me, they fallen are."
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),57,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 57:5-11,2,4,8,N,29,7,"My heart is fix'd, my heart is fix'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),57,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 57:5-11,2,4,8,Y,30,7,O God; I'll sing and praise.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),57,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 57:5-11,2,4,8,N,31,8,"My glory wake; wake psalt'ry, harp;"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),57,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 57:5-11,2,4,8,Y,32,8,myself I'll early raise.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),57,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 57:5-11,2,5,9,N,33,9,"I'll praise thee 'mong the people, Lord;"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),57,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 57:5-11,2,5,9,Y,34,9,'mong nations sing will I:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),57,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 57:5-11,2,5,9,N,35,10,"For great to heav'n thy mercy is,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),57,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 57:5-11,2,5,9,Y,36,10,thy truth is to the sky.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),57,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 57:5-11,2,5,10,N,37,11,"O Lord, exalted be thy name"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),57,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 57:5-11,2,5,10,Y,38,11,above the heav'ns to stand:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),57,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 57:5-11,2,5,10,N,39,11,Do thou thy glory far advance
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),57,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 57:5-11,2,5,10,Y,40,11,above both sea and land.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),58,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 58:1-5,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Do ye, O congregation,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),58,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 58:1-5,1,1,1,Y,2,1,indeed speak righteousness?
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),58,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 58:1-5,1,1,1,N,3,1,"O ye that are the sons of men,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),58,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 58:1-5,1,1,1,Y,4,1,judge ye with uprightness?
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),58,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 58:1-5,1,1,2,N,5,2,"Yea, ev'n within your very hearts"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),58,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 58:1-5,1,1,2,Y,6,2,ye wickedness have done;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),58,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 58:1-5,1,1,2,N,7,2,And ye the vi'lence of your hands
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),58,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 58:1-5,1,1,2,Y,8,2,do weigh the earth upon.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),58,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 58:1-5,1,2,3,N,9,3,"The wicked men estranged are,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),58,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 58:1-5,1,2,3,Y,10,3,ev'n from the very womb;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),58,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 58:1-5,1,2,3,N,11,3,"They, speaking lies, do stray as soon"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),58,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 58:1-5,1,2,3,Y,12,3,as to the world they come.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),58,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 58:1-5,1,2,4,N,13,4,Unto a serpent's poison like
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),58,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 58:1-5,1,2,4,Y,14,4,their poison doth appear;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),58,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 58:1-5,1,2,4,N,15,4,"Yea, they are like the adder deaf,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),58,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 58:1-5,1,2,4,Y,16,4,that closely stops her ear;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),58,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 58:1-5,1,3,5,N,17,5,That so she may not hear the voice
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),58,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 58:1-5,1,3,5,Y,18,5,"of one that charm her would,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),58,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 58:1-5,1,3,5,N,19,5,"No, not though he most cunning were,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),58,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 58:1-5,1,3,5,Y,20,5,and charm most wisely could.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),58,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 58:6-9,2,3,6,N,21,6,"Their teeth, O God, within their mouth"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),58,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 58:6-9,2,3,6,Y,22,6,break thou in pieces small;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),58,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 58:6-9,2,3,6,N,23,6,"The great teeth break thou out, O Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),58,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 58:6-9,2,3,6,Y,24,6,of these young lions all.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),58,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 58:6-9,2,4,7,N,25,7,"Let them like waters melt away,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),58,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 58:6-9,2,4,7,Y,26,7,which downward still do flow:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),58,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 58:6-9,2,4,7,N,27,7,"In pieces cut his arrows all,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),58,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 58:6-9,2,4,7,Y,28,7,when he shall bend his bow.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),58,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 58:6-9,2,4,8,N,29,8,"Like to a snail that melts away,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),58,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 58:6-9,2,4,8,Y,30,8,let each of them be gone;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),58,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 58:6-9,2,4,8,N,31,8,"Like woman's birth untimely, that"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),58,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 58:6-9,2,4,8,Y,32,8,they never see the sun.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),58,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 58:6-9,2,5,9,N,33,9,He shall them take away before
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),58,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 58:6-9,2,5,9,Y,34,9,"your pots the thorns can find,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),58,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 58:6-9,2,5,9,N,35,9,"Both living, and in fury great,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),58,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 58:6-9,2,5,9,Y,36,9,as with a stormy wind.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),58,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 58:10-11,3,5,10,N,37,10,"The righteous, when he vengeance sees,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),58,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 58:10-11,3,5,10,Y,38,10,he shall be joyful then;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),58,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 58:10-11,3,5,10,N,39,10,The righteous one shall wash his feet
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),58,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 58:10-11,3,5,10,Y,40,10,in blood of wicked men.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),58,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 58:10-11,3,6,11,N,41,11,"So men shall say, The righteous man"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),58,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 58:10-11,3,6,11,Y,42,11,reward shall never miss:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),58,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 58:10-11,3,6,11,N,43,11,And verily upon the earth
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),58,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 58:10-11,3,6,11,Y,44,11,a God to judge there is.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:1-4,1,1,1,N,1,1,"My God, deliver me from those"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:1-4,1,1,1,Y,2,1,that are mine enemies;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:1-4,1,1,1,N,3,1,And do thou me defend from those
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:1-4,1,1,1,Y,4,1,that up against me rise.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:1-4,1,1,2,N,5,2,Do thou deliver me from them
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:1-4,1,1,2,Y,6,2,that work iniquity;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:1-4,1,1,2,N,7,2,And give me safety from the men
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:1-4,1,1,2,Y,8,2,of bloody cruelty.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:1-4,1,2,3,N,9,3,"For, lo, they for my soul lay wait:"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:1-4,1,2,3,Y,10,3,the mighty do combine
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:1-4,1,2,3,N,11,3,"Against me, Lord; not for my fault,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:1-4,1,2,3,Y,12,3,nor any sin of mine.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:1-4,1,2,4,N,13,4,"They run, and, without fault in me,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:1-4,1,2,4,Y,14,4,themselves do ready make:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:1-4,1,2,4,N,15,4,Awake to meet me with thy help;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:1-4,1,2,4,Y,16,4,and do thou notice take.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:5-9,2,3,5,N,17,5,"Awake therefore, Lord God of hosts,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:5-9,2,3,5,Y,18,5,"thou God of Israel,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:5-9,2,3,5,N,19,5,To visit heathen all: spare none
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:5-9,2,3,5,Y,20,5,that wickedly rebel.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:5-9,2,3,6,N,21,6,At ev'ning they go to and fro;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:5-9,2,3,6,Y,22,6,"they make great noise and sound,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:5-9,2,3,6,N,23,6,"Like to a dog, and often walk"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:5-9,2,3,6,Y,24,6,about the city round.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:5-9,2,4,7,N,25,7,"Behold, they belch out with their mouth,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:5-9,2,4,7,Y,26,7,and in their lips are swords:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:5-9,2,4,7,N,27,7,"For they do say thus, Who is he"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:5-9,2,4,7,Y,28,7,that now doth hear our words?
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:5-9,2,4,8,N,29,8,"But thou, O Lord, shalt laugh at them,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:5-9,2,4,8,Y,30,8,and all the heathen mock.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:5-9,2,4,8,N,31,9,While he's in pow'r I'll wait on thee;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:5-9,2,4,8,Y,32,9,for God is my high rock.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:10-12,3,5,9,N,33,10,He of my mercy that is God
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:10-12,3,5,9,Y,34,10,betimes shall me prevent;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:10-12,3,5,9,N,35,10,Upon mine en'mies God shall let
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:10-12,3,5,9,Y,36,10,me see mine heart's content.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:10-12,3,5,10,N,37,11,"Them slay not, lest my folk forget;"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:10-12,3,5,10,Y,38,11,but scatter them abroad
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:10-12,3,5,10,N,39,11,"By thy strong pow'r; and bring them down,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:10-12,3,5,10,Y,40,11,O thou our shield and God.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:10-12,3,6,11,N,41,12,"For their mouth's sin, and for the words"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:10-12,3,6,11,Y,42,12,"that from their lips do fly,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:10-12,3,6,11,N,43,12,Let them be taken in their pride;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:10-12,3,6,11,Y,44,12,because they curse and lie.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:13-17,4,6,12,N,45,13,"In wrath consume them, them consume,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:13-17,4,6,12,Y,46,13,that so they may not be:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:13-17,4,6,12,N,47,13,And that in Jacob God doth rule
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:13-17,4,6,12,Y,48,13,to th' earth's ends let them see.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:13-17,4,7,13,N,49,14,"At ev'ning let thou them return,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:13-17,4,7,13,Y,50,14,"making great noise and sound,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:13-17,4,7,13,N,51,14,"Like to a dog, and often walk"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:13-17,4,7,13,Y,52,14,about the city round.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:13-17,4,7,14,N,53,15,"And let them wander up and down,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:13-17,4,7,14,Y,54,15,in seeking food to eat;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:13-17,4,7,14,N,55,15,And let them grudge when they shall not
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:13-17,4,7,14,Y,56,15,be satisfy'd with meat.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:13-17,4,8,15,N,57,16,But of thy pow'r I'll sing aloud;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:13-17,4,8,15,Y,58,16,at morn thy mercy praise:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:13-17,4,8,15,N,59,16,"For thou to me my refuge wast,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:13-17,4,8,15,Y,60,16,"and tow'r, in troublous days."
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:13-17,4,8,16,N,61,17,"O God, thou art my strength, I will"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:13-17,4,8,16,Y,62,17,sing praises unto thee;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:13-17,4,8,16,N,63,17,"For God is my defence, a God"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),59,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 59:13-17,4,8,16,Y,64,17,of mercy unto me.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),60,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 60:1-5,1,1,1,N,1,1,"O Lord, thou hast rejected us,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),60,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 60:1-5,1,1,1,Y,2,1,and scatter'd us abroad;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),60,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 60:1-5,1,1,1,N,3,1,Thou justly hast displeased been;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),60,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 60:1-5,1,1,1,Y,4,1,"return to us, O God."
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),60,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 60:1-5,1,1,2,N,5,2,The earth to tremble thou hast made;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),60,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 60:1-5,1,1,2,Y,6,2,therein didst breaches make:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),60,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 60:1-5,1,1,2,N,7,2,"Do thou thereof the breaches heal,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),60,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 60:1-5,1,1,2,Y,8,2,because the land doth shake.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),60,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 60:1-5,1,2,3,N,9,3,Unto thy people thou hard things
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),60,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 60:1-5,1,2,3,Y,10,3,"hast shew'd, and on them sent;"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),60,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 60:1-5,1,2,3,N,11,3,And thou hast caused us to drink
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),60,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 60:1-5,1,2,3,Y,12,3,wine of astonishment.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),60,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 60:1-5,1,2,4,N,13,4,And yet a banner thou hast giv'n
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),60,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 60:1-5,1,2,4,Y,14,4,to them who thee do fear;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),60,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 60:1-5,1,2,4,N,15,4,"That it by them, because of truth,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),60,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 60:1-5,1,2,4,Y,16,4,displayed may appear.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),60,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 60:1-5,1,3,5,N,17,5,That thy beloved people may
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),60,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 60:1-5,1,3,5,Y,18,5,"deliver'd be from thrall,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),60,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 60:1-5,1,3,5,N,19,5,"Save with the pow'r of thy right hand,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),60,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 60:1-5,1,3,5,Y,20,5,and hear me when I call.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),60,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 60:6-8,2,3,6,N,21,6,God in his holiness hath spoke;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),60,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 60:6-8,2,3,6,Y,22,6,herein I will take pleasure:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),60,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 60:6-8,2,3,6,N,23,6,"Shechem I will divide, and forth"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),60,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 60:6-8,2,3,6,Y,24,6,will Succoth's valley measure.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),60,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 60:6-8,2,4,7,N,25,7,Gilead I claim as mine by right;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),60,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 60:6-8,2,4,7,Y,26,7,Manasseh mine shall be;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),60,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 60:6-8,2,4,7,N,27,7,Ephraim is of mine head the strength;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),60,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 60:6-8,2,4,7,Y,28,7,Judah gives laws for me;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),60,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 60:6-8,2,4,8,N,29,8,Moab's my washing-pot; my shoe
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),60,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 60:6-8,2,4,8,Y,30,8,I'll over Edom throw;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),60,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 60:6-8,2,4,8,N,31,8,And over Palestina's land
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),60,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 60:6-8,2,4,8,Y,32,8,I will in triumph go.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),60,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 60:9-12,3,5,9,N,33,9,O who is he will bring me to
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),60,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 60:9-12,3,5,9,Y,34,9,the city fortify'd?
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),60,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 60:9-12,3,5,9,N,35,9,O who is he that to the land
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),60,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 60:9-12,3,5,9,Y,36,9,of Edom will me guide?
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),60,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 60:9-12,3,5,10,N,37,10,"O God, which hadest us cast off,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),60,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 60:9-12,3,5,10,Y,38,10,this thing wilt thou not do?
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),60,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 60:9-12,3,5,10,N,39,10,"Ev'n thou, O God, which didest not"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),60,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 60:9-12,3,5,10,Y,40,10,forth with our armies go?
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),60,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 60:9-12,3,6,11,N,41,11,Help us from trouble; for the help
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),60,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 60:9-12,3,6,11,Y,42,11,is vain which man supplies.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),60,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 60:9-12,3,6,11,N,43,12,Through God we'll do great acts; he shall
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),60,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 60:9-12,3,6,11,Y,44,12,tread down our enemies.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),61,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 61:1-3,1,1,1,N,1,1,"O God, give ear unto my cry;"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),61,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 61:1-3,1,1,1,Y,2,1,unto my pray'r attend.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),61,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 61:1-3,1,1,1,N,3,2,From th' utmost corner of the land
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),61,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 61:1-3,1,1,1,Y,4,2,my cry to thee I'll send.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),61,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 61:1-3,1,1,2,N,5,2,"What time my heart is overwhelm'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),61,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 61:1-3,1,1,2,Y,6,2,"and in perplexity,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),61,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 61:1-3,1,1,2,N,7,2,Do thou me lead unto the Rock
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),61,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 61:1-3,1,1,2,Y,8,2,that higher is than I.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),61,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 61:1-3,1,2,3,N,9,3,For thou hast for my refuge been
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),61,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 61:1-3,1,2,3,Y,10,3,a shelter by thy pow'r;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),61,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 61:1-3,1,2,3,N,11,3,And for defence against my foes
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),61,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 61:1-3,1,2,3,Y,12,3,thou hast been a strong tow'r.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),61,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 61:4-8,2,2,4,N,13,4,Within thy tabernacle I
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),61,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 61:4-8,2,2,4,Y,14,4,for ever will abide;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),61,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 61:4-8,2,2,4,N,15,4,And under covert of thy wings
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),61,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 61:4-8,2,2,4,Y,16,4,with confidence me hide.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),61,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 61:4-8,2,3,5,N,17,5,"For thou the vows that I did make,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),61,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 61:4-8,2,3,5,Y,18,5,"O Lord my God, didst hear:"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),61,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 61:4-8,2,3,5,N,19,5,Thou hast giv'n me the heritage
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),61,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 61:4-8,2,3,5,Y,20,5,of those thy name that fear.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),61,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 61:4-8,2,3,6,N,21,6,A life prolong'd for many days
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),61,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 61:4-8,2,3,6,Y,22,6,thou to the king shalt give;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),61,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 61:4-8,2,3,6,N,23,6,Like many generations be
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),61,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 61:4-8,2,3,6,Y,24,6,the years which he shall live.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),61,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 61:4-8,2,4,7,N,25,7,He in God's presence his abode
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),61,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 61:4-8,2,4,7,Y,26,7,for evermore shall have:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),61,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 61:4-8,2,4,7,N,27,7,O do thou truth and mercy both
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),61,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 61:4-8,2,4,7,Y,28,7,"prepare, that may him save."
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),61,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 61:4-8,2,4,8,N,29,8,And so will I perpetually
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),61,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 61:4-8,2,4,8,Y,30,8,sing praise unto thy name;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),61,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 61:4-8,2,4,8,N,31,8,"That having made my vows, I may"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),61,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 61:4-8,2,4,8,Y,32,8,each day perform the same.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),62,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 62:1-4,1,1,1,N,1,1,My soul with expectation
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),62,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 62:1-4,1,1,1,Y,2,1,depends on God indeed;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),62,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 62:1-4,1,1,1,N,3,1,My strength and my salvation doth
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),62,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 62:1-4,1,1,1,Y,4,1,from him alone proceed.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),62,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 62:1-4,1,1,2,N,5,2,"He only my salvation is,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),62,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 62:1-4,1,1,2,Y,6,2,and my strong rock is he:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),62,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 62:1-4,1,1,2,N,7,2,He only is my sure defence;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),62,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 62:1-4,1,1,2,Y,8,2,much mov'd I shall not be.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),62,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 62:1-4,1,2,3,N,9,3,How long will ye against a man
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),62,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 62:1-4,1,2,3,Y,10,3,plot mischief? ye shall all
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),62,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 62:1-4,1,2,3,N,11,3,Be slain; ye as a tott'ring fence
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),62,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 62:1-4,1,2,3,Y,12,3,"shall be, and bowing wall."
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),62,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 62:1-4,1,2,4,N,13,4,They only plot to cast him down
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),62,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 62:1-4,1,2,4,Y,14,4,from his excellency:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),62,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 62:1-4,1,2,4,N,15,4,"They joy in lies; with mouth they bless,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),62,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 62:1-4,1,2,4,Y,16,4,but they curse inwardly.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),62,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 62:5-8,2,3,5,N,17,5,"My soul, wait thou with patience"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),62,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 62:5-8,2,3,5,Y,18,5,upon thy God alone;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),62,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 62:5-8,2,3,5,N,19,5,On him dependeth all my hope
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),62,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 62:5-8,2,3,5,Y,20,5,and expectation.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),62,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 62:5-8,2,3,6,N,21,6,"He only my salvation is,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),62,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 62:5-8,2,3,6,Y,22,6,and my strong rock is he;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),62,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 62:5-8,2,3,6,N,23,6,He only is my sure defence:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),62,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 62:5-8,2,3,6,Y,24,6,I shall not moved be.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),62,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 62:5-8,2,4,7,N,25,7,"In God my glory placed is,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),62,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 62:5-8,2,4,7,Y,26,7,and my salvation sure;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),62,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 62:5-8,2,4,7,N,27,7,"In God the rock is of my strength,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),62,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 62:5-8,2,4,7,Y,28,7,my refuge most secure.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),62,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 62:5-8,2,4,8,N,29,8,"Ye people, place your confidence"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),62,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 62:5-8,2,4,8,Y,30,8,in him continually;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),62,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 62:5-8,2,4,8,N,31,8,Before him pour ye out your heart:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),62,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 62:5-8,2,4,8,Y,32,8,God is our refuge high.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),62,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 62:9-12,3,5,9,N,33,9,"Surely mean men are vanity,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),62,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 62:9-12,3,5,9,Y,34,9,and great men are a lie;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),62,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 62:9-12,3,5,9,N,35,9,"In balance laid, they wholly are"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),62,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 62:9-12,3,5,9,Y,36,9,more light than vanity.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),62,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 62:9-12,3,5,10,N,37,10,"Trust ye not in oppression,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),62,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 62:9-12,3,5,10,Y,38,10,in robb'ry be not vain;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),62,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 62:9-12,3,5,10,N,39,10,"On wealth set not your hearts, when as"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),62,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 62:9-12,3,5,10,Y,40,10,increased is your gain.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),62,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 62:9-12,3,6,11,N,41,11,"God hath it spoken once to me,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),62,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 62:9-12,3,6,11,Y,42,11,"yea, this I heard again,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),62,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 62:9-12,3,6,11,N,43,11,That power to Almighty God
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),62,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 62:9-12,3,6,11,Y,44,11,alone doth appertain.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),62,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 62:9-12,3,6,12,N,45,12,"Yea, mercy also unto thee"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),62,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 62:9-12,3,6,12,Y,46,12,"belongs, O Lord, alone:"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),62,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 62:9-12,3,6,12,N,47,12,For thou according to his work
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),62,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 62:9-12,3,6,12,Y,48,12,rewardest ev'ry one.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),63,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 63:1-5,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Lord, thee my God, I'll early seek:"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),63,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 63:1-5,1,1,1,Y,2,1,my soul doth thirst for thee;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),63,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 63:1-5,1,1,1,N,3,1,"My flesh longs in a dry parch'd land,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),63,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 63:1-5,1,1,1,Y,4,1,wherein no waters be:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),63,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 63:1-5,1,1,2,N,5,2,"That I thy power may behold,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),63,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 63:1-5,1,1,2,Y,6,2,"and brightness of thy face,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),63,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 63:1-5,1,1,2,N,7,2,As I have seen thee heretofore
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),63,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 63:1-5,1,1,2,Y,8,2,within thy holy place.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),63,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 63:1-5,1,2,3,N,9,3,"Since better is thy love than life,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),63,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 63:1-5,1,2,3,Y,10,3,my lips thee praise shall give.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),63,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 63:1-5,1,2,3,N,11,4,"I in thy name will lift my hands,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),63,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 63:1-5,1,2,3,Y,12,4,and bless thee while I live.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),63,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 63:1-5,1,2,4,N,13,5,Ev'n as with marrow and with fat
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),63,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 63:1-5,1,2,4,Y,14,5,my soul shall filled be;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),63,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 63:1-5,1,2,4,N,15,5,Then shall my mouth with joyful lips
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),63,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 63:1-5,1,2,4,Y,16,5,sing praises unto thee:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),63,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 63:6-11,2,3,5,N,17,6,When I do thee upon my bed
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),63,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 63:6-11,2,3,5,Y,18,6,"remember with delight,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),63,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 63:6-11,2,3,5,N,19,6,And when on thee I meditate
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),63,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 63:6-11,2,3,5,Y,20,6,in watches of the night.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),63,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 63:6-11,2,3,6,N,21,7,In shadow of thy wings I'll joy;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),63,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 63:6-11,2,3,6,Y,22,7,for thou mine help hast been.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),63,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 63:6-11,2,3,6,N,23,8,My soul thee follows hard; and me
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),63,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 63:6-11,2,3,6,Y,24,8,thy right hand doth sustain.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),63,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 63:6-11,2,4,7,N,25,9,Who seek my soul to spill shall sink
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),63,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 63:6-11,2,4,7,Y,26,9,down to earth's lowest room.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),63,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 63:6-11,2,4,7,N,27,10,"They by the sword shall be cut off,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),63,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 63:6-11,2,4,7,Y,28,10,and foxes' prey become.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),63,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 63:6-11,2,4,8,N,29,11,"Yet shall the king in God rejoice,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),63,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 63:6-11,2,4,8,Y,30,11,and each one glory shall
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),63,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 63:6-11,2,4,8,N,31,11,That swear by him: but stopp'd shall be
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),63,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 63:6-11,2,4,8,Y,32,11,the mouth of liars all.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),64,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 64:1-4,1,1,1,N,1,1,"When I to thee my prayer make,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),64,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 64:1-4,1,1,1,Y,2,1,"Lord, to my voice give ear;"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),64,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 64:1-4,1,1,1,N,3,1,"My life save from the enemy,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),64,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 64:1-4,1,1,1,Y,4,1,of whom I stand in fear.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),64,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 64:1-4,1,1,2,N,5,2,Me from their secret counsel hide
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),64,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 64:1-4,1,1,2,Y,6,2,who do live wickedly;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),64,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 64:1-4,1,1,2,N,7,2,From insurrection of those men
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),64,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 64:1-4,1,1,2,Y,8,2,that work iniquity:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),64,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 64:1-4,1,2,3,N,9,3,"Who do their tongues with malice whet,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),64,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 64:1-4,1,2,3,Y,10,3,and make them cut like swords;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),64,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 64:1-4,1,2,3,N,11,3,"In whose bent bows are arrows set,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),64,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 64:1-4,1,2,3,Y,12,3,ev'n sharp and bitter words:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),64,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 64:1-4,1,2,4,N,13,4,That they may at the perfect man
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),64,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 64:1-4,1,2,4,Y,14,4,in secret aim their shot;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),64,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 64:1-4,1,2,4,N,15,4,"Yea, suddenly they dare at him"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),64,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 64:1-4,1,2,4,Y,16,4,"to shoot, and fear it not."
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),64,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 64:5-10,2,3,5,N,17,5,"In ill encourage they themselves,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),64,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 64:5-10,2,3,5,Y,18,5,and their snares close do lay:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),64,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 64:5-10,2,3,5,N,19,5,Together conference they have;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),64,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 64:5-10,2,3,5,Y,20,5,Who shall them see? they say.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),64,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 64:5-10,2,3,6,N,21,6,"They have search'd out iniquities,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),64,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 64:5-10,2,3,6,Y,22,6,a perfect search they keep:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),64,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 64:5-10,2,3,6,N,23,6,"Of each of them the inward thought,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),64,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 64:5-10,2,3,6,Y,24,6,"and very heart, is deep."
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),64,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 64:5-10,2,4,7,N,25,7,"God shall an arrow shoot at them,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),64,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 64:5-10,2,4,7,Y,26,7,and wound them suddenly:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),64,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 64:5-10,2,4,7,N,27,8,So their own tongue shall them confound;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),64,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 64:5-10,2,4,7,Y,28,8,all who them see shall fly.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),64,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 64:5-10,2,4,8,N,29,9,"And on all men a fear shall fall,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),64,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 64:5-10,2,4,8,Y,30,9,God's works they shall declare;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),64,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 64:5-10,2,4,8,N,31,9,For they shall wisely notice take
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),64,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 64:5-10,2,4,8,Y,32,9,what these his doings are.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),64,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 64:5-10,2,5,9,N,33,10,"In God the righteous shall rejoice,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),64,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 64:5-10,2,5,9,Y,34,10,and trust upon his might;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),64,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 64:5-10,2,5,9,N,35,10,"Yea, they shall greatly glory all"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),64,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 64:5-10,2,5,9,Y,36,10,in heart that are upright.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:1-4,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Praise waits for thee in Sion, Lord:"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:1-4,1,1,1,Y,2,1,to thee vows paid shall be.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:1-4,1,1,1,N,3,2,"O thou that hearer art of pray'r,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:1-4,1,1,1,Y,4,2,all flesh shall come to thee.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:1-4,1,1,2,N,5,3,"Iniquities, I must confess,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:1-4,1,1,2,Y,6,3,prevail against me do:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:1-4,1,1,2,N,7,3,"But as for our transgressions,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:1-4,1,1,2,Y,8,3,them purge away shalt thou.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:1-4,1,2,3,N,9,4,"Bless'd is the man whom thou dost chuse,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:1-4,1,2,3,Y,10,4,"and mak'st approach to thee,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:1-4,1,2,3,N,11,4,"That he within thy courts, O Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:1-4,1,2,3,Y,12,4,may still a dweller be:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:1-4,1,2,4,N,13,4,We surely shall be satisfy'd
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:1-4,1,2,4,Y,14,4,"with thy abundant grace,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:1-4,1,2,4,N,15,4,"And with the goodness of thy house,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:1-4,1,2,4,Y,16,4,ev'n of thy holy place.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:5-8,2,3,5,N,17,5,"O God of our salvation,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:5-8,2,3,5,Y,18,5,"thou, in thy righteousness,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:5-8,2,3,5,N,19,5,By fearful works unto our pray'rs
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:5-8,2,3,5,Y,20,5,thine answer dost express:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:5-8,2,3,6,N,21,5,"Therefore the ends of all the earth,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:5-8,2,3,6,Y,22,5,and those afar that be
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:5-8,2,3,6,N,23,5,"Upon the sea, their confidence,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:5-8,2,3,6,Y,24,5,"O Lord, will place in thee."
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:5-8,2,4,7,N,25,6,"Who, being girt with pow'r, sets fast"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:5-8,2,4,7,Y,26,6,by his great strength the hills.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:5-8,2,4,7,N,27,7,"Who noise of seas, noise of their waves,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:5-8,2,4,7,Y,28,7,"and people's tumult, stills."
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:5-8,2,4,8,N,29,8,Those in the utmost parts that dwell
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:5-8,2,4,8,Y,30,8,are at thy signs afraid:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:5-8,2,4,8,N,31,8,Th' outgoings of the morn and ev'n
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:5-8,2,4,8,Y,32,8,by thee are joyful made.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:9-13,3,5,9,N,33,9,"The earth thou visit'st, wat'ring it;"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:9-13,3,5,9,Y,34,9,thou mak'st it rich to grow
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:9-13,3,5,9,N,35,9,"With God's full flood; thou corn prepar'st,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:9-13,3,5,9,Y,36,9,when thou provid'st it so.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:9-13,3,5,10,N,37,10,"Her rigs thou wat'rest plenteously,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:9-13,3,5,10,Y,38,10,her furrows settelest:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:9-13,3,5,10,N,39,10,"With show'rs thou dost her mollify,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:9-13,3,5,10,Y,40,10,her spring by thee is blest.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:9-13,3,6,11,N,41,11,So thou the year most lib'rally
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:9-13,3,6,11,Y,42,11,dost with thy goodness crown;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:9-13,3,6,11,N,43,11,And all thy paths abundantly
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:9-13,3,6,11,Y,44,11,on us drop fatness down.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:9-13,3,6,12,N,45,12,"They drop upon the pastures wide,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:9-13,3,6,12,Y,46,12,that do in deserts lie;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:9-13,3,6,12,N,47,12,The little hills on ev'ry side
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:9-13,3,6,12,Y,48,12,rejoice right pleasantly.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:9-13,3,7,13,N,49,13,"With flocks the pastures clothed be,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:9-13,3,7,13,Y,50,13,the vales with corn are clad;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:9-13,3,7,13,N,51,13,"And now they shout and sing to thee,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),65,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 65:9-13,3,7,13,Y,52,13,for thou hast made them glad.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:1-5,1,1,1,N,1,1,"All lands to God in joyful sounds,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:1-5,1,1,1,Y,2,1,aloft your voices raise.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:1-5,1,1,1,N,3,2,"Sing forth the honour of his name,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:1-5,1,1,1,Y,4,2,and glorious make his praise.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:1-5,1,1,2,N,5,3,"Say unto God, How terrible"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:1-5,1,1,2,Y,6,3,in all thy works art thou!
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:1-5,1,1,2,N,7,3,Through thy great pow'r thy foes to thee
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:1-5,1,1,2,Y,8,3,shall be constrain'd to bow.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:1-5,1,2,3,N,9,4,"All on the earth shall worship thee,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:1-5,1,2,3,Y,10,4,they shall thy praise proclaim
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:1-5,1,2,3,N,11,4,In songs: they shall sing cheerfully
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:1-5,1,2,3,Y,12,4,unto thy holy name.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:1-5,1,2,4,N,13,5,"Come, and the works that God hath wrought"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:1-5,1,2,4,Y,14,5,with admiration see:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:1-5,1,2,4,N,15,5,In's working to the sons of men
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:1-5,1,2,4,Y,16,5,most terrible is he.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:6-9,2,3,5,N,17,6,"Into dry land the sea he turn'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:6-9,2,3,5,Y,18,6,and they a passage had;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:6-9,2,3,5,N,19,6,"Ev'n marching through the flood on foot,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:6-9,2,3,5,Y,20,6,there we in him were glad.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:6-9,2,3,6,N,21,7,He ruleth ever by his pow'r;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:6-9,2,3,6,Y,22,7,his eyes the nations see:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:6-9,2,3,6,N,23,7,O let not the rebellious ones
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:6-9,2,3,6,Y,24,7,lift up themselves on high.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:6-9,2,4,7,N,25,8,"Ye people, bless our God; aloud"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:6-9,2,4,7,Y,26,8,the voice speak of his praise:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:6-9,2,4,7,N,27,9,"Our soul in life who safe preserves,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:6-9,2,4,7,Y,28,9,our foot from sliding stays.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:10-15,3,4,8,N,29,10,"For thou didst prove and try us, Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:10-15,3,4,8,Y,30,10,as men do silver try;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:10-15,3,4,8,N,31,11,"Brought'st us into the net, and mad'st"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:10-15,3,4,8,Y,32,11,bands on our loins to lie.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:10-15,3,5,9,N,33,12,Thou hast caus'd men ride o'er our heads;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:10-15,3,5,9,Y,34,12,and though that we did pass
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:10-15,3,5,9,N,35,12,"Through fire and water, yet thou brought'st"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:10-15,3,5,9,Y,36,12,us to a wealthy place.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:10-15,3,5,10,N,37,13,I'll bring burnt off 'rings to thy house;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:10-15,3,5,10,Y,38,13,"to thee my vows I'll pay,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:10-15,3,5,10,N,39,14,"Which my lips utter'd, my mouth spake,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:10-15,3,5,10,Y,40,14,when trouble on me lay.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:10-15,3,6,11,N,41,15,Burnt-sacrifices of fat rams
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:10-15,3,6,11,Y,42,15,with incense I will bring;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:10-15,3,6,11,N,43,15,Of bullocks and of goats I will
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:10-15,3,6,11,Y,44,15,present an offering.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:16-20,4,6,12,N,45,16,"All that fear God, come, hear, I'll tell"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:16-20,4,6,12,Y,46,16,what he did for my soul.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:16-20,4,6,12,N,47,17,"I with my mouth unto him cry'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:16-20,4,6,12,Y,48,17,my tongue did him extol.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:16-20,4,7,13,N,49,18,"If in my heart I sin regard,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:16-20,4,7,13,Y,50,18,the Lord me will not hear:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:16-20,4,7,13,N,51,19,"But surely God me heard, and to"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:16-20,4,7,13,Y,52,19,my prayer's voice gave ear.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:16-20,4,7,14,N,53,20,"O let the Lord, our gracious God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:16-20,4,7,14,Y,54,20,"for ever blessed be,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:16-20,4,7,14,N,55,20,"Who turned not my pray'r from him,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),66,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 66:16-20,4,7,14,Y,56,20,nor yet his grace from me.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),67,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 67:1-7 I,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Lord, bless and pity us,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),67,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 67:1-7 I,1,1,1,Y,2,1,shine on us with thy face:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),67,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 67:1-7 I,1,1,1,N,3,2,"That th' earth thy way, and nations all"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),67,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 67:1-7 I,1,1,1,Y,4,2,may know thy saving grace.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),67,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 67:1-7 I,1,1,2,N,5,3,"Let people praise thee, Lord;"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),67,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 67:1-7 I,1,1,2,Y,6,3,let people all thee praise.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),67,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 67:1-7 I,1,1,2,N,7,4,"O let the nations be glad,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),67,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 67:1-7 I,1,1,2,Y,8,4,in songs their voices raise:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),67,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 67:1-7 I,1,2,3,N,9,4,"Thou'lt justly people judge,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),67,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 67:1-7 I,1,2,3,Y,10,4,on earth rule nations all.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),67,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 67:1-7 I,1,2,3,N,11,5,"Let people praise thee, Lord; let them"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),67,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 67:1-7 I,1,2,3,Y,12,5,"praise thee, both great and small."
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),67,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 67:1-7 I,1,2,4,N,13,6,"The earth her fruit shall yield,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),67,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 67:1-7 I,1,2,4,Y,14,6,our God shall blessing send.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),67,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 67:1-7 I,1,2,4,N,15,7,God shall us bless; men shall him fear
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),67,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 67:1-7 I,1,2,4,Y,16,7,unto earth's utmost end.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),67,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 67:1-7 II,1,2,1,N,1,1,"Lord, unto us be merciful,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),67,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 67:1-7 II,1,2,1,Y,2,1,do thou us also bless;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),67,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 67:1-7 II,1,2,1,N,3,1,And graciously cause shine on us
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),67,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 67:1-7 II,1,2,1,Y,4,1,the brightness of thy face:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),67,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 67:1-7 II,1,2,2,N,5,2,That so thy way upon the earth
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),67,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 67:1-7 II,1,2,2,Y,6,2,to all men may be known;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),67,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 67:1-7 II,1,2,2,N,7,2,Also among the nations all
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),67,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 67:1-7 II,1,2,2,Y,8,2,thy saving health be shown.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),67,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 67:1-7 II,1,3,3,N,9,3,"O let the people praise thee, Lord;"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),67,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 67:1-7 II,1,3,3,Y,10,3,let people all thee praise.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),67,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 67:1-7 II,1,3,3,N,11,4,"O let the nations be glad,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),67,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 67:1-7 II,1,3,3,Y,12,4,and sing for joy always:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),67,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 67:1-7 II,1,3,4,N,13,4,"For rightly thou shalt people judge,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),67,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 67:1-7 II,1,3,4,Y,14,4,and nations rule on earth.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),67,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 67:1-7 II,1,3,4,N,15,5,"Let people praise thee, Lord; let all"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),67,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 67:1-7 II,1,3,4,Y,16,5,the folk praise thee with mirth.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),67,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 67:1-7 II,1,4,5,N,17,6,Then shall the earth yield her increase;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),67,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 67:1-7 II,1,4,5,Y,18,6,"God, our God, bless us shall."
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),67,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 67:1-7 II,1,4,5,N,19,7,God shall us bless; and of the earth
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),67,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 67:1-7 II,1,4,5,Y,20,7,the ends shall fear him all.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:1-4,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Let God arise, and scattered"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:1-4,1,1,1,Y,2,1,let all his en'mies be;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:1-4,1,1,1,N,3,1,And let all those that do him hate
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:1-4,1,1,1,Y,4,1,before his presence flee.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:1-4,1,1,2,N,5,2,"As smoke is driv'n, so drive thou them;"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:1-4,1,1,2,Y,6,2,"as fire melts wax away,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:1-4,1,1,2,N,7,2,Before God's face let wicked men
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:1-4,1,1,2,Y,8,2,so perish and decay.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:1-4,1,2,3,N,9,3,But let the righteous be glad:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:1-4,1,2,3,Y,10,3,let them before God's sight
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:1-4,1,2,3,N,11,3,"Be very joyful; yea, let them"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:1-4,1,2,3,Y,12,3,rejoice with all their might.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:1-4,1,2,4,N,13,4,"To God sing, to his name sing praise;"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:1-4,1,2,4,Y,14,4,"extol him with your voice,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:1-4,1,2,4,N,15,4,"That rides on heav'n, by his name Jah,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:1-4,1,2,4,Y,16,4,before his face rejoice.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:5-8,2,3,5,N,17,5,Because the Lord a father is
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:5-8,2,3,5,Y,18,5,unto the fatherless;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:5-8,2,3,5,N,19,5,"God is the widow's judge, within"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:5-8,2,3,5,Y,20,5,his place of holiness.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:5-8,2,3,6,N,21,6,God doth the solitary set
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:5-8,2,3,6,Y,22,6,in fam'lies: and from bands
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:5-8,2,3,6,N,23,6,The chain'd doth free; but rebels do
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:5-8,2,3,6,Y,24,6,inhabit parched lands.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:5-8,2,4,7,N,25,7,"O God, what time thou didst go forth"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:5-8,2,4,7,Y,26,7,before thy people's face;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:5-8,2,4,7,N,27,7,And when through the great wilderness
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:5-8,2,4,7,Y,28,7,thy glorious marching was;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:5-8,2,4,8,N,29,8,"Then at God's presence shook the earth,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:5-8,2,4,8,Y,30,8,then drops from heaven fell;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:5-8,2,4,8,N,31,8,"This Sinai shook before the Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:5-8,2,4,8,Y,32,8,the God of Israel.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:9-12,3,5,9,N,33,9,"O God, thou to thine heritage"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:9-12,3,5,9,Y,34,9,"didst send a plenteous rain,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:9-12,3,5,9,N,35,9,"Whereby thou, when it weary was,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:9-12,3,5,9,Y,36,9,didst it refresh again.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:9-12,3,5,10,N,37,10,Thy congregation then did make
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:9-12,3,5,10,Y,38,10,their habitation there:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:9-12,3,5,10,N,39,10,"Of thine own goodness for the poor,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:9-12,3,5,10,Y,40,10,"O God, thou didst prepare."
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:9-12,3,6,11,N,41,11,"The Lord himself did give the word,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:9-12,3,6,11,Y,42,11,the word abroad did spread;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:9-12,3,6,11,N,43,11,Great was the company of them
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:9-12,3,6,11,Y,44,11,the same who published.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:9-12,3,6,12,N,45,12,"Kings of great armies foiled were,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:9-12,3,6,12,Y,46,12,and forc'd to flee away;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:9-12,3,6,12,N,47,12,"And women, who remain'd at home,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:9-12,3,6,12,Y,48,12,did distribute the prey.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:13-17,4,7,13,N,49,13,"Though ye have lien among the pots,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:13-17,4,7,13,Y,50,13,"like doves ye shall appear,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:13-17,4,7,13,N,51,13,"Whose wings with silver, and with gold"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:13-17,4,7,13,Y,52,13,whose feathers cover'd are.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:13-17,4,7,14,N,53,14,"When there th' Almighty scatter'd kings,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:13-17,4,7,14,Y,54,14,like Salmon's snow 'twas white.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:13-17,4,7,14,N,55,15,"God's hill is like to Bashan hill,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:13-17,4,7,14,Y,56,15,like Bashan hill for height.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:13-17,4,8,15,N,57,16,"Why do ye leap, ye mountains high?"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:13-17,4,8,15,Y,58,16,this is the hill where God
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:13-17,4,8,15,N,59,16,"Desires to dwell; yea, God in it"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:13-17,4,8,15,Y,60,16,for aye will make abode.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:13-17,4,8,16,N,61,17,"God's chariots twenty thousand are,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:13-17,4,8,16,Y,62,17,thousands of angels strong;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:13-17,4,8,16,N,63,17,"In's holy place God is, as in"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:13-17,4,8,16,Y,64,17,"mount Sinai, them among."
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:18-19,5,9,17,N,65,18,"Thou hast, O Lord, most glorious,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:18-19,5,9,17,Y,66,18,ascended up on high;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:18-19,5,9,17,N,67,18,And in triumph victorious led
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:18-19,5,9,17,Y,68,18,captive captivity:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:18-19,5,9,18,N,69,18,"Thou hast received gifts for men,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:18-19,5,9,18,Y,70,18,for such as did rebel;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:18-19,5,9,18,N,71,18,"Yea, ev'n for them, that God the Lord"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:18-19,5,9,18,Y,72,18,in midst of them might dwell.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:18-19,5,10,19,N,73,19,"Bless'd be the Lord, who is to us"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:18-19,5,10,19,Y,74,19,of our salvation God;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:18-19,5,10,19,N,75,19,Who daily with his benefits
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:18-19,5,10,19,Y,76,19,us plenteously doth load.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:20-23,6,10,20,N,77,20,"He of salvation is the God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:20-23,6,10,20,Y,78,20,who is our God most strong;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:20-23,6,10,20,N,79,20,And unto God the Lord from death
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:20-23,6,10,20,Y,80,20,the issues do belong.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:20-23,6,11,21,N,81,21,But surely God shall wound the head
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:20-23,6,11,21,Y,82,21,of those that are his foes;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:20-23,6,11,21,N,83,21,The hairy scalp of him that still
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:20-23,6,11,21,Y,84,21,on in his trespass goes.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:20-23,6,11,22,N,85,22,"God said, My people I will bring"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:20-23,6,11,22,Y,86,22,again from Bashan hill;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:20-23,6,11,22,N,87,22,"Yea, from the sea's devouring depths"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:20-23,6,11,22,Y,88,22,them bring again I will;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:20-23,6,12,23,N,89,23,That in the blood of enemies
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:20-23,6,12,23,Y,90,23,"thy foot imbru'd may be,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:20-23,6,12,23,N,91,23,And of thy dogs dipp'd in the same
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:20-23,6,12,23,Y,92,23,the tongues thou mayest see.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:24-27,7,12,24,N,93,24,"Thy goings they have seen, O God;"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:24-27,7,12,24,Y,94,24,the steps of majesty
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:24-27,7,12,24,N,95,24,"Of my God, and my mighty King,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:24-27,7,12,24,Y,96,24,within the sanctuary.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:24-27,7,13,25,N,97,25,"Before went singers, players next"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:24-27,7,13,25,Y,98,25,on instruments took way;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:24-27,7,13,25,N,99,25,And them among the damsels were
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:24-27,7,13,25,Y,100,25,that did on timbrels play.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:24-27,7,13,26,N,101,26,Within the congregations
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:24-27,7,13,26,Y,102,26,bless God with one accord:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:24-27,7,13,26,N,103,26,From Isr'el's fountain do ye bless
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:24-27,7,13,26,Y,104,26,and praise the mighty Lord.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:24-27,7,14,27,N,105,27,"With their prince, little Benjamin,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:24-27,7,14,27,Y,106,27,princes and council there
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:24-27,7,14,27,N,107,27,"Of Judah were, there Zabulon's"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:24-27,7,14,27,Y,108,27,and Napht'li's princes were.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:28-31,8,14,28,N,109,28,Thy God commands thy strength; make strong
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:28-31,8,14,28,Y,110,28,"what thou wrought'st for us, Lord."
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:28-31,8,14,28,N,111,29,For thy house at Jerusalem
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:28-31,8,14,28,Y,112,29,kings shall thee gifts afford.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:28-31,8,15,29,N,113,30,"The spearmen's host, the multitude"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:28-31,8,15,29,Y,114,30,"of bulls, which fiercely look,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:28-31,8,15,29,N,115,30,"Those calves which people have forth sent,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:28-31,8,15,29,Y,116,30,"O Lord our God, rebuke,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:28-31,8,15,30,N,117,30,"Till ev'ry one submit himself,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:28-31,8,15,30,Y,118,30,and silver pieces bring:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:28-31,8,15,30,N,119,30,The people that delight in war
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:28-31,8,15,30,Y,120,30,"disperse, O God and King."
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:28-31,8,16,31,N,121,31,Those that be princes great shall then
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:28-31,8,16,31,Y,122,31,come out of Egypt lands;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:28-31,8,16,31,N,123,31,And Ethiopia to God
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:28-31,8,16,31,Y,124,31,shall soon stretch out her hands.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:32-35,9,16,32,N,125,32,"O all ye kingdoms of the earth,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:32-35,9,16,32,Y,126,32,sing praises to this King;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:32-35,9,16,32,N,127,32,"For he is Lord that ruleth all,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:32-35,9,16,32,Y,128,32,unto him praises sing.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:32-35,9,17,33,N,129,33,"To him that rides on heav'ns of heav'ns,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:32-35,9,17,33,Y,130,33,which he of old did found;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:32-35,9,17,33,N,131,33,"Lo, he sends out his voice, a voice"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:32-35,9,17,33,Y,132,33,in might that doth abound.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:32-35,9,17,34,N,133,34,Strength unto God do ye ascribe;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:32-35,9,17,34,Y,134,34,for his excellency
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:32-35,9,17,34,N,135,34,"Is over Israel, his strength"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:32-35,9,17,34,Y,136,34,is in the clouds most high.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:32-35,9,18,35,N,137,35,"Thou'rt from thy temple dreadful, Lord;"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:32-35,9,18,35,Y,138,35,"Isr'el's own God is he,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:32-35,9,18,35,N,139,35,Who gives his people strength and pow'r:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),68,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 68:32-35,9,18,35,Y,140,35,O let God blessed be.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:1-3,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Save me, O God, because the floods"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:1-3,1,1,1,Y,2,1,"do so environ me,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:1-3,1,1,1,N,3,1,That ev'n unto my very soul
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:1-3,1,1,1,Y,4,1,come in the waters be.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:1-3,1,1,2,N,5,2,"I downward in deep mire do sink,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:1-3,1,1,2,Y,6,2,where standing there is none:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:1-3,1,1,2,N,7,2,"I am into deep waters come,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:1-3,1,1,2,Y,8,2,where floods have o'er me gone.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:1-3,1,2,3,N,9,3,"I weary with my crying am,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:1-3,1,2,3,Y,10,3,my throat is also dry'd;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:1-3,1,2,3,N,11,3,"Mine eyes do fail, while for my God"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:1-3,1,2,3,Y,12,3,I waiting do abide.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:4-6,2,2,4,N,13,4,Those men that do without a cause
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:4-6,2,2,4,Y,14,4,"bear hatred unto me,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:4-6,2,2,4,N,15,4,Than are the hairs upon my head
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:4-6,2,2,4,Y,16,4,in number more they be:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:4-6,2,3,5,N,17,4,"They that would me destroy, and are"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:4-6,2,3,5,Y,18,4,"mine en'mies wrongfully,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:4-6,2,3,5,N,19,4,"Are mighty: so what I took not,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:4-6,2,3,5,Y,20,4,to render forc'd was I.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:4-6,2,3,6,N,21,5,"Lord, thou my folly know'st, my sins"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:4-6,2,3,6,Y,22,5,not cover'd are from thee.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:4-6,2,3,6,N,23,6,"Let none that wait on thee be sham'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:4-6,2,3,6,Y,24,6,"Lord God of hosts, for me."
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:4-6,2,4,7,N,25,6,"O Lord, the God of Israel,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:4-6,2,4,7,Y,26,6,"let none, who search do make,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:4-6,2,4,7,N,27,6,"And seek thee, be at any time"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:4-6,2,4,7,Y,28,6,confounded for my sake.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:7-12,3,4,8,N,29,7,"For I have borne reproach for thee,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:7-12,3,4,8,Y,30,7,my face is hid with shame.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:7-12,3,4,8,N,31,8,"To brethren strange, to mother's sons"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:7-12,3,4,8,Y,32,8,an alien I became.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:7-12,3,5,9,N,33,9,"Because the zeal did eat me up,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:7-12,3,5,9,Y,34,9,which to thine house I bear;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:7-12,3,5,9,N,35,9,"And the reproaches cast at thee,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:7-12,3,5,9,Y,36,9,upon me fallen are.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:7-12,3,5,10,N,37,10,"My tears and fasts, t' afflict my soul,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:7-12,3,5,10,Y,38,10,were turned to my shame.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:7-12,3,5,10,N,39,11,"When sackcloth I did wear, to them"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:7-12,3,5,10,Y,40,11,a proverb I became.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:7-12,3,6,11,N,41,12,The men that in the gate do sit
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:7-12,3,6,11,Y,42,12,against me evil spake;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:7-12,3,6,11,N,43,12,They also that vile drunkards were
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:7-12,3,6,11,Y,44,12,of me their song did make.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:13-18,4,6,12,N,45,13,"But, in an acceptable time,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:13-18,4,6,12,Y,46,13,"my pray'r, Lord, is to thee:"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:13-18,4,6,12,N,47,13,"In truth of thy salvation, Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:13-18,4,6,12,Y,48,13,"and mercy great, hear me."
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:13-18,4,7,13,N,49,14,"Deliver me out of the mire,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:13-18,4,7,13,Y,50,14,from sinking do me keep;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:13-18,4,7,13,N,51,14,"Free me from those that do me hate,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:13-18,4,7,13,Y,52,14,and from the waters deep.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:13-18,4,7,14,N,53,15,"Let not the flood on me prevail,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:13-18,4,7,14,Y,54,15,whose water overflows;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:13-18,4,7,14,N,55,15,"Nor deep me swallow, nor the pit"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:13-18,4,7,14,Y,56,15,her mouth upon me close.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:13-18,4,8,15,N,57,16,"Hear me, O Lord, because thy love"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:13-18,4,8,15,Y,58,16,and kindness is most good;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:13-18,4,8,15,N,59,16,"Turn unto me, according to"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:13-18,4,8,15,Y,60,16,thy mercies' multitude.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:13-18,4,8,16,N,61,17,Nor from thy servant hide thy face:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:13-18,4,8,16,Y,62,17,"I'm troubled, soon attend."
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:13-18,4,8,16,N,63,18,"Draw near my soul, and it redeem;"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:13-18,4,8,16,Y,64,18,me from my foes defend.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:19-21,5,9,17,N,65,19,"To thee is my reproach well known,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:19-21,5,9,17,Y,66,19,"my shame, and my disgrace:"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:19-21,5,9,17,N,67,19,Those that mine adversaries be
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:19-21,5,9,17,Y,68,19,are all before thy face.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:19-21,5,9,18,N,69,20,Reproach hath broke my heart; I'm full
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:19-21,5,9,18,Y,70,20,of grief: I look'd for one
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:19-21,5,9,18,N,71,20,"To pity me, but none I found;"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:19-21,5,9,18,Y,72,20,comforters found I none.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:19-21,5,10,19,N,73,21,They also bitter gall did give
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:19-21,5,10,19,Y,74,21,unto me for my meat:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:19-21,5,10,19,N,75,21,"They gave me vinegar to drink,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:19-21,5,10,19,Y,76,21,when as my thirst was great.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:22-24,6,10,20,N,77,22,Before them let their table prove
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:22-24,6,10,20,Y,78,22,a snare; and do thou make
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:22-24,6,10,20,N,79,22,Their welfare and prosperity
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:22-24,6,10,20,Y,80,22,a trap themselves to take.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:22-24,6,11,21,N,81,23,"Let thou their eyes so darken'd be,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:22-24,6,11,21,Y,82,23,that sight may them forsake;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:22-24,6,11,21,N,83,23,And let their loins be made by thee
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:22-24,6,11,21,Y,84,23,continually to shake.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:22-24,6,11,22,N,85,24,"Thy fury pour thou out on them,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:22-24,6,11,22,Y,86,24,and indignation;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:22-24,6,11,22,N,87,24,"And let thy wrathful anger, Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:22-24,6,11,22,Y,88,24,fast hold take them upon.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:25-28,7,12,23,N,89,25,All waste and desolate let be
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:25-28,7,12,23,Y,90,25,their habitation;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:25-28,7,12,23,N,91,25,And in their tabernacles all
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:25-28,7,12,23,Y,92,25,inhabitants be none.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:25-28,7,12,24,N,93,26,"Because him they do persecute,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:25-28,7,12,24,Y,94,26,whom thou didst smite before;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:25-28,7,12,24,N,95,26,They talk unto the grief of those
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:25-28,7,12,24,Y,96,26,whom thou hast wounded sore.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:25-28,7,13,25,N,97,27,Add thou iniquity unto
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:25-28,7,13,25,Y,98,27,their former wickedness;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:25-28,7,13,25,N,99,27,And do not let them come at all
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:25-28,7,13,25,Y,100,27,into thy righteousness.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:25-28,7,13,26,N,101,28,Out of the book of life let them
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:25-28,7,13,26,Y,102,28,be raz'd and blotted quite;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:25-28,7,13,26,N,103,28,Among the just and righteous
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:25-28,7,13,26,Y,104,28,let not their names be writ.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:29-32,8,14,27,N,105,29,But now become exceeding poor
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:29-32,8,14,27,Y,106,29,and sorrowful am I:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:29-32,8,14,27,N,107,29,"By thy salvation, O my God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:29-32,8,14,27,Y,108,29,let me be set on high.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:29-32,8,14,28,N,109,30,The name of God I with a song
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:29-32,8,14,28,Y,110,30,most cheerfully will praise;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:29-32,8,14,28,N,111,30,"And I, in giving thanks to him,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:29-32,8,14,28,Y,112,30,his name shall highly raise.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:29-32,8,15,29,N,113,31,This to the Lord a sacrifice
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:29-32,8,15,29,Y,114,31,more gracious shall prove
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:29-32,8,15,29,N,115,31,"Than bullock, ox, or any beast"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:29-32,8,15,29,Y,116,31,that hath both horn and hoof.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:29-32,8,15,30,N,117,32,"When this the humble men shall see,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:29-32,8,15,30,Y,118,32,it joy to them shall give:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:29-32,8,15,30,N,119,32,"O all ye that do seek the Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:29-32,8,15,30,Y,120,32,your hearts shall ever live.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:33-36,9,16,31,N,121,33,"For God the poor hears, and will not"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:33-36,9,16,31,Y,122,33,his prisoners contemn.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:33-36,9,16,31,N,123,34,"Let heav'n, and earth, and seas, him praise,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:33-36,9,16,31,Y,124,34,and all that move in them.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:33-36,9,16,32,N,125,35,"For God will Judah's cities build,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:33-36,9,16,32,Y,126,35,"and he will Sion save,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:33-36,9,16,32,N,127,35,"That they may dwell therein, and it"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:33-36,9,16,32,Y,128,35,in sure possession have.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:33-36,9,17,33,N,129,36,And they that are his servants' seed
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:33-36,9,17,33,Y,130,36,inherit shall the same;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:33-36,9,17,33,N,131,36,So shall they have their dwelling there
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),69,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 69:33-36,9,17,33,Y,132,36,that love his blessed name.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),70,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 70:1-5 I,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Lord, haste me to deliver;"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),70,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 70:1-5 I,1,1,1,Y,2,1,"with speed, Lord, succour me."
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),70,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 70:1-5 I,1,1,1,N,3,2,Let them that for my soul do seek
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),70,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 70:1-5 I,1,1,1,Y,4,2,sham'd and confounded be:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),70,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 70:1-5 I,1,1,2,N,5,2,"Turn'd back be they, and sham'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),70,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 70:1-5 I,1,1,2,Y,6,2,that in my hurt delight.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),70,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 70:1-5 I,1,1,2,N,7,3,"Turn'd back be they, Ha, ha! that say,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),70,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 70:1-5 I,1,1,2,Y,8,3,their shaming to requite.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),70,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 70:1-5 I,1,2,3,N,9,4,"In thee let all be glad,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),70,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 70:1-5 I,1,2,3,Y,10,4,and joy that seek for thee:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),70,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 70:1-5 I,1,2,3,N,11,4,Let them who thy salvation love
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),70,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 70:1-5 I,1,2,3,Y,12,4,"say still, God praised be."
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),70,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 70:1-5 I,1,2,4,N,13,5,I poor and needy am;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),70,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 70:1-5 I,1,2,4,Y,14,5,"come, Lord, and make no stay:"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),70,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 70:1-5 I,1,2,4,N,15,5,My help thou and deliv'rer art;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),70,First,"6,6,8,6",Ps. 70:1-5 I,1,2,4,Y,16,5,"O Lord, make no delay."
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),70,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 70:1-5 II,1,2,1,N,1,1,"Make haste, O God, me to preserve;"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),70,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 70:1-5 II,1,2,1,Y,2,1,"with speed, Lord, succour me."
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),70,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 70:1-5 II,1,2,1,N,3,2,Let them that for my soul do seek
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),70,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 70:1-5 II,1,2,1,Y,4,2,sham'd and confounded be:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),70,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 70:1-5 II,1,2,2,N,5,2,"Let them be turned back, and sham'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),70,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 70:1-5 II,1,2,2,Y,6,2,that in my hurt delight.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),70,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 70:1-5 II,1,2,2,N,7,3,"Turn'd back be they, Ha, ha! that say,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),70,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 70:1-5 II,1,2,2,Y,8,3,their shaming to requite.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),70,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 70:1-5 II,1,3,3,N,9,4,"O Lord, in thee let all be glad,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),70,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 70:1-5 II,1,3,3,Y,10,4,and joy that seek for thee:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),70,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 70:1-5 II,1,3,3,N,11,4,Let them who thy salvation love
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),70,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 70:1-5 II,1,3,3,Y,12,4,"say still, God praised be."
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),70,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 70:1-5 II,1,3,4,N,13,5,But I both poor and needy am;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),70,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 70:1-5 II,1,3,4,Y,14,5,"come, Lord, and make no stay:"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),70,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 70:1-5 II,1,3,4,N,15,5,My help thou and deliv'rer art;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),70,Second,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 70:1-5 II,1,3,4,Y,16,5,"O Lord, make no delay."
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:1-6,1,1,1,N,1,1,"O Lord, my hope and confidence"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:1-6,1,1,1,Y,2,1,is plac'd in thee alone;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:1-6,1,1,1,N,3,1,Then let thy servant never be
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:1-6,1,1,1,Y,4,1,put to confusion.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:1-6,1,1,2,N,5,2,"And let me, in thy righteousness,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:1-6,1,1,2,Y,6,2,from thee deliv'rance have;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:1-6,1,1,2,N,7,2,"Cause me escape, incline thine ear"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:1-6,1,1,2,Y,8,2,"unto me, and me save."
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:1-6,1,2,3,N,9,3,"Be thou my dwelling-rock, to which"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:1-6,1,2,3,Y,10,3,I ever may resort:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:1-6,1,2,3,N,11,3,"Thou gav'st commandment me to save,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:1-6,1,2,3,Y,12,3,for thou'rt my rock and fort.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:1-6,1,2,4,N,13,4,"Free me, my God, from wicked hands,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:1-6,1,2,4,Y,14,4,hands cruel and unjust:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:1-6,1,2,4,N,15,5,"For thou, O Lord God, art my hope,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:1-6,1,2,4,Y,16,5,and from my youth my trust.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:1-6,1,3,5,N,17,6,Thou from the womb didst hold me up;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:1-6,1,3,5,Y,18,6,thou art the same that me
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:1-6,1,3,5,N,19,6,Out of my mother's bowels took;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:1-6,1,3,5,Y,20,6,I ever will praise thee.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:7-13,2,3,6,N,21,7,To many I a wonder am;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:7-13,2,3,6,Y,22,7,but thou'rt my refuge strong.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:7-13,2,3,6,N,23,8,Fill'd let my mouth be with thy praise
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:7-13,2,3,6,Y,24,8,and honour all day long.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:7-13,2,4,7,N,25,9,"O do not cast me off, when as"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:7-13,2,4,7,Y,26,9,old age doth overtake me;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:7-13,2,4,7,N,27,9,"And when my strength decayed is,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:7-13,2,4,7,Y,28,9,then do not thou forsake me.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:7-13,2,4,8,N,29,10,For those that are mine enemies
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:7-13,2,4,8,Y,30,10,against me speak with hate;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:7-13,2,4,8,N,31,10,And they together counsel take
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:7-13,2,4,8,Y,32,10,that for my soul lay wait.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:7-13,2,5,9,N,33,11,"They said, God leaves him; him pursue"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:7-13,2,5,9,Y,34,11,and take: none will him save.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:7-13,2,5,9,N,35,12,"Be thou not far from me, my God:"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:7-13,2,5,9,Y,36,12,thy speedy help I crave.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:7-13,2,5,10,N,37,13,"Confound, consume them, that unto"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:7-13,2,5,10,Y,38,13,my soul are enemies:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:7-13,2,5,10,N,39,13,Cloth'd be they with reproach and shame
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:7-13,2,5,10,Y,40,13,that do my hurt devise.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:14-16,3,6,11,N,41,14,But I with expectation
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:14-16,3,6,11,Y,42,14,will hope continually;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:14-16,3,6,11,N,43,14,And yet with praises more and more
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:14-16,3,6,11,Y,44,14,I will thee magnify.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:14-16,3,6,12,N,45,15,Thy justice and salvation
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:14-16,3,6,12,Y,46,15,"my mouth abroad shall show,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:14-16,3,6,12,N,47,15,Ev'n all the day; for I thereof
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:14-16,3,6,12,Y,48,15,the numbers do not know.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:14-16,3,7,13,N,49,16,And I will constantly go on
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:14-16,3,7,13,Y,50,16,in strength of God the Lord;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:14-16,3,7,13,N,51,16,"And thine own righteousness, ev'n thine"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:14-16,3,7,13,Y,52,16,"alone, I will record."
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:17-19,4,7,14,N,53,17,"For even from my youth, O God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:17-19,4,7,14,Y,54,17,by thee I have been taught;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:17-19,4,7,14,N,55,17,And hitherto I have declar'd
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:17-19,4,7,14,Y,56,17,the wonders thou hast wrought.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:17-19,4,8,15,N,57,18,"And now, Lord, leave me not, when I"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:17-19,4,8,15,Y,58,18,old and gray-headed grow:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:17-19,4,8,15,N,59,18,Till to this age thy strength and pow'r
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:17-19,4,8,15,Y,60,18,to all to come I show.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:17-19,4,8,16,N,61,19,And thy most perfect righteousness
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:17-19,4,8,16,Y,62,19,"O Lord, is very high,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:17-19,4,8,16,N,63,19,"Who hast so great things done: O God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:17-19,4,8,16,Y,64,19,who is like unto thee?
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:20-24,5,9,17,N,65,20,"Thou, Lord, who great adversities,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:20-24,5,9,17,Y,66,20,"and sore, to me didst show,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:20-24,5,9,17,N,67,20,"Shalt quicken, and bring me again"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:20-24,5,9,17,Y,68,20,from depths of earth below.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:20-24,5,9,18,N,69,21,My greatness and my pow'r thou wilt
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:20-24,5,9,18,Y,70,21,"increase, and far extend:"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:20-24,5,9,18,N,71,21,On ev'ry side against all grief
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:20-24,5,9,18,Y,72,21,thou wilt me comfort send.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:20-24,5,10,19,N,73,22,"Thee, ev'n thy truth, I'll also praise,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:20-24,5,10,19,Y,74,22,"my God, with psaltery:"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:20-24,5,10,19,N,75,22,"Thou Holy One of Israel,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:20-24,5,10,19,Y,76,22,with harp I'll sing to thee.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:20-24,5,10,20,N,77,23,"My lips shall much rejoice in thee,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:20-24,5,10,20,Y,78,23,when I thy praises sound;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:20-24,5,10,20,N,79,23,"My soul, which thou redeemed hast,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:20-24,5,10,20,Y,80,23,in joy shall much abound.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:20-24,5,11,21,N,81,24,"My tongue thy justice shall proclaim,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:20-24,5,11,21,Y,82,24,continuing all day long;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:20-24,5,11,21,N,83,24,"For they confounded are, and sham'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),71,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 71:20-24,5,11,21,Y,84,24,that seek to do me wrong.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:1-4,1,1,1,N,1,1,"O Lord, thy judgments give the king,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:1-4,1,1,1,Y,2,1,his son thy righteousness.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:1-4,1,1,1,N,3,2,"With right he shall thy people judge,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:1-4,1,1,1,Y,4,2,thy poor with uprightness.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:1-4,1,1,2,N,5,3,The lofty mountains shall bring forth
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:1-4,1,1,2,Y,6,3,unto the people peace;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:1-4,1,1,2,N,7,3,Likewise the little hills the same
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:1-4,1,1,2,Y,8,3,shall do by righteousness.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:1-4,1,2,3,N,9,4,"The people's poor ones he shall judge,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:1-4,1,2,3,Y,10,4,the needy's children save;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:1-4,1,2,3,N,11,4,And those shall he in pieces break
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:1-4,1,2,3,Y,12,4,who them oppressed have.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:5-8,2,2,4,N,13,5,"They shall thee fear, while sun and moon"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:5-8,2,2,4,Y,14,5,"do last, through ages all."
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:5-8,2,2,4,N,15,6,"Like rain on mown grass he shall drop,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:5-8,2,2,4,Y,16,6,or show'rs on earth that fall.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:5-8,2,3,5,N,17,7,"The just shall flourish in his days,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:5-8,2,3,5,Y,18,7,and prosper in his reign:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:5-8,2,3,5,N,19,7,"He shall, while doth the moon endure,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:5-8,2,3,5,Y,20,7,abundant peace maintain.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:5-8,2,3,6,N,21,8,His large and great dominion shall
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:5-8,2,3,6,Y,22,8,from sea to sea extend:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:5-8,2,3,6,N,23,8,It from the river shall reach forth
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:5-8,2,3,6,Y,24,8,unto earth's utmost end.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:9-11,3,4,7,N,25,9,They in the wilderness that dwell
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:9-11,3,4,7,Y,26,9,bow down before him must;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:9-11,3,4,7,N,27,9,And they that are his enemies
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:9-11,3,4,7,Y,28,9,shall lick the very dust.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:9-11,3,4,8,N,29,10,"The kings of Tarshish, and the isles,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:9-11,3,4,8,Y,30,10,to him shall presents bring;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:9-11,3,4,8,N,31,10,And unto him shall offer gifts
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:9-11,3,4,8,Y,32,10,Sheba's and Seba's king.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:9-11,3,5,9,N,33,11,"Yea, all the mighty kings on earth"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:9-11,3,5,9,Y,34,11,before him down shall fall;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:9-11,3,5,9,N,35,11,And all the nations of the world
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:9-11,3,5,9,Y,36,11,do service to him shall.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:12-14,4,5,10,N,37,12,"For he the needy shall preserve,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:12-14,4,5,10,Y,38,12,when he to him doth call;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:12-14,4,5,10,N,39,12,"The poor also, and him that hath"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:12-14,4,5,10,Y,40,12,no help of man at all.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:12-14,4,6,11,N,41,13,The poor man and the indigent
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:12-14,4,6,11,Y,42,13,in mercy he shall spare;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:12-14,4,6,11,N,43,13,He shall preserve alive the souls
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:12-14,4,6,11,Y,44,13,of those that needy are.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:12-14,4,6,12,N,45,14,Both from deceit and violence
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:12-14,4,6,12,Y,46,14,their soul he shall set free;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:12-14,4,6,12,N,47,14,And in his sight right precious
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:12-14,4,6,12,Y,48,14,and dear their blood shall be.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:15-17,5,7,13,N,49,15,"Yea, he shall live, and giv'n to him"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:15-17,5,7,13,Y,50,15,shall be of Sheba's gold:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:15-17,5,7,13,N,51,15,"For him still shall they pray, and he"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:15-17,5,7,13,Y,52,15,shall daily be extoll'd.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:15-17,5,7,14,N,53,16,Of corn an handful in the earth
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:15-17,5,7,14,Y,54,16,"on tops of mountains high,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:15-17,5,7,14,N,55,16,"With prosp'rous fruit shall shake, like trees"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:15-17,5,7,14,Y,56,16,on Lebanon that be.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:15-17,5,8,15,N,57,16,"The city shall be flourishing,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:15-17,5,8,15,Y,58,16,her citizens abound
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:15-17,5,8,15,N,59,16,"In number shall, like to the grass"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:15-17,5,8,15,Y,60,16,that grows upon the ground.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:15-17,5,8,16,N,61,17,His name for ever shall endure;
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:15-17,5,8,16,Y,62,17,last like the sun it shall:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:15-17,5,8,16,N,63,17,"Men shall be bless'd in him, and bless'd"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:15-17,5,8,16,Y,64,17,all nations shall him call.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:18-19,6,9,17,N,65,18,"Now blessed be the Lord our God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:18-19,6,9,17,Y,66,18,"the God of Israel,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:18-19,6,9,17,N,67,18,"For he alone doth wondrous works,"
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:18-19,6,9,17,Y,68,18,in glory that excel.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:18-19,6,9,18,N,69,19,And blessed be his glorious name
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:18-19,6,9,18,Y,70,19,to all eternity:
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:18-19,6,9,18,N,71,19,The whole earth let his glory fill.
1650 Psalter,Book 2 (Psalm 42-72),72,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 72:18-19,6,9,18,Y,72,19,"Amen, so let it be."
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:1-5,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Yet God is good to Israel,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:1-5,1,1,1,Y,2,1,to each pure-hearted one.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:1-5,1,1,1,N,3,2,"But as for me, my steps near slipp'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:1-5,1,1,1,Y,4,2,my feet were almost gone.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:1-5,1,1,2,N,5,3,"For I envious was, and grudg'd"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:1-5,1,1,2,Y,6,3,"the foolish folk to see,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:1-5,1,1,2,N,7,3,When I perceiv'd the wicked sort
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:1-5,1,1,2,Y,8,3,enjoy prosperity.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:1-5,1,2,3,N,9,4,For still their strength continueth firm;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:1-5,1,2,3,Y,10,4,their death of bands is free.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:1-5,1,2,3,N,11,5,"They are not toil'd like other men,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:1-5,1,2,3,Y,12,5,"nor plagu'd, as others be."
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:6-11,2,2,4,N,13,6,"Therefore their pride, like to a chain,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:6-11,2,2,4,Y,14,6,them compasseth about;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:6-11,2,2,4,N,15,6,"And, as a garment, violence"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:6-11,2,2,4,Y,16,6,doth cover them throughout.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:6-11,2,3,5,N,17,7,Their eyes stand out with fat; they have
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:6-11,2,3,5,Y,18,7,more than their hearts could wish.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:6-11,2,3,5,N,19,8,They are corrupt; their talk of wrong
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:6-11,2,3,5,Y,20,8,both lewd and lofty is.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:6-11,2,3,6,N,21,9,They set their mouth against the heav'ns
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:6-11,2,3,6,Y,22,9,in their blasphemous talk;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:6-11,2,3,6,N,23,9,And their reproaching tongue throughout
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:6-11,2,3,6,Y,24,9,the earth at large doth walk.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:6-11,2,4,7,N,25,10,His people oftentimes for this
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:6-11,2,4,7,Y,26,10,"look back, and turn about;"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:6-11,2,4,7,N,27,10,Sith waters of so full a cup
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:6-11,2,4,7,Y,28,10,to these are poured out.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:6-11,2,4,8,N,29,11,"And thus they say, How can it be"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:6-11,2,4,8,Y,30,11,that God these things doth know?
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:6-11,2,4,8,N,31,11,"Or, Can there in the Highest be"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:6-11,2,4,8,Y,32,11,knowledge of things below?
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:12-17,3,5,9,N,33,12,"Behold, these are the wicked ones,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:12-17,3,5,9,Y,34,12,yet prosper at their will
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:12-17,3,5,9,N,35,12,In worldly things; they do increase
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:12-17,3,5,9,Y,36,12,in wealth and riches still.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:12-17,3,5,10,N,37,13,I verily have done in vain
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:12-17,3,5,10,Y,38,13,my heart to purify;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:12-17,3,5,10,N,39,13,To no effect in innocence
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:12-17,3,5,10,Y,40,13,washed my hands have I.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:12-17,3,6,11,N,41,14,"For daily, and all day throughout,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:12-17,3,6,11,Y,42,14,great plagues I suffer'd have;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:12-17,3,6,11,N,43,14,"Yea, ev'ry morning I of new"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:12-17,3,6,11,Y,44,14,did chastisement receive.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:12-17,3,6,12,N,45,15,If in this manner foolishly
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:12-17,3,6,12,Y,46,15,"to speak I would intend,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:12-17,3,6,12,N,47,15,"Thy children's generation,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:12-17,3,6,12,Y,48,15,"behold, I should offend."
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:12-17,3,7,13,N,49,16,"When I this thought to know, it was"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:12-17,3,7,13,Y,50,16,too hard a thing for me;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:12-17,3,7,13,N,51,17,"Till to God's sanctuary I went,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:12-17,3,7,13,Y,52,17,then I their end did see.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:18-22,4,7,14,N,53,18,Assuredly thou didst them set
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:18-22,4,7,14,Y,54,18,a slipp'ry place upon;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:18-22,4,7,14,N,55,18,Them suddenly thou castedst down
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:18-22,4,7,14,Y,56,18,into destruction.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:18-22,4,8,15,N,57,19,How in a moment suddenly
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:18-22,4,8,15,Y,58,19,to ruin brought are they!
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:18-22,4,8,15,N,59,19,With fearful terrors utterly
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:18-22,4,8,15,Y,60,19,they are consum'd away.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:18-22,4,8,16,N,61,20,"Ev'n like unto a dream, when one"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:18-22,4,8,16,Y,62,20,from sleeping doth arise;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:18-22,4,8,16,N,63,20,"So thou, O Lord, when thou awak'st,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:18-22,4,8,16,Y,64,20,their image shalt despise.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:18-22,4,9,17,N,65,21,"Thus grieved was my heart in me,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:18-22,4,9,17,Y,66,21,and me my reins opprest:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:18-22,4,9,17,N,67,22,"So rude was I, and ignorant,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:18-22,4,9,17,Y,68,22,and in thy sight a beast.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:23-25,5,9,18,N,69,23,"Nevertheless continually,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:23-25,5,9,18,Y,70,23,"O Lord, I am with thee:"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:23-25,5,9,18,N,71,23,"Thou dost me hold by my right hand,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:23-25,5,9,18,Y,72,23,and still upholdest me.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:23-25,5,10,19,N,73,24,"Thou, with thy counsel, while I live,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:23-25,5,10,19,Y,74,24,wilt me conduct and guide;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:23-25,5,10,19,N,75,24,And to thy glory afterward
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:23-25,5,10,19,Y,76,24,receive me to abide.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:23-25,5,10,20,N,77,25,Whom have I in the heavens high
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:23-25,5,10,20,Y,78,25,"but thee, O Lord, alone?"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:23-25,5,10,20,N,79,25,And in the earth whom I desire
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:23-25,5,10,20,Y,80,25,besides thee there is none.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:26-28,6,11,21,N,81,26,"My flesh and heart doth faint and fail,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:26-28,6,11,21,Y,82,26,but God doth fail me never:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:26-28,6,11,21,N,83,26,For of my heart God is the strength
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:26-28,6,11,21,Y,84,26,and portion for ever.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:26-28,6,11,22,N,85,27,"For, lo, they that are far from thee"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:26-28,6,11,22,Y,86,27,for ever perish shall;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:26-28,6,11,22,N,87,27,Them that a whoring from thee go
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:26-28,6,11,22,Y,88,27,thou hast destroyed all.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:26-28,6,12,23,N,89,28,But surely it is good for me
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:26-28,6,12,23,Y,90,28,that I draw near to God:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:26-28,6,12,23,N,91,28,"In God I trust, that all thy works"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),73,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 73:26-28,6,12,23,Y,92,28,I may declare abroad.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:1-3,1,1,1,N,1,1,"O God, why hast thou cast us off?"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:1-3,1,1,1,Y,2,1,is it for evermore?
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:1-3,1,1,1,N,3,1,Against thy pasture-sheep why doth
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:1-3,1,1,1,Y,4,1,thine anger smoke so sore?
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:1-3,1,1,2,N,5,2,O call to thy rememberance
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:1-3,1,1,2,Y,6,2,"thy congregation,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:1-3,1,1,2,N,7,2,Which thou hast purchased of old;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:1-3,1,1,2,Y,8,2,still think the same upon:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:1-3,1,2,3,N,9,2,"The rod of thine inheritance,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:1-3,1,2,3,Y,10,2,"which thou redeemed hast,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:1-3,1,2,3,N,11,2,"This Sion hill, wherein thou hadst"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:1-3,1,2,3,Y,12,2,thy dwelling in times past.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:1-3,1,2,4,N,13,3,To these long desolations
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:1-3,1,2,4,Y,14,3,"thy feet lift, do not tarry;"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:1-3,1,2,4,N,15,3,For all the ills thy foes have done
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:1-3,1,2,4,Y,16,3,within thy sanctuary.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:4-8,2,3,5,N,17,4,Amidst thy congregations
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:4-8,2,3,5,Y,18,4,thine enemies do roar:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:4-8,2,3,5,N,19,4,Their ensigns they set up for signs
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:4-8,2,3,5,Y,20,4,of triumph thee before.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:4-8,2,3,6,N,21,5,"A man was famous, and was had"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:4-8,2,3,6,Y,22,5,"in estimation,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:4-8,2,3,6,N,23,5,According as he lifted up
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:4-8,2,3,6,Y,24,5,his axe thick trees upon.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:4-8,2,4,7,N,25,6,But all at once with axes now
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:4-8,2,4,7,Y,26,6,"and hammers they go to,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:4-8,2,4,7,N,27,6,And down the carved work thereof
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:4-8,2,4,7,Y,28,6,"they break, and quite undo."
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:4-8,2,4,8,N,29,7,"They fired have thy sanctuary,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:4-8,2,4,8,Y,30,7,"and have defil'd the same,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:4-8,2,4,8,N,31,7,By casting down unto the ground
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:4-8,2,4,8,Y,32,7,the place where dwelt thy name.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:4-8,2,5,9,N,33,8,"Thus said they in their hearts, Let us"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:4-8,2,5,9,Y,34,8,destroy them out of hand:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:4-8,2,5,9,N,35,8,They burnt up all the synagogues
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:4-8,2,5,9,Y,36,8,of God within the land.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:9-11,3,5,10,N,37,9,Our signs we do not now behold;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:9-11,3,5,10,Y,38,9,there is not us among
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:9-11,3,5,10,N,39,9,"A prophet more, nor any one"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:9-11,3,5,10,Y,40,9,that knows the time how long.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:9-11,3,6,11,N,41,10,"How long, Lord, shall the enemy"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:9-11,3,6,11,Y,42,10,thus in reproach exclaim?
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:9-11,3,6,11,N,43,10,And shall the adversary thus
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:9-11,3,6,11,Y,44,10,always blaspheme thy name?
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:9-11,3,6,12,N,45,11,"Thy hand, ev'n thy right hand of might,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:9-11,3,6,12,Y,46,11,why dost thou thus draw back?
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:9-11,3,6,12,N,47,11,O from thy bosom pluck it out
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:9-11,3,6,12,Y,48,11,for our deliv'rance sake.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:12-15,4,7,13,N,49,12,"For certainly God is my King,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:12-15,4,7,13,Y,50,12,"ev'n from the times of old,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:12-15,4,7,13,N,51,12,Working in midst of all the earth
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:12-15,4,7,13,Y,52,12,salvation manifold.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:12-15,4,7,14,N,53,13,"The sea, by thy great pow'r, to part"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:12-15,4,7,14,Y,54,13,asunder thou didst make;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:12-15,4,7,14,N,55,13,"And thou the dragons' heads, O Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:12-15,4,7,14,Y,56,13,within the waters brake.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:12-15,4,8,15,N,57,14,The leviathan's head thou brak'st
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:12-15,4,8,15,Y,58,14,"in pieces, and didst give"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:12-15,4,8,15,N,59,14,Him to be meat unto the folk
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:12-15,4,8,15,Y,60,14,in wilderness that live.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:12-15,4,8,16,N,61,15,"Thou clav'st the fountain and the flood,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:12-15,4,8,16,Y,62,15,which did with streams abound:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:12-15,4,8,16,N,63,15,Thou dry'dst the mighty waters up
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:12-15,4,8,16,Y,64,15,unto the very ground.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:16-19,5,9,17,N,65,16,"Thine only is the day, O Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:16-19,5,9,17,Y,66,16,thine also is the night;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:16-19,5,9,17,N,67,16,And thou alone prepared hast
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:16-19,5,9,17,Y,68,16,the sun and shining light.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:16-19,5,9,18,N,69,17,By thee the borders of the earth
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:16-19,5,9,18,Y,70,17,were settled ev'ry where:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:16-19,5,9,18,N,71,17,The summer and the winter both
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:16-19,5,9,18,Y,72,17,by thee created were.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:16-19,5,10,19,N,73,18,"That th' enemy reproached hath,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:16-19,5,10,19,Y,74,18,O keep it in record;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:16-19,5,10,19,N,75,18,And that the foolish people have
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:16-19,5,10,19,Y,76,18,"blasphem'd thy name, O Lord."
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:16-19,5,10,20,N,77,19,Unto the multitude do not
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:16-19,5,10,20,Y,78,19,thy turtle's soul deliver:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:16-19,5,10,20,N,79,19,The congregation of thy poor
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:16-19,5,10,20,Y,80,19,do not forget for ever.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:20-23,6,11,21,N,81,20,Unto thy cov'nant have respect;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:20-23,6,11,21,Y,82,20,for earth's dark places be
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:20-23,6,11,21,N,83,20,Full of the habitations
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:20-23,6,11,21,Y,84,20,of horrid cruelty.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:20-23,6,11,22,N,85,21,O let not those that be oppress'd
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:20-23,6,11,22,Y,86,21,return again with shame:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:20-23,6,11,22,N,87,21,Let those that poor and needy are
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:20-23,6,11,22,Y,88,21,give praise unto thy name.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:20-23,6,12,23,N,89,22,"Do thou, O God, arise and plead"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:20-23,6,12,23,Y,90,22,the cause that is thine own:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:20-23,6,12,23,N,91,22,Remember how thou art reproach'd
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:20-23,6,12,23,Y,92,22,still by the foolish one.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:20-23,6,12,24,N,93,23,Do not forget the voice of those
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:20-23,6,12,24,Y,94,23,that are thine enemies:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:20-23,6,12,24,N,95,23,Of those the tumult ever grows
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),74,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 74:20-23,6,12,24,Y,96,23,that do against thee rise.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),75,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 75:1-3,1,1,1,N,1,1,"To thee, O God, do we give thanks,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),75,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 75:1-3,1,1,1,Y,2,1,we do give thanks to thee;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),75,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 75:1-3,1,1,1,N,3,1,Because thy wondrous works declare
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),75,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 75:1-3,1,1,1,Y,4,1,thy great name near to be.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),75,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 75:1-3,1,1,2,N,5,2,"I purpose, when I shall receive"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),75,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 75:1-3,1,1,2,Y,6,2,"the congregation,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),75,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 75:1-3,1,1,2,N,7,2,That I shall judgment uprightly
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),75,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 75:1-3,1,1,2,Y,8,2,render to ev'ry one.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),75,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 75:1-3,1,2,3,N,9,3,"Dissolved is the land, with all"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),75,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 75:1-3,1,2,3,Y,10,3,that in the same do dwell;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),75,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 75:1-3,1,2,3,N,11,3,But I the pillars thereof do
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),75,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 75:1-3,1,2,3,Y,12,3,"bear up, and stablish well."
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),75,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 75:4-10,2,2,4,N,13,4,"I to the foolish people said,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),75,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 75:4-10,2,2,4,Y,14,4,Do not deal foolishly;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),75,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 75:4-10,2,2,4,N,15,4,"And unto those that wicked are,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),75,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 75:4-10,2,2,4,Y,16,4,Lift not your horn on high.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),75,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 75:4-10,2,3,5,N,17,5,"Lift not your horn on high, nor speak"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),75,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 75:4-10,2,3,5,Y,18,6,"with stubborn neck. But know,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),75,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 75:4-10,2,3,5,N,19,6,"That not from east, nor west, nor south,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),75,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 75:4-10,2,3,5,Y,20,6,promotion doth flow.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),75,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 75:4-10,2,3,6,N,21,7,"But God is judge; he puts down one,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),75,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 75:4-10,2,3,6,Y,22,7,and sets another up.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),75,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 75:4-10,2,3,6,N,23,8,For in the hand of God most high
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),75,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 75:4-10,2,3,6,Y,24,8,of red wine is a cup:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),75,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 75:4-10,2,4,7,N,25,8,"'Tis full of mixture, he pours forth,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),75,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 75:4-10,2,4,7,Y,26,8,and makes the wicked all
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),75,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 75:4-10,2,4,7,N,27,8,Wring out the bitter dregs thereof;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),75,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 75:4-10,2,4,7,Y,28,8,"yea, and they drink them shall."
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),75,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 75:4-10,2,4,8,N,29,9,"But I for ever will declare,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),75,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 75:4-10,2,4,8,Y,30,9,I Jacob's God will praise.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),75,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 75:4-10,2,4,8,N,31,10,All horns of lewd men I'll cut off;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),75,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 75:4-10,2,4,8,Y,32,10,but just men's horns will raise.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),76,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 76:1-6,1,1,1,N,1,1,"In Judah's land God is well known,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),76,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 76:1-6,1,1,1,Y,2,1,his name's in Isr'el great:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),76,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 76:1-6,1,1,1,N,3,2,"In Salem is his tabernacle,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),76,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 76:1-6,1,1,1,Y,4,2,in Sion is his seat.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),76,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 76:1-6,1,1,2,N,5,3,"There arrows of the bow he brake,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),76,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 76:1-6,1,1,2,Y,6,3,"the shield, the sword, the war."
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),76,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 76:1-6,1,1,2,N,7,4,"More glorious thou than hills of prey,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),76,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 76:1-6,1,1,2,Y,8,4,more excellent art far.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),76,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 76:1-6,1,2,3,N,9,5,"Those that were stout of heart are spoil'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),76,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 76:1-6,1,2,3,Y,10,5,they slept their sleep outright;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),76,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 76:1-6,1,2,3,N,11,5,"And none of those their hands did find,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),76,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 76:1-6,1,2,3,Y,12,5,that were the men of might.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),76,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 76:1-6,1,2,4,N,13,6,"When thy rebuke, O Jacob's God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),76,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 76:1-6,1,2,4,Y,14,6,"had forth against them past,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),76,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 76:1-6,1,2,4,N,15,6,Their horses and their chariots both
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),76,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 76:1-6,1,2,4,Y,16,6,were in a dead sleep cast.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),76,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 76:7-12,2,3,5,N,17,7,"Thou, Lord, ev'n thou art he that should"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),76,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 76:7-12,2,3,5,Y,18,7,be fear'd; and who is he
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),76,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 76:7-12,2,3,5,N,19,7,"That may stand up before thy sight,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),76,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 76:7-12,2,3,5,Y,20,7,if once thou angry be?
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),76,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 76:7-12,2,3,6,N,21,8,From heav'n thou judgment caus'd be heard;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),76,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 76:7-12,2,3,6,Y,22,8,"the earth was still with fear,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),76,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 76:7-12,2,3,6,N,23,9,"When God to judgment rose, to save"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),76,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 76:7-12,2,3,6,Y,24,9,all meek on earth that were.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),76,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 76:7-12,2,4,7,N,25,10,Surely the very wrath of man
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),76,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 76:7-12,2,4,7,Y,26,10,unto thy praise redounds:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),76,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 76:7-12,2,4,7,N,27,10,Thou to the remnant of his wrath
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),76,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 76:7-12,2,4,7,Y,28,10,wilt set restraining bounds.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),76,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 76:7-12,2,4,8,N,29,11,"Vow to the Lord your God, and pay:"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),76,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 76:7-12,2,4,8,Y,30,11,"all ye that near him be,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),76,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 76:7-12,2,4,8,N,31,11,Bring gifts and presents unto him;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),76,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 76:7-12,2,4,8,Y,32,11,for to be fear'd is he.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),76,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 76:7-12,2,5,9,N,33,12,By him the sp'rits shall be cut off
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),76,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 76:7-12,2,5,9,Y,34,12,of those that princes are:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),76,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 76:7-12,2,5,9,N,35,12,Unto the kings that are on earth
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),76,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 76:7-12,2,5,9,Y,36,12,he fearful doth appear.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:1-4,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Unto the Lord I with my voice,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:1-4,1,1,1,Y,2,1,I unto God did cry;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:1-4,1,1,1,N,3,1,"Ev'n with my voice, and unto me"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:1-4,1,1,1,Y,4,1,his ear he did apply.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:1-4,1,1,2,N,5,2,"I in my trouble sought the Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:1-4,1,1,2,Y,6,2,"my sore by night did run,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:1-4,1,1,2,N,7,2,And ceased not; my grieved soul
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:1-4,1,1,2,Y,8,2,did consolation shun.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:1-4,1,2,3,N,9,3,"I to remembrance God did call,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:1-4,1,2,3,Y,10,3,yet trouble did remain;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:1-4,1,2,3,N,11,3,"And overwhelm'd my spirit was,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:1-4,1,2,3,Y,12,3,whilst I did sore complain.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:1-4,1,2,4,N,13,4,"Mine eyes, debarr'd from rest and sleep,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:1-4,1,2,4,Y,14,4,thou makest still to wake;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:1-4,1,2,4,N,15,4,My trouble is so great that I
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:1-4,1,2,4,Y,16,4,unable am to speak.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:5-9,2,3,5,N,17,5,"The days of old to mind I call'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:5-9,2,3,5,Y,18,5,and oft did think upon
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:5-9,2,3,5,N,19,5,The times and ages that are past
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:5-9,2,3,5,Y,20,5,full many years agone.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:5-9,2,3,6,N,21,6,"By night my song I call to mind,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:5-9,2,3,6,Y,22,6,and commune with my heart;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:5-9,2,3,6,N,23,6,My sp'rit did carefully enquire
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:5-9,2,3,6,Y,24,6,how I might ease my smart.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:5-9,2,4,7,N,25,7,"For ever will the Lord cast off,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:5-9,2,4,7,Y,26,7,and gracious be no more?
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:5-9,2,4,7,N,27,8,For ever is his mercy gone?
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:5-9,2,4,7,Y,28,8,fails his word evermore?
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:5-9,2,4,8,N,29,9,Is't true that to be gracious
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:5-9,2,4,8,Y,30,9,the Lord forgotten hath?
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:5-9,2,4,8,N,31,9,And that his tender mercies he
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:5-9,2,4,8,Y,32,9,hath shut up in his wrath?
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:10-13,3,5,9,N,33,10,"Then did I say, That surely this"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:10-13,3,5,9,Y,34,10,is mine infirmity:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:10-13,3,5,9,N,35,10,I'll mind the years of the right hand
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:10-13,3,5,9,Y,36,10,of him that is most High.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:10-13,3,5,10,N,37,11,"Yea, I remember will the works"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:10-13,3,5,10,Y,38,11,performed by the Lord:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:10-13,3,5,10,N,39,11,The wonders done of old by thee
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:10-13,3,5,10,Y,40,11,I surely will record.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:10-13,3,6,11,N,41,12,I also will of all thy works
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:10-13,3,6,11,Y,42,12,my meditation make;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:10-13,3,6,11,N,43,12,And of thy doings to discourse
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:10-13,3,6,11,Y,44,12,great pleasure I will take.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:10-13,3,6,12,N,45,13,"O God, thy way most holy is"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:10-13,3,6,12,Y,46,13,within thy sanctuary;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:10-13,3,6,12,N,47,13,And what god is so great in pow'r
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:10-13,3,6,12,Y,48,13,as is our God most high?
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:14-15,4,7,13,N,49,14,Thou art the God that wonders do'st
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:14-15,4,7,13,Y,50,14,by thy right hand most strong:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:14-15,4,7,13,N,51,14,Thy mighty pow'r thou hast declar'd
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:14-15,4,7,13,Y,52,14,the nations among.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:14-15,4,7,14,N,53,15,To thine own people with thine arm
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:14-15,4,7,14,Y,54,15,thou didst redemption bring;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:14-15,4,7,14,N,55,15,"To Jacob's sons, and to the tribes"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:14-15,4,7,14,Y,56,15,of Joseph that do spring.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:16-20,5,8,15,N,57,16,"The waters, Lord, perceived thee,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:16-20,5,8,15,Y,58,16,the waters saw thee well;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:16-20,5,8,15,N,59,16,And they for fear aside did flee;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:16-20,5,8,15,Y,60,16,the depths on trembling fell.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:16-20,5,8,16,N,61,17,"The clouds in water forth were pour'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:16-20,5,8,16,Y,62,17,sound loudly did the sky;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:16-20,5,8,16,N,63,17,And swiftly through the world abroad
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:16-20,5,8,16,Y,64,17,thine arrows fierce did fly.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:16-20,5,9,17,N,65,18,Thy thunder's voice alongst the heav'n
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:16-20,5,9,17,Y,66,18,a mighty noise did make;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:16-20,5,9,17,N,67,18,"By lightnings lighten'd was the world,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:16-20,5,9,17,Y,68,18,th' earth tremble did and shake.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:16-20,5,9,18,N,69,19,"Thy way is in the sea, and in"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:16-20,5,9,18,Y,70,19,the waters great thy path;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:16-20,5,9,18,N,71,19,"Yet are thy footsteps hid, O Lord;"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:16-20,5,9,18,Y,72,19,none knowledge thereof hath.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:16-20,5,10,19,N,73,20,"Thy people thou didst safely lead,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:16-20,5,10,19,Y,74,20,like to a flock of sheep;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:16-20,5,10,19,N,75,20,By Moses' hand and Aaron's thou
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),77,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 77:16-20,5,10,19,Y,76,20,didst them conduct and keep.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:1-4,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Attend, my people, to my law;"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:1-4,1,1,1,Y,2,1,thereto give thou an ear;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:1-4,1,1,1,N,3,1,The words that from my mouth proceed
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:1-4,1,1,1,Y,4,1,attentively do hear.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:1-4,1,1,2,N,5,2,"My mouth shall speak a parable,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:1-4,1,1,2,Y,6,2,and sayings dark of old;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:1-4,1,1,2,N,7,3,"The same which we have heard and known,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:1-4,1,1,2,Y,8,3,and us our fathers told.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:1-4,1,2,3,N,9,4,We also will them not conceal
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:1-4,1,2,3,Y,10,4,from their posterity;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:1-4,1,2,3,N,11,4,Them to the generation
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:1-4,1,2,3,Y,12,4,to come declare will we:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:1-4,1,2,4,N,13,4,"The praises of the Lord our God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:1-4,1,2,4,Y,14,4,"and his almighty strength,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:1-4,1,2,4,N,15,4,"The wondrous works that he hath done,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:1-4,1,2,4,Y,16,4,we will shew forth at length.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:5-8,2,3,5,N,17,5,His testimony and his law
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:5-8,2,3,5,Y,18,5,"in Isr'el he did place,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:5-8,2,3,5,N,19,5,And charg'd our fathers it to show
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:5-8,2,3,5,Y,20,5,to their succeeding race;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:5-8,2,3,6,N,21,6,That so the race which was to come
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:5-8,2,3,6,Y,22,6,might well them learn and know;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:5-8,2,3,6,N,23,6,"And sons unborn, who should arise,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:5-8,2,3,6,Y,24,6,might to their sons them show:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:5-8,2,4,7,N,25,7,"That they might set their hope in God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:5-8,2,4,7,Y,26,7,and suffer not to fall
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:5-8,2,4,7,N,27,7,"His mighty works out of their mind,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:5-8,2,4,7,Y,28,7,but keep his precepts all:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:5-8,2,4,8,N,29,8,"And might not, like their fathers, be"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:5-8,2,4,8,Y,30,8,a stiff rebellious race;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:5-8,2,4,8,N,31,8,A race not right in heart; with God
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:5-8,2,4,8,Y,32,8,whose sp'rit not stedfast was.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:9-15,3,5,9,N,33,9,"The sons of Ephraim, who nor bows"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:9-15,3,5,9,Y,34,9,"nor other arms did lack,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:9-15,3,5,9,N,35,9,"When as the day of battle was,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:9-15,3,5,9,Y,36,9,they faintly turned back.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:9-15,3,5,10,N,37,10,"They brake God's cov'nant, and refus'd"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:9-15,3,5,10,Y,38,10,in his commands to go;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:9-15,3,5,10,N,39,11,"His works and wonders they forgot,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:9-15,3,5,10,Y,40,11,which he to them did show.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:9-15,3,6,11,N,41,12,Things marvellous he brought to pass;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:9-15,3,6,11,Y,42,12,their fathers them beheld
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:9-15,3,6,11,N,43,12,"Within the land of Egypt done,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:9-15,3,6,11,Y,44,12,"yea, ev'n in Zoan's field."
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:9-15,3,6,12,N,45,13,"By him divided was the sea,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:9-15,3,6,12,Y,46,13,he caus'd them through to pass;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:9-15,3,6,12,N,47,13,"And made the waters so to stand,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:9-15,3,6,12,Y,48,13,as like an heap it was.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:9-15,3,7,13,N,49,14,"With cloud by day, with light of fire"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:9-15,3,7,13,Y,50,14,"all night, he did them guide."
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:9-15,3,7,13,N,51,15,"In desert rocks he clave, and drink,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:9-15,3,7,13,Y,52,15,"as from great depths, supply'd."
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:16-20,4,7,14,N,53,16,"He from the rock brought streams, like floods"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:16-20,4,7,14,Y,54,16,made waters to run down.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:16-20,4,7,14,N,55,17,"Yet sinning more, in desert they"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:16-20,4,7,14,Y,56,17,provok'd the Highest One.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:16-20,4,8,15,N,57,18,"For in their heart they tempted God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:16-20,4,8,15,Y,58,18,"and, speaking with mistrust,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:16-20,4,8,15,N,59,18,They greedily did meat require
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:16-20,4,8,15,Y,60,18,to satisfy their lust.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:16-20,4,8,16,N,61,19,"Against the Lord himself they spake,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:16-20,4,8,16,Y,62,19,"and, murmuring, said thus,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:16-20,4,8,16,N,63,19,A table in the wilderness
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:16-20,4,8,16,Y,64,19,can God prepare for us?
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:16-20,4,9,17,N,65,20,"Behold, he smote the rock, and thence"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:16-20,4,9,17,Y,66,20,came streams and waters great;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:16-20,4,9,17,N,67,20,But can he give his people bread?
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:16-20,4,9,17,Y,68,20,and send them flesh to eat?
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:21-25,5,9,18,N,69,21,"The Lord did hear, and waxed wroth;"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:21-25,5,9,18,Y,70,21,so kindled was a flame
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:21-25,5,9,18,N,71,21,"'Gainst Jacob, and 'gainst Israel"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:21-25,5,9,18,Y,72,21,up indignation came.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:21-25,5,10,19,N,73,22,"For they believ'd not God, nor trust"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:21-25,5,10,19,Y,74,22,in his salvation had;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:21-25,5,10,19,N,75,23,"Though clouds above he did command,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:21-25,5,10,19,Y,76,23,"and heav'n's doors open made,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:21-25,5,10,20,N,77,24,"And manna rain'd on them, and gave"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:21-25,5,10,20,Y,78,24,them corn of heav'n to eat.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:21-25,5,10,20,N,79,25,Man angels' food did eat; to them
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:21-25,5,10,20,Y,80,25,he to the full sent meat.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:26-29,6,11,21,N,81,26,And in the heaven he did cause
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:26-29,6,11,21,Y,82,26,an eastern wind to blow;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:26-29,6,11,21,N,83,26,And by his power he let out
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:26-29,6,11,21,Y,84,26,the southern wind to go.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:26-29,6,11,22,N,85,27,Then flesh as thick as dust he made
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:26-29,6,11,22,Y,86,27,to rain down them among;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:26-29,6,11,22,N,87,27,"And feather'd fowls, like as the sand"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:26-29,6,11,22,Y,88,27,which li'th the shore along.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:26-29,6,12,23,N,89,28,At his command amidst their camp
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:26-29,6,12,23,Y,90,28,"these show'rs of flesh down fell,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:26-29,6,12,23,N,91,28,All round about the tabernacles
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:26-29,6,12,23,Y,92,28,and tents where they did dwell.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:26-29,6,12,24,N,93,29,"So they did eat abundantly,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:26-29,6,12,24,Y,94,29,and had of meat their fill;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:26-29,6,12,24,N,95,29,For he did give to them what was
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:26-29,6,12,24,Y,96,29,their own desire and will.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:30-33,7,13,25,N,97,30,They from their lust had not estrang'd
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:30-33,7,13,25,Y,98,30,their heart and their desire;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:30-33,7,13,25,N,99,30,"But while the meat was in their mouths,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:30-33,7,13,25,Y,100,30,"which they did so require,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:30-33,7,13,26,N,101,31,"God's wrath upon them came, and slew"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:30-33,7,13,26,Y,102,31,the fattest of them all;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:30-33,7,13,26,N,103,31,"So that the choice of Israel,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:30-33,7,13,26,Y,104,31,"o'erthrown by death, did fall."
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:30-33,7,14,27,N,105,32,"Yet, notwithstanding of all this,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:30-33,7,14,27,Y,106,32,they sinned still the more;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:30-33,7,14,27,N,107,32,"And though he had great wonders wrought,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:30-33,7,14,27,Y,108,32,believ'd him not therefore:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:30-33,7,14,28,N,109,33,Wherefore their days in vanity
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:30-33,7,14,28,Y,110,33,he did consume and waste;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:30-33,7,14,28,N,111,33,And by his wrath their wretched years
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:30-33,7,14,28,Y,112,33,away in trouble past.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:34-37,8,15,29,N,113,34,"But when he slew them, then they did"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:34-37,8,15,29,Y,114,34,to seek him shew desire;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:34-37,8,15,29,N,115,34,"Yea, they return'd, and after God"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:34-37,8,15,29,Y,116,34,right early did enquire.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:34-37,8,15,30,N,117,35,"And that the Lord had been their Rock,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:34-37,8,15,30,Y,118,35,they did remember then;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:34-37,8,15,30,N,119,35,Ev'n that the high almighty God
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:34-37,8,15,30,Y,120,35,had their Redeemer been.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:34-37,8,16,31,N,121,36,"Yet with their mouth they flatter'd him,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:34-37,8,16,31,Y,122,36,and spake but feignedly;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:34-37,8,16,31,N,123,36,And they unto the God of truth
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:34-37,8,16,31,Y,124,36,with their false tongues did lie.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:34-37,8,16,32,N,125,37,"For though their words were good, their heart"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:34-37,8,16,32,Y,126,37,with him was not sincere;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:34-37,8,16,32,N,127,37,Unstedfast and perfidious
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:34-37,8,16,32,Y,128,37,they in his cov'nant were.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:38-39,9,17,33,N,129,38,"But, full of pity, he forgave"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:38-39,9,17,33,Y,130,38,"their sin, them did not slay;"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:38-39,9,17,33,N,131,38,"Nor stirr'd up all his wrath, but oft"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:38-39,9,17,33,Y,132,38,his anger turn'd away.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:38-39,9,17,34,N,133,39,For that they were but fading flesh
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:38-39,9,17,34,Y,134,39,to mind he did recall;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:38-39,9,17,34,N,135,39,"A wind that passeth soon away,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:38-39,9,17,34,Y,136,39,and not returns at all.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:40-44,10,18,35,N,137,40,How often did they him provoke
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:40-44,10,18,35,Y,138,40,within the wilderness!
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:40-44,10,18,35,N,139,40,And in the desert did him grieve
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:40-44,10,18,35,Y,140,40,with their rebelliousness!
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:40-44,10,18,36,N,141,41,"Yea, turning back, they tempted God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:40-44,10,18,36,Y,142,41,and limits set upon
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:40-44,10,18,36,N,143,41,"Him, who in midst of Isr'el is"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:40-44,10,18,36,Y,144,41,the only Holy One.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:40-44,10,19,37,N,145,42,"They did not call to mind his pow'r,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:40-44,10,19,37,Y,146,42,nor yet the day when he
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:40-44,10,19,37,N,147,42,Deliver'd them out of the hand
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:40-44,10,19,37,Y,148,42,of their fierce enemy;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:40-44,10,19,38,N,149,43,Nor how great signs in Egypt land
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:40-44,10,19,38,Y,150,43,he openly had wrought;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:40-44,10,19,38,N,151,43,What miracles in Zoan's field
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:40-44,10,19,38,Y,152,43,his hand to pass had brought.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:40-44,10,20,39,N,153,44,How lakes and rivers ev'ry where
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:40-44,10,20,39,Y,154,44,he turned into blood;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:40-44,10,20,39,N,155,44,So that nor man nor beast could drink
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:40-44,10,20,39,Y,156,44,of standing lake or flood.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:45-48,11,20,40,N,157,45,"He brought among them swarms of flies,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:45-48,11,20,40,Y,158,45,which did them sore annoy;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:45-48,11,20,40,N,159,45,And divers kinds of filthy frogs
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:45-48,11,20,40,Y,160,45,he sent them to destroy.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:45-48,11,21,41,N,161,46,He to the caterpillar gave
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:45-48,11,21,41,Y,162,46,the fruits of all their soil;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:45-48,11,21,41,N,163,46,Their labours he deliver'd up
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:45-48,11,21,41,Y,164,46,unto the locusts' spoil.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:45-48,11,21,42,N,165,47,"Their vines with hail, their sycamores"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:45-48,11,21,42,Y,166,47,he with the frost did blast:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:45-48,11,21,42,N,167,48,Their beasts to hail he gave; their flocks
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:45-48,11,21,42,Y,168,48,hot thunderbolts did waste.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:49-51,12,22,43,N,169,49,"Fierce burning wrath he on them cast,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:49-51,12,22,43,Y,170,49,"and indignation strong,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:49-51,12,22,43,N,171,49,"And troubles sore, by sending forth"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:49-51,12,22,43,Y,172,49,ill angels them among.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:49-51,12,22,44,N,173,50,He to his wrath made way; their soul
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:49-51,12,22,44,Y,174,50,from death he did not save;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:49-51,12,22,44,N,175,50,But over to the pestilence
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:49-51,12,22,44,Y,176,50,the lives of them he gave.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:49-51,12,23,45,N,177,51,In Egypt land the first-born all
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:49-51,12,23,45,Y,178,51,he smote down ev'ry where;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:49-51,12,23,45,N,179,51,"Among the tents of Ham, ev'n these"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:49-51,12,23,45,Y,180,51,chief of their strength that were.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:52-55,13,23,46,N,181,52,"But his own people, like to sheep,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:52-55,13,23,46,Y,182,52,thence to go forth he made;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:52-55,13,23,46,N,183,52,"And he, amidst the wilderness,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:52-55,13,23,46,Y,184,52,"them, as a flock, did lead."
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:52-55,13,24,47,N,185,53,"And he them safely on did lead,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:52-55,13,24,47,Y,186,53,so that they did not fear;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:52-55,13,24,47,N,187,53,Whereas their en'mies by the sea
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:52-55,13,24,47,Y,188,53,quite overwhelmed were.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:52-55,13,24,48,N,189,54,To borders of his sanctuary
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:52-55,13,24,48,Y,190,54,"the Lord his people led,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:52-55,13,24,48,N,191,54,Ev'n to the mount which his right hand
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:52-55,13,24,48,Y,192,54,for them had purchased.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:52-55,13,25,49,N,193,55,"The nations of Canaan,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:52-55,13,25,49,Y,194,55,"by his almighty hand,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:52-55,13,25,49,N,195,55,Before their face he did expel
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:52-55,13,25,49,Y,196,55,out of their native land;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:52-55,13,25,50,N,197,55,Which for inheritance to them
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:52-55,13,25,50,Y,198,55,"by line he did divide,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:52-55,13,25,50,N,199,55,And made the tribes of Israel
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:52-55,13,25,50,Y,200,55,within their tents abide.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:56-58,14,26,51,N,201,56,"Yet God most high they did provoke,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:56-58,14,26,51,Y,202,56,and tempted ever still;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:56-58,14,26,51,N,203,56,And to observe his testimonies
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:56-58,14,26,51,Y,204,56,did not incline their will:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:56-58,14,26,52,N,205,57,"But, like their fathers, turned back,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:56-58,14,26,52,Y,206,57,and dealt unfaithfully:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:56-58,14,26,52,N,207,57,"Aside they turned, like a bow"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:56-58,14,26,52,Y,208,57,that shoots deceitfully.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:56-58,14,27,53,N,209,58,For they to anger did provoke
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:56-58,14,27,53,Y,210,58,him with their places high;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:56-58,14,27,53,N,211,58,And with their graven images
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:56-58,14,27,53,Y,212,58,mov'd him to jealousy.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:59-64,15,27,54,N,213,59,"When God heard this, he waxed wroth,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:59-64,15,27,54,Y,214,59,and much loath'd Isr'el then:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:59-64,15,27,54,N,215,60,"So Shiloh's tent he left, the tent"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:59-64,15,27,54,Y,216,60,which he had plac'd with men.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:59-64,15,28,55,N,217,61,And he his strength delivered
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:59-64,15,28,55,Y,218,61,into captivity;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:59-64,15,28,55,N,219,61,He left his glory in the hand
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:59-64,15,28,55,Y,220,61,of his proud enemy.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:59-64,15,28,56,N,221,62,His people also he gave o'er
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:59-64,15,28,56,Y,222,62,unto the sword's fierce rage:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:59-64,15,28,56,N,223,62,So sore his wrath inflamed was
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:59-64,15,28,56,Y,224,62,against his heritage.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:59-64,15,29,57,N,225,63,The fire consum'd their choice young men;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:59-64,15,29,57,Y,226,63,their maids no marriage had;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:59-64,15,29,57,N,227,64,"And when their priests fell by the sword,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:59-64,15,29,57,Y,228,64,their wives no mourning made.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:65-69,16,29,58,N,229,65,"But then the Lord arose, as one"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:65-69,16,29,58,Y,230,65,that doth from sleep awake;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:65-69,16,29,58,N,231,65,"And like a giant that, by wine"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:65-69,16,29,58,Y,232,65,"refresh'd, a shout doth make:"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:65-69,16,30,59,N,233,66,Upon his en'mies' hinder parts
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:65-69,16,30,59,Y,234,66,he made his stroke to fall;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:65-69,16,30,59,N,235,66,And so upon them he did put
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:65-69,16,30,59,Y,236,66,a shame perpetual.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:65-69,16,30,60,N,237,67,"Moreover, he the tabernacle"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:65-69,16,30,60,Y,238,67,of Joseph did refuse;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:65-69,16,30,60,N,239,67,The mighty tribe of Ephraim
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:65-69,16,30,60,Y,240,67,he would in no wise chuse:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:65-69,16,31,61,N,241,68,But he did chuse Jehudah's tribe
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:65-69,16,31,61,Y,242,68,to be the rest above;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:65-69,16,31,61,N,243,68,"And of mount Sion he made choice,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:65-69,16,31,61,Y,244,68,which he so much did love.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:65-69,16,31,62,N,245,69,And he his sanctuary built
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:65-69,16,31,62,Y,246,69,"like to a palace high,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:65-69,16,31,62,N,247,69,Like to the earth which he did found
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:65-69,16,31,62,Y,248,69,to perpetuity.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:70-72,17,32,63,N,249,70,"Of David, that his servant was,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:70-72,17,32,63,Y,250,70,"he also choice did make,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:70-72,17,32,63,N,251,70,And even from the folds of sheep
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:70-72,17,32,63,Y,252,70,was pleased him to take:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:70-72,17,32,64,N,253,71,"From waiting on the ewes with young,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:70-72,17,32,64,Y,254,71,he brought him forth to feed
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:70-72,17,32,64,N,255,71,"Israel, his inheritance,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:70-72,17,32,64,Y,256,71,"his people, Jacob's seed."
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:70-72,17,33,65,N,257,72,So after the integrity
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:70-72,17,33,65,Y,258,72,he of his heart them fed;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:70-72,17,33,65,N,259,72,And by the good skill of his hands
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),78,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 78:70-72,17,33,65,Y,260,72,them wisely governed.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:1-4,1,1,1,N,1,1,"O God, the heathen enter'd have"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:1-4,1,1,1,Y,2,1,thine heritage; by them
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:1-4,1,1,1,N,3,1,Defiled is thy house: on heaps
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:1-4,1,1,1,Y,4,1,they laid Jerusalem.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:1-4,1,1,2,N,5,2,The bodies of thy servants they
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:1-4,1,1,2,Y,6,2,have cast forth to be meat
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:1-4,1,1,2,N,7,2,To rav'nous fowls; thy dear saints' flesh
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:1-4,1,1,2,Y,8,2,they gave to beasts to eat.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:1-4,1,2,3,N,9,3,Their blood about Jerusalem
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:1-4,1,2,3,Y,10,3,like water they have shed;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:1-4,1,2,3,N,11,3,And there was none to bury them
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:1-4,1,2,3,Y,12,3,when they were slain and dead.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:1-4,1,2,4,N,13,4,Unto our neighbours a reproach
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:1-4,1,2,4,Y,14,4,most base become are we;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:1-4,1,2,4,N,15,4,A scorn and laughingstock to them
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:1-4,1,2,4,Y,16,4,that round about us be.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:5-8,2,3,5,N,17,5,"How long, Lord, shall thine anger last?"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:5-8,2,3,5,Y,18,5,wilt thou still keep the same?
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:5-8,2,3,5,N,19,5,And shall thy fervent jealousy
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:5-8,2,3,5,Y,20,5,burn like unto a flame?
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:5-8,2,3,6,N,21,6,"On heathen pour thy fury forth,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:5-8,2,3,6,Y,22,6,"that have thee never known,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:5-8,2,3,6,N,23,6,And on those kingdoms which thy name
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:5-8,2,3,6,Y,24,6,have never call'd upon.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:5-8,2,4,7,N,25,7,For these are they who Jacob have
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:5-8,2,4,7,Y,26,7,devoured cruelly;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:5-8,2,4,7,N,27,7,And they his habitation
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:5-8,2,4,7,Y,28,7,have caused waste to lie.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:5-8,2,4,8,N,29,8,Against us mind not former sins;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:5-8,2,4,8,Y,30,8,thy tender mercies show;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:5-8,2,4,8,N,31,8,"Let them prevent us speedily,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:5-8,2,4,8,Y,32,8,for we're brought very low.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:9-13,3,5,9,N,33,9,"For thy name's glory help us, Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:9-13,3,5,9,Y,34,9,who hast our Saviour been:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:9-13,3,5,9,N,35,9,"Deliver us; for thy name's sake,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:9-13,3,5,9,Y,36,9,O purge away our sin.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:9-13,3,5,10,N,37,10,"Why say the heathen, Where's their God?"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:9-13,3,5,10,Y,38,10,let him to them be known;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:9-13,3,5,10,N,39,10,When those who shed thy servants' blood
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:9-13,3,5,10,Y,40,10,are in our sight o'erthrown.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:9-13,3,6,11,N,41,11,O let the pris'ner's sighs ascend
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:9-13,3,6,11,Y,42,11,before thy sight on high;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:9-13,3,6,11,N,43,11,Preserve those in thy mighty pow'r
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:9-13,3,6,11,Y,44,11,that are design'd to die.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:9-13,3,6,12,N,45,12,And to our neighbours' bosom cause
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:9-13,3,6,12,Y,46,12,"it sev'n-fold render'd be,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:9-13,3,6,12,N,47,12,"Ev'n the reproach wherewith they have,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:9-13,3,6,12,Y,48,12,"O Lord, reproached thee."
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:9-13,3,7,13,N,49,13,"So we thy folk, and pasture-sheep,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:9-13,3,7,13,Y,50,13,shall give thee thanks always;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:9-13,3,7,13,N,51,13,And unto generations all
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),79,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 79:9-13,3,7,13,Y,52,13,we will shew forth thy praise.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:1-3,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Hear, Isr'el's Shepherd! like a flock"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:1-3,1,1,1,Y,2,1,thou that dost Joseph guide;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:1-3,1,1,1,N,3,1,"Shine forth, O thou that dost between"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:1-3,1,1,1,Y,4,1,the cherubims abide.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:1-3,1,1,2,N,5,2,"In Ephraim's, and Benjamin's"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:1-3,1,1,2,Y,6,2,"and in Manasseh's sight,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:1-3,1,1,2,N,7,2,O come for our salvation;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:1-3,1,1,2,Y,8,2,stir up thy strength and might.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:1-3,1,2,3,N,9,3,"Turn us again, O Lord our God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:1-3,1,2,3,Y,10,3,and upon us vouchsafe
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:1-3,1,2,3,N,11,3,"To make thy countenance to shine,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:1-3,1,2,3,Y,12,3,and so we shall be safe.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:4-7,2,2,4,N,13,4,"O Lord of hosts, almighty God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:4-7,2,2,4,Y,14,4,how long shall kindled be
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:4-7,2,2,4,N,15,4,Thy wrath against the prayer made
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:4-7,2,2,4,Y,16,4,by thine own folk to thee?
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:4-7,2,3,5,N,17,5,Thou tears of sorrow giv'st to them
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:4-7,2,3,5,Y,18,5,instead of bread to eat;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:4-7,2,3,5,N,19,5,"Yea, tears instead of drink thou giv'st"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:4-7,2,3,5,Y,20,5,to them in measure great.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:4-7,2,3,6,N,21,6,Thou makest us a strife unto
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:4-7,2,3,6,Y,22,6,our neighbours round about;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:4-7,2,3,6,N,23,6,Our enemies among themselves
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:4-7,2,3,6,Y,24,6,at us do laugh and flout.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:4-7,2,4,7,N,25,7,"Turn us again, O God of hosts,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:4-7,2,4,7,Y,26,7,and upon us vouchsafe
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:4-7,2,4,7,N,27,7,"To make thy countenance to shine,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:4-7,2,4,7,Y,28,7,and so we shall be safe.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:8-11,3,4,8,N,29,8,"A vine from Egypt brought thou hast,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:8-11,3,4,8,Y,30,8,by thine outstretched hand;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:8-11,3,4,8,N,31,8,"And thou the heathen out didst cast,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:8-11,3,4,8,Y,32,8,to plant it in their land.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:8-11,3,5,9,N,33,9,"Before it thou a room didst make,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:8-11,3,5,9,Y,34,9,where it might grow and stand;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:8-11,3,5,9,N,35,9,"Thou causedst it deep root to take,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:8-11,3,5,9,Y,36,9,and it did fill the land.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:8-11,3,5,10,N,37,10,"The mountains vail'd were with its shade,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:8-11,3,5,10,Y,38,10,as with a covering;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:8-11,3,5,10,N,39,10,Like goodly cedars were the boughs
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:8-11,3,5,10,Y,40,10,which out from it did spring.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:8-11,3,6,11,N,41,11,Upon the one hand to the sea
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:8-11,3,6,11,Y,42,11,her boughs she did out send;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:8-11,3,6,11,N,43,11,On th' other side unto the flood
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:8-11,3,6,11,Y,44,11,her branches did extend.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:12-16,4,6,12,N,45,12,"Why hast thou then thus broken down,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:12-16,4,6,12,Y,46,12,and ta'en her hedge away?
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:12-16,4,6,12,N,47,12,"So that all passengers do pluck,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:12-16,4,6,12,Y,48,12,and make of her a prey.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:12-16,4,7,13,N,49,13,The boar who from the forest comes
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:12-16,4,7,13,Y,50,13,doth waste it at his pleasure;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:12-16,4,7,13,N,51,13,The wild beast of the field also
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:12-16,4,7,13,Y,52,13,devours it out of measure.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:12-16,4,7,14,N,53,14,"O God of hosts, we thee beseech,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:12-16,4,7,14,Y,54,14,return now unto thine;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:12-16,4,7,14,N,55,14,"Look down from heav'n in love, behold,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:12-16,4,7,14,Y,56,14,and visit this thy vine:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:12-16,4,8,15,N,57,15,"This vineyard, which thine own right hand"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:12-16,4,8,15,Y,58,15,hath planted us among;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:12-16,4,8,15,N,59,15,"And that same branch, which for thyself"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:12-16,4,8,15,Y,60,15,thou hast made to be strong.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:12-16,4,8,16,N,61,16,"Burnt up it is with flaming fire,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:12-16,4,8,16,Y,62,16,it also is cut down:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:12-16,4,8,16,N,63,16,"They utterly are perished,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:12-16,4,8,16,Y,64,16,when as thy face doth frown.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:17-19,5,9,17,N,65,17,O let thy hand be still upon
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:17-19,5,9,17,Y,66,17,"the Man of thy right hand,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:17-19,5,9,17,N,67,17,"The Son of man, whom for thyself"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:17-19,5,9,17,Y,68,17,thou madest strong to stand.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:17-19,5,9,18,N,69,18,"So henceforth we will not go back,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:17-19,5,9,18,Y,70,18,nor turn from thee at all:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:17-19,5,9,18,N,71,18,"O do thou quicken us, and we"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:17-19,5,9,18,Y,72,18,upon thy name will call.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:17-19,5,10,19,N,73,19,"Turn us again, Lord God of hosts,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:17-19,5,10,19,Y,74,19,and upon us vouchsafe
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:17-19,5,10,19,N,75,19,"To make thy countenance to shine,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),80,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 80:17-19,5,10,19,Y,76,19,and so we shall be safe.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:1-7,1,1,1,N,1,1,Sing loud to God our strength; with joy
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:1-7,1,1,1,Y,2,1,to Jacob's God do sing.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:1-7,1,1,1,N,3,2,"Take up a psalm, the pleasant harp,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:1-7,1,1,1,Y,4,2,timbrel and psalt'ry bring.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:1-7,1,1,2,N,5,3,"Blow trumpets at new-moon, what day"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:1-7,1,1,2,Y,6,3,our feast appointed is:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:1-7,1,1,2,N,7,4,"For charge to Isr'el, and a law"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:1-7,1,1,2,Y,8,4,of Jacob's God was this.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:1-7,1,2,3,N,9,5,To Joseph this a testimony
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:1-7,1,2,3,Y,10,5,"he made, when Egypt land"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:1-7,1,2,3,N,11,5,"He travell'd through, where speech I heard"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:1-7,1,2,3,Y,12,5,I did not understand.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:1-7,1,2,4,N,13,6,"His shoulder I from burdens took,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:1-7,1,2,4,Y,14,6,his hands from pots did free.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:1-7,1,2,4,N,15,7,"Thou didst in trouble on me call,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:1-7,1,2,4,Y,16,7,and I deliver'd thee:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:1-7,1,3,5,N,17,7,In secret place of thundering
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:1-7,1,3,5,Y,18,7,I did thee answer make;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:1-7,1,3,5,N,19,7,And at the streams of Meribah
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:1-7,1,3,5,Y,20,7,of thee a proof did take.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:8-12,2,3,6,N,21,8,"O thou, my people, give an ear,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:8-12,2,3,6,Y,22,8,I'll testify to thee;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:8-12,2,3,6,N,23,8,"To thee, O Isr'el, if thou wilt"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:8-12,2,3,6,Y,24,8,but hearken unto me.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:8-12,2,4,7,N,25,9,In midst of thee there shall not be
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:8-12,2,4,7,Y,26,9,any strange god at all;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:8-12,2,4,7,N,27,9,Nor unto any god unknown
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:8-12,2,4,7,Y,28,9,thou bowing down shalt fall.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:8-12,2,4,8,N,29,10,"I am the Lord thy God, which did"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:8-12,2,4,8,Y,30,10,from Egypt land thee guide;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:8-12,2,4,8,N,31,10,"I'll fill thy mouth abundantly,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:8-12,2,4,8,Y,32,10,do thou it open wide.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:8-12,2,5,9,N,33,11,But yet my people to my voice
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:8-12,2,5,9,Y,34,11,would not attentive be;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:8-12,2,5,9,N,35,11,And ev'n my chosen Israel
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:8-12,2,5,9,Y,36,11,he would have none of me.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:8-12,2,5,10,N,37,12,So to the lust of their own hearts
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:8-12,2,5,10,Y,38,12,I them delivered;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:8-12,2,5,10,N,39,12,And then in counsels of their own
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:8-12,2,5,10,Y,40,12,they vainly wandered.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:13-16,3,6,11,N,41,13,"O that my people had me heard,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:13-16,3,6,11,Y,42,13,Isr'el my ways had chose!
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:13-16,3,6,11,N,43,14,"I had their en'mies soon subdu'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:13-16,3,6,11,Y,44,14,my hand turn'd on their foes.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:13-16,3,6,12,N,45,15,The haters of the Lord to him
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:13-16,3,6,12,Y,46,15,submission should have feign'd;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:13-16,3,6,12,N,47,15,"But as for them, their time should have"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:13-16,3,6,12,Y,48,15,for evermore remain'd.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:13-16,3,7,13,N,49,16,He should have also fed them with
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:13-16,3,7,13,Y,50,16,the finest of the wheat;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:13-16,3,7,13,N,51,16,Of honey from the rock thy fill
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),81,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 81:13-16,3,7,13,Y,52,16,I should have made thee eat.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),82,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 82:1-8,1,1,1,N,1,1,In gods' assembly God doth stand;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),82,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 82:1-8,1,1,1,Y,2,1,he judgeth gods among.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),82,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 82:1-8,1,1,1,N,3,2,"How long, accepting persons vile,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),82,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 82:1-8,1,1,1,Y,4,2,will ye give judgment wrong?
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),82,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 82:1-8,1,1,2,N,5,3,Defend the poor and fatherless;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),82,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 82:1-8,1,1,2,Y,6,3,to poor oppress'd do right.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),82,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 82:1-8,1,1,2,N,7,4,The poor and needy ones set free;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),82,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 82:1-8,1,1,2,Y,8,4,rid them from ill men's might.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),82,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 82:1-8,1,2,3,N,9,5,"They know not, nor will understand;"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),82,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 82:1-8,1,2,3,Y,10,5,in darkness they walk on:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),82,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 82:1-8,1,2,3,N,11,5,All the foundations of the earth
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),82,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 82:1-8,1,2,3,Y,12,5,out of their course are gone.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),82,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 82:1-8,1,2,4,N,13,6,"I said that ye are gods, and are"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),82,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 82:1-8,1,2,4,Y,14,6,sons of the Highest all:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),82,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 82:1-8,1,2,4,N,15,7,"But ye shall die like men, and as"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),82,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 82:1-8,1,2,4,Y,16,7,one of the princes fall.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),82,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 82:1-8,1,3,5,N,17,8,"O God, do thou raise up thyself,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),82,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 82:1-8,1,3,5,Y,18,8,the earth to judgment call:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),82,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 82:1-8,1,3,5,N,19,8,"For thou, as thine inheritance,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),82,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 82:1-8,1,3,5,Y,20,8,shalt take the nations all.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),83,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 83:1-4,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Keep not, O God, we thee entreat,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),83,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 83:1-4,1,1,1,Y,2,1,O keep not silence now:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),83,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 83:1-4,1,1,1,N,3,1,"Do thou not hold thy peace, O God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),83,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 83:1-4,1,1,1,Y,4,1,and still no more be thou.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),83,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 83:1-4,1,1,2,N,5,2,"For, lo, thine enemies a noise"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),83,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 83:1-4,1,1,2,Y,6,2,tumultuously have made;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),83,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 83:1-4,1,1,2,N,7,2,And they that haters are of thee
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),83,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 83:1-4,1,1,2,Y,8,2,have lifted up the head.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),83,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 83:1-4,1,2,3,N,9,3,Against thy chosen people they
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),83,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 83:1-4,1,2,3,Y,10,3,do crafty counsel take;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),83,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 83:1-4,1,2,3,N,11,3,And they against thy hidden ones
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),83,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 83:1-4,1,2,3,Y,12,3,do consultations make.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),83,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 83:1-4,1,2,4,N,13,4,"Come, let us cut them off, said they,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),83,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 83:1-4,1,2,4,Y,14,4,"from being a nation,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),83,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 83:1-4,1,2,4,N,15,4,That of the name of Isr'el may
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),83,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 83:1-4,1,2,4,Y,16,4,no more be mention.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),83,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 83:5-13,2,3,5,N,17,5,"For with joint heart they plot, in league"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),83,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 83:5-13,2,3,5,Y,18,5,against thee they combine.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),83,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 83:5-13,2,3,5,N,19,6,"The tents of Edom, Ishm'elites,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),83,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 83:5-13,2,3,5,Y,20,6,Moab's and Hagar's line;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),83,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 83:5-13,2,3,6,N,21,7,"Gebal, and Ammon, Amalek,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),83,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 83:5-13,2,3,6,Y,22,7,"Philistines, those of Tyre;"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),83,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 83:5-13,2,3,6,N,23,8,"And Assur join'd with them, to help"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),83,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 83:5-13,2,3,6,Y,24,8,Lot's children they conspire.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),83,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 83:5-13,2,4,7,N,25,9,"Do to them as to Midian,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),83,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 83:5-13,2,4,7,Y,26,9,Jabin at Kison strand;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),83,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 83:5-13,2,4,7,N,27,10,"And Sis'ra, which at En-dor fell,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),83,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 83:5-13,2,4,7,Y,28,10,as dung to fat the land.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),83,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 83:5-13,2,4,8,N,29,11,Like Oreb and like Zeeb make
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),83,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 83:5-13,2,4,8,Y,30,11,their noble men to fall;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),83,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 83:5-13,2,4,8,N,31,11,"Like Zeba and Zalmunna like,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),83,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 83:5-13,2,4,8,Y,32,11,make thou their princes all;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),83,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 83:5-13,2,5,9,N,33,12,"Who said, For our possession"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),83,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 83:5-13,2,5,9,Y,34,12,let us God's houses take.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),83,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 83:5-13,2,5,9,N,35,13,"My God, them like a wheel, as chaff"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),83,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 83:5-13,2,5,9,Y,36,13,"before the wind, them make."
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),83,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 83:14-18,3,5,10,N,37,14,"As fire consumes the wood, as flame"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),83,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 83:14-18,3,5,10,Y,38,14,"doth mountains set on fire,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),83,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 83:14-18,3,5,10,N,39,15,Chase and affright them with the storm
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),83,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 83:14-18,3,5,10,Y,40,15,and tempest of thine ire.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),83,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 83:14-18,3,6,11,N,41,16,"Their faces fill with shame, O Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),83,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 83:14-18,3,6,11,Y,42,16,that they may seek thy name.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),83,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 83:14-18,3,6,11,N,43,17,"Let them confounded be, and vex'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),83,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 83:14-18,3,6,11,Y,44,17,and perish in their shame:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),83,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 83:14-18,3,6,12,N,45,18,"That men may know that thou, to whom"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),83,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 83:14-18,3,6,12,Y,46,18,alone doth appertain
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),83,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 83:14-18,3,6,12,N,47,18,"The name Jehovah, dost most high"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),83,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 83:14-18,3,6,12,Y,48,18,o'er all the earth remain.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),84,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 84:1-3,1,1,1,N,1,1,"How lovely is thy dwelling-place,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),84,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 84:1-3,1,1,1,Y,2,1,"O Lord of hosts, to me!"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),84,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 84:1-3,1,1,1,N,3,1,The tabernacles of thy grace
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),84,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 84:1-3,1,1,1,Y,4,1,"how pleasant, Lord, they be!"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),84,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 84:1-3,1,1,2,N,5,2,"My thirsty soul longs veh'mently,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),84,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 84:1-3,1,1,2,Y,6,2,"yea faints, thy courts to see:"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),84,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 84:1-3,1,1,2,N,7,2,"My very heart and flesh cry out,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),84,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 84:1-3,1,1,2,Y,8,2,"O living God, for thee."
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),84,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 84:1-3,1,2,3,N,9,3,"Behold, the sparrow findeth out"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),84,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 84:1-3,1,2,3,Y,10,3,an house wherein to rest;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),84,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 84:1-3,1,2,3,N,11,3,The swallow also for herself
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),84,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 84:1-3,1,2,3,Y,12,3,hath purchased a nest;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),84,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 84:1-3,1,2,4,N,13,3,"Ev'n thine own altars, where she safe"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),84,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 84:1-3,1,2,4,Y,14,3,"her young ones forth may bring,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),84,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 84:1-3,1,2,4,N,15,3,"O thou almighty Lord of hosts,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),84,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 84:1-3,1,2,4,Y,16,3,who art my God and King.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),84,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 84:4-7,2,3,5,N,17,4,"Bless'd are they in thy house that dwell,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),84,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 84:4-7,2,3,5,Y,18,4,they ever give thee praise.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),84,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 84:4-7,2,3,5,N,19,5,"Bless'd is the man whose strength thou art,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),84,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 84:4-7,2,3,5,Y,20,5,in whose heart are thy ways:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),84,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 84:4-7,2,3,6,N,21,6,"Who passing thorough Baca's vale,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),84,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 84:4-7,2,3,6,Y,22,6,therein do dig up wells;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),84,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 84:4-7,2,3,6,N,23,6,Also the rain that falleth down
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),84,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 84:4-7,2,3,6,Y,24,6,the pools with water fills.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),84,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 84:4-7,2,4,7,N,25,7,So they from strength unwearied go
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),84,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 84:4-7,2,4,7,Y,26,7,"still forward unto strength,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),84,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 84:4-7,2,4,7,N,27,7,Until in Sion they appear
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),84,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 84:4-7,2,4,7,Y,28,7,before the Lord at length.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),84,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 84:8-12,3,4,8,N,29,8,"Lord God of hosts, my prayer hear;"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),84,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 84:8-12,3,4,8,Y,30,8,"O Jacob's God, give ear."
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),84,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 84:8-12,3,4,8,N,31,9,"See God our shield, look on the face"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),84,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 84:8-12,3,4,8,Y,32,9,of thine anointed dear.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),84,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 84:8-12,3,5,9,N,33,10,For in thy courts one day excels
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),84,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 84:8-12,3,5,9,Y,34,10,a thousand; rather in
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),84,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 84:8-12,3,5,9,N,35,10,"My God's house will I keep a door,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),84,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 84:8-12,3,5,9,Y,36,10,than dwell in tents of sin.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),84,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 84:8-12,3,5,10,N,37,11,For God the Lord's a sun and shield:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),84,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 84:8-12,3,5,10,Y,38,11,he'll grace and glory give;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),84,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 84:8-12,3,5,10,N,39,11,And will withhold no good from them
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),84,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 84:8-12,3,5,10,Y,40,11,that uprightly do live.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),84,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 84:8-12,3,6,11,N,41,12,"O thou that art the Lord of hosts,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),84,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 84:8-12,3,6,11,Y,42,12,"that man is truly blest,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),84,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 84:8-12,3,6,11,N,43,12,Who by assured confidence
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),84,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 84:8-12,3,6,11,Y,44,12,on thee alone doth rest.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),85,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 85:1-7,1,1,1,N,1,1,"O Lord, thou hast been favourable"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),85,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 85:1-7,1,1,1,Y,2,1,to thy beloved land:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),85,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 85:1-7,1,1,1,N,3,1,Jacob's captivity thou hast
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),85,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 85:1-7,1,1,1,Y,4,1,recall'd with mighty hand.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),85,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 85:1-7,1,1,2,N,5,2,Thou pardoned thy people hast
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),85,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 85:1-7,1,1,2,Y,6,2,all their iniquities;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),85,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 85:1-7,1,1,2,N,7,2,Thou all their trespasses and sins
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),85,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 85:1-7,1,1,2,Y,8,2,hast cover'd from thine eyes.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),85,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 85:1-7,1,2,3,N,9,3,"Thou took'st off all thine ire, and turn'dst"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),85,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 85:1-7,1,2,3,Y,10,3,from thy wrath's furiousness.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),85,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 85:1-7,1,2,3,N,11,4,"Turn us, God of our health, and cause"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),85,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 85:1-7,1,2,3,Y,12,4,thy wrath 'gainst us to cease.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),85,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 85:1-7,1,2,4,N,13,5,Shall thy displeasure thus endure
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),85,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 85:1-7,1,2,4,Y,14,5,against us without end?
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),85,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 85:1-7,1,2,4,N,15,5,Wilt thou to generations all
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),85,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 85:1-7,1,2,4,Y,16,5,thine anger forth extend?
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),85,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 85:1-7,1,3,5,N,17,6,"That in thee may thy people joy,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),85,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 85:1-7,1,3,5,Y,18,6,wilt thou not us revive?
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),85,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 85:1-7,1,3,5,N,19,7,"Shew us thy mercy, Lord, to us"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),85,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 85:1-7,1,3,5,Y,20,7,do thy salvation give.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),85,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 85:8-13,2,3,6,N,21,8,I'll hear what God the Lord will speak:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),85,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 85:8-13,2,3,6,Y,22,8,"to his folk he'll speak peace,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),85,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 85:8-13,2,3,6,N,23,8,And to his saints; but let them not
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),85,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 85:8-13,2,3,6,Y,24,8,return to foolishness.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),85,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 85:8-13,2,4,7,N,25,9,To them that fear him surely near
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),85,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 85:8-13,2,4,7,Y,26,9,is his salvation;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),85,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 85:8-13,2,4,7,N,27,9,That glory in our land may have
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),85,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 85:8-13,2,4,7,Y,28,9,her habitation.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),85,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 85:8-13,2,4,8,N,29,10,"Truth met with mercy, righteousness"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),85,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 85:8-13,2,4,8,Y,30,10,and peace kiss'd mutually:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),85,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 85:8-13,2,4,8,N,31,11,"Truth springs from earth, and righteousness"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),85,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 85:8-13,2,4,8,Y,32,11,looks down from heaven high.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),85,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 85:8-13,2,5,9,N,33,12,"Yea, what is good the Lord shall give;"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),85,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 85:8-13,2,5,9,Y,34,12,our land shall yield increase:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),85,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 85:8-13,2,5,9,N,35,13,"Justice, to set us in his steps,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),85,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 85:8-13,2,5,9,Y,36,13,shall go before his face.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:1-5,1,1,1,N,1,1,"O Lord, do thou bow down thine ear,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:1-5,1,1,1,Y,2,1,and hear me graciously;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:1-5,1,1,1,N,3,1,"Because I sore afflicted am,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:1-5,1,1,1,Y,4,1,and am in poverty.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:1-5,1,1,2,N,5,2,"Because I'm holy, let my soul"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:1-5,1,1,2,Y,6,2,by thee preserved be:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:1-5,1,1,2,N,7,2,"O thou my God, thy servant save,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:1-5,1,1,2,Y,8,2,that puts his trust in thee.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:1-5,1,2,3,N,9,3,"Sith unto thee I daily cry,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:1-5,1,2,3,Y,10,3,be merciful to me.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:1-5,1,2,3,N,11,4,"Rejoice thy servant's soul; for, Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:1-5,1,2,3,Y,12,4,I lift my soul to thee.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:1-5,1,2,4,N,13,5,"For thou art gracious, O Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:1-5,1,2,4,Y,14,5,and ready to forgive;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:1-5,1,2,4,N,15,5,"And rich in mercy, all that call"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:1-5,1,2,4,Y,16,5,upon thee to relieve.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:6-10,2,3,5,N,17,6,"Hear, Lord, my pray'r; unto the voice"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:6-10,2,3,5,Y,18,6,of my request attend:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:6-10,2,3,5,N,19,7,In troublous times I'll call on thee;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:6-10,2,3,5,Y,20,7,for thou wilt answer send.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:6-10,2,3,6,N,21,8,"Lord, there is none among the gods"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:6-10,2,3,6,Y,22,8,that may with thee compare;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:6-10,2,3,6,N,23,8,"And like the works which thou hast done,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:6-10,2,3,6,Y,24,8,not any work is there.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:6-10,2,4,7,N,25,9,All nations whom thou mad'st shall come
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:6-10,2,4,7,Y,26,9,and worship rev'rently
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:6-10,2,4,7,N,27,9,"Before thy face; and they, O Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:6-10,2,4,7,Y,28,9,thy name shall glorify.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:6-10,2,4,8,N,29,10,"Because thou art exceeding great,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:6-10,2,4,8,Y,30,10,and works by thee are done
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:6-10,2,4,8,N,31,10,Which are to be admir'd; and thou
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:6-10,2,4,8,Y,32,10,art God thyself alone.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:11-13,3,5,9,N,33,11,"Teach me thy way, and in thy truth,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:11-13,3,5,9,Y,34,11,"O Lord, then walk will I;"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:11-13,3,5,9,N,35,11,"Unite my heart, that I thy name"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:11-13,3,5,9,Y,36,11,may fear continually.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:11-13,3,5,10,N,37,12,"O Lord my God, with all my heart"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:11-13,3,5,10,Y,38,12,to thee I will give praise;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:11-13,3,5,10,N,39,12,And I the glory will ascribe
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:11-13,3,5,10,Y,40,12,unto thy name always:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:11-13,3,6,11,N,41,13,Because thy mercy toward me
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:11-13,3,6,11,Y,42,13,in greatness doth excel;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:11-13,3,6,11,N,43,13,And thou deliver'd hast my soul
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:11-13,3,6,11,Y,44,13,out from the lowest hell.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:14-17,4,6,12,N,45,14,"O God, the proud against me rise,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:14-17,4,6,12,Y,46,14,"and vi'lent men have met,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:14-17,4,6,12,N,47,14,That for my soul have sought; and thee
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:14-17,4,6,12,Y,48,14,before them have not set.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:14-17,4,7,13,N,49,15,"But thou art full of pity, Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:14-17,4,7,13,Y,50,15,"a God most gracious,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:14-17,4,7,13,N,51,15,"Long-suffering, and in thy truth"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:14-17,4,7,13,Y,52,15,and mercy plenteous.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:14-17,4,7,14,N,53,16,"O turn to me thy countenance,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:14-17,4,7,14,Y,54,16,and mercy on me have;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:14-17,4,7,14,N,55,16,"Thy servant strengthen, and the son"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:14-17,4,7,14,Y,56,16,of thine own handmaid save.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:14-17,4,8,15,N,57,17,"Shew me a sign for good, that they"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:14-17,4,8,15,Y,58,17,"which do me hate may see,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:14-17,4,8,15,N,59,17,"And be asham'd; because thou, Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),86,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 86:14-17,4,8,15,Y,60,17,didst help and comfort me.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),87,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 87:1-7,1,1,1,N,1,1,Upon the hills of holiness
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),87,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 87:1-7,1,1,1,Y,2,1,he his foundation sets.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),87,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 87:1-7,1,1,1,N,3,2,"God, more than Jacob's dwellings all,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),87,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 87:1-7,1,1,1,Y,4,2,delights in Sion's gates.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),87,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 87:1-7,1,1,2,N,5,3,"Things glorious are said of thee,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),87,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 87:1-7,1,1,2,Y,6,3,thou city of the Lord.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),87,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 87:1-7,1,1,2,N,7,4,"Rahab and Babel I, to those"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),87,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 87:1-7,1,1,2,Y,8,4,"that know me, will record:"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),87,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 87:1-7,1,2,3,N,9,4,"Behold ev'n Tyrus, and with it"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),87,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 87:1-7,1,2,3,Y,10,4,"the land of Palestine,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),87,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 87:1-7,1,2,3,N,11,4,And likewise Ethiopia;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),87,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 87:1-7,1,2,3,Y,12,4,this man was born therein.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),87,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 87:1-7,1,2,4,N,13,5,"And it of Sion shall be said,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),87,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 87:1-7,1,2,4,Y,14,5,This man and that man there
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),87,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 87:1-7,1,2,4,N,15,5,Was born; and he that is most High
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),87,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 87:1-7,1,2,4,Y,16,5,himself shall stablish her.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),87,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 87:1-7,1,3,5,N,17,6,"When God the people writes, he'll count"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),87,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 87:1-7,1,3,5,Y,18,6,that this man born was there.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),87,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 87:1-7,1,3,5,N,19,7,There be that sing and play; and all
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),87,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 87:1-7,1,3,5,Y,20,7,my well-springs in thee are.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:1-7,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Lord God, my Saviour, day and night"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:1-7,1,1,1,Y,2,1,before thee cry'd have I.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:1-7,1,1,1,N,3,2,Before thee let my prayer come;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:1-7,1,1,1,Y,4,2,give ear unto my cry.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:1-7,1,1,2,N,5,3,For troubles great do fill my soul;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:1-7,1,1,2,Y,6,3,my life draws nigh the grave.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:1-7,1,1,2,N,7,4,I'm counted with those that go down
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:1-7,1,1,2,Y,8,4,"to pit, and no strength have."
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:1-7,1,2,3,N,9,5,"Ev'n free among the dead, like them"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:1-7,1,2,3,Y,10,5,that slain in grave do lie;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:1-7,1,2,3,N,11,5,"Cut off from thy hand, whom no more"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:1-7,1,2,3,Y,12,5,thou hast in memory.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:1-7,1,2,4,N,13,6,"Thou hast me laid in lowest pit,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:1-7,1,2,4,Y,14,6,in deeps and darksome caves.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:1-7,1,2,4,N,15,7,"Thy wrath lies hard on me, thou hast"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:1-7,1,2,4,Y,16,7,me press'd with all thy waves.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:8-12,2,3,5,N,17,8,"Thou hast put far from me my friends,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:8-12,2,3,5,Y,18,8,thou mad'st them to abhor me;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:8-12,2,3,5,N,19,8,"And I am so shut up, that I"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:8-12,2,3,5,Y,20,8,find no evasion for me.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:8-12,2,3,6,N,21,9,By reason of affliction
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:8-12,2,3,6,Y,22,9,mine eye mourns dolefully:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:8-12,2,3,6,N,23,9,"To thee, Lord, do I call, and stretch"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:8-12,2,3,6,Y,24,9,my hands continually.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:8-12,2,4,7,N,25,10,Wilt thou shew wonders to the dead?
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:8-12,2,4,7,Y,26,10,"shall they rise, and thee bless?"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:8-12,2,4,7,N,27,11,Shall in the grave thy love be told?
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:8-12,2,4,7,Y,28,11,in death thy faithfulness?
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:8-12,2,4,8,N,29,12,"Shall thy great wonders in the dark,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:8-12,2,4,8,Y,30,12,or shall thy righteousness
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:8-12,2,4,8,N,31,12,Be known to any in the land
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:8-12,2,4,8,Y,32,12,of deep forgetfulness?
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:13-18,3,5,9,N,33,13,"But, Lord, to thee I cry'd; my pray'r"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:13-18,3,5,9,Y,34,13,at morn prevent shall thee.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:13-18,3,5,9,N,35,14,"Why, Lord, dost thou cast off my soul,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:13-18,3,5,9,Y,36,14,and hid'st thy face from me?
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:13-18,3,5,10,N,37,15,"Distress'd am I, and from my youth"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:13-18,3,5,10,Y,38,15,I ready am to die;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:13-18,3,5,10,N,39,15,"Thy terrors I have borne, and am"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:13-18,3,5,10,Y,40,15,distracted fearfully.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:13-18,3,6,11,N,41,16,The dreadful fierceness of thy wrath
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:13-18,3,6,11,Y,42,16,quite over me doth go:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:13-18,3,6,11,N,43,16,"Thy terrors great have cut me off,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:13-18,3,6,11,Y,44,16,they did pursue me so.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:13-18,3,6,12,N,45,17,"For round about me ev'ry day,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:13-18,3,6,12,Y,46,17,"like water, they did roll;"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:13-18,3,6,12,N,47,17,"And, gathering together, they"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:13-18,3,6,12,Y,48,17,have compassed my soul.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:13-18,3,7,13,N,49,18,"My friends thou hast put far from me,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:13-18,3,7,13,Y,50,18,and him that did me love;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:13-18,3,7,13,N,51,18,And those that mine acquaintance were
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),88,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 88:13-18,3,7,13,Y,52,18,to darkness didst remove.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:1-4,1,1,1,N,1,1,God's mercies I will ever sing;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:1-4,1,1,1,Y,2,1,and with my mouth I shall
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:1-4,1,1,1,N,3,1,Thy faithfulness make to be known
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:1-4,1,1,1,Y,4,1,to generations all.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:1-4,1,1,2,N,5,2,"For mercy shall be built, said I,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:1-4,1,1,2,Y,6,2,for ever to endure;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:1-4,1,1,2,N,7,2,"Thy faithfulness, ev'n in the heav'ns,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:1-4,1,1,2,Y,8,2,thou wilt establish sure.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:1-4,1,2,3,N,9,3,I with my chosen One have made
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:1-4,1,2,3,Y,10,3,a cov'nant graciously;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:1-4,1,2,3,N,11,3,"And to my servant, whom I lov'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:1-4,1,2,3,Y,12,3,to David sworn have I;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:1-4,1,2,4,N,13,4,That I thy seed establish shall
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:1-4,1,2,4,Y,14,4,"for ever to remain,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:1-4,1,2,4,N,15,4,And will to generations all
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:1-4,1,2,4,Y,16,4,thy throne build and maintain.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:5-7,2,3,5,N,17,5,"The praises of thy wonders, Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:5-7,2,3,5,Y,18,5,the heavens shall express;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:5-7,2,3,5,N,19,5,And in the congregation
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:5-7,2,3,5,Y,20,5,of saints thy faithfulness.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:5-7,2,3,6,N,21,6,For who in heaven with the Lord
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:5-7,2,3,6,Y,22,6,may once himself compare?
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:5-7,2,3,6,N,23,6,Who is like God among the sons
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:5-7,2,3,6,Y,24,6,of those that mighty are?
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:5-7,2,4,7,N,25,7,Great fear in meeting of the saints
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:5-7,2,4,7,Y,26,7,is due unto the Lord;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:5-7,2,4,7,N,27,7,And he of all about him should
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:5-7,2,4,7,Y,28,7,with rev'rence be ador'd.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:8-10,3,4,8,N,29,8,"O thou that art the Lord of hosts,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:8-10,3,4,8,Y,30,8,what Lord in mightiness
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:8-10,3,4,8,N,31,8,Is like to thee? who compass'd round
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:8-10,3,4,8,Y,32,8,art with thy faithfulness.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:8-10,3,5,9,N,33,9,Ev'n in the raging of the sea
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:8-10,3,5,9,Y,34,9,thou over it dost reign;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:8-10,3,5,9,N,35,9,"And when the waves thereof do swell,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:8-10,3,5,9,Y,36,9,thou stillest them again.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:8-10,3,5,10,N,37,10,"Rahab in pieces thou didst break,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:8-10,3,5,10,Y,38,10,like one that slaughter'd is;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:8-10,3,5,10,N,39,10,And with thy mighty arm thou hast
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:8-10,3,5,10,Y,40,10,dispers'd thine enemies.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:11-14,4,6,11,N,41,11,"The heav'ns are thine, thou for thine own"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:11-14,4,6,11,Y,42,11,the earth dost also take;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:11-14,4,6,11,N,43,11,"The world, and fulness of the same,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:11-14,4,6,11,Y,44,11,thy pow'r did found and make.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:11-14,4,6,12,N,45,12,The north and south from thee alone
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:11-14,4,6,12,Y,46,12,their first beginning had;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:11-14,4,6,12,N,47,12,Both Tabor mount and Hermon hill
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:11-14,4,6,12,Y,48,12,shall in thy name be glad.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:11-14,4,7,13,N,49,13,"Thou hast an arm that's full of pow'r,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:11-14,4,7,13,Y,50,13,thy hand is great in might;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:11-14,4,7,13,N,51,13,And thy right hand exceedingly
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:11-14,4,7,13,Y,52,13,exalted is in height.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:11-14,4,7,14,N,53,14,Justice and judgment of thy throne
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:11-14,4,7,14,Y,54,14,are made the dwelling-place;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:11-14,4,7,14,N,55,14,"Mercy, accompany'd with truth,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:11-14,4,7,14,Y,56,14,shall go before thy face.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:15-18,5,8,15,N,57,15,O greatly bless'd the people are
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:15-18,5,8,15,Y,58,15,the joyful sound that know;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:15-18,5,8,15,N,59,15,"In brightness of thy face, O Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:15-18,5,8,15,Y,60,15,they ever on shall go.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:15-18,5,8,16,N,61,16,They in thy name shall all the day
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:15-18,5,8,16,Y,62,16,rejoice exceedingly;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:15-18,5,8,16,N,63,16,And in thy righteousness shall they
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:15-18,5,8,16,Y,64,16,exalted be on high.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:15-18,5,9,17,N,65,17,Because the glory of their strength
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:15-18,5,9,17,Y,66,17,doth only stand in thee;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:15-18,5,9,17,N,67,17,And in thy favour shall our horn
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:15-18,5,9,17,Y,68,17,and pow'r exalted be.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:15-18,5,9,18,N,69,18,For God is our defence; and he
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:15-18,5,9,18,Y,70,18,to us doth safety bring:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:15-18,5,9,18,N,71,18,The Holy One of Israel
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:15-18,5,9,18,Y,72,18,is our almighty King.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:19-23,6,10,19,N,73,19,In vision to thy Holy One
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:19-23,6,10,19,Y,74,19,"thou saidst, I help upon"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:19-23,6,10,19,N,75,19,A strong one laid; out of the folk
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:19-23,6,10,19,Y,76,19,I rais'd a chosen one;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:19-23,6,10,20,N,77,20,"Ev'n David, I have found him out"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:19-23,6,10,20,Y,78,20,a servant unto me;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:19-23,6,10,20,N,79,20,And with my holy oil my King
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:19-23,6,10,20,Y,80,20,anointed him to be.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:19-23,6,11,21,N,81,21,With whom my hand shall stablish'd be;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:19-23,6,11,21,Y,82,21,mine arm shall make him strong.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:19-23,6,11,21,N,83,22,"On him the foe shall not exact,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:19-23,6,11,21,Y,84,22,nor son of mischief wrong.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:19-23,6,11,22,N,85,23,I will beat down before his face
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:19-23,6,11,22,Y,86,23,all his malicious foes;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:19-23,6,11,22,N,87,23,I will them greatly plague who do
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:19-23,6,11,22,Y,88,23,with hatred him oppose.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:24-29,7,12,23,N,89,24,My mercy and my faithfulness
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:24-29,7,12,23,Y,90,24,with him yet still shall be;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:24-29,7,12,23,N,91,24,And in my name his horn and pow'r
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:24-29,7,12,23,Y,92,24,men shall exalted see.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:24-29,7,12,24,N,93,25,His hand and pow'r shall reach afar;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:24-29,7,12,24,Y,94,25,I'll set it in the sea;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:24-29,7,12,24,N,95,25,And his right hand established
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:24-29,7,12,24,Y,96,25,shall in the rivers be.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:24-29,7,13,25,N,97,26,"Thou art my Father, he shall cry,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:24-29,7,13,25,Y,98,26,thou art my God alone;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:24-29,7,13,25,N,99,26,"And he shall say, Thou art the Rock"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:24-29,7,13,25,Y,100,26,of my salvation.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:24-29,7,13,26,N,101,27,"I'll make him my first-born, more high"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:24-29,7,13,26,Y,102,27,than kings of any land.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:24-29,7,13,26,N,103,28,"My love I'll ever keep for him,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:24-29,7,13,26,Y,104,28,my cov'nant fast shall stand.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:24-29,7,14,27,N,105,29,His seed I by my pow'r will make
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:24-29,7,14,27,Y,106,29,for ever to endure;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:24-29,7,14,27,N,107,29,"And, as the days of heav'n, his throne"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:24-29,7,14,27,Y,108,29,"shall stable be, and sure."
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:30-37,8,14,28,N,109,30,But if his children shall forsake
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:30-37,8,14,28,Y,110,30,"my laws, and go astray,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:30-37,8,14,28,N,111,30,"And in my judgments shall not walk,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:30-37,8,14,28,Y,112,30,but wander from my way:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:30-37,8,15,29,N,113,31,"If they my laws break, and do not"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:30-37,8,15,29,Y,114,31,keep my commandements;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:30-37,8,15,29,N,115,32,"I'll visit then their faults with rods,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:30-37,8,15,29,Y,116,32,their sins with chastisements.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:30-37,8,15,30,N,117,33,"Yet I'll not take my love from him,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:30-37,8,15,30,Y,118,33,nor false my promise make.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:30-37,8,15,30,N,119,34,"My cov'nant I'll not break, nor change"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:30-37,8,15,30,Y,120,34,what with my mouth I spake.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:30-37,8,16,31,N,121,35,"Once by my holiness I sware,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:30-37,8,16,31,Y,122,35,to David I'll not lie;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:30-37,8,16,31,N,123,36,"His seed and throne shall, as the sun,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:30-37,8,16,31,Y,124,36,before me last for aye.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:30-37,8,16,32,N,125,37,"It, like the moon, shall ever be"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:30-37,8,16,32,Y,126,37,establish'd stedfastly;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:30-37,8,16,32,N,127,37,And like to that which in the heav'n
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:30-37,8,16,32,Y,128,37,doth witness faithfully.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:38-45,9,17,33,N,129,38,"But thou, displeased, hast cast off,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:38-45,9,17,33,Y,130,38,thou didst abhor and loathe;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:38-45,9,17,33,N,131,38,With him that thine anointed is
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:38-45,9,17,33,Y,132,38,thou hast been very wroth.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:38-45,9,17,34,N,133,39,Thou hast thy servant's covenant
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:38-45,9,17,34,Y,134,39,"made void, and quite cast by;"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:38-45,9,17,34,N,135,39,"Thou hast profan'd his crown, while it"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:38-45,9,17,34,Y,136,39,cast on the ground doth lie.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:38-45,9,18,35,N,137,40,"Thou all his hedges hast broke down,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:38-45,9,18,35,Y,138,40,his strong holds down hast torn.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:38-45,9,18,35,N,139,41,"He to all passers-by a spoil,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:38-45,9,18,35,Y,140,41,to neighbours is a scorn.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:38-45,9,18,36,N,141,42,Thou hast set up his foes' right hand;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:38-45,9,18,36,Y,142,42,mad'st all his en'mies glad:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:38-45,9,18,36,N,143,43,"Turn'd his sword's edge, and him to stand"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:38-45,9,18,36,Y,144,43,in battle hast not made.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:38-45,9,19,37,N,145,44,"His glory thou hast made to cease,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:38-45,9,19,37,Y,146,44,his throne to ground down cast;
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:38-45,9,19,37,N,147,45,"Shorten'd his days of youth, and him"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:38-45,9,19,37,Y,148,45,with shame thou cover'd hast.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:46-49,10,19,38,N,149,46,"How long, Lord, wilt thou hide thyself?"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:46-49,10,19,38,Y,150,46,"for ever, in thine ire?"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:46-49,10,19,38,N,151,46,And shall thine indignation
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:46-49,10,19,38,Y,152,46,burn like unto a fire?
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:46-49,10,20,39,N,153,47,"Remember, Lord, how short a time"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:46-49,10,20,39,Y,154,47,I shall on earth remain:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:46-49,10,20,39,N,155,47,O wherefore is it so that thou
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:46-49,10,20,39,Y,156,47,has made all men in vain?
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:46-49,10,20,40,N,157,48,"What man is he that liveth here,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:46-49,10,20,40,Y,158,48,and death shall never see?
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:46-49,10,20,40,N,159,48,Or from the power of the grave
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:46-49,10,20,40,Y,160,48,what man his soul shall free?
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:46-49,10,21,41,N,161,49,"Thy former loving-kindnesses,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:46-49,10,21,41,Y,162,49,"O Lord, where be they now?"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:46-49,10,21,41,N,163,49,Those which in truth and faithfulness
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:46-49,10,21,41,Y,164,49,to David sworn hast thou?
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:50-52,11,21,42,N,165,50,"Mind, Lord, thy servant's sad reproach;"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:50-52,11,21,42,Y,166,50,how I in bosom bear
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:50-52,11,21,42,N,167,50,"The scornings of the people all,"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:50-52,11,21,42,Y,168,50,who strong and mighty are.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:50-52,11,22,43,N,169,51,Wherewith thy raging enemies
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:50-52,11,22,43,Y,170,51,"reproach'd, O Lord, think on;"
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:50-52,11,22,43,N,171,51,Wherewith they have reproach'd the steps
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:50-52,11,22,43,Y,172,51,of thine anointed one.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:50-52,11,22,44,N,173,52,All blessing to the Lord our God
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:50-52,11,22,44,Y,174,52,let be ascribed then:
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:50-52,11,22,44,N,175,52,For evermore so let it be.
1650 Psalter,Book 3 (Psalm 73-89),89,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 89:50-52,11,22,44,Y,176,52,"Amen, yea, and amen."
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:1-4,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Lord, thou hast been our dwelling-place"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:1-4,1,1,1,Y,2,1,in generations all.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:1-4,1,1,1,N,3,2,Before thou ever hadst brought forth
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:1-4,1,1,1,Y,4,2,the mountains great or small;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:1-4,1,1,2,N,5,2,"Ere ever thou hadst form'd the earth,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:1-4,1,1,2,Y,6,2,and all the world abroad;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:1-4,1,1,2,N,7,2,Ev'n thou from everlasting art
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:1-4,1,1,2,Y,8,2,to everlasting God.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:1-4,1,2,3,N,9,3,Thou dost unto destruction
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:1-4,1,2,3,Y,10,3,man that is mortal turn;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:1-4,1,2,3,N,11,3,"And unto them thou say'st, Again,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:1-4,1,2,3,Y,12,3,"ye sons of men, return."
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:1-4,1,2,4,N,13,4,Because a thousand years appear
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:1-4,1,2,4,Y,14,4,no more before thy sight
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:1-4,1,2,4,N,15,4,"Than yesterday, when it is past,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:1-4,1,2,4,Y,16,4,or than a watch by night.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:5-9,2,3,5,N,17,5,As with an overflowing flood
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:5-9,2,3,5,Y,18,5,thou carry'st them away:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:5-9,2,3,5,N,19,5,"They like a sleep are, like the grass"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:5-9,2,3,5,Y,20,5,that grows at morn are they.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:5-9,2,3,6,N,21,6,"At morn it flourishes and grows,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:5-9,2,3,6,Y,22,6,cut down at ev'n doth fade.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:5-9,2,3,6,N,23,7,"For by thine anger we're consum'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:5-9,2,3,6,Y,24,7,thy wrath makes us afraid.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:5-9,2,4,7,N,25,8,Our sins thou and iniquities
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:5-9,2,4,7,Y,26,8,"dost in thy presence place,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:5-9,2,4,7,N,27,8,And sett'st our secret faults before
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:5-9,2,4,7,Y,28,8,the brightness of thy face.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:5-9,2,4,8,N,29,9,For in thine anger all our days
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:5-9,2,4,8,Y,30,9,do pass on to an end;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:5-9,2,4,8,N,31,9,"And as a tale that hath been told,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:5-9,2,4,8,Y,32,9,so we our years do spend.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:10-12,3,5,9,N,33,10,Threescore and ten years do sum up
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:10-12,3,5,9,Y,34,10,"our days and years, we see;"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:10-12,3,5,9,N,35,10,"Or, if, by reason of more strength,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:10-12,3,5,9,Y,36,10,in some fourscore they be:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:10-12,3,5,10,N,37,10,Yet doth the strength of such old men
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:10-12,3,5,10,Y,38,10,but grief and labour prove;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:10-12,3,5,10,N,39,10,"For it is soon cut off, and we"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:10-12,3,5,10,Y,40,10,"fly hence, and soon remove."
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:10-12,3,6,11,N,41,11,Who knows the power of thy wrath?
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:10-12,3,6,11,Y,42,11,according to thy fear
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:10-12,3,6,11,N,43,12,"So is thy wrath: Lord, teach thou us"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:10-12,3,6,11,Y,44,12,our end in mind to bear;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:10-12,3,6,12,N,45,12,"And so to count our days, that we"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:10-12,3,6,12,Y,46,12,our hearts may still apply
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:10-12,3,6,12,N,47,12,"To learn thy wisdom and thy truth,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:10-12,3,6,12,Y,48,12,that we may live thereby.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:13-17,4,7,13,N,49,13,"Turn yet again to us, O Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:13-17,4,7,13,Y,50,13,how long thus shall it be?
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:13-17,4,7,13,N,51,13,Let it repent thee now for those
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:13-17,4,7,13,Y,52,13,that servants are to thee.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:13-17,4,7,14,N,53,14,"O with thy tender mercies, Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:13-17,4,7,14,Y,54,14,us early satisfy;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:13-17,4,7,14,N,55,14,"So we rejoice shall all our days,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:13-17,4,7,14,Y,56,14,and still be glad in thee.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:13-17,4,8,15,N,57,15,"According as the days have been,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:13-17,4,8,15,Y,58,15,"wherein we grief have had,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:13-17,4,8,15,N,59,15,"And years wherein we ill have seen,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:13-17,4,8,15,Y,60,15,so do thou make us glad.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:13-17,4,8,16,N,61,16,O let thy work and pow'r appear
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:13-17,4,8,16,Y,62,16,thy servants' face before;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:13-17,4,8,16,N,63,16,And shew unto their children dear
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:13-17,4,8,16,Y,64,16,thy glory evermore:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:13-17,4,9,17,N,65,17,And let the beauty of the Lord
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:13-17,4,9,17,Y,66,17,our God be us upon:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:13-17,4,9,17,N,67,17,"Our handy-works establish thou,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),90,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 90:13-17,4,9,17,Y,68,17,establish them each one.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:1-4,1,1,1,N,1,1,He that doth in the secret place
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:1-4,1,1,1,Y,2,1,"of the most High reside,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:1-4,1,1,1,N,3,1,Under the shade of him that is
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:1-4,1,1,1,Y,4,1,th' Almighty shall abide.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:1-4,1,1,2,N,5,2,"I of the Lord my God will say,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:1-4,1,1,2,Y,6,2,"He is my refuge still,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:1-4,1,1,2,N,7,2,"He is my fortress, and my God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:1-4,1,1,2,Y,8,2,and in him trust I will.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:1-4,1,2,3,N,9,3,"Assuredly he shall thee save,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:1-4,1,2,3,Y,10,3,and give deliverance
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:1-4,1,2,3,N,11,3,"From subtile fowler's snare, and from"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:1-4,1,2,3,Y,12,3,the noisome pestilence.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:1-4,1,2,4,N,13,4,His feathers shall thee hide; thy trust
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:1-4,1,2,4,Y,14,4,under his wings shall be:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:1-4,1,2,4,N,15,4,His faithfulness shall be a shield
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:1-4,1,2,4,Y,16,4,and buckler unto thee.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:5-8,2,3,5,N,17,5,Thou shalt not need to be afraid
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:5-8,2,3,5,Y,18,5,for terrors of the night;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:5-8,2,3,5,N,19,5,Nor for the arrow that doth fly
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:5-8,2,3,5,Y,20,5,"by day, while it is light;"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:5-8,2,3,6,N,21,6,"Nor for the pestilence, that walks"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:5-8,2,3,6,Y,22,6,in darkness secretly;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:5-8,2,3,6,N,23,6,"Nor for destruction, that doth waste"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:5-8,2,3,6,Y,24,6,at noon-day openly.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:5-8,2,4,7,N,25,7,"A thousand at thy side shall fall,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:5-8,2,4,7,Y,26,7,on thy right hand shall lie
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:5-8,2,4,7,N,27,7,Ten thousand dead; yet unto thee
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:5-8,2,4,7,Y,28,7,it shall not once come nigh.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:5-8,2,4,8,N,29,8,"Only thou with thine eyes shalt look,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:5-8,2,4,8,Y,30,8,and a beholder be;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:5-8,2,4,8,N,31,8,And thou therein the just reward
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:5-8,2,4,8,Y,32,8,of wicked men shalt see.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:9-13,3,5,9,N,33,9,"Because the Lord, who constantly"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:9-13,3,5,9,Y,34,9,"my refuge is alone,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:9-13,3,5,9,N,35,9,"Ev'n the most High, is made by thee"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:9-13,3,5,9,Y,36,9,thy habitation;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:9-13,3,5,10,N,37,10,No plague shall near thy dwelling come;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:9-13,3,5,10,Y,38,10,no ill shall thee befall:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:9-13,3,5,10,N,39,11,For thee to keep in all thy ways
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:9-13,3,5,10,Y,40,11,his angels charge he shall.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:9-13,3,6,11,N,41,12,"They in their hands shall bear thee up,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:9-13,3,6,11,Y,42,12,still waiting thee upon;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:9-13,3,6,11,N,43,12,Lest thou at any time should'st dash
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:9-13,3,6,11,Y,44,12,thy foot against a stone.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:9-13,3,6,12,N,45,13,"Upon the adder thou shalt tread,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:9-13,3,6,12,Y,46,13,and on the lion strong;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:9-13,3,6,12,N,47,13,"Thy feet on dragons trample shall,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:9-13,3,6,12,Y,48,13,and on the lions young.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:14-16,4,7,13,N,49,14,"Because on me he set his love,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:14-16,4,7,13,Y,50,14,I'll save and set him free;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:14-16,4,7,13,N,51,14,"Because my great name he hath known,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:14-16,4,7,13,Y,52,14,I will him set on high.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:14-16,4,7,14,N,53,15,"He'll call on me, I'll answer him;"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:14-16,4,7,14,Y,54,15,I will be with him still
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:14-16,4,7,14,N,55,15,"In trouble, to deliver him,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:14-16,4,7,14,Y,56,15,and honour him I will.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:14-16,4,8,15,N,57,16,With length of days unto his mind
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:14-16,4,8,15,Y,58,16,I will him satisfy;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:14-16,4,8,15,N,59,16,I also my salvation
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),91,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 91:14-16,4,8,15,Y,60,16,will cause his eyes to see.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:1-4,1,1,1,N,1,1,To render thanks unto the Lord
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:1-4,1,1,1,Y,2,1,"it is a comely thing,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:1-4,1,1,1,N,3,1,"And to thy name, O thou most High,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:1-4,1,1,1,Y,4,1,due praise aloud to sing.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:1-4,1,1,2,N,5,2,Thy loving-kindness to shew forth
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:1-4,1,1,2,Y,6,2,when shines the morning light;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:1-4,1,1,2,N,7,2,And to declare thy faithfulness
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:1-4,1,1,2,Y,8,2,with pleasure ev'ry night.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:1-4,1,2,3,N,9,3,"On a ten-stringed instrument,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:1-4,1,2,3,Y,10,3,"upon the psaltery,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:1-4,1,2,3,N,11,3,"And on the harp with solemn sound,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:1-4,1,2,3,Y,12,3,and grave sweet melody.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:1-4,1,2,4,N,13,4,"For thou, Lord, by thy mighty works"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:1-4,1,2,4,Y,14,4,hast made my heart right glad;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:1-4,1,2,4,N,15,4,And I will triumph in the works
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:1-4,1,2,4,Y,16,4,which by thine hands were made.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:5-8,2,3,5,N,17,5,"How great, Lord, are thy works! each thought"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:5-8,2,3,5,Y,18,5,of thine a deep it is:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:5-8,2,3,5,N,19,6,A brutish man it knoweth not;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:5-8,2,3,5,Y,20,6,fools understand not this.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:5-8,2,3,6,N,21,7,When those that lewd and wicked are
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:5-8,2,3,6,Y,22,7,"spring quickly up like grass,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:5-8,2,3,6,N,23,7,And workers of iniquity
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:5-8,2,3,6,Y,24,7,do flourish all apace;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:5-8,2,4,7,N,25,7,It is that they for ever may
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:5-8,2,4,7,Y,26,7,destroyed be and slain;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:5-8,2,4,7,N,27,8,"But thou, O Lord, art the most High,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:5-8,2,4,7,Y,28,8,for ever to remain.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:9-11,3,4,8,N,29,9,"For, lo, thine enemies, O Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:9-11,3,4,8,Y,30,9,thine en'mies perish shall;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:9-11,3,4,8,N,31,9,The workers of iniquity
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:9-11,3,4,8,Y,32,9,shall be dispersed all.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:9-11,3,5,9,N,33,10,"But thou shalt, like unto the horn"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:9-11,3,5,9,Y,34,10,"of th' unicorn, exalt"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:9-11,3,5,9,N,35,10,My horn on high: thou with fresh oil
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:9-11,3,5,9,Y,36,10,anoint me also shalt.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:9-11,3,5,10,N,37,11,Mine eyes shall also my desire
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:9-11,3,5,10,Y,38,11,see on mine enemies;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:9-11,3,5,10,N,39,11,Mine ears shall of the wicked hear
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:9-11,3,5,10,Y,40,11,that do against me rise.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:12-15,4,6,11,N,41,12,But like the palm-tree flourishing
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:12-15,4,6,11,Y,42,12,shall be the righteous one;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:12-15,4,6,11,N,43,12,He shall like to the cedar grow
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:12-15,4,6,11,Y,44,12,that is in Lebanon.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:12-15,4,6,12,N,45,13,Those that within the house of God
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:12-15,4,6,12,Y,46,13,"are planted by his grace,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:12-15,4,6,12,N,47,13,"They shall grow up, and flourish all"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:12-15,4,6,12,Y,48,13,in our God's holy place.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:12-15,4,7,13,N,49,14,"And in old age, when others fade,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:12-15,4,7,13,Y,50,14,they fruit still forth shall bring;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:12-15,4,7,13,N,51,14,"They shall be fat, and full of sap,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:12-15,4,7,13,Y,52,14,and aye be flourishing;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:12-15,4,7,14,N,53,15,To shew that upright is the Lord:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:12-15,4,7,14,Y,54,15,he is a rock to me;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:12-15,4,7,14,N,55,15,And he from all unrighteousness
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),92,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 92:12-15,4,7,14,Y,56,15,is altogether free.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),93,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 93:1-5,1,1,1,N,1,1,"The Lord doth reign, and cloth'd is he"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),93,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 93:1-5,1,1,1,Y,2,1,with majesty most bright;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),93,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 93:1-5,1,1,1,N,3,1,"His works do shew him cloth'd to be,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),93,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 93:1-5,1,1,1,Y,4,1,and girt about with might.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),93,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 93:1-5,1,1,2,N,5,1,"The world is also stablished,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),93,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 93:1-5,1,1,2,Y,6,1,that it cannot depart.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),93,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 93:1-5,1,1,2,N,7,2,"Thy throne is fix'd of old, and thou"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),93,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 93:1-5,1,1,2,Y,8,2,from everlasting art.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),93,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 93:1-5,1,2,3,N,9,3,"The floods, O Lord, have lifted up,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),93,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 93:1-5,1,2,3,Y,10,3,they lifted up their voice;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),93,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 93:1-5,1,2,3,N,11,3,"The floods have lifted up their waves,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),93,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 93:1-5,1,2,3,Y,12,3,and made a mighty noise.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),93,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 93:1-5,1,2,4,N,13,4,"But yet the Lord, that is on high,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),93,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 93:1-5,1,2,4,Y,14,4,is more of might by far
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),93,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 93:1-5,1,2,4,N,15,4,"Than noise of many waters is,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),93,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 93:1-5,1,2,4,Y,16,4,or great sea-billows are.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),93,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 93:1-5,1,3,5,N,17,5,Thy testimonies ev'ry one
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),93,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 93:1-5,1,3,5,Y,18,5,in faithfulness excel;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),93,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 93:1-5,1,3,5,N,19,5,"And holiness for ever, Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),93,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 93:1-5,1,3,5,Y,20,5,thine house becometh well.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:1-4,1,1,1,N,1,1,"O Lord God, unto whom alone"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:1-4,1,1,1,Y,2,1,all vengeance doth belong;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:1-4,1,1,1,N,3,1,"O mighty God, who vengeance own'st,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:1-4,1,1,1,Y,4,1,"shine forth, avenging wrong."
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:1-4,1,1,2,N,5,2,"Lift up thyself, thou of the earth"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:1-4,1,1,2,Y,6,2,the sov'reign Judge that art;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:1-4,1,1,2,N,7,2,And unto those that are so proud
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:1-4,1,1,2,Y,8,2,a due reward impart.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:1-4,1,2,3,N,9,3,"How long, O mighty God, shall they"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:1-4,1,2,3,Y,10,3,"who lewd and wicked be,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:1-4,1,2,3,N,11,3,How long shall they who wicked are
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:1-4,1,2,3,Y,12,3,thus triumph haughtily?
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:1-4,1,2,4,N,13,4,How long shall things most hard by them
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:1-4,1,2,4,Y,14,4,be uttered and told?
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:1-4,1,2,4,N,15,4,And all that work iniquity
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:1-4,1,2,4,Y,16,4,to boast themselves be bold?
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:5-10,2,3,5,N,17,5,"Thy folk they break in pieces, Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:5-10,2,3,5,Y,18,5,thine heritage oppress:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:5-10,2,3,5,N,19,6,"The widow they and stranger slay,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:5-10,2,3,5,Y,20,6,and kill the fatherless.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:5-10,2,3,6,N,21,7,"Yet say they, God it shall not see,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:5-10,2,3,6,Y,22,7,nor God of Jacob know.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:5-10,2,3,6,N,23,8,Ye brutish people! understand;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:5-10,2,3,6,Y,24,8,fools! when wise will ye grow?
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:5-10,2,4,7,N,25,9,"The Lord did plant the ear of man,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:5-10,2,4,7,Y,26,9,and hear then shall not he?
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:5-10,2,4,7,N,27,9,"He only form'd the eye, and then"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:5-10,2,4,7,Y,28,9,shall he not clearly see?
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:5-10,2,4,8,N,29,10,"He that the nations doth correct,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:5-10,2,4,8,Y,30,10,shall he not chastise you?
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:5-10,2,4,8,N,31,10,"He knowledge unto man doth teach,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:5-10,2,4,8,Y,32,10,and shall himself not know?
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:11-15,3,5,9,N,33,11,Man's thoughts to be but vanity
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:11-15,3,5,9,Y,34,11,the Lord doth well discern.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:11-15,3,5,9,N,35,12,"Bless'd is the man thou chast'nest, Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:11-15,3,5,9,Y,36,12,and mak'st thy law to learn:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:11-15,3,5,10,N,37,13,That thou may'st give him rest from days
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:11-15,3,5,10,Y,38,13,"of sad adversity,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:11-15,3,5,10,N,39,13,Until the pit be digg'd for those
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:11-15,3,5,10,Y,40,13,that work iniquity.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:11-15,3,6,11,N,41,14,For sure the Lord will not cast off
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:11-15,3,6,11,Y,42,14,"those that his people be,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:11-15,3,6,11,N,43,14,Neither his own inheritance
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:11-15,3,6,11,Y,44,14,quit and forsake will he:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:11-15,3,6,12,N,45,15,But judgment unto righteousness
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:11-15,3,6,12,Y,46,15,shall yet return again;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:11-15,3,6,12,N,47,15,And all shall follow after it
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:11-15,3,6,12,Y,48,15,that are right-hearted men.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:16-19,4,7,13,N,49,16,Who will rise up for me against
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:16-19,4,7,13,Y,50,16,those that do wickedly?
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:16-19,4,7,13,N,51,16,Who will stand up for me 'gainst those
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:16-19,4,7,13,Y,52,16,that work iniquity?
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:16-19,4,7,14,N,53,17,Unless the Lord had been my help
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:16-19,4,7,14,Y,54,17,"when I was sore opprest,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:16-19,4,7,14,N,55,17,Almost my soul had in the house
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:16-19,4,7,14,Y,56,17,of silence been at rest.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:16-19,4,8,15,N,57,18,"When I had uttered this word,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:16-19,4,8,15,Y,58,18,"(my foot doth slip away,)"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:16-19,4,8,15,N,59,18,"Thy mercy held me up, O Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:16-19,4,8,15,Y,60,18,thy goodness did me stay.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:16-19,4,8,16,N,61,19,Amidst the multitude of thoughts
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:16-19,4,8,16,Y,62,19,"which in my heart do fight,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:16-19,4,8,16,N,63,19,"My soul, lest it be overcharg'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:16-19,4,8,16,Y,64,19,thy comforts do delight.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:20-23,5,9,17,N,65,20,Shall of iniquity the throne
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:20-23,5,9,17,Y,66,20,"have fellowship with thee,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:20-23,5,9,17,N,67,20,"Which mischief, cunningly contriv'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:20-23,5,9,17,Y,68,20,doth by a law decree?
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:20-23,5,9,18,N,69,21,"Against the righteous souls they join,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:20-23,5,9,18,Y,70,21,they guiltless blood condemn.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:20-23,5,9,18,N,71,22,"But of my refuge God's the rock,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:20-23,5,9,18,Y,72,22,and my defence from them.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:20-23,5,10,19,N,73,23,On them their own iniquity
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:20-23,5,10,19,Y,74,23,"the Lord shall bring and lay,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:20-23,5,10,19,N,75,23,And cut them off in their own sin;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),94,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 94:20-23,5,10,19,Y,76,23,our Lord God shall them slay.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),95,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 95:1-5,1,1,1,N,1,1,"O come, let us sing to the Lord:"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),95,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 95:1-5,1,1,1,Y,2,1,"come, let us ev'ry one"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),95,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 95:1-5,1,1,1,N,3,1,A joyful noise make to the Rock
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),95,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 95:1-5,1,1,1,Y,4,1,of our salvation.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),95,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 95:1-5,1,1,2,N,5,2,Let us before his presence come
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),95,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 95:1-5,1,1,2,Y,6,2,with praise and thankful voice;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),95,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 95:1-5,1,1,2,N,7,2,"Let us sing psalms to him with grace,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),95,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 95:1-5,1,1,2,Y,8,2,and make a joyful noise.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),95,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 95:1-5,1,2,3,N,9,3,"For God, a great God, and great King,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),95,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 95:1-5,1,2,3,Y,10,3,above all gods he is.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),95,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 95:1-5,1,2,3,N,11,4,"Depths of the earth are in his hand,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),95,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 95:1-5,1,2,3,Y,12,4,the strength of hills is his.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),95,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 95:1-5,1,2,4,N,13,5,"To him the spacious sea belongs,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),95,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 95:1-5,1,2,4,Y,14,5,for he the same did make;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),95,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 95:1-5,1,2,4,N,15,5,The dry land also from his hands
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),95,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 95:1-5,1,2,4,Y,16,5,its form at first did take.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),95,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 95:6-11,2,3,5,N,17,6,"O come, and let us worship him,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),95,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 95:6-11,2,3,5,Y,18,6,"let us bow down withal,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),95,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 95:6-11,2,3,5,N,19,6,And on our knees before the Lord
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),95,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 95:6-11,2,3,5,Y,20,6,our Maker let us fall.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),95,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 95:6-11,2,3,6,N,21,7,"For he's our God, the people we"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),95,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 95:6-11,2,3,6,Y,22,7,"of his own pasture are,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),95,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 95:6-11,2,3,6,N,23,7,"And of his hand the sheep; to-day,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),95,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 95:6-11,2,3,6,Y,24,7,"if ye his voice will hear,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),95,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 95:6-11,2,4,7,N,25,8,"Then harden not your hearts, as in"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),95,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 95:6-11,2,4,7,Y,26,8,"the provocation,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),95,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 95:6-11,2,4,7,N,27,8,"As in the desert, on the day"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),95,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 95:6-11,2,4,7,Y,28,8,of the tentation:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),95,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 95:6-11,2,4,8,N,29,9,"When me your fathers tempt'd and prov'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),95,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 95:6-11,2,4,8,Y,30,9,and did my working see;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),95,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 95:6-11,2,4,8,N,31,10,Ev'n for the space of forty years
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),95,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 95:6-11,2,4,8,Y,32,10,this race hath grieved me.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),95,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 95:6-11,2,5,9,N,33,10,"I said, This people errs in heart,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),95,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 95:6-11,2,5,9,Y,34,10,my ways they do not know:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),95,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 95:6-11,2,5,9,N,35,11,"To whom I sware in wrath, that to"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),95,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 95:6-11,2,5,9,Y,36,11,my rest they should not go.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),96,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 96:1-5,1,1,1,N,1,1,O sing a new song to the Lord:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),96,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 96:1-5,1,1,1,Y,2,1,sing all the earth to God.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),96,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 96:1-5,1,1,1,N,3,2,"To God sing, bless his name, shew still"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),96,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 96:1-5,1,1,1,Y,4,2,his saving health abroad.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),96,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 96:1-5,1,1,2,N,5,3,Among the heathen nations
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),96,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 96:1-5,1,1,2,Y,6,3,his glory do declare;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),96,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 96:1-5,1,1,2,N,7,3,And unto all the people shew
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),96,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 96:1-5,1,1,2,Y,8,3,his works that wondrous are.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),96,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 96:1-5,1,2,3,N,9,4,"For great's the Lord, and greatly he"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),96,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 96:1-5,1,2,3,Y,10,4,is to be magnify'd;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),96,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 96:1-5,1,2,3,N,11,4,"Yea, worthy to be fear'd is he"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),96,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 96:1-5,1,2,3,Y,12,4,above all gods beside.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),96,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 96:1-5,1,2,4,N,13,5,"For all the gods are idols dumb,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),96,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 96:1-5,1,2,4,Y,14,5,which blinded nations fear;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),96,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 96:1-5,1,2,4,N,15,5,"But our God is the Lord, by whom"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),96,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 96:1-5,1,2,4,Y,16,5,the heav'ns created were.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),96,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 96:6-9,2,3,5,N,17,6,"Great honour is before his face,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),96,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 96:6-9,2,3,5,Y,18,6,and majesty divine;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),96,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 96:6-9,2,3,5,N,19,6,"Strength is within his holy place,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),96,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 96:6-9,2,3,5,Y,20,6,and there doth beauty shine.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),96,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 96:6-9,2,3,6,N,21,7,"Do ye ascribe unto the Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),96,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 96:6-9,2,3,6,Y,22,7,"of people ev'ry tribe,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),96,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 96:6-9,2,3,6,N,23,7,"Glory do ye unto the Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),96,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 96:6-9,2,3,6,Y,24,7,and mighty pow'r ascribe.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),96,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 96:6-9,2,4,7,N,25,8,Give ye the glory to the Lord
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),96,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 96:6-9,2,4,7,Y,26,8,that to his name is due;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),96,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 96:6-9,2,4,7,N,27,8,"Come ye into his courts, and bring"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),96,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 96:6-9,2,4,7,Y,28,8,an offering with you.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),96,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 96:6-9,2,4,8,N,29,9,"In beauty of his holiness,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),96,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 96:6-9,2,4,8,Y,30,9,O do the Lord adore;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),96,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 96:6-9,2,4,8,N,31,9,Likewise let all the earth throughout
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),96,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 96:6-9,2,4,8,Y,32,9,tremble his face before.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),96,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 96:10-13,3,5,9,N,33,10,"Among the heathen say, God reigns;"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),96,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 96:10-13,3,5,9,Y,34,10,the world shall stedfastly
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),96,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 96:10-13,3,5,9,N,35,10,Be fix'd from moving; he shall judge
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),96,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 96:10-13,3,5,9,Y,36,10,the people righteously.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),96,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 96:10-13,3,5,10,N,37,11,"Let heav'ns be glad before the Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),96,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 96:10-13,3,5,10,Y,38,11,and let the earth rejoice;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),96,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 96:10-13,3,5,10,N,39,11,"Let seas, and all that is therein,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),96,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 96:10-13,3,5,10,Y,40,11,"cry out, and make a noise."
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),96,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 96:10-13,3,6,11,N,41,12,"Let fields rejoice, and ev'ry thing"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),96,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 96:10-13,3,6,11,Y,42,12,that springeth of the earth:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),96,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 96:10-13,3,6,11,N,43,12,Then woods and ev'ry tree shall sing
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),96,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 96:10-13,3,6,11,Y,44,12,with gladness and with mirth
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),96,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 96:10-13,3,6,12,N,45,13,"Before the Lord; because he comes,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),96,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 96:10-13,3,6,12,Y,46,13,to judge the earth comes he:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),96,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 96:10-13,3,6,12,N,47,13,"He'll judge the world with righteousness,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),96,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 96:10-13,3,6,12,Y,48,13,the people faithfully.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),97,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 97:1-7,1,1,1,N,1,1,"God reigneth, let the earth be glad,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),97,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 97:1-7,1,1,1,Y,2,1,and isles rejoice each one.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),97,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 97:1-7,1,1,1,N,3,2,Dark clouds him compass; and in right
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),97,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 97:1-7,1,1,1,Y,4,2,with judgment dwells his throne.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),97,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 97:1-7,1,1,2,N,5,3,"Fire goes before him, and his foes"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),97,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 97:1-7,1,1,2,Y,6,3,it burns up round about:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),97,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 97:1-7,1,1,2,N,7,4,His lightnings lighten did the world;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),97,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 97:1-7,1,1,2,Y,8,4,"earth saw, and shook throughout."
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),97,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 97:1-7,1,2,3,N,9,5,"Hills at the presence of the Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),97,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 97:1-7,1,2,3,Y,10,5,"like wax, did melt away;"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),97,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 97:1-7,1,2,3,N,11,5,Ev'n at the presence of the Lord
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),97,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 97:1-7,1,2,3,Y,12,5,"of all the earth, I say."
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),97,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 97:1-7,1,2,4,N,13,6,"The heav'ns declare his righteousness,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),97,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 97:1-7,1,2,4,Y,14,6,all men his glory see.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),97,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 97:1-7,1,2,4,N,15,7,"All who serve graven images,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),97,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 97:1-7,1,2,4,Y,16,7,confounded let them be.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),97,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 97:1-7,1,3,5,N,17,7,"Who do of idols boast themselves,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),97,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 97:1-7,1,3,5,Y,18,7,let shame upon them fall:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),97,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 97:1-7,1,3,5,N,19,7,"Ye that are called gods, see that"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),97,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 97:1-7,1,3,5,Y,20,7,ye do him worship all.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),97,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 97:8-12,2,3,6,N,21,8,"Sion did hear, and joyful was,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),97,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 97:8-12,2,3,6,Y,22,8,glad Judah's daughters were;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),97,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 97:8-12,2,3,6,N,23,8,"They much rejoic'd, O Lord, because"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),97,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 97:8-12,2,3,6,Y,24,8,thy judgments did appear.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),97,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 97:8-12,2,4,7,N,25,9,"For thou, O Lord, art high above"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),97,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 97:8-12,2,4,7,Y,26,9,all things on earth that are;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),97,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 97:8-12,2,4,7,N,27,9,Above all other gods thou art
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),97,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 97:8-12,2,4,7,Y,28,9,exalted very far.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),97,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 97:8-12,2,4,8,N,29,10,"Hate ill, all ye that love the Lord:"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),97,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 97:8-12,2,4,8,Y,30,10,his saints' souls keepeth he;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),97,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 97:8-12,2,4,8,N,31,10,And from the hands of wicked men
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),97,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 97:8-12,2,4,8,Y,32,10,he sets them safe and free.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),97,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 97:8-12,2,5,9,N,33,11,For all those that be righteous
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),97,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 97:8-12,2,5,9,Y,34,11,"sown is a joyful light,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),97,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 97:8-12,2,5,9,N,35,11,And gladness sown is for all those
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),97,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 97:8-12,2,5,9,Y,36,11,that are in heart upright.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),97,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 97:8-12,2,5,10,N,37,12,"Ye righteous, in the Lord rejoice;"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),97,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 97:8-12,2,5,10,Y,38,12,"express your thankfulness,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),97,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 97:8-12,2,5,10,N,39,12,When ye into your memory
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),97,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 97:8-12,2,5,10,Y,40,12,do call his holiness.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),98,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 98:1-3,1,1,1,N,1,1,"O sing a new song to the Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),98,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 98:1-3,1,1,1,Y,2,1,for wonders he hath done:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),98,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 98:1-3,1,1,1,N,3,1,His right hand and his holy arm
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),98,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 98:1-3,1,1,1,Y,4,1,him victory hath won.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),98,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 98:1-3,1,1,2,N,5,2,The Lord God his salvation
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),98,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 98:1-3,1,1,2,Y,6,2,hath caused to be known;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),98,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 98:1-3,1,1,2,N,7,2,His justice in the heathen's sight
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),98,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 98:1-3,1,1,2,Y,8,2,he openly hath shown.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),98,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 98:1-3,1,2,3,N,9,3,He mindful of his grace and truth
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),98,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 98:1-3,1,2,3,Y,10,3,to Isr'el's house hath been;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),98,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 98:1-3,1,2,3,N,11,3,And the salvation of our God
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),98,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 98:1-3,1,2,3,Y,12,3,all ends of th' earth have seen.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),98,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 98:4-9,2,2,4,N,13,4,Let all the earth unto the Lord
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),98,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 98:4-9,2,2,4,Y,14,4,send forth a joyful noise;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),98,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 98:4-9,2,2,4,N,15,4,"Lift up your voice aloud to him,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),98,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 98:4-9,2,2,4,Y,16,4,"sing praises, and rejoice."
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),98,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 98:4-9,2,3,5,N,17,5,"With harp, with harp, and voice of psalms,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),98,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 98:4-9,2,3,5,Y,18,5,unto Jehovah sing:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),98,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 98:4-9,2,3,5,N,19,6,"With trumpets, cornets, gladly sound"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),98,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 98:4-9,2,3,5,Y,20,6,before the Lord the King.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),98,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 98:4-9,2,3,6,N,21,7,Let seas and all their fulness roar;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),98,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 98:4-9,2,3,6,Y,22,7,"the world, and dwellers there;"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),98,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 98:4-9,2,3,6,N,23,8,"Let floods clap hands, and let the hills"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),98,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 98:4-9,2,3,6,Y,24,8,together joy declare
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),98,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 98:4-9,2,4,7,N,25,9,"Before the Lord; because he comes,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),98,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 98:4-9,2,4,7,Y,26,9,to judge the earth comes he:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),98,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 98:4-9,2,4,7,N,27,9,"He'll judge the world with righteousness,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),98,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 98:4-9,2,4,7,Y,28,9,his folk with equity.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),99,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 99:1-5,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Th' eternal Lord doth reign as king,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),99,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 99:1-5,1,1,1,Y,2,1,let all the people quake;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),99,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 99:1-5,1,1,1,N,3,1,"He sits between the cherubims,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),99,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 99:1-5,1,1,1,Y,4,1,let th' earth be mov'd and shake.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),99,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 99:1-5,1,1,2,N,5,2,The Lord in Sion great and high
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),99,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 99:1-5,1,1,2,Y,6,2,above all people is;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),99,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 99:1-5,1,1,2,N,7,3,Thy great and dreadful name (for it
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),99,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 99:1-5,1,1,2,Y,8,3,is holy) let them bless.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),99,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 99:1-5,1,2,3,N,9,4,The king's strength also judgment loves;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),99,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 99:1-5,1,2,3,Y,10,4,thou settlest equity:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),99,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 99:1-5,1,2,3,N,11,4,Just judgment thou dost execute
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),99,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 99:1-5,1,2,3,Y,12,4,in Jacob righteously.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),99,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 99:1-5,1,2,4,N,13,5,"The Lord our God exalt on high,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),99,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 99:1-5,1,2,4,Y,14,5,and rev'rently do ye
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),99,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 99:1-5,1,2,4,N,15,5,Before his footstool worship him:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),99,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 99:1-5,1,2,4,Y,16,5,the Holy One is he.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),99,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 99:6-9,2,3,5,N,17,6,"Moses and Aaron 'mong his priests,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),99,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 99:6-9,2,3,5,Y,18,6,"Samuel, with them that call"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),99,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 99:6-9,2,3,5,N,19,6,"Upon his name: these call'd on God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),99,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 99:6-9,2,3,5,Y,20,6,and he them answer'd all.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),99,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 99:6-9,2,3,6,N,21,7,Within the pillar of the cloud
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),99,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 99:6-9,2,3,6,Y,22,7,he unto them did speak:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),99,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 99:6-9,2,3,6,N,23,7,"The testimonies he them taught,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),99,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 99:6-9,2,3,6,Y,24,7,"and laws, they did not break."
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),99,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 99:6-9,2,4,7,N,25,8,"Thou answer'dst them, O Lord our God;"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),99,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 99:6-9,2,4,7,Y,26,8,thou wast a God that gave
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),99,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 99:6-9,2,4,7,N,27,8,"Pardon to them, though on their deeds"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),99,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 99:6-9,2,4,7,Y,28,8,thou wouldest vengeance have.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),99,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 99:6-9,2,4,8,N,29,9,"Do ye exalt the Lord our God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),99,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 99:6-9,2,4,8,Y,30,9,and at his holy hill
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),99,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 99:6-9,2,4,8,N,31,9,Do ye him worship: for the Lord
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),99,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 99:6-9,2,4,8,Y,32,9,our God is holy still.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),100,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 100:1-5 I,1,1,1,N,1,1,"O all ye lands, unto the Lord"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),100,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 100:1-5 I,1,1,1,Y,2,1,make ye a joyful noise.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),100,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 100:1-5 I,1,1,1,N,3,2,"Serve God with gladness, him before"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),100,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 100:1-5 I,1,1,1,Y,4,2,come with a singing voice.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),100,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 100:1-5 I,1,1,2,N,5,3,Know ye the Lord that he is God;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),100,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 100:1-5 I,1,1,2,Y,6,3,"not we, but he us made:"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),100,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 100:1-5 I,1,1,2,N,7,3,"We are his people, and the sheep"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),100,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 100:1-5 I,1,1,2,Y,8,3,within his pasture fed.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),100,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 100:1-5 I,1,2,3,N,9,4,"Enter his gates and courts with praise,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),100,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 100:1-5 I,1,2,3,Y,10,4,to thank him go ye thither:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),100,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 100:1-5 I,1,2,3,N,11,4,"To him express your thankfulness,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),100,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 100:1-5 I,1,2,3,Y,12,4,and bless his name together.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),100,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 100:1-5 I,1,2,4,N,13,5,"Because the Lord our God is good,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),100,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 100:1-5 I,1,2,4,Y,14,5,his mercy faileth never;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),100,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 100:1-5 I,1,2,4,N,15,5,And to all generations
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),100,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 100:1-5 I,1,2,4,Y,16,5,his truth endureth ever.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),101,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 101:1-4,1,1,1,N,1,1,"I mercy will and judgment sing,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),101,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 101:1-4,1,1,1,Y,2,1,"Lord, I will sing to thee."
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),101,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 101:1-4,1,1,1,N,3,2,With wisdom in a perfect way
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),101,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 101:1-4,1,1,1,Y,4,2,shall my behaviour be.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),101,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 101:1-4,1,1,2,N,5,2,"O when, in kindness unto me,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),101,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 101:1-4,1,1,2,Y,6,2,wilt thou be pleas'd to come?
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),101,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 101:1-4,1,1,2,N,7,2,I with a perfect heart will walk
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),101,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 101:1-4,1,1,2,Y,8,2,within my house at home.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),101,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 101:1-4,1,2,3,N,9,3,I will endure no wicked thing
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),101,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 101:1-4,1,2,3,Y,10,3,before mine eyes to be:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),101,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 101:1-4,1,2,3,N,11,3,"I hate their work that turn aside,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),101,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 101:1-4,1,2,3,Y,12,3,it shall not cleave to me.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),101,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 101:1-4,1,2,4,N,13,4,A stubborn and a froward heart
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),101,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 101:1-4,1,2,4,Y,14,4,depart quite from me shall;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),101,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 101:1-4,1,2,4,N,15,4,A person giv'n to wickedness
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),101,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 101:1-4,1,2,4,Y,16,4,I will not know at all.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),101,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 101:5-8,2,3,5,N,17,5,I'll cut him off that slandereth
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),101,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 101:5-8,2,3,5,Y,18,5,his neighbour privily:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),101,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 101:5-8,2,3,5,N,19,5,"The haughty heart I will not bear,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),101,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 101:5-8,2,3,5,Y,20,5,nor him that looketh high.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),101,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 101:5-8,2,3,6,N,21,6,Upon the faithful of the land
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),101,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 101:5-8,2,3,6,Y,22,6,"mine eyes shall be, that they"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),101,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 101:5-8,2,3,6,N,23,6,May dwell with me: he shall me serve
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),101,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 101:5-8,2,3,6,Y,24,6,that walks in perfect way.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),101,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 101:5-8,2,4,7,N,25,7,Who of deceit a worker is
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),101,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 101:5-8,2,4,7,Y,26,7,in my house shall not dwell;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),101,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 101:5-8,2,4,7,N,27,7,And in my presence shall he not
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),101,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 101:5-8,2,4,7,Y,28,7,remain that lies doth tell.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),101,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 101:5-8,2,4,8,N,29,8,"Yea, all the wicked of the land"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),101,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 101:5-8,2,4,8,Y,30,8,early destroy will I;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),101,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 101:5-8,2,4,8,N,31,8,All from God's city to cut off
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),101,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 101:5-8,2,4,8,Y,32,8,that work iniquity.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:1-7 I,1,1,1,N,1,1,"O Lord, unto my pray'r give ear,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:1-7 I,1,1,1,Y,2,1,my cry let come to thee;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:1-7 I,1,1,1,N,3,2,And in the day of my distress
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:1-7 I,1,1,1,Y,4,2,hide not thy face from me.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:1-7 I,1,1,2,N,5,2,"Give ear to me; what time I call,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:1-7 I,1,1,2,Y,6,2,to answer me make haste:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:1-7 I,1,1,2,N,7,3,"For, as an hearth, my bones are burnt,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:1-7 I,1,1,2,Y,8,3,"my days, like smoke, do waste."
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:1-7 I,1,2,3,N,9,4,"My heart within me smitten is,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:1-7 I,1,2,3,Y,10,4,and it is withered
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:1-7 I,1,2,3,N,11,4,Like very grass; so that I do
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:1-7 I,1,2,3,Y,12,4,forget to eat my bread.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:1-7 I,1,2,4,N,13,5,By reason of my groaning voice
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:1-7 I,1,2,4,Y,14,5,my bones cleave to my skin.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:1-7 I,1,2,4,N,15,6,Like pelican in wilderness
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:1-7 I,1,2,4,Y,16,6,forsaken I have been:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:1-7 I,1,3,5,N,17,6,"I like an owl in desert am,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:1-7 I,1,3,5,Y,18,6,that nightly there doth moan;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:1-7 I,1,3,5,N,19,7,"I watch, and like a sparrow am"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:1-7 I,1,3,5,Y,20,7,on the house-top alone.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:8-12 I,2,3,6,N,21,8,My bitter en'mies all the day
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:8-12 I,2,3,6,Y,22,8,reproaches cast on me;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:8-12 I,2,3,6,N,23,8,"And, being mad at me, with rage"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:8-12 I,2,3,6,Y,24,8,against me sworn they be.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:8-12 I,2,4,7,N,25,9,For why? I ashes eaten have
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:8-12 I,2,4,7,Y,26,9,"like bread, in sorrows deep;"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:8-12 I,2,4,7,N,27,9,My drink I also mingled have
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:8-12 I,2,4,7,Y,28,9,with tears that I did weep.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:8-12 I,2,4,8,N,29,10,Thy wrath and indignation
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:8-12 I,2,4,8,Y,30,10,did cause this grief and pain;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:8-12 I,2,4,8,N,31,10,"For thou hast lift me up on high,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:8-12 I,2,4,8,Y,32,10,and cast me down again.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:8-12 I,2,5,9,N,33,11,"My days are like unto a shade,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:8-12 I,2,5,9,Y,34,11,which doth declining pass;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:8-12 I,2,5,9,N,35,11,"And I am dry'd and withered,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:8-12 I,2,5,9,Y,36,11,ev'n like unto the grass.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:8-12 I,2,5,10,N,37,12,"But thou, Lord, everlasting art,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:8-12 I,2,5,10,Y,38,12,and thy remembrance shall
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:8-12 I,2,5,10,N,39,12,"Continually endure, and be"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:8-12 I,2,5,10,Y,40,12,to generations all.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:13-15 I,3,6,11,N,41,13,"Thou shalt arise, and mercy have"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:13-15 I,3,6,11,Y,42,13,upon thy Sion yet;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:13-15 I,3,6,11,N,43,13,"The time to favour her is come,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:13-15 I,3,6,11,Y,44,13,the time that thou hast set.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:13-15 I,3,6,12,N,45,14,For in her rubbish and her stones
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:13-15 I,3,6,12,Y,46,14,thy servants pleasure take;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:13-15 I,3,6,12,N,47,14,"Yea, they the very dust thereof"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:13-15 I,3,6,12,Y,48,14,do favour for her sake.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:13-15 I,3,7,13,N,49,15,So shall the heathen people fear
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:13-15 I,3,7,13,Y,50,15,the Lord's most holy name;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:13-15 I,3,7,13,N,51,15,And all the kings on earth shall dread
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:13-15 I,3,7,13,Y,52,15,thy glory and thy fame.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:16-18 I,4,7,14,N,53,16,When Sion by the mighty Lord
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:16-18 I,4,7,14,Y,54,16,"built up again shall be,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:16-18 I,4,7,14,N,55,16,In glory then and majesty
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:16-18 I,4,7,14,Y,56,16,to men appear shall he.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:16-18 I,4,8,15,N,57,17,The prayer of the destitute
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:16-18 I,4,8,15,Y,58,17,he surely will regard;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:16-18 I,4,8,15,N,59,17,"Their prayer will he not despise,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:16-18 I,4,8,15,Y,60,17,by him it shall be heard.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:16-18 I,4,8,16,N,61,18,For generations yet to come
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:16-18 I,4,8,16,Y,62,18,this shall be on record:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:16-18 I,4,8,16,N,63,18,So shall the people that shall be
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:16-18 I,4,8,16,Y,64,18,created praise the Lord.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:19-22 I,5,9,17,N,65,19,He from his sanctuary's height
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:19-22 I,5,9,17,Y,66,19,hath downward cast his eye;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:19-22 I,5,9,17,N,67,19,And from his glorious throne in heav'n
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:19-22 I,5,9,17,Y,68,19,the Lord the earth did spy;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:19-22 I,5,9,18,N,69,20,That of the mournful prisoner
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:19-22 I,5,9,18,Y,70,20,"the groanings he might hear,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:19-22 I,5,9,18,N,71,20,To set them free that unto death
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:19-22 I,5,9,18,Y,72,20,by men appointed are:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:19-22 I,5,10,19,N,73,21,That they in Sion may declare
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:19-22 I,5,10,19,Y,74,21,"the Lord's most holy name,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:19-22 I,5,10,19,N,75,21,And publish in Jerusalem
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:19-22 I,5,10,19,Y,76,21,the praises of the same;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:19-22 I,5,10,20,N,77,22,When as the people gather shall
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:19-22 I,5,10,20,Y,78,22,"in troops with one accord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:19-22 I,5,10,20,N,79,22,When kingdoms shall assembled be
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:19-22 I,5,10,20,Y,80,22,to serve the highest Lord.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:23-24 I,6,11,21,N,81,23,My wonted strength and force he hath
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:23-24 I,6,11,21,Y,82,23,"abated in the way,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:23-24 I,6,11,21,N,83,23,And he my days hath shortened:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:23-24 I,6,11,21,Y,84,24,"Thus therefore did I say,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:23-24 I,6,11,22,N,85,24,"My God, in mid-time of my days"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:23-24 I,6,11,22,Y,86,24,take thou me not away:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:23-24 I,6,11,22,N,87,24,From age to age eternally
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:23-24 I,6,11,22,Y,88,24,thy years endure and stay.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:25-28 I,7,12,23,N,89,25,The firm foundation of the earth
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:25-28 I,7,12,23,Y,90,25,of old time thou hast laid;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:25-28 I,7,12,23,N,91,25,The heavens also are the work
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:25-28 I,7,12,23,Y,92,25,which thine own hands have made.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:25-28 I,7,12,24,N,93,26,"Thou shalt for evermore endure,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:25-28 I,7,12,24,Y,94,26,but they shall perish all;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:25-28 I,7,12,24,N,95,26,"Yea, ev'ry one of them wax old,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:25-28 I,7,12,24,Y,96,26,"like to a garment, shall:"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:25-28 I,7,13,25,N,97,26,"Thou, as a vesture, shalt them change,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:25-28 I,7,13,25,Y,98,26,and they shall changed be:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:25-28 I,7,13,25,N,99,27,"But thou the same art, and thy years"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:25-28 I,7,13,25,Y,100,27,are to eternity.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:25-28 I,7,13,26,N,101,28,The children of thy servants shall
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:25-28 I,7,13,26,Y,102,28,continually endure;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:25-28 I,7,13,26,N,103,28,"And in thy sight, O Lord, their seed"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 102:25-28 I,7,13,26,Y,104,28,shall be establish'd sure.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:1-7 II,1,13,1,N,1,1,"Lord, hear my pray'r, and let my cry"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:1-7 II,1,13,1,N,2,1,Have speedy access unto thee;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:1-7 II,1,13,1,N,3,2,In day of my calamity
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:1-7 II,1,13,1,N,4,2,O hide not thou thy face from me.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:1-7 II,1,13,2,N,5,2,Hear when I call to thee; that day
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:1-7 II,1,13,2,N,6,2,An answer speedily return:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:1-7 II,1,13,2,N,7,3,"My days, like smoke, consume away,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:1-7 II,1,13,2,N,8,3,"And, as an hearth, my bones do burn."
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:1-7 II,1,14,3,N,9,4,"My heart is wounded very sore,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:1-7 II,1,14,3,N,10,4,"And withered, like grass doth fade:"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:1-7 II,1,14,3,N,11,4,I am forgetful grown therefore
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:1-7 II,1,14,3,N,12,4,To take and eat my daily bread.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:1-7 II,1,14,4,N,13,5,"By reason of my smart within,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:1-7 II,1,14,4,N,14,5,"And voice of my most grievous groans,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:1-7 II,1,14,4,N,15,5,"My flesh consumed is, my skin,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:1-7 II,1,14,4,N,16,5,"All parch'd, doth cleave unto my bones."
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:1-7 II,1,15,5,N,17,6,"The pelican of wilderness,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:1-7 II,1,15,5,N,18,6,"The owl in desert, I do match;"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:1-7 II,1,15,5,N,19,7,"And, sparrow-like, companionless,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:1-7 II,1,15,5,N,20,7,"Upon the house's top, I watch."
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:8-12 II,2,15,6,N,21,8,"I all day long am made a scorn,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:8-12 II,2,15,6,N,22,8,Reproach'd by my malicious foes:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:8-12 II,2,15,6,N,23,8,"The madmen are against me sworn,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:8-12 II,2,15,6,N,24,8,The men against me that arose.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:8-12 II,2,16,7,N,25,9,"For I have ashes eaten up,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:8-12 II,2,16,7,N,26,9,To me as if they had been bread;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:8-12 II,2,16,7,N,27,9,And with my drink I in my cup
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:8-12 II,2,16,7,N,28,9,Of bitter tears a mixture made.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:8-12 II,2,16,8,N,29,10,"Because thy wrath was not appeas'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:8-12 II,2,16,8,N,30,10,And dreadful indignation:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:8-12 II,2,16,8,N,31,10,"Therefore it was that thou me rais'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:8-12 II,2,16,8,N,32,10,And thou again didst cast me down.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:8-12 II,2,17,9,N,33,11,"My days are like a shade alway,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:8-12 II,2,17,9,N,34,11,Which doth declining swiftly pass;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:8-12 II,2,17,9,N,35,11,"And I am withered away,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:8-12 II,2,17,9,N,36,11,Much like unto the fading grass.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:8-12 II,2,17,10,N,37,12,"But thou, O Lord, shalt still endure,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:8-12 II,2,17,10,N,38,12,"From change and all mutation free,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:8-12 II,2,17,10,N,39,12,And to all generations sure
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:8-12 II,2,17,10,N,40,12,Shall thy remembrance ever be.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:13-15 II,3,18,11,N,41,13,"Thou shalt arise, and mercy yet"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:13-15 II,3,18,11,N,42,13,Thou to mount Sion shalt extend:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:13-15 II,3,18,11,N,43,13,"Her time for favour which was set,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:13-15 II,3,18,11,N,44,13,"Behold, is now come to an end."
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:13-15 II,3,18,12,N,45,14,"Thy saints take pleasure in her stones,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:13-15 II,3,18,12,N,46,14,Her very dust to them is dear.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:13-15 II,3,18,12,N,47,15,All heathen lands and kingly thrones
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:13-15 II,3,18,12,N,48,15,On earth thy glorious name shall fear.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:16-22 II,4,19,13,N,49,16,"God in his glory shall appear,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:16-22 II,4,19,13,N,50,16,When Sion he builds and repairs.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:16-22 II,4,19,13,N,51,17,He shall regard and lend his ear
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:16-22 II,4,19,13,N,52,17,Unto the needy's humble pray'rs:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:16-22 II,4,19,14,N,53,17,Th' afflicted's pray'r he will not scorn.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:16-22 II,4,19,14,N,54,18,All times this shall be on record:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:16-22 II,4,19,14,N,55,18,And generations yet unborn
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:16-22 II,4,19,14,N,56,18,Shall praise and magnify the Lord.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:16-22 II,4,20,15,N,57,19,"He from his holy place look'd down,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:16-22 II,4,20,15,N,58,19,The earth he view'd from heav'n on high;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:16-22 II,4,20,15,N,59,20,"To hear the pris'ner's mourning groan,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:16-22 II,4,20,15,N,60,20,And free them that are doom'd to die;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:16-22 II,4,20,16,N,61,21,"That Sion, and Jerus'lem too,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:16-22 II,4,20,16,N,62,21,"His name and praise may well record,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:16-22 II,4,20,16,N,63,22,When people and the kingdoms do
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:16-22 II,4,20,16,N,64,22,Assemble all to praise the Lord.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:23-28 II,5,21,17,N,65,23,"My strength he weaken'd in the way,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:23-28 II,5,21,17,N,66,23,My days of life he shortened.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:23-28 II,5,21,17,N,67,24,"My God, O take me not away"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:23-28 II,5,21,17,N,68,24,"In mid-time of my days, I said:"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:23-28 II,5,21,18,N,69,24,Thy years throughout all ages last.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:23-28 II,5,21,18,N,70,25,Of old thou hast established
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:23-28 II,5,21,18,N,71,25,The earth's foundation firm and fast:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:23-28 II,5,21,18,N,72,25,Thy mighty hands the heav'ns have made.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:23-28 II,5,22,19,N,73,26,"They perish shall, as garments do,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:23-28 II,5,22,19,N,74,26,But thou shalt evermore endure;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:23-28 II,5,22,19,N,75,26,"As vestures, thou shalt change them so;"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:23-28 II,5,22,19,N,76,26,And they shall all be changed sure:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:23-28 II,5,22,20,N,77,27,But from all changes thou art free;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:23-28 II,5,22,20,N,78,27,Thy endless years do last for aye.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:23-28 II,5,22,20,N,79,28,"Thy servants, and their seed who be,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),102,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 102:23-28 II,5,22,20,N,80,28,Establish'd shall before thee stay.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:1-5,1,1,1,N,1,1,"O thou my soul, bless God the Lord;"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:1-5,1,1,1,Y,2,1,and all that in me is
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:1-5,1,1,1,N,3,1,Be stirred up his holy name
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:1-5,1,1,1,Y,4,1,to magnify and bless.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:1-5,1,1,2,N,5,2,"Bless, O my soul, the Lord thy God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:1-5,1,1,2,Y,6,2,and not forgetful be
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:1-5,1,1,2,N,7,2,Of all his gracious benefits
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:1-5,1,1,2,Y,8,2,he hath bestow'd on thee.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:1-5,1,2,3,N,9,3,All thine iniquities who doth
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:1-5,1,2,3,Y,10,3,most graciously forgive:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:1-5,1,2,3,N,11,3,Who thy diseases all and pains
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:1-5,1,2,3,Y,12,3,"doth heal, and thee relieve."
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:1-5,1,2,4,N,13,4,"Who doth redeem thy life, that thou"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:1-5,1,2,4,Y,14,4,to death may'st not go down;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:1-5,1,2,4,N,15,4,Who thee with loving-kindness doth
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:1-5,1,2,4,Y,16,4,and tender mercies crown:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:1-5,1,3,5,N,17,5,Who with abundance of good things
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:1-5,1,3,5,Y,18,5,doth satisfy thy mouth;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:1-5,1,3,5,N,19,5,"So that, ev'n as the eagle's age,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:1-5,1,3,5,Y,20,5,renewed is thy youth.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:6-12,2,3,6,N,21,6,God righteous judgment executes
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:6-12,2,3,6,Y,22,6,for all oppressed ones.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:6-12,2,3,6,N,23,7,"His ways to Moses, he his acts"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:6-12,2,3,6,Y,24,7,made known to Isr'el's sons.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:6-12,2,4,7,N,25,8,"The Lord our God is merciful,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:6-12,2,4,7,Y,26,8,"and he is gracious,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:6-12,2,4,7,N,27,8,"Long-suffering, and slow to wrath,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:6-12,2,4,7,Y,28,8,in mercy plenteous.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:6-12,2,4,8,N,29,9,"He will not chide continually,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:6-12,2,4,8,Y,30,9,nor keep his anger still.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:6-12,2,4,8,N,31,10,"With us he dealt not as we sinn'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:6-12,2,4,8,Y,32,10,nor did requite our ill.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:6-12,2,5,9,N,33,11,For as the heaven in its height
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:6-12,2,5,9,Y,34,11,the earth surmounteth far;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:6-12,2,5,9,N,35,11,So great to those that do him fear
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:6-12,2,5,9,Y,36,11,his tender mercies are:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:6-12,2,5,10,N,37,12,As far as east is distant from
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:6-12,2,5,10,Y,38,12,"the west, so far hath he"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:6-12,2,5,10,N,39,12,"From us removed, in his love,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:6-12,2,5,10,Y,40,12,all our iniquity.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:13-18,3,6,11,N,41,13,Such pity as a father hath
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:13-18,3,6,11,Y,42,13,unto his children dear;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:13-18,3,6,11,N,43,13,Like pity shews the Lord to such
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:13-18,3,6,11,Y,44,13,as worship him in fear.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:13-18,3,6,12,N,45,14,"For he remembers we are dust,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:13-18,3,6,12,Y,46,14,and he our frame well knows.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:13-18,3,6,12,N,47,15,"Frail man, his days are like the grass,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:13-18,3,6,12,Y,48,15,as flow'r in field he grows:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:13-18,3,7,13,N,49,16,"For over it the wind doth pass,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:13-18,3,7,13,Y,50,16,and it away is gone;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:13-18,3,7,13,N,51,16,And of the place where once it was
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:13-18,3,7,13,Y,52,16,it shall no more be known.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:13-18,3,7,14,N,53,17,But unto them that do him fear
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:13-18,3,7,14,Y,54,17,God's mercy never ends;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:13-18,3,7,14,N,55,17,And to their children's children still
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:13-18,3,7,14,Y,56,17,his righteousness extends:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:13-18,3,8,15,N,57,18,"To such as keep his covenant,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:13-18,3,8,15,Y,58,18,and mindful are alway
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:13-18,3,8,15,N,59,18,"Of his most just commandements,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:13-18,3,8,15,Y,60,18,that they may them obey.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:19-22,4,8,16,N,61,19,The Lord prepared hath his throne
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:19-22,4,8,16,Y,62,19,in heavens firm to stand;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:19-22,4,8,16,N,63,19,And ev'ry thing that being hath
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:19-22,4,8,16,Y,64,19,his kingdom doth command.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:19-22,4,9,17,N,65,20,"O ye his angels, that excel"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:19-22,4,9,17,Y,66,20,"in strength, bless ye the Lord;"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:19-22,4,9,17,N,67,20,"Ye who obey what he commands,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:19-22,4,9,17,Y,68,20,and hearken to his word.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:19-22,4,9,18,N,69,21,"O bless and magnify the Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:19-22,4,9,18,Y,70,21,ye glorious hosts of his;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:19-22,4,9,18,N,71,21,"Ye ministers, that do fulfil"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:19-22,4,9,18,Y,72,21,whate'er his pleasure is.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:19-22,4,10,19,N,73,22,"O bless the Lord, all ye his works,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:19-22,4,10,19,Y,74,22,wherewith the world is stor'd
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:19-22,4,10,19,N,75,22,In his dominions ev'ry where.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),103,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 103:19-22,4,10,19,Y,76,22,"My soul, bless thou the Lord."
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:1-5,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Bless God, my soul. O Lord my God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:1-5,1,1,1,Y,2,1,thou art exceeding great;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:1-5,1,1,1,N,3,1,With honour and with majesty
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:1-5,1,1,1,Y,4,1,thou clothed art in state.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:1-5,1,1,2,N,5,2,"With light, as with a robe, thyself"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:1-5,1,1,2,Y,6,2,thou coverest about;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:1-5,1,1,2,N,7,2,"And, like unto a curtain, thou"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:1-5,1,1,2,Y,8,2,the heavens stretchest out.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:1-5,1,2,3,N,9,3,Who of his chambers doth the beams
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:1-5,1,2,3,Y,10,3,within the waters lay;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:1-5,1,2,3,N,11,3,"Who doth the clouds his chariot make,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:1-5,1,2,3,Y,12,3,on wings of wind make way.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:1-5,1,2,4,N,13,4,"Who flaming fire his ministers,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:1-5,1,2,4,Y,14,4,"his angels sp'rits, doth make:"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:1-5,1,2,4,N,15,5,"Who earth's foundations did lay,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:1-5,1,2,4,Y,16,5,that it should never shake.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:6-9,2,3,5,N,17,6,"Thou didst it cover with the deep,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:6-9,2,3,5,Y,18,6,as with a garment spread:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:6-9,2,3,5,N,19,6,"The waters stood above the hills,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:6-9,2,3,5,Y,20,6,when thou the word but said.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:6-9,2,3,6,N,21,7,But at the voice of thy rebuke
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:6-9,2,3,6,Y,22,7,"they fled, and would not stay;"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:6-9,2,3,6,N,23,7,They at thy thunder's dreadful voice
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:6-9,2,3,6,Y,24,7,did haste them fast away.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:6-9,2,4,7,N,25,8,"They by the mountains do ascend,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:6-9,2,4,7,Y,26,8,and by the valley-ground
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:6-9,2,4,7,N,27,8,"Descend, unto that very place"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:6-9,2,4,7,Y,28,8,which thou for them didst found.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:6-9,2,4,8,N,29,9,"Thou hast a bound unto them set,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:6-9,2,4,8,Y,30,9,"that they may not pass over,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:6-9,2,4,8,N,31,9,That they do not return again
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:6-9,2,4,8,Y,32,9,the face of earth to cover.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:10-15,3,5,9,N,33,10,"He to the valleys sends the springs,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:10-15,3,5,9,Y,34,10,which run among the hills:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:10-15,3,5,9,N,35,11,"They to all beasts of field give drink,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:10-15,3,5,9,Y,36,11,wild asses drink their fills.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:10-15,3,5,10,N,37,12,By them the fowls of heav'n shall have
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:10-15,3,5,10,Y,38,12,"their habitation,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:10-15,3,5,10,N,39,12,Which do among the branches sing
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:10-15,3,5,10,Y,40,12,with delectation.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:10-15,3,6,11,N,41,13,He from his chambers watereth
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:10-15,3,6,11,Y,42,13,"the hills, when they are dry'd:"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:10-15,3,6,11,N,43,13,With fruit and increase of thy works
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:10-15,3,6,11,Y,44,13,the earth is satisfy'd.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:10-15,3,6,12,N,45,14,"For cattle he makes grass to grow,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:10-15,3,6,12,Y,46,14,he makes the herb to spring
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:10-15,3,6,12,N,47,14,"For th' use of man, that food to him"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:10-15,3,6,12,Y,48,14,he from the earth may bring;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:10-15,3,7,13,N,49,15,"And wine, that to the heart of man"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:10-15,3,7,13,Y,50,15,"doth cheerfulness impart,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:10-15,3,7,13,N,51,15,"Oil that his face makes shine, and bread"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:10-15,3,7,13,Y,52,15,that strengtheneth his heart.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:16-18,4,7,14,N,53,16,The trees of God are full of sap;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:16-18,4,7,14,Y,54,16,the cedars that do stand
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:16-18,4,7,14,N,55,16,"In Lebanon , which planted were"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:16-18,4,7,14,Y,56,16,by his almighty hand.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:16-18,4,8,15,N,57,17,Birds of the air upon their boughs
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:16-18,4,8,15,Y,58,17,do chuse their nests to make;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:16-18,4,8,15,N,59,17,"As for the stork, the fir-tree she"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:16-18,4,8,15,Y,60,17,doth for her dwelling take.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:16-18,4,8,16,N,61,18,The lofty mountains for wild goats
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:16-18,4,8,16,Y,62,18,a place of refuge be;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:16-18,4,8,16,N,63,18,The conies also to the rocks
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:16-18,4,8,16,Y,64,18,do for their safety flee.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:19-23,5,9,17,N,65,19,"He sets the moon in heav'n, thereby"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:19-23,5,9,17,Y,66,19,the seasons to discern:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:19-23,5,9,17,N,67,19,From him the sun his certain time
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:19-23,5,9,17,Y,68,19,of going down doth learn.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:19-23,5,9,18,N,69,20,"Thou darkness mak'st, 'tis night, then beasts"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:19-23,5,9,18,Y,70,20,of forests creep abroad.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:19-23,5,9,18,N,71,21,"The lions young roar for their prey,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:19-23,5,9,18,Y,72,21,and seek their meat from God.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:19-23,5,10,19,N,73,22,"The sun doth rise, and home they flock,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:19-23,5,10,19,Y,74,22,down in their dens they lie.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:19-23,5,10,19,N,75,23,"Man goes to work, his labour he"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:19-23,5,10,19,Y,76,23,doth to the ev'ning ply.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:24-27,6,10,20,N,77,24,"How manifold, Lord, are thy works!"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:24-27,6,10,20,Y,78,24,in wisdom wonderful
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:24-27,6,10,20,N,79,24,Thou ev'ry one of them hast made;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:24-27,6,10,20,Y,80,24,earth's of thy riches full:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:24-27,6,11,21,N,81,25,"So is this great and spacious sea,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:24-27,6,11,21,Y,82,25,"wherein things creeping are,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:24-27,6,11,21,N,83,25,Which number'd cannot be; and beasts
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:24-27,6,11,21,Y,84,25,both great and small are there.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:24-27,6,11,22,N,85,26,There ships go; there thou mak'st to play
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:24-27,6,11,22,Y,86,26,that leviathan great.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:24-27,6,11,22,N,87,27,"These all wait on thee, that thou may'st"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:24-27,6,11,22,Y,88,27,in due time give them meat.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:28-30,7,12,23,N,89,28,That which thou givest unto them
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:28-30,7,12,23,Y,90,28,they gather for their food;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:28-30,7,12,23,N,91,28,"Thine hand thou open'st lib'rally,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:28-30,7,12,23,Y,92,28,they filled are with good.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:28-30,7,12,24,N,93,29,"Thou hid'st thy face; they troubled are,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:28-30,7,12,24,Y,94,29,their breath thou tak'st away;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:28-30,7,12,24,N,95,29,"Then do they die, and to their dust"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:28-30,7,12,24,Y,96,29,return again do they.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:28-30,7,13,25,N,97,30,"Thy quick'ning spirit thou send'st forth,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:28-30,7,13,25,Y,98,30,then they created be;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:28-30,7,13,25,N,99,30,And then the earth's decayed face
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:28-30,7,13,25,Y,100,30,renewed is by thee.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:31-35,8,13,26,N,101,31,The glory of the mighty Lord
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:31-35,8,13,26,Y,102,31,continue shall for ever:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:31-35,8,13,26,N,103,31,The Lord Jehovah shall rejoice
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:31-35,8,13,26,Y,104,31,in all his works together.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:31-35,8,14,27,N,105,32,"Earth, as affrighted, trembleth all,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:31-35,8,14,27,Y,106,32,if he on it but look;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:31-35,8,14,27,N,107,32,"And if the mountains he but touch,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:31-35,8,14,27,Y,108,32,they presently do smoke.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:31-35,8,14,28,N,109,33,"I will sing to the Lord most high,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:31-35,8,14,28,Y,110,33,so long as I shall live;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:31-35,8,14,28,N,111,33,And while I being have I shall
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:31-35,8,14,28,Y,112,33,to my God praises give.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:31-35,8,15,29,N,113,34,Of him my meditation shall
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:31-35,8,15,29,Y,114,34,sweet thoughts to me afford;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:31-35,8,15,29,N,115,34,"And as for me, I will rejoice"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:31-35,8,15,29,Y,116,34,"in God, my only Lord."
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:31-35,8,15,30,N,117,35,"From earth let sinners be consum'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:31-35,8,15,30,Y,118,35,let ill men no more be.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:31-35,8,15,30,N,119,35,"O thou my soul, bless thou the Lord."
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),104,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 104:31-35,8,15,30,Y,120,35,Praise to the Lord give ye.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:1-4,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Give thanks to God, call on his name;"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:1-4,1,1,1,Y,2,1,to men his deeds make known.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:1-4,1,1,1,N,3,2,"Sing ye to him, sing psalms; proclaim"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:1-4,1,1,1,Y,4,2,his wondrous works each one.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:1-4,1,1,2,N,5,3,See that ye in his holy name
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:1-4,1,1,2,Y,6,3,to glory do accord;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:1-4,1,1,2,N,7,3,And let the heart of ev'ry one
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:1-4,1,1,2,Y,8,3,rejoice that seeks the Lord.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:1-4,1,2,3,N,9,4,"The Lord Almighty, and his strength,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:1-4,1,2,3,Y,10,4,with stedfast hearts seek ye:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:1-4,1,2,3,N,11,4,His blessed and his gracious face
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:1-4,1,2,3,Y,12,4,seek ye continually.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:5-7,2,2,4,N,13,5,"Think on the works that he hath done,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:5-7,2,2,4,Y,14,5,which admiration breed;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:5-7,2,2,4,N,15,5,"His wonders, and the judgments all"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:5-7,2,2,4,Y,16,5,which from his mouth proceed;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:5-7,2,3,5,N,17,6,"O ye that are of Abr'ham's race,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:5-7,2,3,5,Y,18,6,his servant well approv'n;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:5-7,2,3,5,N,19,6,"And ye that Jacob's children are,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:5-7,2,3,5,Y,20,6,whom he chose for his own.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:5-7,2,3,6,N,21,7,"Because he, and he only, is"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:5-7,2,3,6,Y,22,7,the mighty Lord our God;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:5-7,2,3,6,N,23,7,And his most righteous judgments are
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:5-7,2,3,6,Y,24,7,in all the earth abroad.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:8-10,3,4,7,N,25,8,"His cov'nant he remember'd hath,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:8-10,3,4,7,Y,26,8,that it may ever stand:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:8-10,3,4,7,N,27,8,To thousand generations
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:8-10,3,4,7,Y,28,8,the word he did command.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:8-10,3,4,8,N,29,9,Which covenant he firmly made
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:8-10,3,4,8,Y,30,9,"with faithful Abraham,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:8-10,3,4,8,N,31,9,"And unto Isaac, by his oath,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:8-10,3,4,8,Y,32,9,he did renew the same:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:8-10,3,5,9,N,33,10,"And unto Jacob, for a law,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:8-10,3,5,9,Y,34,10,"he made it firm and sure,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:8-10,3,5,9,N,35,10,"A covenant to Israel ,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:8-10,3,5,9,Y,36,10,which ever should endure.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:11-15,4,5,10,N,37,11,"He said, I'll give Canaan 's land"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:11-15,4,5,10,Y,38,11,for heritage to you;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:11-15,4,5,10,N,39,12,"While they were strangers there, and few,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:11-15,4,5,10,Y,40,12,in number very few:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:11-15,4,6,11,N,41,13,While yet they went from land to land
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:11-15,4,6,11,Y,42,13,without a sure abode;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:11-15,4,6,11,N,43,13,And while through sundry kingdoms they
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:11-15,4,6,11,Y,44,13,did wander far abroad;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:11-15,4,6,12,N,45,14,"Yet, notwithstanding suffer'd he"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:11-15,4,6,12,Y,46,14,no man to do them wrong:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:11-15,4,6,12,N,47,14,"Yea, for their sakes, he did reprove"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:11-15,4,6,12,Y,48,14,"kings, who were great and strong."
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:11-15,4,7,13,N,49,15,"Thus did he say, Touch ye not those"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:11-15,4,7,13,Y,50,15,"that mine anointed be,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:11-15,4,7,13,N,51,15,Nor do the prophets any harm
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:11-15,4,7,13,Y,52,15,that do pertain to me.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:16-19,5,7,14,N,53,16,"He call'd for famine on the land,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:16-19,5,7,14,Y,54,16,he brake the staff of bread:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:16-19,5,7,14,N,55,17,"But yet he sent a man before,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:16-19,5,7,14,Y,56,17,by whom they should be fed;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:16-19,5,8,15,N,57,17,"Ev'n Joseph, whom unnat'rally"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:16-19,5,8,15,Y,58,17,sell for a slave did they;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:16-19,5,8,15,N,59,18,"Whose feet with fetters they did hurt,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:16-19,5,8,15,Y,60,18,and he in irons lay;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:16-19,5,8,16,N,61,19,Until the time that his word came
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:16-19,5,8,16,Y,62,19,to give him liberty;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:16-19,5,8,16,N,63,19,The word and purpose of the Lord
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:16-19,5,8,16,Y,64,19,did him in prison try.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:20-22,6,9,17,N,65,20,"Then sent the king, and did command"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:20-22,6,9,17,Y,66,20,that he enlarg'd should be:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:20-22,6,9,17,N,67,20,He that the people's ruler was
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:20-22,6,9,17,Y,68,20,did send to set him free.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:20-22,6,9,18,N,69,21,A lord to rule his family
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:20-22,6,9,18,Y,70,21,"he rais'd him, as most fit;"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:20-22,6,9,18,N,71,21,To him of all that he possess'd
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:20-22,6,9,18,Y,72,21,he did the charge commit:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:20-22,6,10,19,N,73,22,That he might at his pleasure bind
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:20-22,6,10,19,Y,74,22,the princes of the land;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:20-22,6,10,19,N,75,22,And he might teach his senators
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:20-22,6,10,19,Y,76,22,wisdom to understand.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:23-25,7,10,20,N,77,23,The people then of Israel
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:23-25,7,10,20,Y,78,23,down into Egypt came;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:23-25,7,10,20,N,79,23,And Jacob also sojourned
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:23-25,7,10,20,Y,80,23,within the land of Ham.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:23-25,7,11,21,N,81,24,And he did greatly by his pow'r
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:23-25,7,11,21,Y,82,24,increase his people there;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:23-25,7,11,21,N,83,24,And stronger than their enemies
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:23-25,7,11,21,Y,84,24,they by his blessing were.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:23-25,7,11,22,N,85,25,Their heart he turned to envy
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:23-25,7,11,22,Y,86,25,"his folk maliciously,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:23-25,7,11,22,N,87,25,With those that his own servants were
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:23-25,7,11,22,Y,88,25,to deal in subtilty.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:26-35,8,12,23,N,89,26,"His servant Moses he did send,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:26-35,8,12,23,Y,90,26,Aaron his chosen one.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:26-35,8,12,23,N,91,27,By these his signs and wonders great
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:26-35,8,12,23,Y,92,27,in Ham's land were made known.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:26-35,8,12,24,N,93,28,"Darkness he sent, and made it dark;"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:26-35,8,12,24,Y,94,28,his word they did obey.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:26-35,8,12,24,N,95,29,"He turn'd their waters into blood,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:26-35,8,12,24,Y,96,29,and he their fish did slay.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:26-35,8,13,25,N,97,30,The land in plenty brought forth frogs
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:26-35,8,13,25,Y,98,30,in chambers of their kings.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:26-35,8,13,25,N,99,31,His word all sorts of flies and lice
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:26-35,8,13,25,Y,100,31,in all their borders brings.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:26-35,8,13,26,N,101,32,"He hail for rain, and flaming fire"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:26-35,8,13,26,Y,102,32,into their land he sent:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:26-35,8,13,26,N,103,33,And he their vines and fig-trees smote:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:26-35,8,13,26,Y,104,33,trees of their coasts he rent.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:26-35,8,14,27,N,105,34,"He spake, and caterpillars came,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:26-35,8,14,27,Y,106,34,locusts did much abound;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:26-35,8,14,27,N,107,35,"Which in their land all herbs consum'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:26-35,8,14,27,Y,108,35,and all fruits of their ground.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:36-41,9,14,28,N,109,36,"He smote all first-born in their land,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:36-41,9,14,28,Y,110,36,chief of their strength each one.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:36-41,9,14,28,N,111,37,"With gold and silver brought them forth,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:36-41,9,14,28,Y,112,37,weak in their tribes were none.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:36-41,9,15,29,N,113,38,"Egypt was glad when forth they went,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:36-41,9,15,29,Y,114,38,their fear on them did light.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:36-41,9,15,29,N,115,39,"He spread a cloud for covering,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:36-41,9,15,29,Y,116,39,and fire to shine by night.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:36-41,9,15,30,N,117,40,"They ask'd, and he brought quails: with bread"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:36-41,9,15,30,Y,118,40,of heav'n he filled them.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:36-41,9,15,30,N,119,41,"He open'd rocks, floods gush'd, and ran"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:36-41,9,15,30,Y,120,41,in deserts like a stream.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:42-45,10,16,31,N,121,42,"For on his holy promise he,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:42-45,10,16,31,Y,122,42,"and servant Abr'ham, thought."
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:42-45,10,16,31,N,123,43,"With joy his people, his elect"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:42-45,10,16,31,Y,124,43,"with gladness, forth he brought."
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:42-45,10,16,32,N,125,44,And unto them the pleasant lands
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:42-45,10,16,32,Y,126,44,he of the heathen gave;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:42-45,10,16,32,N,127,44,That of the people's labour they
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:42-45,10,16,32,Y,128,44,inheritance might have.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:42-45,10,17,33,N,129,45,That they his statutes might observe
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:42-45,10,17,33,Y,130,45,according to his word;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:42-45,10,17,33,N,131,45,And that they might his laws obey.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),105,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 105:42-45,10,17,33,Y,132,45,Give praise unto the Lord.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:1-5,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Give praise and thanks unto the Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:1-5,1,1,1,Y,2,1,for bountiful is he;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:1-5,1,1,1,N,3,1,His tender mercy doth endure
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:1-5,1,1,1,Y,4,1,unto eternity.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:1-5,1,1,2,N,5,2,God's mighty works who can express?
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:1-5,1,1,2,Y,6,2,or shew forth all his praise?
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:1-5,1,1,2,N,7,3,"Blessed are they that judgment keep,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:1-5,1,1,2,Y,8,3,and justly do always.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:1-5,1,2,3,N,9,4,"Remember me, Lord, with that love"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:1-5,1,2,3,Y,10,4,which thou to thine dost bear;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:1-5,1,2,3,N,11,4,"With thy salvation, O my God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:1-5,1,2,3,Y,12,4,to visit me draw near:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:1-5,1,2,4,N,13,5,"That I thy chosen's good may see,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:1-5,1,2,4,Y,14,5,and in their joy rejoice;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:1-5,1,2,4,N,15,5,And may with thine inheritance
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:1-5,1,2,4,Y,16,5,triumph with cheerful voice.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:6-8,2,3,5,N,17,6,"We with our fathers sinned have,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:6-8,2,3,5,Y,18,6,and of iniquity
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:6-8,2,3,5,N,19,6,Too long we have the workers been;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:6-8,2,3,5,Y,20,6,we have done wickedly.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:6-8,2,3,6,N,21,7,"The wonders great, which thou, O Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:6-8,2,3,6,Y,22,7,"didst work in Egypt land,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:6-8,2,3,6,N,23,7,"Our fathers, though they saw, yet them"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:6-8,2,3,6,Y,24,7,they did not understand:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:6-8,2,4,7,N,25,7,And they thy mercies' multitude
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:6-8,2,4,7,Y,26,7,kept not in memory;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:6-8,2,4,7,N,27,7,"But at the sea, ev'n the Red sea,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:6-8,2,4,7,Y,28,7,provok'd him grievously.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:6-8,2,4,8,N,29,8,"Nevertheless he saved them,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:6-8,2,4,8,Y,30,8,ev'n for his own name's sake;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:6-8,2,4,8,N,31,8,That so he might to be well known
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:6-8,2,4,8,Y,32,8,his mighty power make.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:9-12,3,5,9,N,33,9,"When he the Red sea did rebuke,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:9-12,3,5,9,Y,34,9,then dried up it was:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:9-12,3,5,9,N,35,9,"Through depths, as through the wilderness,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:9-12,3,5,9,Y,36,9,he safely made them pass.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:9-12,3,5,10,N,37,10,From hands of those that hated them
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:9-12,3,5,10,Y,38,10,he did his people save;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:9-12,3,5,10,N,39,10,And from the en'my's cruel hand
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:9-12,3,5,10,Y,40,10,to them redemption gave.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:9-12,3,6,11,N,41,11,The waters overwhelm'd their foes;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:9-12,3,6,11,Y,42,11,not one was left alive.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:9-12,3,6,11,N,43,12,"Then they believ'd his word, and praise"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:9-12,3,6,11,Y,44,12,to him in songs did give.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:13-18,4,6,12,N,45,13,But soon did they his mighty works
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:13-18,4,6,12,Y,46,13,"forget unthankfully,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:13-18,4,6,12,N,47,13,And on his counsel and his will
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:13-18,4,6,12,Y,48,13,did not wait patiently;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:13-18,4,7,13,N,49,14,"But much did lust in wilderness,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:13-18,4,7,13,Y,50,14,and God in desert tempt.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:13-18,4,7,13,N,51,15,"He gave them what they sought, but to"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:13-18,4,7,13,Y,52,15,their soul he leanness sent.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:13-18,4,7,14,N,53,16,And against Moses in the camp
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:13-18,4,7,14,Y,54,16,their envy did appear;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:13-18,4,7,14,N,55,16,"At Aaron they, the saint of God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:13-18,4,7,14,Y,56,16,envious also were.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:13-18,4,8,15,N,57,17,"Therefore the earth did open wide,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:13-18,4,8,15,Y,58,17,"and Dathan did devour,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:13-18,4,8,15,N,59,17,And all Abiram's company
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:13-18,4,8,15,Y,60,17,did cover in that hour.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:13-18,4,8,16,N,61,18,Likewise among their company
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:13-18,4,8,16,Y,62,18,a fire was kindled then;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:13-18,4,8,16,N,63,18,And so the hot consuming flame
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:13-18,4,8,16,Y,64,18,burnt up these wicked men.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:19-21,5,9,17,N,65,19,Upon the hill of Horeb they
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:19-21,5,9,17,Y,66,19,"an idol-calf did frame,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:19-21,5,9,17,N,67,19,"A molten image they did make,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:19-21,5,9,17,Y,68,19,and worshipped the same.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:19-21,5,9,18,N,69,20,"And thus their glory, and their God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:19-21,5,9,18,Y,70,20,most vainly changed they
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:19-21,5,9,18,N,71,20,Into the likeness of an ox
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:19-21,5,9,18,Y,72,20,that eateth grass or hay.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:19-21,5,10,19,N,73,21,"They did forget the mighty God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:19-21,5,10,19,Y,74,21,"that had their saviour been,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:19-21,5,10,19,N,75,21,By whom such great things brought to pass
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:19-21,5,10,19,Y,76,21,they had in Egypt seen.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:22-27,6,10,20,N,77,22,"In Ham's land he did wondrous works,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:22-27,6,10,20,Y,78,22,"things terrible did he,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:22-27,6,10,20,N,79,22,When he his mighty hand and arm
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:22-27,6,10,20,Y,80,22,stretch'd out at the Red sea.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:22-27,6,11,21,N,81,23,"Then said he, He would them destroy,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:22-27,6,11,21,Y,82,23,"had not, his wrath to stay,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:22-27,6,11,21,N,83,23,"His chosen Moses stood in breach,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:22-27,6,11,21,Y,84,23,that them he should not slay.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:22-27,6,11,22,N,85,24,"Yea, they despis'd the pleasant land,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:22-27,6,11,22,Y,86,24,believed not his word:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:22-27,6,11,22,N,87,25,"But in their tents they murmured,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:22-27,6,11,22,Y,88,25,not heark'ning to the Lord.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:22-27,6,12,23,N,89,26,Therefore in desert them to slay
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:22-27,6,12,23,Y,90,26,he lifted up his hand:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:22-27,6,12,23,N,91,27,"'Mong nations to o'erthrow their seed,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:22-27,6,12,23,Y,92,27,and scatter in each land.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:28-31,7,12,24,N,93,28,They unto Baal-peor did
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:28-31,7,12,24,Y,94,28,themselves associate;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:28-31,7,12,24,N,95,28,The sacrifices of the dead
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:28-31,7,12,24,Y,96,28,they did profanely eat.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:28-31,7,13,25,N,97,29,"Thus, by their lewd inventions,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:28-31,7,13,25,Y,98,29,they did provoke his ire;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:28-31,7,13,25,N,99,29,And then upon them suddenly
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:28-31,7,13,25,Y,100,29,the plague brake in as fire.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:28-31,7,13,26,N,101,30,"Then Phin'has rose, and justice did,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:28-31,7,13,26,Y,102,30,and so the plague did cease;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:28-31,7,13,26,N,103,31,That to all ages counted was
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:28-31,7,13,26,Y,104,31,to him for righteousness.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:32-35,8,14,27,N,105,32,"And at the waters, where they strove,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:32-35,8,14,27,Y,106,32,"they did him angry make,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:32-35,8,14,27,N,107,32,"In such sort, that it fared ill"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:32-35,8,14,27,Y,108,32,with Moses for their sake:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:32-35,8,14,28,N,109,33,Because they there his spirit meek
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:32-35,8,14,28,Y,110,33,"provoked bitterly,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:32-35,8,14,28,N,111,33,So that he utter'd with his lips
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:32-35,8,14,28,Y,112,33,words unadvisedly.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:32-35,8,15,29,N,113,34,"Nor, as the Lord commanded them,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:32-35,8,15,29,Y,114,34,did they the nations slay:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:32-35,8,15,29,N,115,35,"But with the heathen mingled were,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:32-35,8,15,29,Y,116,35,and learn'd of them their way.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:36-39,9,15,30,N,117,36,"And they their idols serv'd, which did"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:36-39,9,15,30,Y,118,36,a snare unto them turn.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:36-39,9,15,30,N,119,37,Their sons and daughters they to dev'ls
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:36-39,9,15,30,Y,120,37,in sacrifice did burn.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:36-39,9,16,31,N,121,38,In their own children's guiltless blood
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:36-39,9,16,31,Y,122,38,"their hands they did imbrue,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:36-39,9,16,31,N,123,38,Whom to Canaan's idols they
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:36-39,9,16,31,Y,124,38,for sacrifices slew:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:36-39,9,16,32,N,125,38,So was the land defil'd with blood.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:36-39,9,16,32,Y,126,39,"They stain'd with their own way,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:36-39,9,16,32,N,127,39,And with their own inventions
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:36-39,9,16,32,Y,128,39,a whoring they did stray.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:40-43,10,17,33,N,129,40,Against his people kindled was
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:40-43,10,17,33,Y,130,40,"the wrath of God therefore,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:40-43,10,17,33,N,131,40,Insomuch that he did his own
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:40-43,10,17,33,Y,132,40,inheritance abhor.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:40-43,10,17,34,N,133,41,He gave them to the heathen's hand;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:40-43,10,17,34,Y,134,41,their foes did them command.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:40-43,10,17,34,N,135,42,"Their en'mies them oppress'd, they were"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:40-43,10,17,34,Y,136,42,made subject to their hand.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:40-43,10,18,35,N,137,43,He many times deliver'd them;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:40-43,10,18,35,Y,138,43,but with their counsel so
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:40-43,10,18,35,N,139,43,"They him provok'd, that for their sin"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:40-43,10,18,35,Y,140,43,they were brought very low.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:44-48,11,18,36,N,141,44,"Yet their affliction he beheld,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:44-48,11,18,36,Y,142,44,when he did hear their cry:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:44-48,11,18,36,N,143,45,And he for them his covenant
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:44-48,11,18,36,Y,144,45,did call to memory;
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:44-48,11,19,37,N,145,45,After his mercies' multitude
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:44-48,11,19,37,Y,146,46,he did repent: And made
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:44-48,11,19,37,N,147,46,Them to be pity'd of all those
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:44-48,11,19,37,Y,148,46,who did them captive lead.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:44-48,11,19,38,N,149,47,"O Lord our God, us save, and gather"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:44-48,11,19,38,Y,150,47,"the heathen from among,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:44-48,11,19,38,N,151,47,That we thy holy name may praise
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:44-48,11,19,38,Y,152,47,in a triumphant song.
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:44-48,11,20,39,N,153,48,"Bless'd be JEHOVAH, Isr'el's God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:44-48,11,20,39,Y,154,48,to all eternity:
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:44-48,11,20,39,N,155,48,"Let all the people say, Amen."
1650 Psalter,Book 4 (Psalm 90-106),106,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 106:44-48,11,20,39,Y,156,48,Praise to the Lord give ye.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:1-7,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Praise God, for he is good: for still"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:1-7,1,1,1,N,2,1,his mercies lasting be.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:1-7,1,1,1,N,3,2,"Let God's redeemed say so, whom he"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:1-7,1,1,1,N,4,2,from th' en'my's hand did free;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:1-7,1,1,2,N,5,3,"And gathered them out of the lands,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:1-7,1,1,2,N,6,3,"from north, south, east, and west."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:1-7,1,1,2,N,7,4,"They strayed in desert's pathless way,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:1-7,1,1,2,N,8,4,no city found to rest.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:1-7,1,2,3,N,9,5,For thirst and hunger in them faints
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:1-7,1,2,3,N,10,6,"their soul. When straits them press,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:1-7,1,2,3,N,11,6,"They cry unto the Lord, and he"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:1-7,1,2,3,N,12,6,them frees from their distress.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:1-7,1,2,4,N,13,7,Them also in a way to walk
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:1-7,1,2,4,N,14,7,"that right is he did guide,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:1-7,1,2,4,N,15,7,"That they might to a city go,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:1-7,1,2,4,N,16,7,wherein they might abide.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:8-9,2,3,5,N,17,8,O that men to the Lord would give
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:8-9,2,3,5,N,18,8,"praise for his goodness then,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:8-9,2,3,5,N,19,8,And for his works of wonder done
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:8-9,2,3,5,N,20,8,unto the sons of men!
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:8-9,2,3,6,N,21,9,For he the soul that longing is
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:8-9,2,3,6,N,22,9,doth fully satisfy;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:8-9,2,3,6,N,23,9,With goodness he the hungry soul
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:8-9,2,3,6,N,24,9,doth fill abundantly.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:10-14,3,4,7,N,25,10,"Such as shut up in darkness deep,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:10-14,3,4,7,N,26,10,"and in death's shade abide,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:10-14,3,4,7,N,27,10,"Whom strongly hath affliction bound,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:10-14,3,4,7,N,28,10,and irons fast have tried:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:10-14,3,4,8,N,29,11,Because against the words of God
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:10-14,3,4,8,N,30,11,"they wrought rebelliously,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:10-14,3,4,8,N,31,11,And they the counsel did contemn
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:10-14,3,4,8,N,32,11,of him that is most High:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:10-14,3,5,9,N,33,12,"Their heart he did bring down with grief,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:10-14,3,5,9,N,34,12,"they fell, no help could have."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:10-14,3,5,9,N,35,13,"In trouble then they cried to God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:10-14,3,5,9,N,36,13,he them from straits did save.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:10-14,3,5,10,N,37,14,"He out of darkness did them bring,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:10-14,3,5,10,N,38,14,and from death's shade them take;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:10-14,3,5,10,N,39,14,"These bands, wherewith they had been bound,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:10-14,3,5,10,N,40,14,asunder quite he brake.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:15-16,4,6,11,N,41,15,O that men to the Lord would give
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:15-16,4,6,11,N,42,15,"praise for his goodness then,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:15-16,4,6,11,N,43,15,And for his works of wonder done
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:15-16,4,6,11,N,44,15,unto the sons of men!
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:15-16,4,6,12,N,45,15,""
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:15-16,4,7,12,N,46,16,Because the mighty gates of brass
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:15-16,4,7,12,N,47,16,"in pieces he did tear,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:15-16,4,7,12,N,48,16,By him in sunder also cut
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:15-16,4,7,13,N,49,16,the bars of iron were.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:17-22,5,8,13,N,50,17,"Fools, for their sin, and their offence,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:17-22,5,8,13,N,51,17,do sore affliction bear;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:17-22,5,8,13,N,52,18,All kind of meat their soul abhors;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:17-22,5,8,14,N,53,18,they to death's gates draw near.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:17-22,5,8,14,N,54,18,""
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:17-22,5,9,14,N,55,19,In grief they cry to God; he saves
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:17-22,5,9,14,N,56,19,them from their miseries.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:17-22,5,9,15,N,57,20,"He sends his word, them heals, and them"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:17-22,5,9,15,N,58,20,from their destructions frees.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:17-22,5,10,15,N,59,21,O that men to the Lord would give
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:17-22,5,10,15,N,60,21,"praise for his goodness then,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:17-22,5,10,16,N,61,21,And for his works of wonder done
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:17-22,5,10,16,N,62,21,unto the sons of men!
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:17-22,5,10,16,N,63,22,And let them sacrifice to him
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:17-22,5,10,16,N,64,22,off 'rings of thankfulness;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:17-22,5,10,17,N,65,22,And let them shew abroad his works
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:17-22,5,10,17,N,66,22,in songs of joyfulness.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:23-28,6,11,17,N,67,23,"Who go to sea in ships, and in"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:23-28,6,11,17,N,68,23,"great waters trading be,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:23-28,6,11,18,N,69,24,Within the deep these men God's works
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:23-28,6,11,18,N,70,24,and his great wonders see.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:23-28,6,11,18,N,71,24,""
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:23-28,6,12,18,N,72,25,"For he commands, and forth in haste"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:23-28,6,12,19,N,73,25,"the stormy tempest flies,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:23-28,6,12,19,N,74,25,Which makes the sea with rolling waves
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:23-28,6,12,19,N,75,25,aloft to swell and rise.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:23-28,6,13,19,N,76,26,"They mount to heav'n, then to the depths"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:23-28,6,13,20,N,77,26,they do go down again;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:23-28,6,13,20,N,78,26,Their soul doth faint and melt away
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:23-28,6,13,20,N,79,26,with trouble and with pain.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:23-28,6,13,20,N,80,27,"They reel and stagger like one drunk,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:23-28,6,13,21,N,81,27,at their wit's end they be:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:23-28,6,13,21,N,82,28,"Then they to God in trouble cry,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:23-28,6,13,21,N,83,28,who them from straits doth free.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:29-32,7,14,21,N,84,29,The storm is chang'd into a calm
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:29-32,7,14,22,N,85,29,at his command and will;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:29-32,7,14,22,N,86,29,"So that the waves, which rag'd before,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:29-32,7,14,22,N,87,29,now quiet are and still.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:29-32,7,14,22,N,88,29,""
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:29-32,7,15,23,N,89,30,"Then are they glad, because at rest"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:29-32,7,15,23,N,90,30,and quiet now they be:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:29-32,7,15,23,N,91,30,"So to the haven he them brings,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:29-32,7,15,23,N,92,30,which they desir'd to see.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:29-32,7,16,24,N,93,31,O that men to the Lord would give
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:29-32,7,16,24,N,94,31,"praise for his goodness then,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:29-32,7,16,24,N,95,31,And for his works of wonder done
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:29-32,7,16,24,N,96,31,unto the sons of men!
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:29-32,7,16,25,N,97,32,Among the people gathered
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:29-32,7,16,25,N,98,32,let them exalt his name;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:29-32,7,16,25,N,99,32,Among assembled elders spread
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:29-32,7,16,25,N,100,32,his most renowned fame.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:33-38,8,18,26,N,101,33,"He to dry land turns water-springs,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:33-38,8,18,26,N,102,33,and floods to wilderness;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:33-38,8,18,26,N,103,34,"For sins of those that dwell therein,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:33-38,8,18,26,N,104,34,fat land to barrenness.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:33-38,8,18,27,N,105,35,The burnt and parched wilderness
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:33-38,8,18,27,N,106,35,to water-pools he brings;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:33-38,8,18,27,N,107,35,The ground that was dried up before
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:33-38,8,18,27,N,108,35,he turns to water-springs:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:33-38,8,20,28,N,109,36,"And there, for dwelling, he a place"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:33-38,8,20,28,N,110,36,"doth to the hungry give,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:33-38,8,20,28,N,111,36,That they a city may prepare
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:33-38,8,20,28,N,112,36,commodiously to live.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:33-38,8,20,29,N,113,37,"There sow they fields, and vineyards plant,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:33-38,8,20,29,N,114,37,to yield fruits of increase.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:33-38,8,20,29,N,115,38,"His blessing makes them multiply,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:33-38,8,20,29,N,116,38,lets not their beasts decrease.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:39-43,9,22,30,N,117,39,"Again they are diminished,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:39-43,9,22,30,N,118,39,"and very low brought down,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:39-43,9,22,30,N,119,39,"Through sorrow and affliction,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:39-43,9,22,30,N,120,39,and great oppression.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:39-43,9,22,31,N,121,39,""
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:39-43,9,23,31,N,122,40,"He upon princes pours contempt,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:39-43,9,23,31,N,123,40,"and causeth them to stray,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:39-43,9,23,31,N,124,40,"And wander in a wilderness,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:39-43,9,23,32,N,125,40,wherein there is no way.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:39-43,9,24,32,N,126,41,Yet setteth he the poor on high
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:39-43,9,24,32,N,127,41,"from all his miseries,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:39-43,9,24,32,N,128,41,"And he, much like unto a flock,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:39-43,9,24,33,N,129,41,doth make him families.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:39-43,9,24,33,N,130,42,"They that are righteous shall rejoice,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:39-43,9,24,33,N,131,42,when they the same shall see;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:39-43,9,24,33,N,132,42,"And, as ashamed, stop her mouth"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:39-43,9,24,34,N,133,42,shall all iniquity.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:39-43,9,25,34,N,134,43,"Whoso is wise, and will these things"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:39-43,9,25,34,N,135,43,"observe, and them record,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:39-43,9,25,34,N,136,43,Ev'n they shall understand the love
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),107,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 107:39-43,9,25,35,N,137,43,and kindness of the Lord.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),108,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 108:1-6,1,1,1,N,1,1,"My heart is fix'd, Lord; I will sing,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),108,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 108:1-6,1,1,1,Y,2,1,and with my glory praise.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),108,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 108:1-6,1,1,1,N,3,2,Awake up psaltery and harp;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),108,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 108:1-6,1,1,1,Y,4,2,myself I'll early raise.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),108,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 108:1-6,1,1,2,N,5,3,"I'll praise thee 'mong the people, Lord;"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),108,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 108:1-6,1,1,2,Y,6,3,'mong nations sing will I:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),108,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 108:1-6,1,1,2,N,7,4,"For above heav'n thy mercy's great,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),108,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 108:1-6,1,1,2,Y,8,4,thy truth doth reach the sky.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),108,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 108:1-6,1,2,3,N,9,5,"Be thou above the heavens, Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),108,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 108:1-6,1,2,3,Y,10,5,exalted gloriously;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),108,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 108:1-6,1,2,3,N,11,5,Thy glory all the earth above
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),108,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 108:1-6,1,2,3,Y,12,5,be lifted up on high.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),108,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 108:1-6,1,2,4,N,13,6,That those who thy beloved are
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),108,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 108:1-6,1,2,4,Y,14,6,"delivered may be,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),108,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 108:1-6,1,2,4,N,15,6,"O do thou save with thy right hand,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),108,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 108:1-6,1,2,4,Y,16,6,and answer give to me.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),108,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 108:7-9,2,3,5,N,17,7,"God in his holiness hath said,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),108,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 108:7-9,2,3,5,Y,18,7,Herein I will take pleasure;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),108,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 108:7-9,2,3,5,N,19,7,"Shechem I will divide, and forth"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),108,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 108:7-9,2,3,5,Y,20,7,will Succoth's valley measure.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),108,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 108:7-9,2,3,6,N,21,8,Gilead I claim as mine by right;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),108,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 108:7-9,2,3,6,Y,22,8,Manasseh mine shall be;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),108,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 108:7-9,2,3,6,N,23,8,Ephraim is of my head the strength;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),108,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 108:7-9,2,3,6,Y,24,8,Judah gives laws for me;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),108,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 108:7-9,2,4,7,N,25,9,Moab's my washing-pot; my shoe
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),108,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 108:7-9,2,4,7,Y,26,9,I'll over Edom throw;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),108,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 108:7-9,2,4,7,N,27,9,Over the land of Palestine
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),108,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 108:7-9,2,4,7,Y,28,9,I will in triumph go.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),108,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 108:10-13,3,4,8,N,29,10,O who is he will bring me to
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),108,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 108:10-13,3,4,8,Y,30,10,the city fortify'd?
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),108,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 108:10-13,3,4,8,N,31,10,O who is he that to the land
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),108,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 108:10-13,3,4,8,Y,32,10,of Edom will me guide?
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),108,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 108:10-13,3,5,9,N,33,11,"O God, thou who hadst cast us off,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),108,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 108:10-13,3,5,9,Y,34,11,this thing wilt thou not do?
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),108,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 108:10-13,3,5,9,N,35,11,"And wilt not thou, ev'n thou, O God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),108,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 108:10-13,3,5,9,Y,36,11,forth with our armies go?
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),108,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 108:10-13,3,5,10,N,37,12,"Do thou from trouble give us help,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),108,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 108:10-13,3,5,10,Y,38,12,for helpless is man's aid.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),108,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 108:10-13,3,5,10,N,39,13,Through God we shall do valiantly;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),108,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 108:10-13,3,5,10,Y,40,13,our foes he shall down tread.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:1-5,1,1,1,N,1,1,"O thou the God of all my praise,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:1-5,1,1,1,Y,2,1,do thou not hold thy peace;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:1-5,1,1,1,N,3,2,For mouths of wicked men to speak
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:1-5,1,1,1,Y,4,2,against me do not cease:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:1-5,1,1,2,N,5,2,The mouths of vile deceitful men
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:1-5,1,1,2,Y,6,2,against me open'd be;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:1-5,1,1,2,N,7,2,And with a false and lying tongue
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:1-5,1,1,2,Y,8,2,they have accused me.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:1-5,1,2,3,N,9,3,They did beset me round about
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:1-5,1,2,3,Y,10,3,with words of hateful spite:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:1-5,1,2,3,N,11,3,"And though to them no cause I gave,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:1-5,1,2,3,Y,12,3,against me they did fight.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:1-5,1,2,4,N,13,4,"They for my love became my foes,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:1-5,1,2,4,Y,14,4,but I me set to pray.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:1-5,1,2,4,N,15,5,"Evil for good, hatred for love,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:1-5,1,2,4,Y,16,5,to me they did repay.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:6-10,2,3,5,N,17,6,Set thou the wicked over him;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:6-10,2,3,5,Y,18,6,and upon his right hand
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:6-10,2,3,5,N,19,6,"Give thou his greatest enemy,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:6-10,2,3,5,Y,20,6,"ev'n Satan, leave to stand."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:6-10,2,3,6,N,21,7,"And when by thee he shall be judg'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:6-10,2,3,6,Y,22,7,let him condemned be;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:6-10,2,3,6,N,23,7,"And let his pray'r be turn'd to sin,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:6-10,2,3,6,Y,24,7,when he shall call on thee.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:6-10,2,4,7,N,25,8,"Few be his days, and in his room"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:6-10,2,4,7,Y,26,8,his charge another take.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:6-10,2,4,7,N,27,9,"His children let be fatherless,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:6-10,2,4,7,Y,28,9,his wife a widow make.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:6-10,2,4,8,N,29,10,"His children let be vagabonds,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:6-10,2,4,8,Y,30,10,and beg continually;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:6-10,2,4,8,N,31,10,And from their places desolate
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:6-10,2,4,8,Y,32,10,seek bread for their supply.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:11-13,3,5,9,N,33,11,Let covetous extortioners
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:11-13,3,5,9,Y,34,11,catch all he hath away:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:11-13,3,5,9,N,35,11,Of all for which he labour'd hath
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:11-13,3,5,9,Y,36,11,let strangers make a prey.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:11-13,3,5,10,N,37,12,"Let there be none to pity him,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:11-13,3,5,10,Y,38,12,let there be none at all
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:11-13,3,5,10,N,39,12,That on his children fatherless
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:11-13,3,5,10,Y,40,12,will let his mercy fall.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:11-13,3,6,11,N,41,13,Let his posterity from earth
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:11-13,3,6,11,Y,42,13,"cut off for ever be,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:11-13,3,6,11,N,43,13,And in the foll'wing age their name
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:11-13,3,6,11,Y,44,13,be blotted out by thee.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:14-16,4,6,12,N,45,14,Let God his father's wickedness
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:14-16,4,6,12,Y,46,14,still to remembrance call;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:14-16,4,6,12,N,47,14,And never let his mother's sin
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:14-16,4,6,12,Y,48,14,be blotted out at all.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:14-16,4,7,13,N,49,15,But let them all before the Lord
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:14-16,4,7,13,Y,50,15,"appear continually,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:14-16,4,7,13,N,51,15,That he may wholly from the earth
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:14-16,4,7,13,Y,52,15,cut off their memory.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:14-16,4,7,14,N,53,16,"Because he mercy minded not,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:14-16,4,7,14,Y,54,16,but persecuted still
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:14-16,4,7,14,N,55,16,"The poor and needy, that he might"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:14-16,4,7,14,Y,56,16,the broken-hearted kill.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:17-20,5,8,15,N,57,17,"As he in cursing pleasure took,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:17-20,5,8,15,Y,58,17,so let it to him fall;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:17-20,5,8,15,N,59,17,"As he delighted not to bless,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:17-20,5,8,15,Y,60,17,so bless him not at all.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:17-20,5,8,16,N,61,18,"As cursing he like clothes put on,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:17-20,5,8,16,Y,62,18,"into his bowels so,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:17-20,5,8,16,N,63,18,"Like water, and into his bones,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:17-20,5,8,16,Y,64,18,"like oil, down let it go."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:17-20,5,9,17,N,65,19,Like to the garment let it be
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:17-20,5,9,17,Y,66,19,"which doth himself array,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:17-20,5,9,17,N,67,19,"And for a girdle, wherewith he"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:17-20,5,9,17,Y,68,19,is girt about alway.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:17-20,5,9,18,N,69,20,From God let this be their reward
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:17-20,5,9,18,Y,70,20,"that en'mies are to me,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:17-20,5,9,18,N,71,20,And their reward that speak against
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:17-20,5,9,18,Y,72,20,my soul maliciously.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:21-25,6,10,19,N,73,21,"But do thou, for thine own name's sake,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:21-25,6,10,19,Y,74,21,"O God the Lord, for me:"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:21-25,6,10,19,N,75,21,"Sith good and sweet thy mercy is,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:21-25,6,10,19,Y,76,21,from trouble set me free.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:21-25,6,10,20,N,77,22,"For I am poor and indigent,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:21-25,6,10,20,Y,78,22,"afflicted sore am I,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:21-25,6,10,20,N,79,22,My heart within me also is
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:21-25,6,10,20,Y,80,22,wounded exceedingly.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:21-25,6,11,21,N,81,23,"I pass like a declining shade,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:21-25,6,11,21,Y,82,23,am like the locust tost:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:21-25,6,11,21,N,83,24,"My knees through fasting weaken'd are,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:21-25,6,11,21,Y,84,24,my flesh hath fatness lost.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:21-25,6,11,22,N,85,25,I also am a vile reproach
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:21-25,6,11,22,Y,86,25,unto them made to be;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:21-25,6,11,22,N,87,25,And they that did upon me look
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:21-25,6,11,22,Y,88,25,did shake their heads at me.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:26-29,7,12,23,N,89,26,"O do thou help and succour me,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:26-29,7,12,23,Y,90,26,who art my God and Lord:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:26-29,7,12,23,N,91,26,"And, for thy tender mercy's sake,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:26-29,7,12,23,Y,92,26,safety to me afford:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:26-29,7,12,24,N,93,27,That thereby they may know that this
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:26-29,7,12,24,Y,94,27,is thy almighty hand;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:26-29,7,12,24,N,95,27,"And that thou, Lord, hast done the same,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:26-29,7,12,24,Y,96,27,they may well understand.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:26-29,7,13,25,N,97,28,"Although they curse with spite, yet, Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:26-29,7,13,25,Y,98,28,bless thou with loving voice:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:26-29,7,13,25,N,99,28,Let them asham'd be when they rise;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:26-29,7,13,25,Y,100,28,thy servant let rejoice.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:26-29,7,13,26,N,101,29,Let thou mine adversaries all
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:26-29,7,13,26,Y,102,29,with shame be clothed over;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:26-29,7,13,26,N,103,29,And let their own confusion
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:26-29,7,13,26,Y,104,29,"them, as a mantle, cover."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:30-31,8,14,27,N,105,30,"But as for me, I with my mouth"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:30-31,8,14,27,Y,106,30,will greatly praise the Lord;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:30-31,8,14,27,N,107,30,And I among the multitude
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:30-31,8,14,27,Y,108,30,his praises will record.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:30-31,8,14,28,N,109,31,For he shall stand at his right hand
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:30-31,8,14,28,Y,110,31,"who is in poverty,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:30-31,8,14,28,N,111,31,To save him from all those that would
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),109,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 109:30-31,8,14,28,Y,112,31,condemn his soul to die.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),110,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 110:1-4,1,1,1,N,1,1,"The Lord did say unto my Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),110,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 110:1-4,1,1,1,Y,2,1,"Sit thou at my right hand,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),110,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 110:1-4,1,1,1,N,3,1,"Until I make thy foes a stool,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),110,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 110:1-4,1,1,1,Y,4,1,whereon thy feet may stand.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),110,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 110:1-4,1,1,2,N,5,2,The Lord shall out of Sion send
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),110,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 110:1-4,1,1,2,Y,6,2,the rod of thy great pow'r:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),110,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 110:1-4,1,1,2,N,7,2,In midst of all thine enemies
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),110,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 110:1-4,1,1,2,Y,8,2,be thou the governor.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),110,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 110:1-4,1,2,3,N,9,3,A willing people in thy day
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),110,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 110:1-4,1,2,3,Y,10,3,"of pow'r shall come to thee,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),110,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 110:1-4,1,2,3,N,11,3,In holy beauties from morn's womb;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),110,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 110:1-4,1,2,3,Y,12,3,thy youth like dew shall be.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),110,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 110:1-4,1,2,4,N,13,4,"The Lord himself hath made an oath,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),110,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 110:1-4,1,2,4,Y,14,4,"and will repent him never,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),110,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 110:1-4,1,2,4,N,15,4,Of th' order of Melchisedec
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),110,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 110:1-4,1,2,4,Y,16,4,thou art a priest for ever.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),110,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 110:5-7,2,3,5,N,17,5,"The glorious and mighty Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),110,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 110:5-7,2,3,5,Y,18,5,"that sits at thy right hand,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),110,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 110:5-7,2,3,5,N,19,5,"Shall, in his day of wrath, strike through"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),110,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 110:5-7,2,3,5,Y,20,5,kings that do him withstand.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),110,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 110:5-7,2,3,6,N,21,6,"He shall among the heathen judge,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),110,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 110:5-7,2,3,6,Y,22,6,he shall with bodies dead
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),110,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 110:5-7,2,3,6,N,23,6,The places fill: o'er many lands
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),110,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 110:5-7,2,3,6,Y,24,6,he wound shall ev'ry head.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),110,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 110:5-7,2,4,7,N,25,7,The brook that runneth in the way
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),110,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 110:5-7,2,4,7,Y,26,7,with drink shall him supply;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),110,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 110:5-7,2,4,7,N,27,7,"And, for this cause, in triumph he"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),110,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 110:5-7,2,4,7,Y,28,7,shall lift his head on high.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),111,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 111:1-5,1,1,1,N,1,1,Praise ye the Lord: with my whole heart
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),111,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 111:1-5,1,1,1,Y,2,1,"I will God's praise declare,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),111,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 111:1-5,1,1,1,N,3,1,Where the assemblies of the just
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),111,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 111:1-5,1,1,1,Y,4,1,and congregations are.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),111,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 111:1-5,1,1,2,N,5,2,The whole works of the Lord our God
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),111,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 111:1-5,1,1,2,Y,6,2,"are great above all measure,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),111,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 111:1-5,1,1,2,N,7,2,Sought out they are of ev'ry one
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),111,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 111:1-5,1,1,2,Y,8,2,that doth therein take pleasure.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),111,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 111:1-5,1,2,3,N,9,3,"His work most honourable is,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),111,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 111:1-5,1,2,3,Y,10,3,"most glorious and pure,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),111,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 111:1-5,1,2,3,N,11,3,And his untainted righteousness
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),111,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 111:1-5,1,2,3,Y,12,3,for ever doth endure.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),111,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 111:1-5,1,2,4,N,13,4,His works most wonderful he hath
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),111,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 111:1-5,1,2,4,Y,14,4,made to be thought upon:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),111,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 111:1-5,1,2,4,N,15,4,"The Lord is gracious, and he is"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),111,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 111:1-5,1,2,4,Y,16,4,full of compassion.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),111,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 111:1-5,1,3,5,N,17,5,He giveth meat unto all those
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),111,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 111:1-5,1,3,5,Y,18,5,that truly do him fear;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),111,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 111:1-5,1,3,5,N,19,5,And evermore his covenant
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),111,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 111:1-5,1,3,5,Y,20,5,he in his mind will bear.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),111,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 111:6-10,2,3,6,N,21,6,He did the power of his works
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),111,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 111:6-10,2,3,6,Y,22,6,"unto his people show,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),111,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 111:6-10,2,3,6,N,23,6,When he the heathen's heritage
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),111,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 111:6-10,2,3,6,Y,24,6,upon them did bestow.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),111,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 111:6-10,2,4,7,N,25,7,His handy-works are truth and right;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),111,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 111:6-10,2,4,7,Y,26,7,all his commands are sure:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),111,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 111:6-10,2,4,7,N,27,8,"And, done in truth and uprightness,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),111,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 111:6-10,2,4,7,Y,28,8,they evermore endure.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),111,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 111:6-10,2,4,8,N,29,9,He sent redemption to his folk;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),111,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 111:6-10,2,4,8,Y,30,9,his covenant for aye
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),111,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 111:6-10,2,4,8,N,31,9,He did command: holy his name
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),111,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 111:6-10,2,4,8,Y,32,9,and rev'rend is alway.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),111,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 111:6-10,2,5,9,N,33,10,Wisdom's beginning is God's fear:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),111,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 111:6-10,2,5,9,Y,34,10,good understanding they
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),111,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 111:6-10,2,5,9,N,35,10,Have all that his commands fulfill:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),111,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 111:6-10,2,5,9,Y,36,10,his praise endures for aye.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),112,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 112:1-3,1,1,1,N,1,1,Praise ye the Lord. The man is bless'd
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),112,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 112:1-3,1,1,1,Y,2,1,"that fears the Lord aright,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),112,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 112:1-3,1,1,1,N,3,1,He who in his commandements
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),112,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 112:1-3,1,1,1,Y,4,1,doth greatly take delight.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),112,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 112:1-3,1,1,2,N,5,2,His seed and offspring powerful
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),112,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 112:1-3,1,1,2,Y,6,2,shall be the earth upon:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),112,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 112:1-3,1,1,2,N,7,2,Of upright men blessed shall be
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),112,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 112:1-3,1,1,2,Y,8,2,the generation.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),112,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 112:1-3,1,2,3,N,9,3,Riches and wealth shall ever be
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),112,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 112:1-3,1,2,3,Y,10,3,within his house in store;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),112,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 112:1-3,1,2,3,N,11,3,And his unspotted righteousness
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),112,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 112:1-3,1,2,3,Y,12,3,endures for evermore.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),112,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 112:4-6,2,2,4,N,13,4,"Unto the upright light doth rise,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),112,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 112:4-6,2,2,4,Y,14,4,though he in darkness be:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),112,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 112:4-6,2,2,4,N,15,4,"Compassionate, and merciful,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),112,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 112:4-6,2,2,4,Y,16,4,"and righteous, is he."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),112,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 112:4-6,2,3,5,N,17,5,"A good man doth his favour shew,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),112,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 112:4-6,2,3,5,Y,18,5,and doth to others lend:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),112,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 112:4-6,2,3,5,N,19,5,He with discretion his affairs
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),112,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 112:4-6,2,3,5,Y,20,5,will guide unto the end.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),112,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 112:4-6,2,3,6,N,21,6,Surely there is not any thing
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),112,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 112:4-6,2,3,6,Y,22,6,that ever shall him move:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),112,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 112:4-6,2,3,6,N,23,6,The righteous man's memorial
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),112,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 112:4-6,2,3,6,Y,24,6,shall everlasting prove.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),112,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 112:7-10,3,4,7,N,25,7,"When he shall evil tidings hear,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),112,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 112:7-10,3,4,7,Y,26,7,he shall not be afraid:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),112,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 112:7-10,3,4,7,N,27,7,"His heart is fix'd, his confidence"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),112,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 112:7-10,3,4,7,Y,28,7,upon the Lord is stay'd.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),112,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 112:7-10,3,4,8,N,29,8,"His heart is firmly stablished,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),112,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 112:7-10,3,4,8,Y,30,8,"afraid he shall not be,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),112,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 112:7-10,3,4,8,N,31,8,Until upon his enemies
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),112,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 112:7-10,3,4,8,Y,32,8,he his desire shall see.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),112,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 112:7-10,3,5,9,N,33,9,"He hath dispers'd, giv'n to the poor;"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),112,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 112:7-10,3,5,9,Y,34,9,his righteousness shall be
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),112,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 112:7-10,3,5,9,N,35,9,To ages all; with honour shall
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),112,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 112:7-10,3,5,9,Y,36,9,his horn be raised high.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),112,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 112:7-10,3,5,10,N,37,10,"The wicked shall it see, and fret,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),112,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 112:7-10,3,5,10,Y,38,10,"his teeth gnash, melt away:"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),112,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 112:7-10,3,5,10,N,39,10,What wicked men do most desire
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),112,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 112:7-10,3,5,10,Y,40,10,shall utterly decay.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),113,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 113:1-6,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Praise God: ye servants of the Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),113,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 113:1-6,1,1,1,Y,2,1,"O praise, the Lord's name praise."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),113,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 113:1-6,1,1,1,N,3,2,"Yea, blessed be the name of God"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),113,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 113:1-6,1,1,1,Y,4,2,from this time forth always.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),113,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 113:1-6,1,1,2,N,5,3,"From rising sun to where it sets,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),113,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 113:1-6,1,1,2,Y,6,3,God's name is to be prais'd.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),113,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 113:1-6,1,1,2,N,7,4,"Above all nations God is high,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),113,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 113:1-6,1,1,2,Y,8,4,'bove heav'ns his glory rais'd.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),113,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 113:1-6,1,2,3,N,9,5,Unto the Lord our God that dwells
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),113,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 113:1-6,1,2,3,Y,10,5,"on high, who can compare?"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),113,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 113:1-6,1,2,3,N,11,6,Himself that humbleth things to see
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),113,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 113:1-6,1,2,3,Y,12,6,in heav'n and earth that are.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),113,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 113:7-9,2,2,4,N,13,7,"He from the dust doth raise the poor,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),113,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 113:7-9,2,2,4,Y,14,7,that very low doth lie;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),113,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 113:7-9,2,2,4,N,15,7,And from the dunghill lifts the man
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),113,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 113:7-9,2,2,4,Y,16,7,oppress'd with poverty;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),113,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 113:7-9,2,3,5,N,17,8,"That he may highly him advance,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),113,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 113:7-9,2,3,5,Y,18,8,and with the princes set;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),113,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 113:7-9,2,3,5,N,19,8,With those that of his people are
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),113,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 113:7-9,2,3,5,Y,20,8,"the chief, ev'n princes great."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),113,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 113:7-9,2,3,6,N,21,9,The barren woman house to keep
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),113,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 113:7-9,2,3,6,Y,22,9,"he maketh, and to be"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),113,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 113:7-9,2,3,6,N,23,9,Of sons a mother full of joy.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),113,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 113:7-9,2,3,6,Y,24,9,Praise to the Lord give ye.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),114,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 114:1-6,1,1,1,N,1,1,"When Isr'el out of Egypt went,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),114,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 114:1-6,1,1,1,Y,2,1,"and did his dwelling change,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),114,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 114:1-6,1,1,1,N,3,1,When Jacob's house went out from those
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),114,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 114:1-6,1,1,1,Y,4,1,"that were of language strange,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),114,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 114:1-6,1,1,2,N,5,2,"He Judah did his sanctuary,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),114,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 114:1-6,1,1,2,Y,6,2,his kingdom Isr'el make:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),114,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 114:1-6,1,1,2,N,7,3,"The sea it saw, and quickly fled,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),114,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 114:1-6,1,1,2,Y,8,3,Jordan was driven back.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),114,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 114:1-6,1,2,3,N,9,4,"Like rams the mountains, and like lambs"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),114,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 114:1-6,1,2,3,Y,10,4,the hills skipp'd to and fro.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),114,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 114:1-6,1,2,3,N,11,5,"O sea, why fledd'st thou? Jordan, back"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),114,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 114:1-6,1,2,3,Y,12,5,why wast thou driven so?
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),114,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 114:1-6,1,2,4,N,13,6,"Ye mountains great, wherefore was it"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),114,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 114:1-6,1,2,4,Y,14,6,that ye did skip like rams?
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),114,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 114:1-6,1,2,4,N,15,6,"And wherefore was it, little hills,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),114,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 114:1-6,1,2,4,Y,16,6,that ye did leap like lambs?
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),114,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 114:7-8,2,3,5,N,17,7,"O at the presence of the Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),114,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 114:7-8,2,3,5,Y,18,7,"earth, tremble thou for fear,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),114,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 114:7-8,2,3,5,N,19,7,While as the presence of the God
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),114,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 114:7-8,2,3,5,Y,20,7,of Jacob doth appear:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),114,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 114:7-8,2,3,6,N,21,8,Who from the hard and stony rock
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),114,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 114:7-8,2,3,6,Y,22,8,did standing water bring;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),114,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 114:7-8,2,3,6,N,23,8,And by his pow'r did turn the flint
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),114,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 114:7-8,2,3,6,Y,24,8,into a water-spring.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),115,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 115:1-3,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Not unto us, Lord, not to us,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),115,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 115:1-3,1,1,1,Y,2,1,but do thou glory take
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),115,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 115:1-3,1,1,1,N,3,1,"Unto thy name, ev'n for thy truth,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),115,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 115:1-3,1,1,1,Y,4,1,and for thy mercy's sake.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),115,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 115:1-3,1,1,2,N,5,2,"O wherefore should the heathen say,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),115,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 115:1-3,1,1,2,Y,6,2,Where is their God now gone?
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),115,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 115:1-3,1,1,2,N,7,3,"But our God in the heavens is,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),115,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 115:1-3,1,1,2,Y,8,3,what pleas'd him he hath done.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),115,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 115:4-11,2,2,3,N,9,4,"Their idols silver are and gold,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),115,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 115:4-11,2,2,3,Y,10,4,work of men's hands they be.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),115,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 115:4-11,2,2,3,N,11,5,"Mouths have they, but they do not speak;"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),115,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 115:4-11,2,2,3,Y,12,5,"and eyes, but do not see;"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),115,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 115:4-11,2,2,4,N,13,6,"Ears have they, but they do not hear;"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),115,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 115:4-11,2,2,4,Y,14,6,"noses, but savour not;"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),115,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 115:4-11,2,2,4,N,15,7,"Hands, feet, but handle not, nor walk;"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),115,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 115:4-11,2,2,4,Y,16,7,nor speak they through their throat.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),115,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 115:4-11,2,3,5,N,17,8,"Like them their makers are, and all"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),115,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 115:4-11,2,3,5,Y,18,8,on them their trust that build.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),115,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 115:4-11,2,3,5,N,19,9,"O Isr'el, trust thou in the Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),115,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 115:4-11,2,3,5,Y,20,9,he is their help and shield.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),115,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 115:4-11,2,3,6,N,21,10,"O Aaron's house, trust in the Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),115,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 115:4-11,2,3,6,Y,22,10,their help and shield is he.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),115,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 115:4-11,2,3,6,N,23,11,"Ye that fear God, trust in the Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),115,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 115:4-11,2,3,6,Y,24,11,their help and shield he'll be.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),115,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 115:12-18,3,4,7,N,25,12,"The Lord of us hath mindful been,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),115,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 115:12-18,3,4,7,Y,26,12,and he will bless us still:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),115,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 115:12-18,3,4,7,N,27,12,"He will the house of Isr'el bless,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),115,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 115:12-18,3,4,7,Y,28,12,bless Aaron's house he will.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),115,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 115:12-18,3,4,8,N,29,13,"Both small and great, that fear the Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),115,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 115:12-18,3,4,8,Y,30,13,he will them surely bless.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),115,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 115:12-18,3,4,8,N,31,14,"The Lord will you, you and your seed,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),115,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 115:12-18,3,4,8,Y,32,14,aye more and more increase.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),115,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 115:12-18,3,5,9,N,33,15,"O blessed are ye of the Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),115,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 115:12-18,3,5,9,Y,34,15,who made the earth and heav'n.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),115,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 115:12-18,3,5,9,N,35,16,"The heav'n, ev'n heav'ns, are God's, but he"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),115,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 115:12-18,3,5,9,Y,36,16,earth to men's sons hath giv'n.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),115,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 115:12-18,3,5,10,N,37,17,"The dead, nor who to silence go,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),115,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 115:12-18,3,5,10,Y,38,17,God's praise do not record.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),115,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 115:12-18,3,5,10,N,39,18,But henceforth we for ever will
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),115,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 115:12-18,3,5,10,Y,40,18,bless God. Praise ye the Lord.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),116,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 116:1-6,1,1,1,N,1,1,"I love the Lord, because my voice"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),116,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 116:1-6,1,1,1,Y,2,1,and prayers he did hear.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),116,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 116:1-6,1,1,1,N,3,2,"I, while I live, will call on him,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),116,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 116:1-6,1,1,1,Y,4,2,who bow'd to me his ear.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),116,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 116:1-6,1,1,2,N,5,3,Of death the cords and sorrows did
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),116,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 116:1-6,1,1,2,Y,6,3,about me compass round;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),116,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 116:1-6,1,1,2,N,7,3,"The pains of hell took hold on me,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),116,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 116:1-6,1,1,2,Y,8,3,I grief and trouble found.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),116,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 116:1-6,1,2,3,N,9,4,Upon the name of God the Lord
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),116,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 116:1-6,1,2,3,Y,10,4,"then did I call, and say,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),116,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 116:1-6,1,2,3,N,11,4,"Deliver thou my soul, O Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),116,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 116:1-6,1,2,3,Y,12,4,I do thee humbly pray.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),116,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 116:1-6,1,2,4,N,13,5,"God merciful and righteous is,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),116,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 116:1-6,1,2,4,Y,14,5,"yea, gracious is our Lord."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),116,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 116:1-6,1,2,4,N,15,6,"God saves the meek: I was brought low,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),116,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 116:1-6,1,2,4,Y,16,6,he did me help afford.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),116,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 116:7-14,2,3,5,N,17,7,"O thou my soul, do thou return"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),116,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 116:7-14,2,3,5,Y,18,7,unto thy quiet rest;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),116,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 116:7-14,2,3,5,N,19,7,"For largely, lo, the Lord to thee"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),116,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 116:7-14,2,3,5,Y,20,7,his bounty hath exprest.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),116,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 116:7-14,2,3,6,N,21,8,For my distressed soul from death
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),116,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 116:7-14,2,3,6,Y,22,8,deliver'd was by thee:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),116,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 116:7-14,2,3,6,N,23,8,"Thou didst my mourning eyes from tears,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),116,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 116:7-14,2,3,6,Y,24,8,"my feet from falling, free."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),116,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 116:7-14,2,4,7,N,25,9,I in the land of those that live
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),116,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 116:7-14,2,4,7,Y,26,9,will walk the Lord before.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),116,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 116:7-14,2,4,7,N,27,10,"I did believe, therefore I spake:"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),116,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 116:7-14,2,4,7,Y,28,10,I was afflicted sore.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),116,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 116:7-14,2,4,8,N,29,11,"I said, when I was in my haste,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),116,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 116:7-14,2,4,8,Y,30,11,that all men liars be.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),116,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 116:7-14,2,4,8,N,31,12,What shall I render to the Lord
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),116,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 116:7-14,2,4,8,Y,32,12,for all his gifts to me?
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),116,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 116:7-14,2,5,9,N,33,13,"I'll of salvation take the cup,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),116,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 116:7-14,2,5,9,Y,34,13,on God's name will I call:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),116,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 116:7-14,2,5,9,N,35,14,I'll pay my vows now to the Lord
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),116,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 116:7-14,2,5,9,Y,36,14,before his people all.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),116,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 116:15-19,3,5,10,N,37,15,Dear in God's sight is his saints' death.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),116,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 116:15-19,3,5,10,Y,38,16,"Thy servant, Lord, am I;"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),116,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 116:15-19,3,5,10,N,39,16,"Thy servant sure, thine handmaid's son:"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),116,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 116:15-19,3,5,10,Y,40,16,my bands thou didst untie.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),116,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 116:15-19,3,6,11,N,41,17,"Thank-off 'rings I to thee will give,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),116,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 116:15-19,3,6,11,Y,42,17,and on God's name will call.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),116,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 116:15-19,3,6,11,N,43,18,I'll pay my vows now to the Lord
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),116,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 116:15-19,3,6,11,Y,44,18,before his people all;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),116,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 116:15-19,3,6,12,N,45,19,"Within the courts of God's own house,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),116,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 116:15-19,3,6,12,Y,46,19,"within the midst of thee,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),116,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 116:15-19,3,6,12,N,47,19,O city of Jerusalem.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),116,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 116:15-19,3,6,12,Y,48,19,Praise to the Lord give ye.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),117,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 117:1-2,1,1,1,N,1,1,"O give ye praise unto the Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),117,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 117:1-2,1,1,1,Y,2,1,all nations that be;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),117,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 117:1-2,1,1,1,N,3,1,"Likewise, ye people all, accord"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),117,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 117:1-2,1,1,1,Y,4,1,his name to magnify.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),117,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 117:1-2,1,1,2,N,5,2,For great to us-ward ever are
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),117,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 117:1-2,1,1,2,Y,6,2,his loving-kindnesses:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),117,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 117:1-2,1,1,2,N,7,2,His truth endures for evermore.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),117,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 117:1-2,1,1,2,Y,8,2,The Lord O do ye bless.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:1-7,1,1,1,N,1,1,"O praise the Lord, for he is good;"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:1-7,1,1,1,Y,2,1,his mercy lasteth ever.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:1-7,1,1,1,N,3,2,"Let those of Israel now say,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:1-7,1,1,1,Y,4,2,His mercy faileth never.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:1-7,1,1,2,N,5,3,"Now let the house of Aaron say,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:1-7,1,1,2,Y,6,3,His mercy lasteth ever.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:1-7,1,1,2,N,7,4,"Let those that fear the Lord now say,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:1-7,1,1,2,Y,8,4,His mercy faileth never.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:1-7,1,2,3,N,9,5,I in distress call'd on the Lord;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:1-7,1,2,3,Y,10,5,the Lord did answer me:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:1-7,1,2,3,N,11,5,"He in a large place did me set,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:1-7,1,2,3,Y,12,5,from trouble made me free.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:1-7,1,2,4,N,13,6,"The mighty Lord is on my side,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:1-7,1,2,4,Y,14,6,I will not be afraid;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:1-7,1,2,4,N,15,6,For any thing that man can do
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:1-7,1,2,4,Y,16,6,I shall not be dismay'd.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:1-7,1,3,5,N,17,7,The Lord doth take my part with them
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:1-7,1,3,5,Y,18,7,that help to succour me:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:1-7,1,3,5,N,19,7,Therefore on those that do me hate
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:1-7,1,3,5,Y,20,7,I my desire shall see.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:8-14,2,3,6,N,21,8,Better it is to trust in God
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:8-14,2,3,6,Y,22,8,than trust in man's defence;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:8-14,2,3,6,N,23,9,Better to trust in God than make
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:8-14,2,3,6,Y,24,9,princes our confidence.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:8-14,2,4,7,N,25,10,"The nations, joining all in one,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:8-14,2,4,7,Y,26,10,did compass me about:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:8-14,2,4,7,N,27,10,But in the Lord's most holy name
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:8-14,2,4,7,Y,28,10,I shall them all root out.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:8-14,2,4,8,N,29,11,"They compass'd me about; I say,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:8-14,2,4,8,Y,30,11,they compass'd me about:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:8-14,2,4,8,N,31,11,But in the Lord's most holy name
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:8-14,2,4,8,Y,32,11,I shall them all root out.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:8-14,2,5,9,N,33,12,Like bees they compass'd me about;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:8-14,2,5,9,Y,34,12,like unto thorns that flame
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:8-14,2,5,9,N,35,12,They quenched are: for them shall I
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:8-14,2,5,9,Y,36,12,destroy in God's own name.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:8-14,2,5,10,N,37,13,"Thou sore hast thrust, that I might fall,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:8-14,2,5,10,Y,38,13,but my Lord helped me.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:8-14,2,5,10,N,39,14,"God my salvation is become,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:8-14,2,5,10,Y,40,14,my strength and song is he.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:15-21,3,6,11,N,41,15,In dwellings of the righteous
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:15-21,3,6,11,Y,42,15,is heard the melody
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:15-21,3,6,11,N,43,15,Of joy and health: the Lord's right hand
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:15-21,3,6,11,Y,44,15,doth ever valiantly.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:15-21,3,6,12,N,45,16,The right hand of the mighty Lord
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:15-21,3,6,12,Y,46,16,exalted is on high;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:15-21,3,6,12,N,47,16,The right hand of the mighty Lord
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:15-21,3,6,12,Y,48,16,doth ever valiantly.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:15-21,3,7,13,N,49,17,"I shall not die, but live, and shall"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:15-21,3,7,13,Y,50,17,the works of God discover.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:15-21,3,7,13,N,51,18,"The Lord hath me chastised sore,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:15-21,3,7,13,Y,52,18,but not to death giv'n over.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:15-21,3,7,14,N,53,19,O set ye open unto me
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:15-21,3,7,14,Y,54,19,the gates of righteousness;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:15-21,3,7,14,N,55,19,"Then will I enter into them,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:15-21,3,7,14,Y,56,19,and I the Lord will bless.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:15-21,3,8,15,N,57,20,"This is the gate of God, by it"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:15-21,3,8,15,Y,58,20,the just shall enter in.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:15-21,3,8,15,N,59,21,"Thee will I praise, for thou me heard'st"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:15-21,3,8,15,Y,60,21,and hast my safety been.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:22-29,4,8,16,N,61,22,"That stone is made head corner-stone,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:22-29,4,8,16,Y,62,22,which builders did despise:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:22-29,4,8,16,N,63,23,"This is the doing of the Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:22-29,4,8,16,Y,64,23,and wondrous in our eyes.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:22-29,4,9,17,N,65,24,"This is the day God made, in it"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:22-29,4,9,17,Y,66,24,we'll joy triumphantly.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:22-29,4,9,17,N,67,25,"Save now, I pray thee, Lord; I pray,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:22-29,4,9,17,Y,68,25,send now prosperity.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:22-29,4,9,18,N,69,26,Blessed is he in God's great name
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:22-29,4,9,18,Y,70,26,that cometh us to save:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:22-29,4,9,18,N,71,26,"We, from the house which to the Lord"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:22-29,4,9,18,Y,72,26,"pertains, you blessed have."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:22-29,4,10,19,N,73,27,"God is the Lord, who unto us"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:22-29,4,10,19,Y,74,27,hath made light to arise:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:22-29,4,10,19,N,75,27,Bind ye unto the altar's horns
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:22-29,4,10,19,Y,76,27,with cords the sacrifice.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:22-29,4,10,20,N,77,28,"Thou art my God, I'll thee exalt;"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:22-29,4,10,20,Y,78,28,"my God, I will thee praise."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:22-29,4,10,20,N,79,29,"Give thanks to God, for he is good:"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),118,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 118:22-29,4,10,20,Y,80,29,his mercy lasts always.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:1-4,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Blessed are they that undefil'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:1-4,1,1,1,Y,2,1,and straight are in the way;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:1-4,1,1,1,N,3,1,Who in the Lord's most holy law
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:1-4,1,1,1,Y,4,1,"do walk, and do not stray."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:1-4,1,1,2,N,5,2,Blessed are they who to observe
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:1-4,1,1,2,Y,6,2,his statutes are inclin'd;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:1-4,1,1,2,N,7,2,And who do seek the living God
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:1-4,1,1,2,Y,8,2,with their whole heart and mind.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:1-4,1,2,3,N,9,3,"Such in his ways do walk, and they"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:1-4,1,2,3,Y,10,3,do no iniquity.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:1-4,1,2,3,N,11,4,Thou hast commanded us to keep
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:1-4,1,2,3,Y,12,4,thy precepts carefully.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:5-8,2,2,4,N,13,5,O that thy statutes to observe
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:5-8,2,2,4,Y,14,5,thou would'st my ways direct!
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:5-8,2,2,4,N,15,6,"Then shall I not be sham'd, when I"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:5-8,2,2,4,Y,16,6,thy precepts all respect.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:5-8,2,3,5,N,17,7,Then with integrity of heart
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:5-8,2,3,5,Y,18,7,"thee will I praise and bless,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:5-8,2,3,5,N,19,7,When I the judgments all have learn'd
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:5-8,2,3,5,Y,20,7,of thy pure righteousness.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:5-8,2,3,6,N,21,8,That I will keep thy statutes all
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:5-8,2,3,6,Y,22,8,firmly resolv'd have I:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:5-8,2,3,6,N,23,8,"O do not then, most gracious God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:5-8,2,3,6,Y,24,8,forsake me utterly.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:9-12,3,3,7,N,25,9,By what means shall a young man learn
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:9-12,3,3,7,Y,26,9,his way to purify?
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:9-12,3,3,7,N,27,9,If he according to thy word
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:9-12,3,3,7,Y,28,9,thereto attentive be.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:9-12,3,3,8,N,29,10,Unfeignedly thee have I sought
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:9-12,3,3,8,Y,30,10,with all my soul and heart:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:9-12,3,3,8,N,31,10,O let me not from the right path
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:9-12,3,3,8,Y,32,10,of thy commands depart.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:9-12,3,4,9,N,33,11,"Thy word I in my heart have hid,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:9-12,3,4,9,Y,34,11,that I offend not thee.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:9-12,3,4,9,N,35,12,"O Lord, thou ever blessed art,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:9-12,3,4,9,Y,36,12,thy statutes teach thou me.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:13-16,4,4,10,N,37,13,The judgments of thy mouth each one
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:13-16,4,4,10,Y,38,13,my lips declared have:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:13-16,4,4,10,N,39,14,More joy thy testimonies' way
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:13-16,4,4,10,Y,40,14,than riches all me gave.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:13-16,4,5,11,N,41,15,I will thy holy precepts make
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:13-16,4,5,11,Y,42,15,my meditation;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:13-16,4,5,11,N,43,15,And carefully I'll have respect
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:13-16,4,5,11,Y,44,15,unto thy ways each one.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:13-16,4,5,12,N,45,16,Upon thy statutes my delight
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:13-16,4,5,12,Y,46,16,shall constantly be set:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:13-16,4,5,12,N,47,16,"And, by thy grace, I never will"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:13-16,4,5,12,Y,48,16,thy holy word forget.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:17-20,5,5,13,N,49,17,"With me thy servant, in thy grace,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:17-20,5,5,13,Y,50,17,"Deal bountifully, Lord;"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:17-20,5,5,13,N,51,17,"That by thy favour I may live,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:17-20,5,5,13,Y,52,17,and duly keep thy word.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:17-20,5,5,14,N,53,18,"Open mine eyes, that of thy law"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:17-20,5,5,14,Y,54,18,the wonders I may see.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:17-20,5,5,14,N,55,19,"I am a stranger on this earth,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:17-20,5,5,14,Y,56,19,hide not thy laws from me.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:17-20,5,6,15,N,57,20,"My soul within me breaks, and doth"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:17-20,5,6,15,Y,58,20,"much fainting still endure,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:17-20,5,6,15,N,59,20,Through longing that it hath all times
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:17-20,5,6,15,Y,60,20,unto thy judgments pure.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:21-24,6,6,16,N,61,21,"Thou hast rebuk'd the cursed proud,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:21-24,6,6,16,Y,62,21,who from thy precepts swerve.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:21-24,6,6,16,N,63,22,"Reproach and shame remove from me,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:21-24,6,6,16,Y,64,22,for I thy laws observe.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:21-24,6,7,17,N,65,23,"Against me princes spake with spite,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:21-24,6,7,17,Y,66,23,while they in council sat:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:21-24,6,7,17,N,67,23,But I thy servant did upon
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:21-24,6,7,17,Y,68,23,thy statutes meditate.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:21-24,6,7,18,N,69,24,"My comfort, and my heart's delight,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:21-24,6,7,18,Y,70,24,thy testimonies be;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:21-24,6,7,18,N,71,24,"And they, in all my doubts and fears,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:21-24,6,7,18,Y,72,24,are counsellors to me.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:25-28,7,7,19,N,73,25,"My soul to dust cleaves: quicken me,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:25-28,7,7,19,Y,74,25,according to thy word.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:25-28,7,7,19,N,75,26,"My ways I shew'd, and me thou heard'st:"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:25-28,7,7,19,Y,76,26,"teach me thy statutes, Lord."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:25-28,7,7,20,N,77,27,The way of thy commandements
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:25-28,7,7,20,Y,78,27,make me aright to know;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:25-28,7,7,20,N,79,27,So all thy works that wondrous are
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:25-28,7,7,20,Y,80,27,I shall to others show.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:25-28,7,8,21,N,81,28,"My soul doth melt, and drop away,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:25-28,7,8,21,Y,82,28,for heaviness and grief:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:25-28,7,8,21,N,83,28,"To me, according to thy word,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:25-28,7,8,21,Y,84,28,"give strength, and send relief."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:29-32,8,8,22,N,85,29,From me the wicked way of lies
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:29-32,8,8,22,Y,86,29,let far removed be;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:29-32,8,8,22,N,87,29,And graciously thy holy law
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:29-32,8,8,22,Y,88,29,do thou grant unto me.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:29-32,8,9,23,N,89,30,I chosen have the perfect way
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:29-32,8,9,23,Y,90,30,of truth and verity:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:29-32,8,9,23,N,91,30,Thy judgments that most righteous are
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:29-32,8,9,23,Y,92,30,before me laid have I.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:29-32,8,9,24,N,93,31,I to thy testimonies cleave;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:29-32,8,9,24,Y,94,31,shame do not on me cast.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:29-32,8,9,24,N,95,32,"I'll run thy precepts' way, when thou"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:29-32,8,9,24,Y,96,32,my heart enlarged hast.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:41-43,11,9,25,N,97,41,Let thy sweet mercies also come
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:41-43,11,9,25,Y,98,41,"and visit me, O Lord;"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:41-43,11,9,25,N,99,41,"Ev'n thy benign salvation,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:41-43,11,9,25,Y,100,41,according to thy word.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:41-43,11,9,26,N,101,42,So shall I have wherewith I may
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:41-43,11,9,26,Y,102,42,"give him an answer just,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:41-43,11,9,26,N,103,42,Who spitefully reproacheth me;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:41-43,11,9,26,Y,104,42,for in thy word I trust.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:41-43,11,10,27,N,105,43,The word of truth out of my mouth
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:41-43,11,10,27,Y,106,43,take thou not utterly;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:41-43,11,10,27,N,107,43,For on thy judgments righteous
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:41-43,11,10,27,Y,108,43,my hope doth still rely.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:44-48,12,10,28,N,109,44,So shall I keep for evermore
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:44-48,12,10,28,Y,110,44,thy law continually.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:44-48,12,10,28,N,111,45,"And, sith that I thy precepts seek,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:44-48,12,10,28,Y,112,45,I'll walk at liberty.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:44-48,12,11,29,N,113,46,"I'll speak thy word to kings, and I"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:44-48,12,11,29,Y,114,46,with shame shall not be mov'd;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:44-48,12,11,29,N,115,47,And will delight myself always
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:44-48,12,11,29,Y,116,47,"in thy laws, which I lov'd."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:44-48,12,11,30,N,117,48,"To thy commandments, which I lov'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:44-48,12,11,30,Y,118,48,my hands lift up I will;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:44-48,12,11,30,N,119,48,And I will also meditate
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:44-48,12,11,30,Y,120,48,upon thy statutes still.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:49-51,13,11,31,N,121,49,"Remember, Lord, thy gracious word"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:49-51,13,11,31,Y,122,49,"thou to thy servant spake,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:49-51,13,11,31,N,123,49,"Which, for a ground of my sure hope,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:49-51,13,11,31,Y,124,49,thou causedst me to take.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:49-51,13,11,32,N,125,50,This word of thine my comfort is
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:49-51,13,11,32,Y,126,50,in mine affliction:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:49-51,13,11,32,N,127,50,For in my straits I am reviv'd
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:49-51,13,11,32,Y,128,50,by this thy word alone.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:49-51,13,12,33,N,129,51,The men whose hearts with pride are stuff'd
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:49-51,13,12,33,Y,130,51,did greatly me deride;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:49-51,13,12,33,N,131,51,Yet from thy straight commandements
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:49-51,13,12,33,Y,132,51,I have not turn'd aside.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:52-56,14,12,34,N,133,52,"Thy judgments righteous, O Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:52-56,14,12,34,Y,134,52,"which thou of old forth gave,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:52-56,14,12,34,N,135,52,"I did remember, and myself"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:52-56,14,12,34,Y,136,52,by them comforted have.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:52-56,14,13,35,N,137,53,"Horror took hold on me, because"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:52-56,14,13,35,Y,138,53,ill men thy law forsake.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:52-56,14,13,35,N,139,54,I in my house of pilgrimage
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:52-56,14,13,35,Y,140,54,thy laws my songs do make.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:52-56,14,13,36,N,141,55,"Thy name by night, Lord, I did mind,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:52-56,14,13,36,Y,142,55,and I have kept thy law.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:52-56,14,13,36,N,143,56,"And this I had, because thy word"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:52-56,14,13,36,Y,144,56,"I kept, and stood in awe."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:57-59,15,13,37,N,145,57,"Thou my sure portion art alone,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:57-59,15,13,37,Y,146,57,"which I did chuse, O Lord:"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:57-59,15,13,37,N,147,57,"I have resolv'd, and said, that I"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:57-59,15,13,37,Y,148,57,would keep thy holy word.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:57-59,15,13,38,N,149,58,With my whole heart I did entreat
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:57-59,15,13,38,Y,150,58,thy face and favour free:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:57-59,15,13,38,N,151,58,According to thy gracious word
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:57-59,15,13,38,Y,152,58,be merciful to me.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:57-59,15,14,39,N,153,59,"I thought upon my former ways,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:57-59,15,14,39,Y,154,59,and did my life well try;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:57-59,15,14,39,N,155,59,And to thy testimonies pure
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:57-59,15,14,39,Y,156,59,my feet then turned I.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:60-64,16,14,40,N,157,60,"I did not stay, nor linger long,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:60-64,16,14,40,Y,158,60,as those that slothful are;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:60-64,16,14,40,N,159,60,But hastily thy laws to keep
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:60-64,16,14,40,Y,160,60,myself I did prepare.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:60-64,16,15,41,N,161,61,Bands of ill men me robb'd; yet I
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:60-64,16,15,41,Y,162,61,thy precepts did not slight.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:60-64,16,15,41,N,163,62,"I'll rise at midnight thee to praise,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:60-64,16,15,41,Y,164,62,ev'n for thy judgments right.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:60-64,16,15,42,N,165,63,I am companion to all those
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:60-64,16,15,42,Y,166,63,"who fear, and thee obey."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:60-64,16,15,42,N,167,64,"O Lord, thy mercy fills the earth:"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:60-64,16,15,42,Y,168,64,"teach me thy laws, I pray."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:65-69,17,15,43,N,169,65,"Well hast thou with thy servant dealt,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:65-69,17,15,43,Y,170,65,as thou didst promise give.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:65-69,17,15,43,N,171,66,"Good judgment me, and knowledge teach,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:65-69,17,15,43,Y,172,66,for I thy word believe.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:65-69,17,15,44,N,173,67,Ere I afflicted was I stray'd;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:65-69,17,15,44,Y,174,67,but now I keep thy word.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:65-69,17,15,44,N,175,68,"Both good thou art, and good thou do'st:"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:65-69,17,15,44,Y,176,68,"teach me thy statutes, Lord."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:65-69,17,16,45,N,177,69,The men that are puff 'd up with pride
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:65-69,17,16,45,Y,178,69,against me forg'd a lie;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:65-69,17,16,45,N,179,69,Yet thy commandements observe
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:65-69,17,16,45,Y,180,69,with my whole heart will I.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:70-72,18,16,46,N,181,70,"Their hearts, through worldly ease and wealth,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:70-72,18,16,46,Y,182,70,as fat as grease they be:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:70-72,18,16,46,N,183,70,But in thy holy law I take
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:70-72,18,16,46,Y,184,70,delight continually.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:70-72,18,17,47,N,185,71,It hath been very good for me
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:70-72,18,17,47,Y,186,71,"that I afflicted was,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:70-72,18,17,47,N,187,71,"That I might well instructed be,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:70-72,18,17,47,Y,188,71,and learn thy holy laws.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:70-72,18,17,48,N,189,72,The word that cometh from thy mouth
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:70-72,18,17,48,Y,190,72,is better unto me
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:70-72,18,17,48,N,191,72,Than many thousands and great sums
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:70-72,18,17,48,Y,192,72,of gold and silver be.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:73-76,19,17,49,N,193,73,Thou mad'st and fashion'dst me: thy laws
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:73-76,19,17,49,Y,194,73,"to know give wisdom, Lord."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:73-76,19,17,49,N,195,74,So who thee fear shall joy to see
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:73-76,19,17,49,Y,196,74,me trusting in thy word.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:73-76,19,17,50,N,197,75,That very right thy judgments are
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:73-76,19,17,50,Y,198,75,"I know, and do confess;"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:73-76,19,17,50,N,199,75,And that thou hast afflicted me
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:73-76,19,17,50,Y,200,75,in truth and faithfulness.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:73-76,19,18,51,N,201,76,"O let thy kindness merciful,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:73-76,19,18,51,Y,202,76,"I pray thee, comfort me,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:73-76,19,18,51,N,203,76,As to thy servant faithfully
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:73-76,19,18,51,Y,204,76,was promised by thee.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:77-80,20,18,52,N,205,77,And let thy tender mercies come
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:77-80,20,18,52,Y,206,77,"to me, that I may live;"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:77-80,20,18,52,N,207,77,Because thy holy laws to me
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:77-80,20,18,52,Y,208,77,sweet delectation give.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:77-80,20,19,53,N,209,78,"Lord, let the proud ashamed be;"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:77-80,20,19,53,Y,210,78,"for they, without a cause,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:77-80,20,19,53,N,211,78,With me perversely dealt: but I
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:77-80,20,19,53,Y,212,78,will muse upon thy laws.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:77-80,20,19,54,N,213,79,"Let such as fear thee, and have known"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:77-80,20,19,54,Y,214,79,"thy statutes, turn to me."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:77-80,20,19,54,N,215,80,"My heart let in thy laws be sound,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:77-80,20,19,54,Y,216,80,that sham'd I never be.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:81-84,21,19,55,N,217,81,My soul for thy salvation faints;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:81-84,21,19,55,Y,218,81,yet I thy word believe.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:81-84,21,19,55,N,219,82,"Mine eyes fail for thy word: I say,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:81-84,21,19,55,Y,220,82,When wilt thou comfort give?
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:81-84,21,19,56,N,221,83,"For like a bottle I'm become,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:81-84,21,19,56,Y,222,83,that in the smoke is set:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:81-84,21,19,56,N,223,83,"I'm black, and parch'd with grief; yet I"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:81-84,21,19,56,Y,224,83,thy statutes not forget.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:81-84,21,20,57,N,225,84,How many are thy servant's days?
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:81-84,21,20,57,Y,226,84,when wilt thou execute
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:81-84,21,20,57,N,227,84,Just judgment on these wicked men
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:81-84,21,20,57,Y,228,84,that do me persecute?
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:85-88,22,20,58,N,229,85,"The proud have digged pits for me,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:85-88,22,20,58,Y,230,85,which is against thy laws.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:85-88,22,20,58,N,231,86,"Thy words all faithful are: help me,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:85-88,22,20,58,Y,232,86,pursu'd without a cause.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:85-88,22,21,59,N,233,87,"They so consum'd me, that on earth"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:85-88,22,21,59,Y,234,87,my life they scarce did leave:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:85-88,22,21,59,N,235,87,"Thy precepts yet forsook I not,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:85-88,22,21,59,Y,236,87,but close to them did cleave.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:85-88,22,21,60,N,237,88,"After thy loving-kindness, Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:85-88,22,21,60,Y,238,88,"me quicken, and preserve:"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:85-88,22,21,60,N,239,88,The testimony of thy mouth
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:85-88,22,21,60,Y,240,88,so shall I still observe.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:89-92,23,21,61,N,241,89,"Thy word for ever is, O Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:89-92,23,21,61,Y,242,89,in heaven settled fast;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:89-92,23,21,61,N,243,90,Unto all generations
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:89-92,23,21,61,Y,244,90,thy faithfulness doth last:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:89-92,23,21,62,N,245,90,"The earth thou hast established,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:89-92,23,21,62,Y,246,90,and it abides by thee.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:89-92,23,21,62,N,247,91,This day they stand as thou ordain'dst;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:89-92,23,21,62,Y,248,91,for all thy servants be.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:89-92,23,22,63,N,249,92,Unless in thy most perfect law
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:89-92,23,22,63,Y,250,92,"my soul delights had found,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:89-92,23,22,63,N,251,92,"I should have perished, when as"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:89-92,23,22,63,Y,252,92,my troubles did abound.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:93-96,24,22,64,N,253,93,Thy precepts I will ne'er forget;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:93-96,24,22,64,Y,254,93,they quick'ning to me brought.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:93-96,24,22,64,N,255,94,"Lord, I am thine; O save thou me:"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:93-96,24,22,64,Y,256,94,thy precepts I have sought.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:93-96,24,23,65,N,257,95,"For me the wicked have laid wait,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:93-96,24,23,65,Y,258,95,me seeking to destroy:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:93-96,24,23,65,N,259,95,But I thy testimonies true
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:93-96,24,23,65,Y,260,95,consider will with joy.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:93-96,24,23,66,N,261,96,An end of all perfection
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:93-96,24,23,66,Y,262,96,"here have I seen, O God:"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:93-96,24,23,66,N,263,96,"But as for thy commandement,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:93-96,24,23,66,Y,264,96,it is exceeding broad.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:97-100,25,23,67,N,265,97,O how love I thy law! it is
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:97-100,25,23,67,Y,266,97,my study all the day:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:97-100,25,23,67,N,267,98,It makes me wiser than my foes;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:97-100,25,23,67,Y,268,98,for it doth with me stay.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:97-100,25,23,68,N,269,99,Than all my teachers now I have
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:97-100,25,23,68,Y,270,99,more understanding far;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:97-100,25,23,68,N,271,99,Because my meditation
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:97-100,25,23,68,Y,272,99,thy testimonies are.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:97-100,25,24,69,N,273,100,In understanding I excel
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:97-100,25,24,69,Y,274,100,those that are ancients;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:97-100,25,24,69,N,275,100,For I endeavoured to keep
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:97-100,25,24,69,Y,276,100,all thy commandements.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:101-104,26,24,70,N,277,101,"My feet from each ill way I stay'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:101-104,26,24,70,Y,278,101,that I may keep thy word.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:101-104,26,24,70,N,279,102,I from thy judgments have not swerv'd;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:101-104,26,24,70,Y,280,102,"for thou hast taught me, Lord."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:101-104,26,25,71,N,281,103,"How sweet unto my taste, O Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:101-104,26,25,71,Y,282,103,are all thy words of truth!
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:101-104,26,25,71,N,283,103,"Yea, I do find them sweeter far"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:101-104,26,25,71,Y,284,103,than honey to my mouth.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:101-104,26,25,72,N,285,104,"I through thy precepts, that are pure,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:101-104,26,25,72,Y,286,104,do understanding get;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:101-104,26,25,72,N,287,104,I therefore ev'ry way that's false
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:101-104,26,25,72,Y,288,104,with all my heart do hate.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:105-108,27,25,73,N,289,105,"Thy word is to my feet a lamp,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:105-108,27,25,73,Y,290,105,and to my path a light.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:105-108,27,25,73,N,291,106,"I sworn have, and I will perform,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:105-108,27,25,73,Y,292,106,to keep thy judgments right.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:105-108,27,25,74,N,293,107,I am with sore affliction
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:105-108,27,25,74,Y,294,107,"ev'n overwhelm'd, O Lord:"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:105-108,27,25,74,N,295,107,"In mercy raise and quicken me,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:105-108,27,25,74,Y,296,107,according to thy word.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:105-108,27,26,75,N,297,108,The free-will-off 'rings of my mouth
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:105-108,27,26,75,Y,298,108,"accept, I thee beseech:"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:105-108,27,26,75,N,299,108,"And unto me thy servant, Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:105-108,27,26,75,Y,300,108,thy judgments clearly teach.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:109-112,28,26,76,N,301,109,"Though still my soul be in my hand,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:109-112,28,26,76,Y,302,109,thy laws I'll not forget.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:109-112,28,26,76,N,303,110,"I err'd not from them, though for me"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:109-112,28,26,76,Y,304,110,the wicked snares did set.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:109-112,28,27,77,N,305,111,I of thy testimonies have
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:109-112,28,27,77,Y,306,111,"above all things made choice,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:109-112,28,27,77,N,307,111,To be my heritage for aye;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:109-112,28,27,77,Y,308,111,for they my heart rejoice.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:109-112,28,27,78,N,309,112,I carefully inclined have
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:109-112,28,27,78,Y,310,112,my heart still to attend;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:109-112,28,27,78,N,311,112,That I thy statutes may perform
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:109-112,28,27,78,Y,312,112,alway unto the end.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:113-116,29,27,79,N,313,113,"I hate the thoughts of vanity,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:113-116,29,27,79,Y,314,113,but love thy law do I.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:113-116,29,27,79,N,315,114,My shield and hiding-place thou art:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:113-116,29,27,79,Y,316,114,I on thy word rely.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:113-116,29,27,80,N,317,115,All ye that evil-doers are
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:113-116,29,27,80,Y,318,115,from me depart away;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:113-116,29,27,80,N,319,115,For the commandments of my God
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:113-116,29,27,80,Y,320,115,I purpose to obey.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:113-116,29,28,81,N,321,116,According to thy faithful word
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:113-116,29,28,81,Y,322,116,"uphold and stablish me,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:113-116,29,28,81,N,323,116,"That I may live, and of my hope"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:113-116,29,28,81,Y,324,116,ashamed never be.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:117-120,30,28,82,N,325,117,"Hold thou me up, so shall I be"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:117-120,30,28,82,Y,326,117,in peace and safety still;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:117-120,30,28,82,N,327,117,And to thy statutes have respect
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:117-120,30,28,82,Y,328,117,continually I will.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:117-120,30,29,83,N,329,118,Thou tread'st down all that love to stray;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:117-120,30,29,83,Y,330,118,false their deceit doth prove.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:117-120,30,29,83,N,331,119,"Lewd men, like dross, away thou putt'st;"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:117-120,30,29,83,Y,332,119,therefore thy law I love.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:117-120,30,29,84,N,333,120,For fear of thee my very flesh
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:117-120,30,29,84,Y,334,120,"doth tremble, all dismay'd;"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:117-120,30,29,84,N,335,120,"And of thy righteous judgments, Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:117-120,30,29,84,Y,336,120,my soul is much afraid.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:121-123,31,29,85,N,337,121,"To all men I have judgment done,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:121-123,31,29,85,Y,338,121,performing justice right;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:121-123,31,29,85,N,339,121,Then let me not be left unto
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:121-123,31,29,85,Y,340,121,my fierce oppressors' might.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:121-123,31,29,86,N,341,122,"For good unto thy servant, Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:121-123,31,29,86,Y,342,122,thy servant's surety be:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:121-123,31,29,86,N,343,122,From the oppression of the proud
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:121-123,31,29,86,Y,344,122,do thou deliver me.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:121-123,31,30,87,N,345,123,Mine eyes do fail with looking long
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:121-123,31,30,87,Y,346,123,"for thy salvation,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:121-123,31,30,87,N,347,123,The word of thy pure righteousness
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:121-123,31,30,87,Y,348,123,while I do wait upon.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:124-128,32,30,88,N,349,124,"In mercy with thy servant deal,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:124-128,32,30,88,Y,350,124,thy laws me teach and show.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:124-128,32,30,88,N,351,125,"I am thy servant, wisdom give,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:124-128,32,30,88,Y,352,125,that I thy laws may know.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:124-128,32,31,89,N,353,126,"'Tis time thou work, Lord; for they have"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:124-128,32,31,89,Y,354,126,made void thy law divine.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:124-128,32,31,89,N,355,127,Therefore thy precepts more I love
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:124-128,32,31,89,Y,356,127,"than gold, yea, gold most fine."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:124-128,32,31,90,N,357,128,Concerning all things thy commands
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:124-128,32,31,90,Y,358,128,all right I judge therefore;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:124-128,32,31,90,N,359,128,And ev'ry false and wicked way
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:124-128,32,31,90,Y,360,128,I perfectly abhor.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:129-132,33,31,91,N,361,129,"Thy statutes, Lord, are wonderful,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:129-132,33,31,91,Y,362,129,my soul them keeps with care.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:129-132,33,31,91,N,363,130,"The entrance of thy words gives light,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:129-132,33,31,91,Y,364,130,makes wise who simple are.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:129-132,33,31,92,N,365,131,"My mouth I have wide opened,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:129-132,33,31,92,Y,366,131,"and panted earnestly,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:129-132,33,31,92,N,367,131,While after thy commandements
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:129-132,33,31,92,Y,368,131,I long'd exceedingly.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:129-132,33,32,93,N,369,132,"Look on me, Lord, and merciful"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:129-132,33,32,93,Y,370,132,"do thou unto me prove,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:129-132,33,32,93,N,371,132,As thou art wont to do to those
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:129-132,33,32,93,Y,372,132,thy name who truly love.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:133-136,34,32,94,N,373,133,O let my footsteps in thy word
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:133-136,34,32,94,Y,374,133,aright still order'd be:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:133-136,34,32,94,N,375,133,Let no iniquity obtain
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:133-136,34,32,94,Y,376,133,dominion over me.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:133-136,34,33,95,N,377,134,From man's oppression save thou me;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:133-136,34,33,95,Y,378,134,so keep thy laws I will.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:133-136,34,33,95,N,379,135,Thy face make on thy servant shine;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:133-136,34,33,95,Y,380,135,teach me thy statutes still.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:133-136,34,33,96,N,381,136,Rivers of waters from mine eyes
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:133-136,34,33,96,Y,382,136,"did run down, when I saw"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:133-136,34,33,96,N,383,136,"How wicked men run on in sin,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:133-136,34,33,96,Y,384,136,and do not keep thy law.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:137-141,35,33,97,N,385,137,"O Lord, thou art most righteous;"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:137-141,35,33,97,Y,386,137,thy judgments are upright.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:137-141,35,33,97,N,387,138,Thy testimonies thou command'st
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:137-141,35,33,97,Y,388,138,most faithful are and right.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:137-141,35,33,98,N,389,139,"My zeal hath ev'n consumed me,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:137-141,35,33,98,Y,390,139,because mine enemies
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:137-141,35,33,98,N,391,139,"Thy holy words forgotten have,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:137-141,35,33,98,Y,392,139,and do thy laws despise.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:137-141,35,34,99,N,393,140,"Thy word's most pure, therefore on it"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:137-141,35,34,99,Y,394,140,thy servant's love is set.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:137-141,35,34,99,N,395,141,"Small, and despis'd I am, yet I"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:137-141,35,34,99,Y,396,141,thy precepts not forget.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:142-144,36,34,100,N,397,142,Thy righteousness is righteousness
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:142-144,36,34,100,Y,398,142,which ever doth endure:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:142-144,36,34,100,N,399,142,"Thy holy law, Lord, also is"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:142-144,36,34,100,Y,400,142,the very truth most pure.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:142-144,36,35,101,N,401,143,"Trouble and anguish have me found,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:142-144,36,35,101,Y,402,143,and taken hold on me:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:142-144,36,35,101,N,403,143,Yet in my trouble my delight
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:142-144,36,35,101,Y,404,143,thy just commandments be.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:142-144,36,35,102,N,405,144,Eternal righteousness is in
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:142-144,36,35,102,Y,406,144,thy testimonies all:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:142-144,36,35,102,N,407,144,"Lord, to me understanding give,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:142-144,36,35,102,Y,408,144,and ever live I shall.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:145-148,37,35,103,N,409,145,"With my whole heart I cry'd, Lord, hear;"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:145-148,37,35,103,Y,410,145,I will thy word obey.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:145-148,37,35,103,N,411,146,"I cry'd to thee; save me, and I"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:145-148,37,35,103,Y,412,146,will keep thy laws alway.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:145-148,37,35,104,N,413,147,I of the morning did prevent
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:145-148,37,35,104,Y,414,147,"the dawning, and did cry:"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:145-148,37,35,104,N,415,147,For all mine expectation
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:145-148,37,35,104,Y,416,147,did on thy word rely.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:145-148,37,36,105,N,417,148,Mine eyes did timeously prevent
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:145-148,37,36,105,Y,418,148,"the watches of the night,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:145-148,37,36,105,N,419,148,That in thy word with careful mind
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:145-148,37,36,105,Y,420,148,then meditate I might.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:149-152,38,36,106,N,421,149,After thy loving-kindness hear
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:149-152,38,36,106,Y,422,149,"my voice, that calls on thee:"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:149-152,38,36,106,N,423,149,"According to thy judgment, Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:149-152,38,36,106,Y,424,149,revive and quicken me.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:149-152,38,37,107,N,425,150,Who follow mischief they draw nigh;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:149-152,38,37,107,Y,426,150,they from thy law are far:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:149-152,38,37,107,N,427,151,"But thou art near, Lord; most firm truth"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:149-152,38,37,107,Y,428,151,all thy commandments are.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:149-152,38,37,108,N,429,152,"As for thy testimonies all,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:149-152,38,37,108,Y,430,152,"of old this have I try'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:149-152,38,37,108,N,431,152,That thou hast surely founded them
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:149-152,38,37,108,Y,432,152,for ever to abide.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:153-156,39,37,109,N,433,153,"Consider mine affliction,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:153-156,39,37,109,Y,434,153,in safety do me set:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:153-156,39,37,109,N,435,153,"Deliver me, O Lord, for I"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:153-156,39,37,109,Y,436,153,thy law do not forget.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:153-156,39,37,110,N,437,154,After thy word revive thou me:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:153-156,39,37,110,Y,438,154,"save me, and plead my cause."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:153-156,39,37,110,N,439,155,Salvation is from sinners far;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:153-156,39,37,110,Y,440,155,for they seek not thy laws.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:153-156,39,38,111,N,441,156,"O Lord, both great and manifold"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:153-156,39,38,111,Y,442,156,thy tender mercies be:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:153-156,39,38,111,N,443,156,"According to thy judgments just,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:153-156,39,38,111,Y,444,156,revive and quicken me.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:157-160,40,38,112,N,445,157,"My persecutors many are,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:157-160,40,38,112,Y,446,157,and foes that do combine;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:157-160,40,38,112,N,447,157,Yet from thy testimonies pure
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:157-160,40,38,112,Y,448,157,my heart doth not decline.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:157-160,40,39,113,N,449,158,"I saw transgressors, and was griev'd;"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:157-160,40,39,113,Y,450,158,for they keep not thy word.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:157-160,40,39,113,N,451,159,See how I love thy law! as thou
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:157-160,40,39,113,Y,452,159,"art kind, me quicken, Lord."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:157-160,40,39,114,N,453,160,From the beginning all thy word
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:157-160,40,39,114,Y,454,160,hath been most true and sure:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:157-160,40,39,114,N,455,160,Thy righteous judgments ev'ry one
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:157-160,40,39,114,Y,456,160,for evermore endure.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:161-164,41,39,115,N,457,161,"Princes have persecuted me,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:161-164,41,39,115,Y,458,161,although no cause they saw:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:161-164,41,39,115,N,459,161,But still of thy most holy word
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:161-164,41,39,115,Y,460,161,my heart doth stand in awe.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:161-164,41,39,116,N,461,162,"I at thy word rejoice, as one"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:161-164,41,39,116,Y,462,162,of spoil that finds great store.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:161-164,41,39,116,N,463,163,Thy law I love; but lying all
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:161-164,41,39,116,Y,464,163,I hate and do abhor.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:161-164,41,40,117,N,465,164,Sev'n times a-day it is my care
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:161-164,41,40,117,Y,466,164,to give due praise to thee;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:161-164,41,40,117,N,467,164,"Because of all thy judgments, Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:161-164,41,40,117,Y,468,164,which righteous ever be.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:165-168,42,40,118,N,469,165,Great peace have they who love thy law;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:165-168,42,40,118,Y,470,165,offence they shall have none.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:165-168,42,40,118,N,471,166,"I hop'd for thy salvation, Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:165-168,42,40,118,Y,472,166,and thy commands have done.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:165-168,42,41,119,N,473,167,My soul thy testimonies pure
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:165-168,42,41,119,Y,474,167,observed carefully;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:165-168,42,41,119,N,475,167,"On them my heart is set, and them"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:165-168,42,41,119,Y,476,167,I love exceedingly.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:165-168,42,41,120,N,477,168,Thy testimonies and thy laws
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:165-168,42,41,120,Y,478,168,I kept with special care;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:165-168,42,41,120,N,479,168,For all my works and ways each one
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:165-168,42,41,120,Y,480,168,before thee open are.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:169-172,43,41,121,N,481,169,O let my earnest pray'r and cry
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:169-172,43,41,121,Y,482,169,"come near before thee, Lord:"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:169-172,43,41,121,N,483,169,"Give understanding unto me,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:169-172,43,41,121,Y,484,169,according to thy word.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:169-172,43,41,122,N,485,170,Let my request before thee come:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:169-172,43,41,122,Y,486,170,after thy word me free.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:169-172,43,41,122,N,487,171,"My lips shall utter praise, when thou"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:169-172,43,41,122,Y,488,171,hast taught thy laws to me.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:169-172,43,42,123,N,489,172,My tongue of thy most blessed word
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:169-172,43,42,123,Y,490,172,"shall speak, and it confess;"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:169-172,43,42,123,N,491,172,Because all thy commandements
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:169-172,43,42,123,Y,492,172,are perfect righteousness.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:173-176,44,42,124,N,493,173,Let thy strong hand make help to me:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:173-176,44,42,124,Y,494,173,thy precepts are my choice.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:173-176,44,42,124,N,495,174,"I long'd for thy salvation, Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:173-176,44,42,124,Y,496,174,and in thy law rejoice.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:173-176,44,43,125,N,497,175,"O let my soul live, and it shall"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:173-176,44,43,125,Y,498,175,give praises unto thee;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:173-176,44,43,125,N,499,175,And let thy judgments gracious
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:173-176,44,43,125,Y,500,175,be helpful unto me.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:173-176,44,43,126,N,501,176,"I, like a lost sheep, went astray;"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:173-176,44,43,126,Y,502,176,"thy servant seek, and find:"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:173-176,44,43,126,N,503,176,For thy commands I suffer'd not
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),119,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 119:173-176,44,43,126,Y,504,176,to slip out of my mind.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),120,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 120:1-7,1,1,1,N,1,1,"In my distress to God I cry'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),120,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 120:1-7,1,1,1,Y,2,1,and he gave ear to me.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),120,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 120:1-7,1,1,1,N,3,2,"From lying lips, and guileful tongue,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),120,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 120:1-7,1,1,1,Y,4,2,"O Lord, my soul set free."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),120,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 120:1-7,1,1,2,N,5,3,What shall be giv'n thee? or what shall
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),120,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 120:1-7,1,1,2,Y,6,3,"be done to thee, false tongue?"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),120,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 120:1-7,1,1,2,N,7,4,"Ev'n burning coals of juniper,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),120,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 120:1-7,1,1,2,Y,8,4,sharp arrows of the strong.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),120,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 120:1-7,1,2,3,N,9,5,Woe's me that I in Mesech am
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),120,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 120:1-7,1,2,3,Y,10,5,a sojourner so long;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),120,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 120:1-7,1,2,3,N,11,5,That I in tabernacles dwell
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),120,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 120:1-7,1,2,3,Y,12,5,to Kedar that belong.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),120,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 120:1-7,1,2,4,N,13,6,My soul with him that hateth peace
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),120,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 120:1-7,1,2,4,Y,14,6,hath long a dweller been.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),120,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 120:1-7,1,2,4,N,15,7,"I am for peace; but when I speak,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),120,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 120:1-7,1,2,4,Y,16,7,for battle they are keen
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),121,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 121:1-8,1,1,1,N,1,1,"I to the hills will lift mine eyes,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),121,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 121:1-8,1,1,1,Y,2,1,from whence doth come mine aid.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),121,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 121:1-8,1,1,1,N,3,2,"My safety cometh from the Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),121,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 121:1-8,1,1,1,Y,4,2,who heav'n and earth hath made.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),121,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 121:1-8,1,1,2,N,5,3,"Thy foot he'll not let slide, nor will"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),121,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 121:1-8,1,1,2,Y,6,3,he slumber that thee keeps.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),121,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 121:1-8,1,1,2,N,7,4,"Behold, he that keeps Israel,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),121,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 121:1-8,1,1,2,Y,8,4,"he slumbers not, nor sleeps."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),121,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 121:1-8,1,2,3,N,9,5,"The Lord thee keeps, the Lord thy shade"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),121,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 121:1-8,1,2,3,Y,10,5,on thy right hand doth stay:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),121,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 121:1-8,1,2,3,N,11,6,"The moon by night thee shall not smite,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),121,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 121:1-8,1,2,3,Y,12,6,nor yet the sun by day.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),121,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 121:1-8,1,2,4,N,13,7,The Lord shall keep thy soul; he shall
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),121,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 121:1-8,1,2,4,Y,14,7,preserve thee from all ill.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),121,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 121:1-8,1,2,4,N,15,8,Henceforth thy going out and in
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),121,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 121:1-8,1,2,4,Y,16,8,God keep for ever will.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),122,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 122:1-5,1,1,1,N,1,1,"I joy'd when to the house of God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),122,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 122:1-5,1,1,1,Y,2,1,"Go up, they said to me."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),122,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 122:1-5,1,1,1,N,3,2,"Jerusalem, within thy gates"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),122,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 122:1-5,1,1,1,Y,4,2,our feet shall standing be.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),122,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 122:1-5,1,1,2,N,5,3,"Jerus'lem, as a city, is"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),122,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 122:1-5,1,1,2,Y,6,3,compactly built together:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),122,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 122:1-5,1,1,2,N,7,4,"Unto that place the tribes go up,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),122,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 122:1-5,1,1,2,Y,8,4,the tribes of God go thither:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),122,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 122:1-5,1,2,3,N,9,4,"To Isr'el's testimony, there"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),122,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 122:1-5,1,2,3,Y,10,4,to God's name thanks to pay.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),122,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 122:1-5,1,2,3,N,11,5,"For thrones of judgment, ev'n the thrones"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),122,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 122:1-5,1,2,3,Y,12,5,"of David's house, there stay."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),122,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 122:6-9,2,2,4,N,13,6,Pray that Jerusalem may have
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),122,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 122:6-9,2,2,4,Y,14,6,peace and felicity:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),122,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 122:6-9,2,2,4,N,15,6,Let them that love thee and thy peace
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),122,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 122:6-9,2,2,4,Y,16,6,have still prosperity.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),122,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 122:6-9,2,3,5,N,17,7,Therefore I wish that peace may still
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),122,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 122:6-9,2,3,5,Y,18,7,"within thy walls remain,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),122,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 122:6-9,2,3,5,N,19,7,And ever may thy palaces
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),122,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 122:6-9,2,3,5,Y,20,7,prosperity retain.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),122,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 122:6-9,2,3,6,N,21,8,"Now, for my friends' and brethren's sakes,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),122,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 122:6-9,2,3,6,Y,22,8,"Peace be in thee, I'll say."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),122,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 122:6-9,2,3,6,N,23,9,"And for the house of God our Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),122,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 122:6-9,2,3,6,Y,24,9,I'll seek thy good alway.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),123,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 123:1-4,1,1,1,N,1,1,"O thou that dwellest in the heav'ns,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),123,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 123:1-4,1,1,1,Y,2,1,I lift mine eyes to thee.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),123,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 123:1-4,1,1,1,N,3,2,"Behold, as servants' eyes do look"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),123,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 123:1-4,1,1,1,Y,4,2,"their masters' hand to see,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),123,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 123:1-4,1,1,2,N,5,2,As handmaid's eyes her mistress' hand;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),123,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 123:1-4,1,1,2,Y,6,2,so do our eyes attend
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),123,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 123:1-4,1,1,2,N,7,2,"Upon the Lord our God, until"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),123,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 123:1-4,1,1,2,Y,8,2,to us he mercy send.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),123,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 123:1-4,1,2,3,N,9,3,"O Lord, be gracious to us,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),123,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 123:1-4,1,2,3,Y,10,3,unto us gracious be;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),123,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 123:1-4,1,2,3,N,11,3,Because replenish'd with contempt
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),123,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 123:1-4,1,2,3,Y,12,3,exceedingly are we.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),123,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 123:1-4,1,2,4,N,13,4,Our soul is fill'd with scorn of those
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),123,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 123:1-4,1,2,4,Y,14,4,"that at their ease abide,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),123,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 123:1-4,1,2,4,N,15,4,And with the insolent contempt
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),123,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 123:1-4,1,2,4,Y,16,4,of those that swell in pride.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 124:1-8 I,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Had not the Lord been on our side,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 124:1-8 I,1,1,1,Y,2,1,may Israel now say;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 124:1-8 I,1,1,1,N,3,2,"Had not the Lord been on our side,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 124:1-8 I,1,1,1,Y,4,2,when men rose us to slay;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 124:1-8 I,1,1,2,N,5,3,"They had us swallow'd quick, when as"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 124:1-8 I,1,1,2,Y,6,3,their wrath 'gainst us did flame:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 124:1-8 I,1,1,2,N,7,4,"Waters had cover'd us, our soul"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 124:1-8 I,1,1,2,Y,8,4,had sunk beneath the stream.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 124:1-8 I,1,2,3,N,9,5,"Then had the waters, swelling high,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 124:1-8 I,1,2,3,Y,10,5,over our soul made way.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 124:1-8 I,1,2,3,N,11,6,"Bless'd be the Lord, who to their teeth"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 124:1-8 I,1,2,3,Y,12,6,us gave not for a prey.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 124:1-8 I,1,2,4,N,13,7,"Our soul's escaped, as a bird"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 124:1-8 I,1,2,4,Y,14,7,out of the fowler's snare;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 124:1-8 I,1,2,4,N,15,7,"The snare asunder broken is,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 124:1-8 I,1,2,4,Y,16,7,and we escaped are.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 124:1-8 I,1,3,5,N,17,8,Our sure and all-sufficient help
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 124:1-8 I,1,3,5,Y,18,8,is in Jehovah's name;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 124:1-8 I,1,3,5,N,19,8,"His name who did the heav'n create,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,First,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 124:1-8 I,1,3,5,Y,20,8,and who the earth did frame.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,Second,"10,10,10,10",Ps. 124:1-8 II,1,3,1,N,1,1,Now Israel
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,Second,"10,10,10,10",Ps. 124:1-8 II,1,3,1,Y,2,1,"may say, and that truly,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,Second,"10,10,10,10",Ps. 124:1-8 II,1,3,1,N,3,1,If that the Lord
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,Second,"10,10,10,10",Ps. 124:1-8 II,1,3,1,Y,4,1,had not our cause maintain'd;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,Second,"10,10,10,10",Ps. 124:1-8 II,1,3,2,N,5,2,If that the Lord
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,Second,"10,10,10,10",Ps. 124:1-8 II,1,3,2,Y,6,2,"had not our right sustain'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,Second,"10,10,10,10",Ps. 124:1-8 II,1,3,2,N,7,2,When cruel men
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,Second,"10,10,10,10",Ps. 124:1-8 II,1,3,2,Y,8,2,against us furiously
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,Second,"10,10,10,10",Ps. 124:1-8 II,1,3,3,N,9,2,"Rose up in wrath,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,Second,"10,10,10,10",Ps. 124:1-8 II,1,3,3,Y,10,2,to make of us their prey;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,Second,"10,10,10,10",Ps. 124:1-8 II,1,4,3,N,11,3,Then certainly
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,Second,"10,10,10,10",Ps. 124:1-8 II,1,4,3,Y,12,3,"they had devour'd us all,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,Second,"10,10,10,10",Ps. 124:1-8 II,1,4,4,N,13,3,"And swallow'd quick,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,Second,"10,10,10,10",Ps. 124:1-8 II,1,4,4,Y,14,3,for ought that we could deem;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,Second,"10,10,10,10",Ps. 124:1-8 II,1,4,4,N,15,3,"Such was their rage,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,Second,"10,10,10,10",Ps. 124:1-8 II,1,4,4,Y,16,3,as we might well esteem.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,Second,"10,10,10,10",Ps. 124:1-8 II,1,4,5,N,17,4,And as fierce floods
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,Second,"10,10,10,10",Ps. 124:1-8 II,1,4,5,Y,18,4,"before them all things drown,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,Second,"10,10,10,10",Ps. 124:1-8 II,1,4,5,N,19,4,So had they brought
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,Second,"10,10,10,10",Ps. 124:1-8 II,1,4,5,N,20,4,our soul to death quite down.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,Second,"10,10,10,10",Ps. 124:1-8 II,1,5,6,N,21,5,"The raging streams,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,Second,"10,10,10,10",Ps. 124:1-8 II,1,5,6,Y,22,5,"with their proud swelling waves,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,Second,"10,10,10,10",Ps. 124:1-8 II,1,5,6,N,23,5,Had then our soul
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,Second,"10,10,10,10",Ps. 124:1-8 II,1,5,6,Y,24,5,o'erwhelmed in the deep.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,Second,"10,10,10,10",Ps. 124:1-8 II,1,5,7,N,25,6,"But bless'd be God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,Second,"10,10,10,10",Ps. 124:1-8 II,1,5,7,Y,26,6,"who doth us safely keep,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,Second,"10,10,10,10",Ps. 124:1-8 II,1,5,7,N,27,6,And hath not giv'n
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,Second,"10,10,10,10",Ps. 124:1-8 II,1,5,7,Y,28,6,us for a living prey
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,Second,"10,10,10,10",Ps. 124:1-8 II,1,5,8,N,29,6,"Unto their teeth,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,Second,"10,10,10,10",Ps. 124:1-8 II,1,5,8,Y,30,6,and bloody cruelty.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,Second,"10,10,10,10",Ps. 124:1-8 II,1,6,8,N,31,7,Ev'n as a bird
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,Second,"10,10,10,10",Ps. 124:1-8 II,1,6,8,Y,32,7,out of the fowler's snare
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,Second,"10,10,10,10",Ps. 124:1-8 II,1,6,9,N,33,7,"Escapes away,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,Second,"10,10,10,10",Ps. 124:1-8 II,1,6,9,Y,34,7,so is our soul set free:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,Second,"10,10,10,10",Ps. 124:1-8 II,1,6,9,N,35,7,"Broke are their nets,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,Second,"10,10,10,10",Ps. 124:1-8 II,1,6,9,Y,36,7,and thus escaped we.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,Second,"10,10,10,10",Ps. 124:1-8 II,1,6,10,N,37,8,Therefore our help
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,Second,"10,10,10,10",Ps. 124:1-8 II,1,6,10,Y,38,8,"is in the Lord's great name,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,Second,"10,10,10,10",Ps. 124:1-8 II,1,6,10,N,39,8,Who heav'n and earth
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),124,Second,"10,10,10,10",Ps. 124:1-8 II,1,6,10,Y,40,8,by his great pow'r did frame.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),125,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 125:1-5,1,1,1,N,1,1,They in the Lord that firmly trust
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),125,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 125:1-5,1,1,1,Y,2,1,"shall be like Sion hill,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),125,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 125:1-5,1,1,1,N,3,1,"Which at no time can be remov'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),125,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 125:1-5,1,1,1,Y,4,1,but standeth ever still.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),125,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 125:1-5,1,1,2,N,5,2,As round about Jerusalem
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),125,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 125:1-5,1,1,2,Y,6,2,"the mountains stand alway,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),125,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 125:1-5,1,1,2,N,7,2,"The Lord his folk doth compass so,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),125,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 125:1-5,1,1,2,Y,8,2,from henceforth and for aye.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),125,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 125:1-5,1,2,3,N,9,3,For ill men's rod upon the lot
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),125,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 125:1-5,1,2,3,Y,10,3,of just men shall not lie;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),125,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 125:1-5,1,2,3,N,11,3,Lest righteous men stretch forth their hands
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),125,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 125:1-5,1,2,3,Y,12,3,unto iniquity.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),125,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 125:1-5,1,2,4,N,13,4,Do thou to all those that be good
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),125,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 125:1-5,1,2,4,Y,14,4,"thy goodness, Lord, impart;"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),125,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 125:1-5,1,2,4,N,15,4,And do thou good to those that are
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),125,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 125:1-5,1,2,4,Y,16,4,upright within their heart.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),125,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 125:1-5,1,3,5,N,17,5,But as for such as turn aside
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),125,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 125:1-5,1,3,5,Y,18,5,"after their crooked way,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),125,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 125:1-5,1,3,5,N,19,5,God shall lead forth with wicked men:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),125,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 125:1-5,1,3,5,Y,20,5,on Isr'el peace shall stay.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),126,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 126:1-6,1,1,1,N,1,1,"When Sion's bondage God turn'd back,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),126,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 126:1-6,1,1,1,Y,2,1,as men that dream'd were we.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),126,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 126:1-6,1,1,1,N,3,2,"Then fill'd with laughter was our mouth,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),126,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 126:1-6,1,1,1,Y,4,2,our tongue with melody:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),126,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 126:1-6,1,1,2,N,5,2,"They 'mong the heathen said, The Lord"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),126,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 126:1-6,1,1,2,Y,6,2,great things for them hath wrought.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),126,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 126:1-6,1,1,2,N,7,3,"The Lord hath done great things for us,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),126,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 126:1-6,1,1,2,Y,8,3,whence joy to us is brought.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),126,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 126:1-6,1,2,3,N,9,4,"As streams of water in the south,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),126,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 126:1-6,1,2,3,Y,10,4,"our bondage, Lord, recall."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),126,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 126:1-6,1,2,3,N,11,5,"Who sow in tears, a reaping time"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),126,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 126:1-6,1,2,3,Y,12,5,of joy enjoy they shall.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),126,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 126:1-6,1,2,4,N,13,6,"That man who, bearing precious seed,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),126,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 126:1-6,1,2,4,Y,14,6,"in going forth doth mourn,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),126,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 126:1-6,1,2,4,N,15,6,"He doubtless, bringing back his sheaves,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),126,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 126:1-6,1,2,4,Y,16,6,rejoicing shall return.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),127,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 127:1-5,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Except the Lord do build the house,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),127,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 127:1-5,1,1,1,Y,2,1,the builders lose their pain:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),127,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 127:1-5,1,1,1,N,3,1,"Except the Lord the city keep,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),127,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 127:1-5,1,1,1,Y,4,1,the watchmen watch in vain.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),127,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 127:1-5,1,1,2,N,5,2,"'Tis vain for you to rise betimes,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),127,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 127:1-5,1,1,2,Y,6,2,"or late from rest to keep,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),127,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 127:1-5,1,1,2,N,7,2,To feed on sorrows' bread; so gives
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),127,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 127:1-5,1,1,2,Y,8,2,he his beloved sleep.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),127,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 127:1-5,1,2,3,N,9,3,"Lo, children are God's heritage,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),127,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 127:1-5,1,2,3,Y,10,3,the womb's fruit his reward.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),127,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 127:1-5,1,2,3,N,11,4,"The sons of youth as arrows are,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),127,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 127:1-5,1,2,3,Y,12,4,for strong men's hands prepar'd.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),127,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 127:1-5,1,2,4,N,13,5,O happy is the man that hath
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),127,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 127:1-5,1,2,4,Y,14,5,his quiver fill'd with those;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),127,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 127:1-5,1,2,4,N,15,5,They unashamed in the gate
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),127,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 127:1-5,1,2,4,Y,16,5,shall speak unto their foes.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),128,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 128:1-6,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Bless'd is each one that fears the Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),128,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 128:1-6,1,1,1,Y,2,1,and walketh in his ways;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),128,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 128:1-6,1,1,1,N,3,2,"For of thy labour thou shalt eat,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),128,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 128:1-6,1,1,1,Y,4,2,and happy be always.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),128,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 128:1-6,1,1,2,N,5,3,Thy wife shall as a fruitful vine
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),128,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 128:1-6,1,1,2,Y,6,3,by thy house' sides be found:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),128,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 128:1-6,1,1,2,N,7,3,Thy children like to olive-plants
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),128,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 128:1-6,1,1,2,Y,8,3,about thy table round.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),128,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 128:1-6,1,2,3,N,9,4,"Behold, the man that fears the Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),128,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 128:1-6,1,2,3,Y,10,4,thus blessed shall he be.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),128,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 128:1-6,1,2,3,N,11,5,The Lord shall out of Sion give
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),128,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 128:1-6,1,2,3,Y,12,5,his blessing unto thee:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),128,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 128:1-6,1,2,4,N,13,5,Thou shalt Jerus'lem's good behold
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),128,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 128:1-6,1,2,4,Y,14,5,whilst thou on earth dost dwell.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),128,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 128:1-6,1,2,4,N,15,6,"Thou shalt thy children's children see,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),128,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 128:1-6,1,2,4,Y,16,6,and peace on Israel.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),129,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 129:1-8,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Oft did they vex me from my youth,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),129,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 129:1-8,1,1,1,Y,2,1,may Isr'el now declare;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),129,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 129:1-8,1,1,1,N,3,2,"Oft did they vex me from my youth,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),129,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 129:1-8,1,1,1,Y,4,2,yet not victorious were.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),129,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 129:1-8,1,1,2,N,5,3,The plowers plow'd upon my back;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),129,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 129:1-8,1,1,2,Y,6,3,they long their furrows drew.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),129,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 129:1-8,1,1,2,N,7,4,The righteous Lord did cut the cords
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),129,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 129:1-8,1,1,2,Y,8,4,of the ungodly crew.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),129,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 129:1-8,1,2,3,N,9,5,Let Sion's haters all be turn'd
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),129,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 129:1-8,1,2,3,Y,10,5,back with confusion.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),129,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 129:1-8,1,2,3,N,11,6,"As grass on houses' tops be they,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),129,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 129:1-8,1,2,3,Y,12,6,which fades ere it be grown:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),129,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 129:1-8,1,2,4,N,13,7,Whereof enough to fill his hand
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),129,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 129:1-8,1,2,4,Y,14,7,the mower cannot find;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),129,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 129:1-8,1,2,4,N,15,7,"Nor can the man his bosom fill,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),129,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 129:1-8,1,2,4,Y,16,7,whose work is sheaves to bind.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),129,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 129:1-8,1,3,5,N,17,8,"Neither say they who do go by,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),129,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 129:1-8,1,3,5,Y,18,8,God's blessing on you rest:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),129,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 129:1-8,1,3,5,N,19,8,We in the name of God the Lord
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),129,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 129:1-8,1,3,5,Y,20,8,do wish you to be blest.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),130,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 130:1-8,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Lord, from the depths to thee I cry'd."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),130,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 130:1-8,1,1,1,Y,2,2,"My voice, Lord, do thou hear:"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),130,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 130:1-8,1,1,1,N,3,2,Unto my supplication's voice
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),130,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 130:1-8,1,1,1,Y,4,2,give an attentive ear.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),130,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 130:1-8,1,1,2,N,5,3,"Lord, who shall stand, if thou, O Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),130,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 130:1-8,1,1,2,Y,6,3,should'st mark iniquity?
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),130,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 130:1-8,1,1,2,N,7,4,"But yet with thee forgiveness is,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),130,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 130:1-8,1,1,2,Y,8,4,that fear'd thou mayest be.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),130,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 130:1-8,1,2,3,N,9,5,"I wait for God, my soul doth wait,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),130,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 130:1-8,1,2,3,Y,10,5,my hope is in his word.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),130,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 130:1-8,1,2,3,N,11,6,"More than they that for morning watch,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),130,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 130:1-8,1,2,3,Y,12,6,my soul waits for the Lord;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),130,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 130:1-8,1,2,4,N,13,6,"I say, more than they that do watch"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),130,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 130:1-8,1,2,4,Y,14,6,the morning light to see.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),130,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 130:1-8,1,2,4,N,15,7,"Let Israel hope in the Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),130,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 130:1-8,1,2,4,Y,16,7,for with him mercies be;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),130,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 130:1-8,1,3,5,N,17,7,And plenteous redemption
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),130,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 130:1-8,1,3,5,Y,18,7,is ever found with him.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),130,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 130:1-8,1,3,5,N,19,8,And from all his iniquities
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),130,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 130:1-8,1,3,5,Y,20,8,he Isr'el shall redeem.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),131,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 131:1-3,1,1,1,N,1,1,"My heart not haughty is, O Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),131,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 131:1-3,1,1,1,Y,2,1,mine eyes not lofty be;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),131,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 131:1-3,1,1,1,N,3,1,"Nor do I deal in matters great,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),131,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 131:1-3,1,1,1,Y,4,1,or things too high for me.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),131,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 131:1-3,1,1,2,N,5,2,I surely have myself behav'd
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),131,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 131:1-3,1,1,2,Y,6,2,"with quiet sp'rit and mild,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),131,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 131:1-3,1,1,2,N,7,2,As child of mother wean'd: my soul
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),131,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 131:1-3,1,1,2,Y,8,2,is like a weaned child.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),131,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 131:1-3,1,2,3,N,9,3,Upon the Lord let all the hope
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),131,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 131:1-3,1,2,3,Y,10,3,"of Israel rely,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),131,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 131:1-3,1,2,3,N,11,3,Ev'n from the time that present is
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),131,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 131:1-3,1,2,3,Y,12,3,unto eternity.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:1-8,1,1,1,N,1,1,"David, and his afflictions all,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:1-8,1,1,1,Y,2,1,"Lord, do thou think upon;"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:1-8,1,1,1,N,3,2,"How unto God he sware, and vow'd"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:1-8,1,1,1,Y,4,2,to Jacob's mighty One.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:1-8,1,1,2,N,5,3,"I will not come within my house,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:1-8,1,1,2,Y,6,3,nor rest in bed at all;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:1-8,1,1,2,N,7,4,"Nor shall mine eyes take any sleep,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:1-8,1,1,2,Y,8,4,nor eyelids slumber shall;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:1-8,1,2,3,N,9,5,"Till for the Lord a place I find,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:1-8,1,2,3,Y,10,5,where he may make abode;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:1-8,1,2,3,N,11,5,A place of habitation
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:1-8,1,2,3,Y,12,5,for Jacob's mighty God.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:1-8,1,2,4,N,13,6,"Lo, at the place of Ephratah"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:1-8,1,2,4,Y,14,6,of it we understood;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:1-8,1,2,4,N,15,6,"And we did find it in the fields,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:1-8,1,2,4,Y,16,6,and city of the wood.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:1-8,1,3,5,N,17,7,"We'll go into his tabernacles,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:1-8,1,3,5,Y,18,7,and at his footstool bow.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:1-8,1,3,5,N,19,8,"Arise, O Lord, into thy rest,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:1-8,1,3,5,Y,20,8,"th' ark of thy strength, and thou."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:9-12,2,3,6,N,21,9,"O let thy priests be clothed, Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:9-12,2,3,6,Y,22,9,with truth and righteousness;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:9-12,2,3,6,N,23,9,And let all those that are thy saints
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:9-12,2,3,6,Y,24,9,shout loud for joyfulness.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:9-12,2,4,7,N,25,10,"For thine own servant David's sake,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:9-12,2,4,7,Y,26,10,do not deny thy grace;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:9-12,2,4,7,N,27,10,Nor of thine own anointed one
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:9-12,2,4,7,Y,28,10,turn thou away the face.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:9-12,2,4,8,N,29,11,"The Lord in truth to David sware,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:9-12,2,4,8,Y,30,11,"he will not turn from it,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:9-12,2,4,8,N,31,11,I of thy body's fruit will make
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:9-12,2,4,8,Y,32,11,upon thy throne to sit.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:9-12,2,5,9,N,33,12,"My cov'nant if thy sons will keep,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:9-12,2,5,9,Y,34,12,"and laws to them made known,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:9-12,2,5,9,N,35,12,Their children then shall also sit
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:9-12,2,5,9,Y,36,12,for ever on thy throne.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:13-18,3,5,10,N,37,13,For God of Sion hath made choice;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:13-18,3,5,10,Y,38,13,there he desires to dwell.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:13-18,3,5,10,N,39,14,"This is my rest, here still I'll stay;"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:13-18,3,5,10,Y,40,14,for I do like it well.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:13-18,3,6,11,N,41,15,Her food I'll greatly bless; her poor
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:13-18,3,6,11,Y,42,15,with bread will satisfy.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:13-18,3,6,11,N,43,16,Her priests I'll clothe with health; her saints
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:13-18,3,6,11,Y,44,16,shall shout forth joyfully.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:13-18,3,6,12,N,45,17,And there will I make David's horn
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:13-18,3,6,12,Y,46,17,to bud forth pleasantly:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:13-18,3,6,12,N,47,17,For him that mine anointed is
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:13-18,3,6,12,Y,48,17,a lamp ordain'd have I.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:13-18,3,7,13,N,49,18,As with a garment I will clothe
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:13-18,3,7,13,Y,50,18,with shame his en'mies all:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:13-18,3,7,13,N,51,18,But yet the crown that he doth wear
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),132,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 132:13-18,3,7,13,Y,52,18,upon him flourish shall.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),133,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 133:1-3,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Behold, how good a thing it is,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),133,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 133:1-3,1,1,1,Y,2,1,"and how becoming well,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),133,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 133:1-3,1,1,1,N,3,1,Together such as brethren are
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),133,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 133:1-3,1,1,1,Y,4,1,in unity to dwell!
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),133,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 133:1-3,1,1,2,N,5,2,"Like precious ointment on the head,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),133,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 133:1-3,1,1,2,Y,6,2,"that down the beard did flow,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),133,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 133:1-3,1,1,2,N,7,2,"Ev'n Aaron's beard, and to the skirts,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),133,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 133:1-3,1,1,2,Y,8,2,did of his garments go.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),133,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 133:1-3,1,2,3,N,9,3,"As Hermon's dew, the dew that doth"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),133,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 133:1-3,1,2,3,Y,10,3,on Sion' hills descend:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),133,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 133:1-3,1,2,3,N,11,3,"For there the blessing God commands,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),133,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 133:1-3,1,2,3,Y,12,3,life that shall never end.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),134,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 134:1-3,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Behold, bless ye the Lord, all ye"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),134,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 134:1-3,1,1,1,Y,2,1,"that his attendants are,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),134,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 134:1-3,1,1,1,N,3,1,"Ev'n you that in God's temple be,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),134,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 134:1-3,1,1,1,Y,4,1,and praise him nightly there.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),134,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 134:1-3,1,1,2,N,5,2,Your hands within God's holy place
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),134,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 134:1-3,1,1,2,Y,6,2,"lift up, and praise his name."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),134,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 134:1-3,1,1,2,N,7,3,"From Sion' hill the Lord thee bless,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),134,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 134:1-3,1,1,2,Y,8,3,that heav'n and earth did frame.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:1-5,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Praise ye the Lord, the Lord's name praise;"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:1-5,1,1,1,Y,2,1,"his servants, praise ye God."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:1-5,1,1,1,N,3,2,"Who stand in God's house, in the courts"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:1-5,1,1,1,Y,4,2,of our God make abode.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:1-5,1,1,2,N,5,3,"Praise ye the Lord, for he is good;"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:1-5,1,1,2,Y,6,3,unto him praises sing:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:1-5,1,1,2,N,7,3,"Sing praises to his name, because"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:1-5,1,1,2,Y,8,3,it is a pleasant thing.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:1-5,1,2,3,N,9,4,For Jacob to himself the Lord
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:1-5,1,2,3,Y,10,4,"did chuse of his good pleasure,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:1-5,1,2,3,N,11,4,And he hath chosen Israel
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:1-5,1,2,3,Y,12,4,for his peculiar treasure.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:1-5,1,2,4,N,13,5,Because I know assuredly
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:1-5,1,2,4,Y,14,5,"the Lord is very great,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:1-5,1,2,4,N,15,5,And that our Lord above all gods
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:1-5,1,2,4,Y,16,5,in glory hath his seat.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:6-12,2,3,5,N,17,6,"What things soever pleas'd the Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:6-12,2,3,5,Y,18,6,"that in the heav'n did he,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:6-12,2,3,5,N,19,6,"And in the earth, the seas, and all"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:6-12,2,3,5,Y,20,6,the places deep that be.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:6-12,2,3,6,N,21,7,He from the ends of earth doth make
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:6-12,2,3,6,Y,22,7,the vapours to ascend;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:6-12,2,3,6,N,23,7,"With rain he lightnings makes, and wind"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:6-12,2,3,6,Y,24,7,doth from his treasures send.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:6-12,2,4,7,N,25,8,"Egypt's first-born, from man to beast"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:6-12,2,4,7,Y,26,9,who smote. Strange tokens he
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:6-12,2,4,7,N,27,9,"On Phar'oh and his servants sent,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:6-12,2,4,7,Y,28,9,"Egypt, in midst of thee."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:6-12,2,4,8,N,29,10,"He smote great nations, slew great kings:"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:6-12,2,4,8,Y,30,11,"Sihon of Heshbon king,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:6-12,2,4,8,N,31,11,"And Og of Bashan, and to nought"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:6-12,2,4,8,Y,32,11,did Canaan's kingdoms bring:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:6-12,2,5,9,N,33,12,And for a wealthy heritage
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:6-12,2,5,9,Y,34,12,"their pleasant land he gave,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:6-12,2,5,9,N,35,12,"An heritage which Israel,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:6-12,2,5,9,Y,36,12,"his chosen folk, should have."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:13-14,3,5,10,N,37,13,"Thy name, O Lord, shall still endure,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:13-14,3,5,10,Y,38,13,and thy memorial
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:13-14,3,5,10,N,39,13,With honour shall continu'd be
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:13-14,3,5,10,Y,40,13,to generations all.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:13-14,3,6,11,N,41,14,For why? the righteous God will judge
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:13-14,3,6,11,Y,42,14,his people righteously;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:13-14,3,6,11,N,43,14,"Concerning those that do him serve,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:13-14,3,6,11,Y,44,14,himself repent will he.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:15-21,4,6,12,N,45,15,The idols of the nations
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:15-21,4,6,12,Y,46,15,"of silver are and gold,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:15-21,4,6,12,N,47,15,And by the hands of men is made
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:15-21,4,6,12,Y,48,15,their fashion and mould.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:15-21,4,7,13,N,49,16,"Mouths have they, but they do not speak;"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:15-21,4,7,13,Y,50,16,"eyes, but they do not see;"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:15-21,4,7,13,N,51,17,"Ears have they, but hear not; and in"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:15-21,4,7,13,Y,52,17,their mouths no breathing be.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:15-21,4,7,14,N,53,18,Their makers are like them; so are
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:15-21,4,7,14,Y,54,18,all that on them rely.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:15-21,4,7,14,N,55,19,"O Isr'el's house, bless God; bless God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:15-21,4,7,14,Y,56,19,O Aaron's family.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:15-21,4,8,15,N,57,20,"O bless the Lord, of Levi's house"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:15-21,4,8,15,Y,58,20,ye who his servants are;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:15-21,4,8,15,N,59,20,"And bless the holy name of God,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:15-21,4,8,15,Y,60,20,all ye the Lord that fear.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:15-21,4,8,16,N,61,21,And blessed be the Lord our God
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:15-21,4,8,16,Y,62,21,"from Sion's holy hill,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:15-21,4,8,16,N,63,21,Who dwelleth at Jerusalem.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),135,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 135:15-21,4,8,16,Y,64,21,The Lord O praise ye still.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:1-6 I,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Give thanks to God, for good is he:"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:1-6 I,1,1,1,Y,2,1,for mercy hath he ever.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:1-6 I,1,1,1,N,3,2,Thanks to the God of gods give ye:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:1-6 I,1,1,1,Y,4,2,for his grace faileth never.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:1-6 I,1,1,2,N,5,3,Thanks give the Lord of lords unto:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:1-6 I,1,1,2,Y,6,3,for mercy hath he ever.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:1-6 I,1,1,2,N,7,4,Who only wonders great can do:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:1-6 I,1,1,2,Y,8,4,for his grace faileth never.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:1-6 I,1,2,3,N,9,5,Who by his wisdom made heav'ns high:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:1-6 I,1,2,3,Y,10,5,for mercy hath he ever.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:1-6 I,1,2,3,N,11,6,Who stretch'd the earth above the sea:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:1-6 I,1,2,3,Y,12,6,for his grace faileth never.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:7-16 I,2,2,4,N,13,7,To him that made the great lights shine:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:7-16 I,2,2,4,Y,14,7,for mercy hath he ever.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:7-16 I,2,2,4,N,15,8,The sun to rule till day decline:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:7-16 I,2,2,4,Y,16,8,for his grace faileth never.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:7-16 I,2,3,5,N,17,9,The moon and stars to rule by night:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:7-16 I,2,3,5,Y,18,9,for mercy hath he ever.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:7-16 I,2,3,5,N,19,10,Who Egypt's first-born kill'd outright:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:7-16 I,2,3,5,Y,20,10,for his grace faileth never.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:7-16 I,2,3,6,N,21,11,And Isr'el brought from Egypt land:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:7-16 I,2,3,6,Y,22,11,for mercy hath he ever.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:7-16 I,2,3,6,N,23,12,"With stretch'd-out arm, and with strong hand:"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:7-16 I,2,3,6,Y,24,12,for his grace faileth never.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:7-16 I,2,4,7,N,25,13,By whom the Red sea parted was:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:7-16 I,2,4,7,Y,26,13,for mercy hath he ever.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:7-16 I,2,4,7,N,27,14,And through its midst made Isr'el pass:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:7-16 I,2,4,7,Y,28,14,for his grace faileth never.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:7-16 I,2,4,8,N,29,15,But Phar'oh and his host did drown:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:7-16 I,2,4,8,Y,30,15,for mercy hath he ever.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:7-16 I,2,4,8,N,31,16,Who through the desert led his own:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:7-16 I,2,4,8,Y,32,16,for his grace faileth never.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:17-26 I,3,5,9,N,33,17,To him great kings who overthrew:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:17-26 I,3,5,9,Y,34,17,for he hath mercy ever.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:17-26 I,3,5,9,N,35,18,"Yea, famous kings in battle slew:"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:17-26 I,3,5,9,Y,36,18,for his grace faileth never.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:17-26 I,3,5,10,N,37,19,Ev'n Sihon king of Amorites:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:17-26 I,3,5,10,Y,38,19,for he hath mercy ever.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:17-26 I,3,5,10,N,39,20,And Og the king of Bashanites:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:17-26 I,3,5,10,Y,40,20,for his grace faileth never.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:17-26 I,3,6,11,N,41,21,Their land in heritage to have:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:17-26 I,3,6,11,Y,42,21,(for mercy hath he ever.)
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:17-26 I,3,6,11,N,43,22,His servant Isr'el right he gave:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:17-26 I,3,6,11,Y,44,22,for his grace faileth never.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:17-26 I,3,6,12,N,45,23,In our low state who on us thought:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:17-26 I,3,6,12,Y,46,23,for he hath mercy ever.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:17-26 I,3,6,12,N,47,24,And from our foes our freedom wrought:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:17-26 I,3,6,12,Y,48,24,for his grace faileth never.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:17-26 I,3,7,13,N,49,25,Who doth all flesh with food relieve:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:17-26 I,3,7,13,Y,50,25,for he hath mercy ever.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:17-26 I,3,7,13,N,51,26,Thanks to the God of heaven give:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,First,"8,7,8,7",Ps. 136:17-26 I,3,7,13,Y,52,26,for his grace faileth never.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 136:1-6 II,1,7,1,N,1,1,"Praise God, for he is kind:"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 136:1-6 II,1,7,1,N,2,1,His mercy lasts for aye.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 136:1-6 II,1,7,1,N,3,2,Give thanks with heart and mind
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 136:1-6 II,1,7,1,N,4,2,To God of gods alway:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 136:1-6 II,1,7,2,Y,5,2,For certainly
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 136:1-6 II,1,7,2,Y,6,2,His mercies dure
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 136:1-6 II,1,7,2,Y,7,2,Most firm and sure
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 136:1-6 II,1,7,2,Y,8,2,Eternally.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 136:1-6 II,1,8,3,N,9,3,"The Lord of lords praise ye,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 136:1-6 II,1,8,3,N,10,3,Whose mercies still endure.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 136:1-6 II,1,8,3,N,11,4,Great wonders only he
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 136:1-6 II,1,8,3,N,12,4,Doth work by his great pow'r
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 136:1-6 II,1,8,4,Y,13,4,For certainly
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 136:1-6 II,1,8,4,Y,14,4,His mercies dure
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 136:1-6 II,1,8,4,Y,15,4,Most firm and sure
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 136:1-6 II,1,8,4,Y,16,4,Eternally.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 136:1-6 II,1,9,5,N,17,5,"Which God omnipotent,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 136:1-6 II,1,9,5,N,18,5,"By might and wisdom high,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 136:1-6 II,1,9,5,N,19,5,The heav'n and firmament
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 136:1-6 II,1,9,5,N,20,5,"Did frame, as we may see:"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 136:1-6 II,1,9,6,Y,21,5,For certainly
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 136:1-6 II,1,9,6,Y,22,5,His mercies dure
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 136:1-6 II,1,9,6,Y,23,5,Most firm and sure
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 136:1-6 II,1,9,6,Y,24,5,Eternally.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 136:1-6 II,1,10,7,N,25,6,To him who did outstretch
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 136:1-6 II,1,10,7,N,26,6,"This earth so great and wide,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 136:1-6 II,1,10,7,N,27,6,Above the waters' reach
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 136:1-6 II,1,10,7,N,28,6,Making it to abide:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),136,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 136:1-6 II,1,10,8,Y,29,6,For certainly
