1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),137,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 137:1-6,1,1,1,N,1,1,"By Babel's streams we sat and wept,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),137,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 137:1-6,1,1,1,Y,2,1,when Sion we thought on.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),137,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 137:1-6,1,1,1,N,3,2,In midst thereof we hang'd our harps
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),137,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 137:1-6,1,1,1,Y,4,2,the willow-trees upon.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),137,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 137:1-6,1,1,2,N,5,3,"For there a song required they,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),137,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 137:1-6,1,1,2,Y,6,3,who did us captive bring:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),137,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 137:1-6,1,1,2,N,7,3,"Our spoilers call'd for mirth, and said,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),137,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 137:1-6,1,1,2,Y,8,3,A song of Sion sing.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),137,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 137:1-6,1,2,3,N,9,4,O how the Lord's song shall we sing
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),137,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 137:1-6,1,2,3,Y,10,4,within a foreign land?
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),137,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 137:1-6,1,2,3,N,11,5,"If thee, Jerus'lem, I forget,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),137,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 137:1-6,1,2,3,Y,12,5,skill part from my right hand.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),137,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 137:1-6,1,2,4,N,13,6,"My tongue to my mouth's roof let cleave,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),137,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 137:1-6,1,2,4,Y,14,6,"if I do thee forget,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),137,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 137:1-6,1,2,4,N,15,6,"Jerusalem, and thee above"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),137,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 137:1-6,1,2,4,Y,16,6,my chief joy do not set.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),137,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 137:7-9,2,3,5,N,17,7,"Remember Edom's children, Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),137,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 137:7-9,2,3,5,Y,18,7,"who in Jerus'lems day,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),137,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 137:7-9,2,3,5,N,19,7,"Ev'n unto its foundation,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),137,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 137:7-9,2,3,5,Y,20,7,"Raze, raze it quite, did say."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),137,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 137:7-9,2,3,6,N,21,8,"O daughter thou of Babylon,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),137,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 137:7-9,2,3,6,Y,22,8,near to destruction;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),137,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 137:7-9,2,3,6,N,23,8,"Bless'd shall he be that thee rewards,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),137,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 137:7-9,2,3,6,Y,24,8,as thou to us hast done.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),137,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 137:7-9,2,4,7,N,25,9,"Yea, happy surely shall he be"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),137,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 137:7-9,2,4,7,Y,26,9,thy tender little ones
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),137,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 137:7-9,2,4,7,N,27,9,"Who shall lay hold upon, and them"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),137,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 137:7-9,2,4,7,Y,28,9,shall dash against the stones.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),138,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 138:1-5,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Thee will I praise with all my heart,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),138,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 138:1-5,1,1,1,Y,2,1,I will sing praise to thee
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),138,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 138:1-5,1,1,1,N,3,2,Before the gods: And worship will
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),138,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 138:1-5,1,1,1,Y,4,2,toward thy sanctuary.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),138,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 138:1-5,1,1,2,N,5,2,"I'll praise thy name, ev'n for thy truth,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),138,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 138:1-5,1,1,2,Y,6,2,and kindness of thy love;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),138,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 138:1-5,1,1,2,N,7,2,For thou thy word hast magnify'd
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),138,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 138:1-5,1,1,2,Y,8,2,all thy great name above.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),138,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 138:1-5,1,2,3,N,9,3,Thou didst me answer in the day
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),138,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 138:1-5,1,2,3,Y,10,3,when I to thee did cry;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),138,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 138:1-5,1,2,3,N,11,3,And thou my fainting soul with strength
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),138,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 138:1-5,1,2,3,Y,12,3,didst strengthen inwardly.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),138,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 138:1-5,1,2,4,N,13,4,All kings upon the earth that are
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),138,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 138:1-5,1,2,4,Y,14,4,"shall give thee praise, O Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),138,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 138:1-5,1,2,4,N,15,4,When as they from thy mouth shall hear
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),138,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 138:1-5,1,2,4,Y,16,4,thy true and faithful word.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),138,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 138:1-5,1,3,5,N,17,5,"Yea, in the righteous ways of God"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),138,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 138:1-5,1,3,5,Y,18,5,with gladness they shall sing:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),138,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 138:1-5,1,3,5,N,19,5,For great's the glory of the Lord;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),138,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 138:1-5,1,3,5,Y,20,5,who doth for ever reign.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),138,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 138:6-8,2,3,6,N,21,6,"Though God be high, yet he respects"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),138,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 138:6-8,2,3,6,Y,22,6,all those that lowly be;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),138,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 138:6-8,2,3,6,N,23,6,Whereas the proud and lofty ones
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),138,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 138:6-8,2,3,6,Y,24,6,afar off knoweth he.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),138,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 138:6-8,2,4,7,N,25,7,"Though I in midst of trouble walk,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),138,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 138:6-8,2,4,7,Y,26,7,I life from thee shall have:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),138,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 138:6-8,2,4,7,N,27,7,'Gainst my foes' wrath thou'lt stretch thine hand;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),138,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 138:6-8,2,4,7,Y,28,7,thy right hand shall me save.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),138,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 138:6-8,2,4,8,N,29,8,Surely that which concerneth me
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),138,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 138:6-8,2,4,8,Y,30,8,the Lord will perfect make:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),138,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 138:6-8,2,4,8,N,31,8,"Lord, still thy mercy lasts; do not"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),138,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 138:6-8,2,4,8,Y,32,8,thine own hands' works forsake.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:1-6,1,1,1,N,1,1,"O Lord, thou hast me search'd and known."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:1-6,1,1,1,Y,2,2,"Thou know'st my sitting down,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:1-6,1,1,1,N,3,2,"And rising up; yea, all my thoughts"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:1-6,1,1,1,Y,4,2,afar to thee are known.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:1-6,1,1,2,N,5,3,"My footsteps, and my lying down,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:1-6,1,1,2,Y,6,3,thou compassest always;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:1-6,1,1,2,N,7,3,Thou also most entirely art
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:1-6,1,1,2,Y,8,3,acquaint with all my ways.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:1-6,1,2,3,N,9,4,"For in my tongue, before I speak,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:1-6,1,2,3,Y,10,4,"not any word can be,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:1-6,1,2,3,N,11,4,"But altogether, lo, O Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:1-6,1,2,3,Y,12,4,it is well known to thee.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:1-6,1,2,4,N,13,5,"Behind, before, thou hast beset,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:1-6,1,2,4,Y,14,5,and laid on me thine hand.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:1-6,1,2,4,N,15,6,"Such knowledge is too strange for me,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:1-6,1,2,4,Y,16,6,too high to understand.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:7-12,2,3,5,N,17,7,From thy Sp'rit whither shall I go?
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:7-12,2,3,5,Y,18,7,or from thy presence fly?
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:7-12,2,3,5,N,19,8,"Ascend I heav'n, lo, thou art there;"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:7-12,2,3,5,Y,20,8,"there, if in hell I lie."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:7-12,2,3,6,N,21,9,"Take I the morning wings, and dwell"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:7-12,2,3,6,Y,22,9,in utmost parts of sea;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:7-12,2,3,6,N,23,10,"Ev'n there, Lord, shall thy hand me lead,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:7-12,2,3,6,Y,24,10,thy right hand hold shall me.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:7-12,2,4,7,N,25,11,If I do say that darkness shall
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:7-12,2,4,7,Y,26,11,"me cover from thy sight,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:7-12,2,4,7,N,27,11,Then surely shall the very night
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:7-12,2,4,7,Y,28,11,about me be as light.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:7-12,2,4,8,N,29,12,"Yea, darkness hideth not from thee,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:7-12,2,4,8,Y,30,12,but night doth shine as day:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:7-12,2,4,8,N,31,12,To thee the darkness and the light
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:7-12,2,4,8,Y,32,12,are both alike alway.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:13-16,3,5,9,N,33,13,"For thou possessed hast my reins,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:13-16,3,5,9,Y,34,13,"and thou hast cover'd me,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:13-16,3,5,9,N,35,13,When I within my mother's womb
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:13-16,3,5,9,Y,36,13,inclosed was by thee.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:13-16,3,5,10,N,37,14,Thee will I praise; for fearfully
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:13-16,3,5,10,Y,38,14,and strangely made I am;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:13-16,3,5,10,N,39,14,"Thy works are marv'llous, and right well"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:13-16,3,5,10,Y,40,14,my soul doth know the same.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:13-16,3,6,11,N,41,15,"My substance was not hid from thee,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:13-16,3,6,11,Y,42,15,when as in secret I
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:13-16,3,6,11,N,43,15,Was made; and in earth's lowest parts
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:13-16,3,6,11,Y,44,15,was wrought most curiously.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:13-16,3,6,12,N,45,16,"Thine eyes my substance did behold,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:13-16,3,6,12,Y,46,16,yet being unperfect;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:13-16,3,6,12,N,47,16,And in the volume of thy book
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:13-16,3,6,12,Y,48,16,my members all were writ;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:13-16,3,7,13,N,49,16,Which after in continuance
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:13-16,3,7,13,Y,50,16,"were fashion'd ev'ry one,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:13-16,3,7,13,N,51,16,"When as they yet all shapeless were,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:13-16,3,7,13,Y,52,16,and of them there was none.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:17-18,4,7,14,N,53,17,"How precious also are thy thoughts,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:17-18,4,7,14,Y,54,17,"O gracious God, to me!"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:17-18,4,7,14,N,55,17,And in their sum how passing great
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:17-18,4,7,14,Y,56,17,and numberless they be!
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:17-18,4,8,15,N,57,18,"If I should count them, than the sand"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:17-18,4,8,15,Y,58,18,they more in number be:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:17-18,4,8,15,N,59,18,"What time soever I awake,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:17-18,4,8,15,Y,60,18,I ever am with thee.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:19-24,5,8,16,N,61,19,"Thou, Lord, wilt sure the wicked slay:"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:19-24,5,8,16,Y,62,19,hence from me bloody men.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:19-24,5,8,16,N,63,20,"Thy foes against thee loudly speak,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:19-24,5,8,16,Y,64,20,and take thy name in vain.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:19-24,5,9,17,N,65,21,"Do not I hate all those, O Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:19-24,5,9,17,Y,66,21,that hatred bear to thee?
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:19-24,5,9,17,N,67,21,With those that up against thee rise
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:19-24,5,9,17,Y,68,21,can I but grieved be?
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:19-24,5,9,18,N,69,22,"With perfect hatred them I hate,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:19-24,5,9,18,Y,70,22,my foes I them do hold.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:19-24,5,9,18,N,71,23,"Search me, O God, and know my heart,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:19-24,5,9,18,Y,72,23,"try me, my thoughts unfold:"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:19-24,5,10,19,N,73,24,And see if any wicked way
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:19-24,5,10,19,Y,74,24,there be at all in me;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:19-24,5,10,19,N,75,24,And in thine everlasting way
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),139,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 139:19-24,5,10,19,Y,76,24,to me a leader be.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),140,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 140:1-3,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Lord, from the ill and froward man"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),140,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 140:1-3,1,1,1,Y,2,1,"give me deliverance,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),140,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 140:1-3,1,1,1,N,3,1,And do thou safe preserve me from
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),140,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 140:1-3,1,1,1,Y,4,1,the man of violence:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),140,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 140:1-3,1,1,2,N,5,2,Who in their heart mischievous things
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),140,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 140:1-3,1,1,2,Y,6,2,are meditating ever;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),140,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 140:1-3,1,1,2,N,7,2,And they for war assembled are
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),140,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 140:1-3,1,1,2,Y,8,2,continually together.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),140,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 140:1-3,1,2,3,N,9,3,Much like unto a serpent's tongue
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),140,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 140:1-3,1,2,3,Y,10,3,their tongues they sharp do make;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),140,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 140:1-3,1,2,3,N,11,3,And underneath their lips there lies
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),140,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 140:1-3,1,2,3,Y,12,3,the poison of a snake.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),140,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 140:4-7,2,2,4,N,13,4,"Lord, keep me from the wicked's hands,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),140,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 140:4-7,2,2,4,Y,14,4,from vi'lent men me save;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),140,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 140:4-7,2,2,4,N,15,4,Who utterly to overthrow
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),140,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 140:4-7,2,2,4,Y,16,4,my goings purpos'd have.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),140,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 140:4-7,2,3,5,N,17,5,"The proud for me a snare have hid,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),140,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 140:4-7,2,3,5,Y,18,5,"and cords; yea, they a net"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),140,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 140:4-7,2,3,5,N,19,5,Have by the way-side for me spread;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),140,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 140:4-7,2,3,5,Y,20,5,they gins for me have set.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),140,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 140:4-7,2,3,6,N,21,6,"I said unto the Lord, Thou art"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),140,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 140:4-7,2,3,6,Y,22,6,my God: unto the cry
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),140,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 140:4-7,2,3,6,N,23,6,"Of all my supplications,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),140,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 140:4-7,2,3,6,Y,24,6,"Lord, do thine ear apply."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),140,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 140:4-7,2,4,7,N,25,7,"O God the Lord, who art the strength"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),140,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 140:4-7,2,4,7,Y,26,7,of my salvation:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),140,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 140:4-7,2,4,7,N,27,7,A cov'ring in the day of war
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),140,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 140:4-7,2,4,7,Y,28,7,my head thou hast put on.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),140,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 140:8-13,3,4,8,N,29,8,"Unto the wicked man, O Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),140,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 140:8-13,3,4,8,Y,30,8,his wishes do not grant;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),140,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 140:8-13,3,4,8,N,31,8,"Nor further thou his ill device,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),140,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 140:8-13,3,4,8,Y,32,8,lest they themselves should vaunt.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),140,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 140:8-13,3,5,9,N,33,9,As for the head and chief of those
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),140,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 140:8-13,3,5,9,Y,34,9,"about that compass me,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),140,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 140:8-13,3,5,9,N,35,9,Ev'n by the mischief of their lips
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),140,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 140:8-13,3,5,9,Y,36,9,let thou them cover'd be.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),140,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 140:8-13,3,5,10,N,37,10,"Let burning coals upon them fall,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),140,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 140:8-13,3,5,10,Y,38,10,"them throw in fiery flame,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),140,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 140:8-13,3,5,10,N,39,10,"And in deep pits, that they no more"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),140,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 140:8-13,3,5,10,Y,40,10,may rise out of the same.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),140,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 140:8-13,3,6,11,N,41,11,Let not an evil speaker be
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),140,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 140:8-13,3,6,11,Y,42,11,on earth established:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),140,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 140:8-13,3,6,11,N,43,11,"Mischief shall hunt the vi'lent man,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),140,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 140:8-13,3,6,11,Y,44,11,till he be ruined.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),140,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 140:8-13,3,6,12,N,45,12,I know God will th' afflicted's cause
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),140,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 140:8-13,3,6,12,Y,46,12,"maintain, and poor men's right."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),140,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 140:8-13,3,6,12,N,47,13,Surely the just shall praise thy name;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),140,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 140:8-13,3,6,12,Y,48,13,th' upright dwell in thy sight.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),141,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 141:1-4,1,1,1,N,1,1,"O Lord, I unto thee do cry,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),141,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 141:1-4,1,1,1,Y,2,1,"do thou make haste to me,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),141,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 141:1-4,1,1,1,N,3,1,"And give an ear unto my voice,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),141,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 141:1-4,1,1,1,Y,4,1,when I cry unto thee.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),141,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 141:1-4,1,1,2,N,5,2,As incense let my prayer be
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),141,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 141:1-4,1,1,2,Y,6,2,directed in thine eyes;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),141,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 141:1-4,1,1,2,N,7,2,And the uplifting of my hands
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),141,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 141:1-4,1,1,2,Y,8,2,as th' ev 'ning sacrifice.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),141,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 141:1-4,1,2,3,N,9,3,"Set, Lord, a watch before my mouth,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),141,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 141:1-4,1,2,3,Y,10,3,keep of my lips the door.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),141,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 141:1-4,1,2,3,N,11,4,My heart incline thou not unto
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),141,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 141:1-4,1,2,3,Y,12,4,"the ills I should abhor,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),141,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 141:1-4,1,2,4,N,13,4,To practise wicked works with men
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),141,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 141:1-4,1,2,4,Y,14,4,that work iniquity;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),141,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 141:1-4,1,2,4,N,15,4,And with their delicates my taste
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),141,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 141:1-4,1,2,4,Y,16,4,let me not satisfy.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),141,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 141:5-7,2,3,5,N,17,5,"Let him that righteous is me smite,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),141,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 141:5-7,2,3,5,Y,18,5,it shall a kindness be;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),141,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 141:5-7,2,3,5,N,19,5,"Let him reprove, I shall it count"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),141,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 141:5-7,2,3,5,Y,20,5,a precious oil to me:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),141,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 141:5-7,2,3,6,N,21,5,Such smiting shall not break my head;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),141,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 141:5-7,2,3,6,Y,22,5,"for yet the time shall fall,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),141,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 141:5-7,2,3,6,N,23,5,When I in their calamities
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),141,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 141:5-7,2,3,6,Y,24,5,to God pray for them shall.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),141,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 141:5-7,2,4,7,N,25,6,When as their judges down shall be
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),141,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 141:5-7,2,4,7,Y,26,6,"in stony places cast,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),141,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 141:5-7,2,4,7,N,27,6,Then shall they hear my words; for they
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),141,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 141:5-7,2,4,7,Y,28,6,shall sweet be to their taste.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),141,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 141:5-7,2,4,8,N,29,7,About the grave's devouring mouth
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),141,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 141:5-7,2,4,8,Y,30,7,"our bones are scatter'd round,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),141,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 141:5-7,2,4,8,N,31,7,As wood which men do cut and cleave
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),141,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 141:5-7,2,4,8,Y,32,7,lies scatter'd on the ground.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),141,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 141:8-10,3,5,9,N,33,8,"But unto thee, O God the Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),141,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 141:8-10,3,5,9,Y,34,8,mine eyes uplifted be:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),141,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 141:8-10,3,5,9,N,35,8,My soul do not leave destitute;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),141,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 141:8-10,3,5,9,Y,36,8,my trust is set on thee.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),141,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 141:8-10,3,5,10,N,37,9,"Lord, keep me safely from the snares"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),141,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 141:8-10,3,5,10,Y,38,9,which they for me prepare;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),141,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 141:8-10,3,5,10,N,39,9,And from the subtile gins of them
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),141,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 141:8-10,3,5,10,Y,40,9,that wicked workers are.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),141,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 141:8-10,3,6,11,N,41,10,Let workers of iniquity
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),141,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 141:8-10,3,6,11,Y,42,10,"into their own nets fall,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),141,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 141:8-10,3,6,11,N,43,10,"Whilst I do, by thine help, escape"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),141,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 141:8-10,3,6,11,Y,44,10,the danger of them all.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),142,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 142:1-4,1,1,1,N,1,1,"I with my voice cry'd to the Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),142,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 142:1-4,1,1,1,Y,2,1,with it made my request:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),142,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 142:1-4,1,1,1,N,3,2,"Pour'd out to him my plaint, to him"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),142,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 142:1-4,1,1,1,Y,4,2,my trouble I exprest.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),142,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 142:1-4,1,1,2,N,5,3,"When in me was o'erwhelm'd my sp'rit,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),142,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 142:1-4,1,1,2,Y,6,3,then well thou knew'st my way;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),142,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 142:1-4,1,1,2,N,7,3,Where I did walk a snare for me
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),142,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 142:1-4,1,1,2,Y,8,3,they privily did lay.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),142,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 142:1-4,1,2,3,N,9,4,"I look'd on my right hand, and view'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),142,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 142:1-4,1,2,3,Y,10,4,but none to know me were;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),142,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 142:1-4,1,2,3,N,11,4,"All refuge failed me, no man"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),142,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 142:1-4,1,2,3,Y,12,4,did for my soul take care.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),142,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 142:5-7,2,2,4,N,13,5,"I cry'd to thee; I said, Thou art"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),142,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 142:5-7,2,2,4,Y,14,5,"my refuge, Lord, alone;"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),142,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 142:5-7,2,2,4,N,15,5,And in the land of those that live
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),142,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 142:5-7,2,2,4,Y,16,5,thou art my portion.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),142,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 142:5-7,2,3,5,N,17,6,"Because I am brought very low,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),142,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 142:5-7,2,3,5,Y,18,6,attend unto my cry:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),142,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 142:5-7,2,3,5,N,19,6,"Me from my persecutors save,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),142,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 142:5-7,2,3,5,Y,20,6,who stronger are than I.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),142,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 142:5-7,2,3,6,N,21,7,"From prison bring my soul, that I"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),142,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 142:5-7,2,3,6,Y,22,7,thy name may glorify:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),142,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 142:5-7,2,3,6,N,23,7,"The just shall compass me, when thou"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),142,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 142:5-7,2,3,6,Y,24,7,with me deal'st bounteously.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 143:1-4 I,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Lord, hear my pray'r, attend my suits;"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 143:1-4 I,1,1,1,Y,2,1,and in thy faithfulness
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 143:1-4 I,1,1,1,N,3,1,"Give thou an answer unto me,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 143:1-4 I,1,1,1,Y,4,1,and in thy righteousness.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 143:1-4 I,1,1,2,N,5,2,Thy servant also bring thou not
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 143:1-4 I,1,1,2,Y,6,2,in judgment to be try'd:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 143:1-4 I,1,1,2,N,7,2,Because no living man can be
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 143:1-4 I,1,1,2,Y,8,2,in thy sight justify'd.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 143:1-4 I,1,2,3,N,9,3,"For th' en'my hath pursu'd my soul,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 143:1-4 I,1,2,3,Y,10,3,my life to ground down tread:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 143:1-4 I,1,2,3,N,11,3,"In darkness he hath made me dwell,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 143:1-4 I,1,2,3,Y,12,3,as who have long been dead.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 143:1-4 I,1,2,4,N,13,4,My sp'rit is therefore overwhelm'd
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 143:1-4 I,1,2,4,Y,14,4,in me perplexedly;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 143:1-4 I,1,2,4,N,15,4,Within me is my very heart
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 143:1-4 I,1,2,4,Y,16,4,amazed wondrously.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 143:5-9 I,2,3,5,N,17,5,"I call to mind the days of old,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 143:5-9 I,2,3,5,Y,18,5,to meditate I use
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 143:5-9 I,2,3,5,N,19,5,On all thy works; upon the deeds
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 143:5-9 I,2,3,5,Y,20,5,I of thy hands do muse.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 143:5-9 I,2,3,6,N,21,6,My hands to thee I stretch; my soul
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 143:5-9 I,2,3,6,Y,22,6,"thirsts, as dry land, for thee."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 143:5-9 I,2,3,6,N,23,7,"Haste, Lord, to hear, my spirit fails:"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 143:5-9 I,2,3,6,Y,24,7,hide not thy face from me;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 143:5-9 I,2,4,7,N,25,7,Lest like to them I do become
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 143:5-9 I,2,4,7,Y,26,7,that go down to the dust.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 143:5-9 I,2,4,7,N,27,8,At morn let me thy kindness hear;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 143:5-9 I,2,4,7,Y,28,8,for in thee do I trust.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 143:5-9 I,2,4,8,N,29,8,Teach me the way that I should walk:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 143:5-9 I,2,4,8,Y,30,8,I lift my soul to thee.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 143:5-9 I,2,4,8,N,31,9,"Lord, free me from my foes; I flee"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 143:5-9 I,2,4,8,Y,32,9,to thee to cover me.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 143:10-12 I,3,5,9,N,33,10,"Because thou art my God, to do"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 143:10-12 I,3,5,9,Y,34,10,thy will do me instruct:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 143:10-12 I,3,5,9,N,35,10,"Thy Sp'rit is good, me to the land"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 143:10-12 I,3,5,9,Y,36,10,of uprightness conduct.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 143:10-12 I,3,5,10,N,37,11,"Revive and quicken me, O Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 143:10-12 I,3,5,10,Y,38,11,ev'n for thine own name's sake;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 143:10-12 I,3,5,10,N,39,11,"And do thou, for thy righteousness,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 143:10-12 I,3,5,10,Y,40,11,my soul from trouble take.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 143:10-12 I,3,6,11,N,41,12,And of thy mercy slay my foes;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 143:10-12 I,3,6,11,Y,42,12,let all destroyed be
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 143:10-12 I,3,6,11,N,43,12,That do afflict my soul: for I
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 143:10-12 I,3,6,11,Y,44,12,a servant am to thee.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:1-5 II,1,6,1,N,1,1,"Oh, hear my prayer, Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:1-5 II,1,6,1,N,2,1,And unto my desire
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:1-5 II,1,6,1,N,3,1,"To bow thine ear accord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:1-5 II,1,6,1,N,4,1,I humbly thee require;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:1-5 II,1,6,2,N,5,1,"And, in thy faithfulness,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:1-5 II,1,6,2,N,6,1,"Unto me answer make,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:1-5 II,1,6,2,N,7,1,"And, in thy righteousness,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:1-5 II,1,6,2,N,8,1,Upon me pity take.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:1-5 II,1,7,3,N,9,2,In judgment enter not
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:1-5 II,1,7,3,N,10,2,With me thy servant poor;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:1-5 II,1,7,3,N,11,2,"For why, this well I wot,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:1-5 II,1,7,3,N,12,2,No sinner can endure
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:1-5 II,1,7,4,N,13,2,"The sight of thee, O God:"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:1-5 II,1,7,4,N,14,2,"If thou his deeds shalt try,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:1-5 II,1,7,4,N,15,2,He dare make none abode
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:1-5 II,1,7,4,N,16,2,Himself to justify.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:1-5 II,1,8,5,N,17,3,"Behold, the cruel foe"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:1-5 II,1,8,5,N,18,3,"Me persecutes with spite,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:1-5 II,1,8,5,N,19,3,My soul to overthrow:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:1-5 II,1,8,5,N,20,3,"Yea, he my life down quite"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:1-5 II,1,8,6,N,21,3,"Unto the ground hath smote,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:1-5 II,1,8,6,N,22,3,And made me dwell full low
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:1-5 II,1,8,6,N,23,3,"In darkness, as forgot,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:1-5 II,1,8,6,N,24,3,Or men dead long ago.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:1-5 II,1,9,7,N,25,4,"Therefore my sp'rit much vex'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:1-5 II,1,9,7,N,26,4,O'erwhelm'd is me within;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:1-5 II,1,9,7,N,27,4,My heart right sore perplex'd
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:1-5 II,1,9,7,N,28,4,And desolate hath been.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:1-5 II,1,9,8,N,29,5,Yet I do call to mind
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:1-5 II,1,9,8,N,30,5,"What ancient days record,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:1-5 II,1,9,8,N,31,5,Thy works of ev'ry kind
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:1-5 II,1,9,8,N,32,5,"I think upon, O Lord."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:6-12 II,2,10,9,N,33,6,"Lo, I do stretch my hands"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:6-12 II,2,10,9,N,34,6,"To thee, my help alone;"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:6-12 II,2,10,9,N,35,6,For thou well understands
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:6-12 II,2,10,9,N,36,6,All my complaint and moan:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:6-12 II,2,10,10,N,37,6,"My thirsting soul desires,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:6-12 II,2,10,10,N,38,6,"And longeth after thee,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:6-12 II,2,10,10,N,39,6,As thirsty ground requires
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:6-12 II,2,10,10,N,40,6,With rain refresh'd to be.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:6-12 II,2,11,11,N,41,7,"Lord, let my pray'r prevail,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:6-12 II,2,11,11,N,42,7,To answer it make speed;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:6-12 II,2,11,11,N,43,7,"For, lo, my sp'rit doth fail:"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:6-12 II,2,11,11,N,44,7,Hide not thy face in need;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:6-12 II,2,11,12,N,45,7,Lest I be like to those
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:6-12 II,2,11,12,N,46,7,"That do in darkness sit,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:6-12 II,2,11,12,N,47,7,Or him that downward goes
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:6-12 II,2,11,12,N,48,7,Into the dreadful pit.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:6-12 II,2,12,13,N,49,8,"Because I trust in thee,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:6-12 II,2,12,13,N,50,8,"O Lord, cause me to hear"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:6-12 II,2,12,13,N,51,8,"Thy loving-kindness free,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:6-12 II,2,12,13,N,52,8,When morning doth appear:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:6-12 II,2,12,14,N,53,8,Cause me to know the way
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:6-12 II,2,12,14,N,54,8,Wherein my path should be;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:6-12 II,2,12,14,N,55,8,"For why, my soul on high"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:6-12 II,2,12,14,N,56,8,I do lift up to thee.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:6-12 II,2,13,15,N,57,9,From my fierce enemy
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:6-12 II,2,13,15,N,58,9,"In safety do me guide,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:6-12 II,2,13,15,N,59,9,"Because I flee to thee,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:6-12 II,2,13,15,N,60,9,"Lord, that thou may'st me hide."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:6-12 II,2,13,16,N,61,10,"My God alone art thou,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:6-12 II,2,13,16,N,62,10,Teach me thy righteousness:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:6-12 II,2,13,16,N,63,10,"Thy Sp'rit's good, lead me to"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:6-12 II,2,13,16,N,64,10,The land of uprightness.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:6-12 II,2,14,17,N,65,11,"O Lord, for thy name's sake,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:6-12 II,2,14,17,N,66,11,Be pleas'd to quicken me;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:6-12 II,2,14,17,N,67,11,"And, for thy truth, forth take"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:6-12 II,2,14,17,N,68,11,My soul from misery.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:6-12 II,2,14,18,N,69,12,And of thy grace destroy
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:6-12 II,2,14,18,N,70,12,"My foes, and put to shame"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:6-12 II,2,14,18,N,71,12,All who my soul annoy;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),143,Second,"6,6,6,6",Ps. 143:6-12 II,2,14,18,N,72,12,For I thy servant am.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:1-2,1,1,1,N,1,1,"O blessed ever be the Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:1-2,1,1,1,Y,2,1,"who is my strength and might,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:1-2,1,1,1,N,3,1,"Who doth instruct my hands to war,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:1-2,1,1,1,Y,4,1,my fingers teach to fight.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:1-2,1,1,2,N,5,2,"My goodness, fortress, my high tow'r,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:1-2,1,1,2,Y,6,2,"deliverer, and shield,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:1-2,1,1,2,N,7,2,In whom I trust: who under me
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:1-2,1,1,2,Y,8,2,my people makes to yield.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:3-8,2,2,3,N,9,3,"Lord, what is man, that thou of him"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:3-8,2,2,3,Y,10,3,dost so much knowledge take?
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:3-8,2,2,3,N,11,3,"Or son of man, that thou of him"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:3-8,2,2,3,Y,12,3,so great account dost make?
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:3-8,2,2,4,N,13,4,"Man is like vanity; his days,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:3-8,2,2,4,Y,14,4,"as shadows, pass away."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:3-8,2,2,4,N,15,5,"Lord, bow thy heav'ns, come down,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:3-8,2,2,4,Y,16,5,"touch thou the hills, and smoke shall they."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:3-8,2,3,5,N,17,6,"Cast forth thy lightning, scatter them;"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:3-8,2,3,5,Y,18,6,"thine arrows shoot, them rout."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:3-8,2,3,5,N,19,7,"Thine hand send from above, me save;"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:3-8,2,3,5,Y,20,7,from great depths draw me out;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:3-8,2,3,6,N,21,7,"And from the hand of children strange,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:3-8,2,3,6,Y,22,8,Whose mouth speaks vanity;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:3-8,2,3,6,N,23,8,And their right hand is a right hand
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:3-8,2,3,6,Y,24,8,that works deceitfully.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:9-11,3,4,7,N,25,9,"A new song I to thee will sing,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:9-11,3,4,7,Y,26,9,"Lord, on a psaltery;"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:9-11,3,4,7,N,27,9,I on a ten-string'd instrument
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:9-11,3,4,7,Y,28,9,will praises sing to thee.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:9-11,3,4,8,N,29,10,Ev'n he it is that unto kings
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:9-11,3,4,8,Y,30,10,salvation doth send;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:9-11,3,4,8,N,31,10,Who his own servant David doth
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:9-11,3,4,8,Y,32,10,from hurtful sword defend.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:9-11,3,5,9,N,33,11,"O free me from strange children's hand,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:9-11,3,5,9,Y,34,11,whose mouth speaks vanity;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:9-11,3,5,9,N,35,11,And their right hand a right hand is
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:9-11,3,5,9,Y,36,11,that works deceitfully.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:12-15,4,5,10,N,37,12,"That, as the plants, our sons may be"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:12-15,4,5,10,Y,38,12,in youth grown up that are;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:12-15,4,5,10,N,39,12,"Our daughters like to corner-stones,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:12-15,4,5,10,Y,40,12,carv'd like a palace fair.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:12-15,4,6,11,N,41,13,That to afford all kind of store
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:12-15,4,6,11,Y,42,13,our garners may be fill'd;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:12-15,4,6,11,N,43,13,"That our sheep thousands, in our streets"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:12-15,4,6,11,Y,44,13,ten thousands they may yield.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:12-15,4,6,12,N,45,14,"That strong our oxen be for work,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:12-15,4,6,12,Y,46,14,"that no in-breaking be,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:12-15,4,6,12,N,47,14,Nor going out; and that our streets
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:12-15,4,6,12,Y,48,14,may from complaints be free.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:12-15,4,7,13,N,49,15,Those people blessed are who be
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:12-15,4,7,13,Y,50,15,in such a case as this;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:12-15,4,7,13,N,51,15,"Yea, blessed all those people are,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),144,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 144:12-15,4,7,13,Y,52,15,whose God Jehovah is.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:1-7 I,1,1,1,N,1,1,"I'll thee extol, my God, O King;"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:1-7 I,1,1,1,Y,2,1,I'll bless thy name always.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:1-7 I,1,1,1,N,3,2,"Thee will I bless each day, and will"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:1-7 I,1,1,1,Y,4,2,thy name for ever praise.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:1-7 I,1,1,2,N,5,3,"Great is the Lord, much to be prais'd;"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:1-7 I,1,1,2,Y,6,3,his greatness search exceeds.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:1-7 I,1,1,2,N,7,4,"Race unto race shall praise thy works,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:1-7 I,1,1,2,Y,8,4,and shew thy mighty deeds.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:1-7 I,1,2,3,N,9,5,I of thy glorious majesty
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:1-7 I,1,2,3,Y,10,5,the honour will record;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:1-7 I,1,2,3,N,11,5,"I'll speak of all thy mighty works,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:1-7 I,1,2,3,Y,12,5,"which wondrous are, O Lord."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:1-7 I,1,2,4,N,13,6,"Men of thine acts the might shall show,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:1-7 I,1,2,4,Y,14,6,thine acts that dreadful are;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:1-7 I,1,2,4,N,15,6,"And I, thy glory to advance,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:1-7 I,1,2,4,Y,16,6,thy greatness will declare.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:1-7 I,1,3,5,N,17,7,The mem'ry of thy goodness great
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:1-7 I,1,3,5,Y,18,7,they largely shall express;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:1-7 I,1,3,5,N,19,7,With songs of praise they shall extol
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:1-7 I,1,3,5,Y,20,7,thy perfect righteousness.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:8-12 I,2,3,6,N,21,8,"The Lord is very gracious,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:8-12 I,2,3,6,Y,22,8,in him compassions flow;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:8-12 I,2,3,6,N,23,8,"In mercy he is very great,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:8-12 I,2,3,6,Y,24,8,and is to anger slow.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:8-12 I,2,4,7,N,25,9,The Lord Jehovah unto all
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:8-12 I,2,4,7,Y,26,9,his goodness doth declare;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:8-12 I,2,4,7,N,27,9,And over all his other works
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:8-12 I,2,4,7,Y,28,9,his tender mercies are.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:8-12 I,2,4,8,N,29,10,"Thee all thy works shall praise, O Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:8-12 I,2,4,8,Y,30,10,and thee thy saints shall bless;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:8-12 I,2,4,8,N,31,11,"They shall thy kingdom's glory show,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:8-12 I,2,4,8,Y,32,11,thy pow'r by speech express:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:8-12 I,2,5,9,N,33,12,To make the sons of men to know
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:8-12 I,2,5,9,Y,34,12,"his acts done mightily,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:8-12 I,2,5,9,N,35,12,And of his kingdom th' excellent
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:8-12 I,2,5,9,Y,36,12,and glorious majesty.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:13-16 I,3,5,10,N,37,13,"Thy kingdom shall for ever stand,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:13-16 I,3,5,10,Y,38,13,thy reign through ages all.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:13-16 I,3,5,10,N,39,14,"God raiseth all that are bow'd down,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:13-16 I,3,5,10,Y,40,14,upholdeth all that fall.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:13-16 I,3,6,11,N,41,15,"The eyes of all things wait on thee,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:13-16 I,3,6,11,Y,42,15,the giver of all good;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:13-16 I,3,6,11,N,43,15,"And thou, in time convenient,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:13-16 I,3,6,11,Y,44,15,bestow'st on them their food:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:13-16 I,3,6,12,N,45,16,"Thine hand thou open'st lib'rally,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:13-16 I,3,6,12,Y,46,16,and of thy bounty gives
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:13-16 I,3,6,12,N,47,16,Enough to satisfy the need
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:13-16 I,3,6,12,Y,48,16,of ev'ry thing that lives.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:17-21 I,4,7,13,N,49,17,"The Lord is just in all his ways,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:17-21 I,4,7,13,Y,50,17,holy in his works all.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:17-21 I,4,7,13,N,51,18,"God's near to all that call on him,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:17-21 I,4,7,13,Y,52,18,in truth that on him call.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:17-21 I,4,7,14,N,53,19,He will accomplish the desire
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:17-21 I,4,7,14,Y,54,19,of those that do him fear:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:17-21 I,4,7,14,N,55,19,"He also will deliver them,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:17-21 I,4,7,14,Y,56,19,and he their cry will hear.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:17-21 I,4,8,15,N,57,20,"The Lord preserves all who him love,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:17-21 I,4,8,15,Y,58,20,that nought can them annoy:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:17-21 I,4,8,15,N,59,20,But he all those that wicked are
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:17-21 I,4,8,15,Y,60,20,will utterly destroy.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:17-21 I,4,8,16,N,61,21,My mouth the praises of the Lord
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:17-21 I,4,8,16,Y,62,21,to publish cease shall never:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:17-21 I,4,8,16,N,63,21,Let all flesh bless his holy name
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 145:17-21 I,4,8,16,Y,64,21,for ever and for ever.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:1-7 II,1,8,1,N,1,1,"O Lord, thou art my God and King;"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:1-7 II,1,8,1,N,2,1,Thee will I magnify and praise:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:1-7 II,1,8,1,N,3,1,"I will thee bless, and gladly sing"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:1-7 II,1,8,1,N,4,1,Unto thy holy name always.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:1-7 II,1,8,2,N,5,2,"Each day I rise I will thee bless,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:1-7 II,1,8,2,N,6,2,And praise thy name time without end.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:1-7 II,1,8,2,N,7,3,"Much to be prais'd, and great God is;"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:1-7 II,1,8,2,N,8,3,His greatness none can comprehend.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:1-7 II,1,9,3,N,9,4,"Race shall thy works praise unto race,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:1-7 II,1,9,3,N,10,4,The mighty acts show done by thee.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:1-7 II,1,9,3,N,11,5,"I will speak of the glorious grace,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:1-7 II,1,9,3,N,12,5,And honour of thy majesty;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:1-7 II,1,9,4,N,13,5,Thy wondrous works I will record.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:1-7 II,1,9,4,N,14,6,By men the might shall be extoll'd
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:1-7 II,1,9,4,N,15,6,"Of all thy dreadful acts, O Lord:"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:1-7 II,1,9,4,N,16,6,And I thy greatness will unfold.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:1-7 II,1,10,5,N,17,7,They utter shall abundantly
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:1-7 II,1,10,5,N,18,7,The mem'ry of thy goodness great;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:1-7 II,1,10,5,N,19,7,"And shall sing praises cheerfully,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:1-7 II,1,10,5,N,20,7,Whilst they thy righteousness relate.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:8-12 II,2,10,6,N,21,8,"The Lord our God is gracious,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:8-12 II,2,10,6,N,22,8,Compassionate is he also;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:8-12 II,2,10,6,N,23,8,"In mercy he is plenteous,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:8-12 II,2,10,6,N,24,8,But unto wrath and anger slow.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:8-12 II,2,11,7,N,25,9,Good unto all men is the Lord:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:8-12 II,2,11,7,N,26,9,O'er all his works his mercy is.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:8-12 II,2,11,7,N,27,10,Thy works all praise to thee afford:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:8-12 II,2,11,7,N,28,10,"Thy saints, O Lord, thy name shall bless."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:8-12 II,2,11,8,N,29,11,The glory of thy kingdom show
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:8-12 II,2,11,8,N,30,11,"Shall they, and of thy power tell:"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:8-12 II,2,11,8,N,31,12,"That so men's sons his deeds may know,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:8-12 II,2,11,8,N,32,12,His kingdom's grace that doth excel.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:13-16 II,3,12,9,N,33,13,"Thy kingdom hath none end at all,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:13-16 II,3,12,9,N,34,13,It doth through ages all remain.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:13-16 II,3,12,9,N,35,14,"The Lord upholdeth all that fall,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:13-16 II,3,12,9,N,36,14,The cast-down raiseth up again.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:13-16 II,3,12,10,N,37,15,"The eyes of all things, Lord, attend,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:13-16 II,3,12,10,N,38,15,"And on thee wait that here do live,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:13-16 II,3,12,10,N,39,15,"And thou, in season due, dost send"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:13-16 II,3,12,10,N,40,15,Sufficient food them to relieve.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:13-16 II,3,13,11,N,41,16,"Yea, thou thine hand dost open wide,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:13-16 II,3,13,11,N,42,16,And ev'ry thing dost satisfy
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:13-16 II,3,13,11,N,43,16,"That lives, and doth on earth abide,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:13-16 II,3,13,11,N,44,16,Of thy great liberality.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:17-21 II,4,13,12,N,45,17,"The Lord is just in his ways all,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:17-21 II,4,13,12,N,46,17,And holy in his works each one.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:17-21 II,4,13,12,N,47,18,"He's near to all that on him call,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:17-21 II,4,13,12,N,48,18,Who call in truth on him alone.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:17-21 II,4,14,13,N,49,19,God will the just desire fulfil
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:17-21 II,4,14,13,N,50,19,Of such as do him fear and dread:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:17-21 II,4,14,13,N,51,19,"Their cry regard, and hear he will,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:17-21 II,4,14,13,N,52,19,And save them in the time of need.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:17-21 II,4,14,14,N,53,20,"The Lord preserves all, more and less,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:17-21 II,4,14,14,N,54,20,That bear to him a loving heart:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:17-21 II,4,14,14,N,55,20,But workers all of wickedness
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:17-21 II,4,14,14,N,56,20,"Destroy will he, and clean subvert."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:17-21 II,4,15,15,N,57,21,Therefore my mouth and lips I'll frame
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:17-21 II,4,15,15,N,58,21,To speak the praises of the Lord:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:17-21 II,4,15,15,N,59,21,To magnify his holy name
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),145,Second,"8,8,8,8",Ps. 145:17-21 II,4,15,15,N,60,21,For ever let all flesh accord.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),146,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 146:1-4,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Praise God. The Lord praise, O my soul."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),146,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 146:1-4,1,1,1,Y,2,2,I'll praise God while I live;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),146,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 146:1-4,1,1,1,N,3,2,While I have being to my God
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),146,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 146:1-4,1,1,1,Y,4,2,in songs I'll praises give.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),146,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 146:1-4,1,1,2,N,5,3,"Trust not in princes, nor man's son,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),146,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 146:1-4,1,1,2,Y,6,3,in whom there is no stay:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),146,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 146:1-4,1,1,2,N,7,4,"His breath departs, to's earth he turns;"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),146,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 146:1-4,1,1,2,Y,8,4,that day his thoughts decay.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),146,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 146:5-8,2,2,3,N,9,5,"O happy is that man and blest,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),146,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 146:5-8,2,2,3,Y,10,5,whom Jacob's God doth aid;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),146,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 146:5-8,2,2,3,N,11,5,"Whose hope upon the Lord doth rest,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),146,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 146:5-8,2,2,3,Y,12,5,and on his God is stay'd:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),146,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 146:5-8,2,2,4,N,13,6,"Who made the earth and heavens high,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),146,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 146:5-8,2,2,4,Y,14,6,"who made the swelling deep,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),146,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 146:5-8,2,2,4,N,15,6,And all that is within the same;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),146,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 146:5-8,2,2,4,Y,16,6,who truth doth ever keep:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),146,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 146:5-8,2,3,5,N,17,7,Who righteous judgment executes
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),146,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 146:5-8,2,3,5,Y,18,7,"for those oppress'd that be,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),146,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 146:5-8,2,3,5,N,19,7,Who to the hungry giveth food;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),146,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 146:5-8,2,3,5,Y,20,7,God sets the pris'ners free.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),146,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 146:5-8,2,3,6,N,21,8,"The Lord doth give the blind their sight,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),146,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 146:5-8,2,3,6,Y,22,8,the bowed down doth raise:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),146,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 146:5-8,2,3,6,N,23,8,The Lord doth dearly love all those
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),146,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 146:5-8,2,3,6,Y,24,8,that walk in upright ways.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),146,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 146:9-10,3,4,7,N,25,9,"The stranger's shield, the widow's stay,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),146,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 146:9-10,3,4,7,Y,26,9,"the orphan's help, is he:"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),146,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 146:9-10,3,4,7,N,27,9,But yet by him the wicked's way
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),146,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 146:9-10,3,4,7,Y,28,9,turn'd upside down shall be.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),146,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 146:9-10,3,4,8,N,29,10,The Lord shall reign for evermore:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),146,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 146:9-10,3,4,8,Y,30,10,"thy God, O Sion, he"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),146,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 146:9-10,3,4,8,N,31,10,Reigns to all generations.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),146,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 146:9-10,3,4,8,Y,32,10,Praise to the Lord give ye.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:1-5,1,1,1,N,1,1,Praise ye the Lord; for it is good
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:1-5,1,1,1,Y,2,1,praise to our God to sing:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:1-5,1,1,1,N,3,1,"For it is pleasant, and to praise"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:1-5,1,1,1,Y,4,1,it is a comely thing.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:1-5,1,1,2,N,5,2,God doth build up Jerusalem;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:1-5,1,1,2,Y,6,2,and he it is alone
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:1-5,1,1,2,N,7,2,That the dispers'd of Israel
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:1-5,1,1,2,Y,8,2,doth gather into one.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:1-5,1,2,3,N,9,3,"Those that are broken in their heart,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:1-5,1,2,3,Y,10,3,"and grieved in their minds,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:1-5,1,2,3,N,11,3,"He healeth, and their painful wounds"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:1-5,1,2,3,Y,12,3,he tenderly up-binds.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:1-5,1,2,4,N,13,4,He counts the number of the stars;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:1-5,1,2,4,Y,14,4,he names them ev'ry one.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:1-5,1,2,4,N,15,5,"Great is our Lord, and of great pow'r;"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:1-5,1,2,4,Y,16,5,his wisdom search can none.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:6-11,2,3,5,N,17,6,The Lord lifts up the meek; and casts
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:6-11,2,3,5,Y,18,6,the wicked to the ground.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:6-11,2,3,5,N,19,7,"Sing to the Lord, and give him thanks;"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:6-11,2,3,5,Y,20,7,on harp his praises sound;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:6-11,2,3,6,N,21,8,"Who covereth the heav'n with clouds,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:6-11,2,3,6,Y,22,8,who for the earth below
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:6-11,2,3,6,N,23,8,"Prepareth rain, who maketh grass"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:6-11,2,3,6,Y,24,8,upon the mountains grow.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:6-11,2,4,7,N,25,9,"He gives the beast his food, he feeds"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:6-11,2,4,7,Y,26,9,the ravens young that cry.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:6-11,2,4,7,N,27,10,"His pleasure not in horses' strength,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:6-11,2,4,7,Y,28,10,"nor in man's legs, doth lie."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:6-11,2,4,8,N,29,11,But in all those that do him fear
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:6-11,2,4,8,Y,30,11,the Lord doth pleasure take;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:6-11,2,4,8,N,31,11,In those that to his mercy do
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:6-11,2,4,8,Y,32,11,by hope themselves betake.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:12-18,3,5,9,N,33,12,"The Lord praise, O Jerusalem;"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:12-18,3,5,9,Y,34,12,"Sion, thy God confess:"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:12-18,3,5,9,N,35,13,For thy gates' bars he maketh strong;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:12-18,3,5,9,Y,36,13,thy sons in thee doth bless.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:12-18,3,5,10,N,37,14,He in thy borders maketh peace;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:12-18,3,5,10,Y,38,14,with fine wheat filleth thee.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:12-18,3,5,10,N,39,15,"He sends forth his command on earth,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:12-18,3,5,10,Y,40,15,his word runs speedily.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:12-18,3,6,11,N,41,16,"Hoar-frost, like ashes, scatt'reth he;"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:12-18,3,6,11,Y,42,16,like wool he snow doth give:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:12-18,3,6,11,N,43,17,Like morsels casteth forth his ice;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:12-18,3,6,11,Y,44,17,who in its cold can live?
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:12-18,3,6,12,N,45,18,"He sendeth forth his mighty word,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:12-18,3,6,12,Y,46,18,and melteth them again;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:12-18,3,6,12,N,47,18,"His wind he makes to blow, and then"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:12-18,3,6,12,Y,48,18,the waters flow amain.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:19-20,4,7,13,N,49,19,The doctrine of his holy word
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:19-20,4,7,13,Y,50,19,to Jacob he doth show;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:19-20,4,7,13,N,51,19,His statutes and his judgments he
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:19-20,4,7,13,Y,52,19,gives Israel to know.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:19-20,4,7,14,N,53,20,To any nation never he
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:19-20,4,7,14,Y,54,20,such favour did afford;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:19-20,4,7,14,N,55,20,For they his judgments have not known.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),147,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 147:19-20,4,7,14,Y,56,20,O do ye praise the Lord.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 148:1-6 I,1,1,1,N,1,1,"Praise God. From heavens praise the Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 148:1-6 I,1,1,1,Y,2,1,in heights praise to him be.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 148:1-6 I,1,1,1,N,3,2,"All ye his angels, praise ye him;"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 148:1-6 I,1,1,1,Y,4,2,"his hosts all, praise him ye."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 148:1-6 I,1,1,2,N,5,3,"O praise ye him, both sun and moon,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 148:1-6 I,1,1,2,Y,6,3,"praise him, all stars of light."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 148:1-6 I,1,1,2,N,7,4,"Ye heav'ns of heav'ns him praise, and floods"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 148:1-6 I,1,1,2,Y,8,4,above the heavens' height.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 148:1-6 I,1,2,3,N,9,5,Let all the creatures praise the name
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 148:1-6 I,1,2,3,Y,10,5,of our almighty Lord:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 148:1-6 I,1,2,3,N,11,5,"For he commanded, and they were"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 148:1-6 I,1,2,3,Y,12,5,created by his word.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 148:1-6 I,1,2,4,N,13,6,"He also, for all times to come,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 148:1-6 I,1,2,4,Y,14,6,hath them establish'd sure;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 148:1-6 I,1,2,4,N,15,6,"He hath appointed them a law,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 148:1-6 I,1,2,4,Y,16,6,which ever shall endure.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 148:7-14 I,2,3,5,N,17,7,"Praise ye Jehovah from the earth,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 148:7-14 I,2,3,5,Y,18,7,"dragons, and ev'ry deep:"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 148:7-14 I,2,3,5,N,19,8,"Fire, hail, snow, vapour, stormy wind,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 148:7-14 I,2,3,5,Y,20,8,his word that fully keep.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 148:7-14 I,2,3,6,N,21,9,"All hills and mountains, fruitful trees,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 148:7-14 I,2,3,6,Y,22,9,and all ye cedars high:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 148:7-14 I,2,3,6,N,23,10,"Beasts, and all cattle, creeping things,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 148:7-14 I,2,3,6,Y,24,10,and all ye birds that fly.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 148:7-14 I,2,4,7,N,25,11,"Kings of the earth, all nations,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 148:7-14 I,2,4,7,Y,26,11,"princes, earth's judges all:"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 148:7-14 I,2,4,7,N,27,12,"Both young men, yea, and maidens too,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 148:7-14 I,2,4,7,Y,28,12,"old men, and children small."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 148:7-14 I,2,4,8,N,29,13,Let them God's name praise; for his name
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 148:7-14 I,2,4,8,Y,30,13,alone is excellent:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 148:7-14 I,2,4,8,N,31,13,His glory reacheth far above
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 148:7-14 I,2,4,8,Y,32,13,the earth and firmament.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 148:7-14 I,2,5,9,N,33,14,"His people's horn, the praise of all"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 148:7-14 I,2,5,9,Y,34,14,"his saints, exalteth he;"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 148:7-14 I,2,5,9,N,35,14,"Ev'n Isr'el's seed, a people near"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 148:7-14 I,2,5,9,Y,36,14,to him. The Lord praise ye.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 148:1-14 II,1,5,1,N,1,1,"The Lord of heav'n confess,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 148:1-14 II,1,5,1,Y,2,1,On high his glory raise.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 148:1-14 II,1,5,1,N,3,2,"Him let all angels bless,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 148:1-14 II,1,5,1,Y,4,2,Him all his armies praise.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 148:1-14 II,1,5,2,N,5,3,Him glorify
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 148:1-14 II,1,5,2,N,6,3,"Sun, moon, and stars;"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 148:1-14 II,1,5,2,N,7,4,"Ye higher spheres,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 148:1-14 II,1,5,2,N,8,4,And cloudy sky.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 148:1-14 II,1,6,3,N,9,5,"From God your beings are,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 148:1-14 II,1,6,3,Y,10,5,Him therefore famous make;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 148:1-14 II,1,6,3,N,11,5,"You all created were,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 148:1-14 II,1,6,3,Y,12,5,When he the word but spake.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 148:1-14 II,1,6,4,N,13,6,"And from that place,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 148:1-14 II,1,6,4,N,14,6,Where fix'd you be
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 148:1-14 II,1,6,4,N,15,6,"By his decree,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 148:1-14 II,1,6,4,N,16,6,You cannot pass.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 148:1-14 II,1,7,5,N,17,7,"Praise God from earth below,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 148:1-14 II,1,7,5,Y,18,7,"Ye dragons, and ye deeps:"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 148:1-14 II,1,7,5,N,19,8,"Fire, hail, clouds, wind, and snow."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 148:1-14 II,1,7,5,Y,20,8,Whom in command he keeps.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 148:1-14 II,1,7,6,N,21,9,"Praise ye his name,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 148:1-14 II,1,7,6,N,22,9,"Hills great and small,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 148:1-14 II,1,7,6,N,23,9,Trees low and tall;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 148:1-14 II,1,7,6,N,24,10,Beasts wild and tame;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 148:1-14 II,1,8,7,N,25,10,All things that creep or fly.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 148:1-14 II,1,8,7,Y,26,11,"Ye kings, ye vulgar throng,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 148:1-14 II,1,8,7,N,27,11,All princes mean or high;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 148:1-14 II,1,8,7,Y,28,12,"Both men and virgins young,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 148:1-14 II,1,8,8,N,29,12,"Ev'n young and old,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 148:1-14 II,1,8,8,N,30,13,Exalt his name;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 148:1-14 II,1,8,8,N,31,13,For much his fame
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 148:1-14 II,1,8,8,N,32,13,Should be extoll'd.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 148:1-14 II,1,9,9,N,33,13,O let God's name be prais'd
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 148:1-14 II,1,9,9,Y,34,13,Above both earth and sky;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 148:1-14 II,1,9,9,N,35,14,"For he his saints hath rais'd,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 148:1-14 II,1,9,9,Y,36,14,And set their horn on high;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 148:1-14 II,1,9,10,N,37,14,Ev'n those that be
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 148:1-14 II,1,9,10,N,38,14,"Of Isr'el's race,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 148:1-14 II,1,9,10,N,39,14,Near to his grace.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),148,Second,"6,6,6,6,8,8",Ps. 148:1-14 II,1,9,10,N,40,14,The Lord praise ye.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),149,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 149:1-4,1,1,1,N,1,1,Praise ye the Lord: unto him sing
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),149,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 149:1-4,1,1,1,Y,2,1,"a new song, and his praise"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),149,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 149:1-4,1,1,1,N,3,1,In the assembly of his saints
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),149,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 149:1-4,1,1,1,Y,4,1,in sweet psalms do ye raise.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),149,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 149:1-4,1,1,2,N,5,2,"Let Isr'el in his Maker joy,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),149,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 149:1-4,1,1,2,Y,6,2,and to him praises sing:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),149,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 149:1-4,1,1,2,N,7,2,Let all that Sion's children are
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),149,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 149:1-4,1,1,2,Y,8,2,be joyful in their King.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),149,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 149:1-4,1,2,3,N,9,3,O let them unto his great name
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),149,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 149:1-4,1,2,3,Y,10,3,give praises in the dance;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),149,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 149:1-4,1,2,3,N,11,3,Let them with timbrel and with harp
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),149,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 149:1-4,1,2,3,Y,12,3,in songs his praise advance.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),149,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 149:1-4,1,2,4,N,13,4,For God doth pleasure take in those
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),149,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 149:1-4,1,2,4,Y,14,4,that his own people be;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),149,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 149:1-4,1,2,4,N,15,4,And he with his salvation
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),149,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 149:1-4,1,2,4,Y,16,4,the meek will beautify.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),149,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 149:5-9,2,3,5,N,17,5,And in his glory excellent
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),149,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 149:5-9,2,3,5,Y,18,5,let all his saints rejoice:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),149,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 149:5-9,2,3,5,N,19,5,Let them to him upon their beds
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),149,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 149:5-9,2,3,5,Y,20,5,aloud lift up their voice.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),149,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 149:5-9,2,3,6,N,21,6,Let in their mouth aloft be rais'd
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),149,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 149:5-9,2,3,6,Y,22,6,"the high praise of the Lord,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),149,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 149:5-9,2,3,6,N,23,6,And let them have in their right hand
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),149,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 149:5-9,2,3,6,Y,24,6,a sharp two-edged sword;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),149,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 149:5-9,2,4,7,N,25,7,To execute the vengeance due
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),149,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 149:5-9,2,4,7,Y,26,7,"upon the heathen all,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),149,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 149:5-9,2,4,7,N,27,7,And make deserved punishment
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),149,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 149:5-9,2,4,7,Y,28,7,upon the people fall.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),149,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 149:5-9,2,4,8,N,29,8,"And ev'n with chains, as pris'ners, bind"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),149,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 149:5-9,2,4,8,Y,30,8,their kings that them command;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),149,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 149:5-9,2,4,8,N,31,8,"Yea, and with iron fetters strong,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),149,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 149:5-9,2,4,8,Y,32,8,the nobles of their land.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),149,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 149:5-9,2,5,9,N,33,9,On them the judgment to perform
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),149,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 149:5-9,2,5,9,Y,34,9,found written in his word:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),149,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 149:5-9,2,5,9,N,35,9,This honour is to all his saints.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),149,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 149:5-9,2,5,9,Y,36,9,O do ye praise the Lord.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),150,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 150:1-6,1,1,1,N,1,1,Praise ye the Lord. God's praise within
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),150,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 150:1-6,1,1,1,Y,2,1,his sanctuary raise;
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),150,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 150:1-6,1,1,1,N,3,1,And to him in the firmament
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),150,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 150:1-6,1,1,1,Y,4,1,of his pow'r give ye praise.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),150,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 150:1-6,1,1,2,N,5,2,"Because of all his mighty acts,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),150,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 150:1-6,1,1,2,Y,6,2,with praise him magnify:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),150,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 150:1-6,1,1,2,N,7,2,"O praise him, as he doth excel"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),150,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 150:1-6,1,1,2,Y,8,2,in glorious majesty.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),150,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 150:1-6,1,2,3,N,9,3,Praise him with trumpet's sound; his praise
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),150,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 150:1-6,1,2,3,Y,10,3,with psaltery advance:
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),150,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 150:1-6,1,2,3,N,11,4,"With timbrel, harp, string'd instruments,"
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),150,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 150:1-6,1,2,3,Y,12,4,"and organs, in the dance."
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),150,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 150:1-6,1,2,4,N,13,5,Praise him on cymbals loud; him praise
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),150,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 150:1-6,1,2,4,Y,14,5,on cymbals sounding high.
1650 Psalter,Book 5 (Psalm 107-150),150,First,"8,6,8,6",Ps. 150:1-6,1,2,4,N,15,6,Let each thing breathing praise the Lord.
